2218  return ExprError();
2219  break;
2220  case Builtin::BI__builtin_frame_address:
2221  case Builtin::BI__builtin_return_address: {
2222  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 0xFFFF))
2223  return ExprError();
2224 
2225  // -Wframe-address warning if non-zero passed to builtin
2226  // return/frame address.
2227  Expr::EvalResult Result;
2228  if (!TheCall->getArg(0)->isValueDependent() &&
2229  TheCall->getArg(0)->EvaluateAsInt(Result, getASTContext()) &&
2230  Result.Val.getInt() != 0)
2231  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_frame_address)
2232  << ((BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_return_address)
2233  ? "__builtin_return_address"
2234  : "__builtin_frame_address")
2235  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
2236  break;
2237  }
2238 
2239  // __builtin_elementwise_abs restricts the element type to signed integers or
2240  // floating point types only.
2241  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_abs: {
2242  if (PrepareBuiltinElementwiseMathOneArgCall(TheCall))
2243  return ExprError();
2244 
2245  QualType ArgTy = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
2246  QualType EltTy = ArgTy;
2247 
2248  if (auto *VecTy = EltTy->getAs<VectorType>())
2249  EltTy = VecTy->getElementType();
2250  if (EltTy->isUnsignedIntegerType()) {
2251  Diag(TheCall->getArg(0)->getBeginLoc(),
2252  diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
2253  << 1 << /* signed integer or float ty*/ 3 << ArgTy;
2254  return ExprError();
2255  }
2256  break;
2257  }
2258 
2259  // These builtins restrict the element type to floating point
2260  // types only.
2261  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_ceil:
2262  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_floor:
2263  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_roundeven:
2264  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_trunc: {
2265  if (PrepareBuiltinElementwiseMathOneArgCall(TheCall))
2266  return ExprError();
2267 
2268  QualType ArgTy = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
2269  QualType EltTy = ArgTy;
2270 
2271  if (auto *VecTy = EltTy->getAs<VectorType>())
2272  EltTy = VecTy->getElementType();
2273  if (!EltTy->isFloatingType()) {
2274  Diag(TheCall->getArg(0)->getBeginLoc(),
2275  diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
2276  << 1 << /* float ty*/ 5 << ArgTy;
2277 
2278  return ExprError();
2279  }
2280  break;
2281  }
2282 
2283  // These builtins restrict the element type to integer
2284  // types only.
2285  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_add_sat:
2286  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_sub_sat: {
2287  if (SemaBuiltinElementwiseMath(TheCall))
2288  return ExprError();
2289 
2290  const Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
2291  QualType ArgTy = Arg->getType();
2292  QualType EltTy = ArgTy;
2293 
2294  if (auto *VecTy = EltTy->getAs<VectorType>())
2295  EltTy = VecTy->getElementType();
2296 
2297  if (!EltTy->isIntegerType()) {
2298  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
2299  << 1 << /* integer ty */ 6 << ArgTy;
2300  return ExprError();
2301  }
2302  break;
2303  }
2304 
2305  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_min:
2306  case Builtin::BI__builtin_elementwise_max:
2307  if (SemaBuiltinElementwiseMath(TheCall))
2308  return ExprError();
2309  break;
2310  case Builtin::BI__builtin_reduce_max:
2311  case Builtin::BI__builtin_reduce_min: {
2312  if (PrepareBuiltinReduceMathOneArgCall(TheCall))
2313  return ExprError();
2314 
2315  const Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
2316  const auto *TyA = Arg->getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
2317  if (!TyA) {
2318  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
2319  << 1 << /* vector ty*/ 4 << Arg->getType();
2320  return ExprError();
2321  }
2322 
2323  TheCall->setType(TyA->getElementType());
2324  break;
2325  }
2326 
2327  // These builtins support vectors of integers only.
2328  case Builtin::BI__builtin_reduce_xor:
2329  case Builtin::BI__builtin_reduce_or:
2330  case Builtin::BI__builtin_reduce_and: {
2331  if (PrepareBuiltinReduceMathOneArgCall(TheCall))
2332  return ExprError();
2333 
2334  const Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
2335  const auto *TyA = Arg->getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
2336  if (!TyA || !TyA->getElementType()->isIntegerType()) {
2337  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
2338  << 1 << /* vector of integers */ 6 << Arg->getType();
2339  return ExprError();
2340  }
2341  TheCall->setType(TyA->getElementType());
2342  break;
2343  }
2344 
2345  case Builtin::BI__builtin_matrix_transpose:
2346  return SemaBuiltinMatrixTranspose(TheCall, TheCallResult);
2347 
2348  case Builtin::BI__builtin_matrix_column_major_load:
2349  return SemaBuiltinMatrixColumnMajorLoad(TheCall, TheCallResult);
2350 
2351  case Builtin::BI__builtin_matrix_column_major_store:
2352  return SemaBuiltinMatrixColumnMajorStore(TheCall, TheCallResult);
2353 
2354  case Builtin::BI__builtin_get_device_side_mangled_name: {
2355  auto Check = [](CallExpr *TheCall) {
2356  if (TheCall->getNumArgs() != 1)
2357  return false;
2358  auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(TheCall->getArg(0)->IgnoreImpCasts());
2359  if (!DRE)
2360  return false;
2361  auto *D = DRE->getDecl();
2362  if (!isa<FunctionDecl>(D) && !isa<VarDecl>(D))
2363  return false;
2364  return D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() ||
2365  D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() || D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>();
2366  };
2367  if (!Check(TheCall)) {
2368  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
2369  diag::err_hip_invalid_args_builtin_mangled_name);
2370  return ExprError();
2371  }
2372  }
2373  }
2374 
2375  // Since the target specific builtins for each arch overlap, only check those
2376  // of the arch we are compiling for.
2377  if (Context.BuiltinInfo.isTSBuiltin(BuiltinID)) {
2378  if (Context.BuiltinInfo.isAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID)) {
2379  assert(Context.getAuxTargetInfo() &&
2380  "Aux Target Builtin, but not an aux target?");
2381 
2382  if (CheckTSBuiltinFunctionCall(
2383  *Context.getAuxTargetInfo(),
2384  Context.BuiltinInfo.getAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID), TheCall))
2385  return ExprError();
2386 
2387  // Detect when host builtins are used in device code only
2388  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
2389  SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
2390  diag::err_builtin_target_unsupported);
2391  } else {
2392  if (CheckTSBuiltinFunctionCall(Context.getTargetInfo(), BuiltinID,
2393  TheCall))
2394  return ExprError();
2395  }
2396  }
2397 
2398  return TheCallResult;
2399 }
2400 
2401 // Get the valid immediate range for the specified NEON type code.
2402 static unsigned RFT(unsigned t, bool shift = false, bool ForceQuad = false) {
2403  NeonTypeFlags Type(t);
2404  int IsQuad = ForceQuad ? true : Type.isQuad();
2405  switch (Type.getEltType()) {
2406  case NeonTypeFlags::Int8:
2407  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly8:
2408  return shift ? 7 : (8 << IsQuad) - 1;
2409  case NeonTypeFlags::Int16:
2410  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly16:
2411  return shift ? 15 : (4 << IsQuad) - 1;
2412  case NeonTypeFlags::Int32:
2413  return shift ? 31 : (2 << IsQuad) - 1;
2414  case NeonTypeFlags::Int64:
2415  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly64:
2416  return shift ? 63 : (1 << IsQuad) - 1;
2417  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly128:
2418  return shift ? 127 : (1 << IsQuad) - 1;
2419  case NeonTypeFlags::Float16:
2420  assert(!shift && "cannot shift float types!");
2421  return (4 << IsQuad) - 1;
2422  case NeonTypeFlags::Float32:
2423  assert(!shift && "cannot shift float types!");
2424  return (2 << IsQuad) - 1;
2425  case NeonTypeFlags::Float64:
2426  assert(!shift && "cannot shift float types!");
2427  return (1 << IsQuad) - 1;
2428  case NeonTypeFlags::BFloat16:
2429  assert(!shift && "cannot shift float types!");
2430  return (4 << IsQuad) - 1;
2431  }
2432  llvm_unreachable("Invalid NeonTypeFlag!");
2433 }
2434 
2435 /// getNeonEltType - Return the QualType corresponding to the elements of
2436 /// the vector type specified by the NeonTypeFlags. This is used to check
2437 /// the pointer arguments for Neon load/store intrinsics.
2438 static QualType getNeonEltType(NeonTypeFlags Flags, ASTContext &Context,
2439  bool IsPolyUnsigned, bool IsInt64Long) {
2440  switch (Flags.getEltType()) {
2441  case NeonTypeFlags::Int8:
2442  return Flags.isUnsigned() ? Context.UnsignedCharTy : Context.SignedCharTy;
2443  case NeonTypeFlags::Int16:
2444  return Flags.isUnsigned() ? Context.UnsignedShortTy : Context.ShortTy;
2445  case NeonTypeFlags::Int32:
2446  return Flags.isUnsigned() ? Context.UnsignedIntTy : Context.IntTy;
2447  case NeonTypeFlags::Int64:
2448  if (IsInt64Long)
2449  return Flags.isUnsigned() ? Context.UnsignedLongTy : Context.LongTy;
2450  else
2451  return Flags.isUnsigned() ? Context.UnsignedLongLongTy
2452  : Context.LongLongTy;
2453  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly8:
2454  return IsPolyUnsigned ? Context.UnsignedCharTy : Context.SignedCharTy;
2455  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly16:
2456  return IsPolyUnsigned ? Context.UnsignedShortTy : Context.ShortTy;
2457  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly64:
2458  if (IsInt64Long)
2459  return Context.UnsignedLongTy;
2460  else
2461  return Context.UnsignedLongLongTy;
2462  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly128:
2463  break;
2464  case NeonTypeFlags::Float16:
2465  return Context.HalfTy;
2466  case NeonTypeFlags::Float32:
2467  return Context.FloatTy;
2468  case NeonTypeFlags::Float64:
2469  return Context.DoubleTy;
2470  case NeonTypeFlags::BFloat16:
2471  return Context.BFloat16Ty;
2472  }
2473  llvm_unreachable("Invalid NeonTypeFlag!");
2474 }
2475 
2476 bool Sema::CheckSVEBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
2477  // Range check SVE intrinsics that take immediate values.
2478  SmallVector<std::tuple<int,int,int>, 3> ImmChecks;
2479 
2480  switch (BuiltinID) {
2481  default:
2482  return false;
2483 #define GET_SVE_IMMEDIATE_CHECK
2484 #include "clang/Basic/arm_sve_sema_rangechecks.inc"
2485 #undef GET_SVE_IMMEDIATE_CHECK
2486  }
2487 
2488  // Perform all the immediate checks for this builtin call.
2489  bool HasError = false;
2490  for (auto &I : ImmChecks) {
2491  int ArgNum, CheckTy, ElementSizeInBits;
2492  std::tie(ArgNum, CheckTy, ElementSizeInBits) = I;
2493 
2494  typedef bool(*OptionSetCheckFnTy)(int64_t Value);
2495 
2496  // Function that checks whether the operand (ArgNum) is an immediate
2497  // that is one of the predefined values.
2498  auto CheckImmediateInSet = [&](OptionSetCheckFnTy CheckImm,
2499  int ErrDiag) -> bool {
2500  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
2501  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
2502  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
2503  return false;
2504 
2505  // Check constant-ness first.
2506  llvm::APSInt Imm;
2507  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Imm))
2508  return true;
2509 
2510  if (!CheckImm(Imm.getSExtValue()))
2511  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), ErrDiag) << Arg->getSourceRange();
2512  return false;
2513  };
2514 
2515  switch ((SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckType)CheckTy) {
2516  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck0_31:
2517  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, 31))
2518  HasError = true;
2519  break;
2520  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck0_13:
2521  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, 13))
2522  HasError = true;
2523  break;
2524  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck1_16:
2525  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 1, 16))
2526  HasError = true;
2527  break;
2528  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck0_7:
2529  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, 7))
2530  HasError = true;
2531  break;
2532  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckExtract:
2533  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0,
2534  (2048 / ElementSizeInBits) - 1))
2535  HasError = true;
2536  break;
2537  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckShiftRight:
2538  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 1, ElementSizeInBits))
2539  HasError = true;
2540  break;
2541  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckShiftRightNarrow:
2542  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 1,
2543  ElementSizeInBits / 2))
2544  HasError = true;
2545  break;
2546  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckShiftLeft:
2547  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0,
2548  ElementSizeInBits - 1))
2549  HasError = true;
2550  break;
2551  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckLaneIndex:
2552  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0,
2553  (128 / (1 * ElementSizeInBits)) - 1))
2554  HasError = true;
2555  break;
2556  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckLaneIndexCompRotate:
2557  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0,
2558  (128 / (2 * ElementSizeInBits)) - 1))
2559  HasError = true;
2560  break;
2561  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckLaneIndexDot:
2562  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0,
2563  (128 / (4 * ElementSizeInBits)) - 1))
2564  HasError = true;
2565  break;
2566  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckComplexRot90_270:
2567  if (CheckImmediateInSet([](int64_t V) { return V == 90 || V == 270; },
2568  diag::err_rotation_argument_to_cadd))
2569  HasError = true;
2570  break;
2571  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheckComplexRotAll90:
2572  if (CheckImmediateInSet(
2573  [](int64_t V) {
2574  return V == 0 || V == 90 || V == 180 || V == 270;
2575  },
2576  diag::err_rotation_argument_to_cmla))
2577  HasError = true;
2578  break;
2579  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck0_1:
2580  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, 1))
2581  HasError = true;
2582  break;
2583  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck0_2:
2584  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, 2))
2585  HasError = true;
2586  break;
2587  case SVETypeFlags::ImmCheck0_3:
2588  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, 3))
2589  HasError = true;
2590  break;
2591  }
2592  }
2593 
2594  return HasError;
2595 }
2596 
2597 bool Sema::CheckNeonBuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI,
2598  unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
2599  llvm::APSInt Result;
2600  uint64_t mask = 0;
2601  unsigned TV = 0;
2602  int PtrArgNum = -1;
2603  bool HasConstPtr = false;
2604  switch (BuiltinID) {
2605 #define GET_NEON_OVERLOAD_CHECK
2606 #include "clang/Basic/arm_neon.inc"
2607 #include "clang/Basic/arm_fp16.inc"
2608 #undef GET_NEON_OVERLOAD_CHECK
2609  }
2610 
2611  // For NEON intrinsics which are overloaded on vector element type, validate
2612  // the immediate which specifies which variant to emit.
2613  unsigned ImmArg = TheCall->getNumArgs()-1;
2614  if (mask) {
2615  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ImmArg, Result))
2616  return true;
2617 
2618  TV = Result.getLimitedValue(64);
2619  if ((TV > 63) || (mask & (1ULL << TV)) == 0)
2620  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_invalid_neon_type_code)
2621  << TheCall->getArg(ImmArg)->getSourceRange();
2622  }
2623 
2624  if (PtrArgNum >= 0) {
2625  // Check that pointer arguments have the specified type.
2626  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(PtrArgNum);
2627  if (ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Arg))
2628  Arg = ICE->getSubExpr();
2629  ExprResult RHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Arg);
2630  QualType RHSTy = RHS.get()->getType();
2631 
2632  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch = TI.getTriple().getArch();
2633  bool IsPolyUnsigned = Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64 ||
2634  Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_32 ||
2635  Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_be;
2636  bool IsInt64Long = TI.getInt64Type() == TargetInfo::SignedLong;
2637  QualType EltTy =
2638  getNeonEltType(NeonTypeFlags(TV), Context, IsPolyUnsigned, IsInt64Long);
2639  if (HasConstPtr)
2640  EltTy = EltTy.withConst();
2641  QualType LHSTy = Context.getPointerType(EltTy);
2642  AssignConvertType ConvTy;
2643  ConvTy = CheckSingleAssignmentConstraints(LHSTy, RHS);
2644  if (RHS.isInvalid())
2645  return true;
2646  if (DiagnoseAssignmentResult(ConvTy, Arg->getBeginLoc(), LHSTy, RHSTy,
2647  RHS.get(), AA_Assigning))
2648  return true;
2649  }
2650 
2651  // For NEON intrinsics which take an immediate value as part of the
2652  // instruction, range check them here.
2653  unsigned i = 0, l = 0, u = 0;
2654  switch (BuiltinID) {
2655  default:
2656  return false;
2657  #define GET_NEON_IMMEDIATE_CHECK
2658  #include "clang/Basic/arm_neon.inc"
2659  #include "clang/Basic/arm_fp16.inc"
2660  #undef GET_NEON_IMMEDIATE_CHECK
2661  }
2662 
2663  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, l, u + l);
2664 }
2665 
2666 bool Sema::CheckMVEBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
2667  switch (BuiltinID) {
2668  default:
2669  return false;
2670  #include "clang/Basic/arm_mve_builtin_sema.inc"
2671  }
2672 }
2673 
2674 bool Sema::CheckCDEBuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI, unsigned BuiltinID,
2675  CallExpr *TheCall) {
2676  bool Err = false;
2677  switch (BuiltinID) {
2678  default:
2679  return false;
2680 #include "clang/Basic/arm_cde_builtin_sema.inc"
2681  }
2682 
2683  if (Err)
2684  return true;
2685 
2686  return CheckARMCoprocessorImmediate(TI, TheCall->getArg(0), /*WantCDE*/ true);
2687 }
2688 
2689 bool Sema::CheckARMCoprocessorImmediate(const TargetInfo &TI,
2690  const Expr *CoprocArg, bool WantCDE) {
2691  if (isConstantEvaluated())
2692  return false;
2693 
2694  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
2695  if (CoprocArg->isTypeDependent() || CoprocArg->isValueDependent())
2696  return false;
2697 
2698  llvm::APSInt CoprocNoAP = *CoprocArg->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
2699  int64_t CoprocNo = CoprocNoAP.getExtValue();
2700  assert(CoprocNo >= 0 && "Coprocessor immediate must be non-negative");
2701 
2702  uint32_t CDECoprocMask = TI.getARMCDECoprocMask();
2703  bool IsCDECoproc = CoprocNo <= 7 && (CDECoprocMask & (1 << CoprocNo));
2704 
2705  if (IsCDECoproc != WantCDE)
2706  return Diag(CoprocArg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arm_invalid_coproc)
2707  << (int)CoprocNo << (int)WantCDE << CoprocArg->getSourceRange();
2708 
2709  return false;
2710 }
2711 
2712 bool Sema::CheckARMBuiltinExclusiveCall(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall,
2713  unsigned MaxWidth) {
2714  assert((BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
2715  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex ||
2716  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
2717  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stlex ||
2718  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
2719  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex ||
2720  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
2721  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stlex) &&
2722  "unexpected ARM builtin");
2723  bool IsLdrex = BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
2724  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex ||
2725  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
2726  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex;
2727 
2728  DeclRefExpr *DRE =cast<DeclRefExpr>(TheCall->getCallee()->IgnoreParenCasts());
2729 
2730  // Ensure that we have the proper number of arguments.
2731  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, IsLdrex ? 1 : 2))
2732  return true;
2733 
2734  // Inspect the pointer argument of the atomic builtin. This should always be
2735  // a pointer type, whose element is an integral scalar or pointer type.
2736  // Because it is a pointer type, we don't have to worry about any implicit
2737  // casts here.
2738  Expr *PointerArg = TheCall->getArg(IsLdrex ? 0 : 1);
2739  ExprResult PointerArgRes = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(PointerArg);
2740  if (PointerArgRes.isInvalid())
2741  return true;
2742  PointerArg = PointerArgRes.get();
2743 
2744  const PointerType *pointerType = PointerArg->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
2745  if (!pointerType) {
2746  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_must_be_pointer)
2747  << PointerArg->getType() << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
2748  return true;
2749  }
2750 
2751  // ldrex takes a "const volatile T*" and strex takes a "volatile T*". Our next
2752  // task is to insert the appropriate casts into the AST. First work out just
2753  // what the appropriate type is.
2754  QualType ValType = pointerType->getPointeeType();
2755  QualType AddrType = ValType.getUnqualifiedType().withVolatile();
2756  if (IsLdrex)
2757  AddrType.addConst();
2758 
2759  // Issue a warning if the cast is dodgy.
2760  CastKind CastNeeded = CK_NoOp;
2761  if (!AddrType.isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(ValType)) {
2762  CastNeeded = CK_BitCast;
2763  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_typecheck_convert_discards_qualifiers)
2764  << PointerArg->getType() << Context.getPointerType(AddrType)
2765  << AA_Passing << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
2766  }
2767 
2768  // Finally, do the cast and replace the argument with the corrected version.
2769  AddrType = Context.getPointerType(AddrType);
2770  PointerArgRes = ImpCastExprToType(PointerArg, AddrType, CastNeeded);
2771  if (PointerArgRes.isInvalid())
2772  return true;
2773  PointerArg = PointerArgRes.get();
2774 
2775  TheCall->setArg(IsLdrex ? 0 : 1, PointerArg);
2776 
2777  // In general, we allow ints, floats and pointers to be loaded and stored.
2778  if (!ValType->isIntegerType() && !ValType->isAnyPointerType() &&
2779  !ValType->isBlockPointerType() && !ValType->isFloatingType()) {
2780  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_must_be_pointer_intfltptr)
2781  << PointerArg->getType() << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
2782  return true;
2783  }
2784 
2785  // But ARM doesn't have instructions to deal with 128-bit versions.
2786  if (Context.getTypeSize(ValType) > MaxWidth) {
2787  assert(MaxWidth == 64 && "Diagnostic unexpectedly inaccurate");
2788  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_exclusive_builtin_pointer_size)
2789  << PointerArg->getType() << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
2790  return true;
2791  }
2792 
2793  switch (ValType.getObjCLifetime()) {
2794  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2795  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2796  // okay
2797  break;
2798 
2799  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2800  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2801  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2802  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arc_atomic_ownership)
2803  << ValType << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
2804  return true;
2805  }
2806 
2807  if (IsLdrex) {
2808  TheCall->setType(ValType);
2809  return false;
2810  }
2811 
2812  // Initialize the argument to be stored.
2813  ExprResult ValArg = TheCall->getArg(0);
2814  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
2815  Context, ValType, /*consume*/ false);
2816  ValArg = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), ValArg);
2817  if (ValArg.isInvalid())
2818  return true;
2819  TheCall->setArg(0, ValArg.get());
2820 
2821  // __builtin_arm_strex always returns an int. It's marked as such in the .def,
2822  // but the custom checker bypasses all default analysis.
2823  TheCall->setType(Context.IntTy);
2824  return false;
2825 }
2826 
2827 bool Sema::CheckARMBuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI, unsigned BuiltinID,
2828  CallExpr *TheCall) {
2829  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
2830  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex ||
2831  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
2832  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stlex) {
2833  return CheckARMBuiltinExclusiveCall(BuiltinID, TheCall, 64);
2834  }
2835 
2836  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_prefetch) {
2837  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1) ||
2838  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 1);
2839  }
2840 
2841  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
2842  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64)
2843  return SemaBuiltinARMSpecialReg(BuiltinID, TheCall, 0, 3, false);
2844 
2845  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
2846  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
2847  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr ||
2848  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp)
2849  return SemaBuiltinARMSpecialReg(BuiltinID, TheCall, 0, 5, true);
2850 
2851  if (CheckNeonBuiltinFunctionCall(TI, BuiltinID, TheCall))
2852  return true;
2853  if (CheckMVEBuiltinFunctionCall(BuiltinID, TheCall))
2854  return true;
2855  if (CheckCDEBuiltinFunctionCall(TI, BuiltinID, TheCall))
2856  return true;
2857 
2858  // For intrinsics which take an immediate value as part of the instruction,
2859  // range check them here.
2860  // FIXME: VFP Intrinsics should error if VFP not present.
2861  switch (BuiltinID) {
2862  default: return false;
2863  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ssat:
2864  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 1, 32);
2865  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_usat:
2866  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 31);
2867  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ssat16:
2868  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 1, 16);
2869  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_usat16:
2870  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 15);
2871  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_vcvtr_f:
2872  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_vcvtr_d:
2873  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1);
2874  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_dmb:
2875  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_dsb:
2876  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_isb:
2877  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_dbg:
2878  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 15);
2879  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_cdp:
2880  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_cdp2:
2881  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcr:
2882  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcr2:
2883  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrc:
2884  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrc2:
2885  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcrr:
2886  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcrr2:
2887  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrrc:
2888  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrrc2:
2889  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldc:
2890  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldcl:
2891  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldc2:
2892  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldc2l:
2893  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stc:
2894  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stcl:
2895  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stc2:
2896  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stc2l:
2897  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 15) ||
2898  CheckARMCoprocessorImmediate(TI, TheCall->getArg(0),
2899  /*WantCDE*/ false);
2900  }
2901 }
2902 
2903 bool Sema::CheckAArch64BuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI,
2904  unsigned BuiltinID,
2905  CallExpr *TheCall) {
2906  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
2907  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex ||
2908  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
2909  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stlex) {
2910  return CheckARMBuiltinExclusiveCall(BuiltinID, TheCall, 128);
2911  }
2912 
2913  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_prefetch) {
2914  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1) ||
2915  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 2) ||
2916  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 3, 0, 1) ||
2917  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 4, 0, 1);
2918  }
2919 
2920  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
2921  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64)
2922  return SemaBuiltinARMSpecialReg(BuiltinID, TheCall, 0, 5, true);
2923 
2924  // Memory Tagging Extensions (MTE) Intrinsics
2925  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_irg ||
2926  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_addg ||
2927  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_gmi ||
2928  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldg ||
2929  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stg ||
2930  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_subp) {
2931  return SemaBuiltinARMMemoryTaggingCall(BuiltinID, TheCall);
2932  }
2933 
2934  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
2935  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
2936  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr ||
2937  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp)
2938  return SemaBuiltinARMSpecialReg(BuiltinID, TheCall, 0, 5, true);
2939 
2940  // Only check the valid encoding range. Any constant in this range would be
2941  // converted to a register of the form S1_2_C3_C4_5. Let the hardware throw
2942  // an exception for incorrect registers. This matches MSVC behavior.
2943  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_ReadStatusReg ||
2944  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_WriteStatusReg)
2945  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 0x7fff);
2946 
2947  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__getReg)
2948  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 31);
2949 
2950  if (CheckNeonBuiltinFunctionCall(TI, BuiltinID, TheCall))
2951  return true;
2952 
2953  if (CheckSVEBuiltinFunctionCall(BuiltinID, TheCall))
2954  return true;
2955 
2956  // For intrinsics which take an immediate value as part of the instruction,
2957  // range check them here.
2958  unsigned i = 0, l = 0, u = 0;
2959  switch (BuiltinID) {
2960  default: return false;
2961  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_dmb:
2962  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_dsb:
2963  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_isb: l = 0; u = 15; break;
2964  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_tcancel: l = 0; u = 65535; break;
2965  }
2966 
2967  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, l, u + l);
2968 }
2969 
2970 static bool isValidBPFPreserveFieldInfoArg(Expr *Arg) {
2971  if (Arg->getType()->getAsPlaceholderType())
2972  return false;
2973 
2974  // The first argument needs to be a record field access.
2975  // If it is an array element access, we delay decision
2976  // to BPF backend to check whether the access is a
2977  // field access or not.
2978  return (Arg->IgnoreParens()->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField ||
2979  isa<MemberExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParens()) ||
2980  isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParens()));
2981 }
2982 
2983 static bool isEltOfVectorTy(ASTContext &Context, CallExpr *Call, Sema &S,
2984  QualType VectorTy, QualType EltTy) {
2985  QualType VectorEltTy = VectorTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2986  if (!Context.hasSameType(VectorEltTy, EltTy)) {
2987  S.Diag(Call->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_call_different_arg_types)
2988  << Call->getSourceRange() << VectorEltTy << EltTy;
2989  return false;
2990  }
2991  return true;
2992 }
2993 
2994 static bool isValidBPFPreserveTypeInfoArg(Expr *Arg) {
2995  QualType ArgType = Arg->getType();
2996  if (ArgType->getAsPlaceholderType())
2997  return false;
2998 
2999  // for TYPE_EXISTENCE/TYPE_SIZEOF reloc type
3000  // format:
3001  // 1. __builtin_preserve_type_info(*(<type> *)0, flag);
3002  // 2. <type> var;
3003  // __builtin_preserve_type_info(var, flag);
3004  if (!isa<DeclRefExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParens()) &&
3005  !isa<UnaryOperator>(Arg->IgnoreParens()))
3006  return false;
3007 
3008  // Typedef type.
3009  if (ArgType->getAs<TypedefType>())
3010  return true;
3011 
3012  // Record type or Enum type.
3013  const Type *Ty = ArgType->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
3014  if (const auto *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
3015  if (!RT->getDecl()->getDeclName().isEmpty())
3016  return true;
3017  } else if (const auto *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>()) {
3018  if (!ET->getDecl()->getDeclName().isEmpty())
3019  return true;
3020  }
3021 
3022  return false;
3023 }
3024 
3025 static bool isValidBPFPreserveEnumValueArg(Expr *Arg) {
3026  QualType ArgType = Arg->getType();
3027  if (ArgType->getAsPlaceholderType())
3028  return false;
3029 
3030  // for ENUM_VALUE_EXISTENCE/ENUM_VALUE reloc type
3031  // format:
3032  // __builtin_preserve_enum_value(*(<enum_type> *)<enum_value>,
3033  // flag);
3034  const auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Arg->IgnoreParens());
3035  if (!UO)
3036  return false;
3037 
3038  const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CStyleCastExpr>(UO->getSubExpr());
3039  if (!CE)
3040  return false;
3041  if (CE->getCastKind() != CK_IntegralToPointer &&
3042  CE->getCastKind() != CK_NullToPointer)
3043  return false;
3044 
3045  // The integer must be from an EnumConstantDecl.
3046  const auto *DR = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(CE->getSubExpr());
3047  if (!DR)
3048  return false;
3049 
3050  const EnumConstantDecl *Enumerator =
3051  dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(DR->getDecl());
3052  if (!Enumerator)
3053  return false;
3054 
3055  // The type must be EnumType.
3056  const Type *Ty = ArgType->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
3057  const auto *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
3058  if (!ET)
3059  return false;
3060 
3061  // The enum value must be supported.
3062  return llvm::is_contained(ET->getDecl()->enumerators(), Enumerator);
3063 }
3064 
3065 bool Sema::CheckBPFBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID,
3066  CallExpr *TheCall) {
3067  assert((BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_field_info ||
3068  BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_btf_type_id ||
3069  BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_type_info ||
3070  BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_enum_value) &&
3071  "unexpected BPF builtin");
3072 
3073  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
3074  return true;
3075 
3076  // The second argument needs to be a constant int
3077  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(1);
3078  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Value = Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
3079  diag::kind kind;
3080  if (!Value) {
3081  if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_field_info)
3082  kind = diag::err_preserve_field_info_not_const;
3083  else if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_btf_type_id)
3084  kind = diag::err_btf_type_id_not_const;
3085  else if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_type_info)
3086  kind = diag::err_preserve_type_info_not_const;
3087  else
3088  kind = diag::err_preserve_enum_value_not_const;
3089  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), kind) << 2 << Arg->getSourceRange();
3090  return true;
3091  }
3092 
3093  // The first argument
3094  Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
3095  bool InvalidArg = false;
3096  bool ReturnUnsignedInt = true;
3097  if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_field_info) {
3098  if (!isValidBPFPreserveFieldInfoArg(Arg)) {
3099  InvalidArg = true;
3100  kind = diag::err_preserve_field_info_not_field;
3101  }
3102  } else if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_type_info) {
3103  if (!isValidBPFPreserveTypeInfoArg(Arg)) {
3104  InvalidArg = true;
3105  kind = diag::err_preserve_type_info_invalid;
3106  }
3107  } else if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_enum_value) {
3108  if (!isValidBPFPreserveEnumValueArg(Arg)) {
3109  InvalidArg = true;
3110  kind = diag::err_preserve_enum_value_invalid;
3111  }
3112  ReturnUnsignedInt = false;
3113  } else if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_btf_type_id) {
3114  ReturnUnsignedInt = false;
3115  }
3116 
3117  if (InvalidArg) {
3118  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), kind) << 1 << Arg->getSourceRange();
3119  return true;
3120  }
3121 
3122  if (ReturnUnsignedInt)
3123  TheCall->setType(Context.UnsignedIntTy);
3124  else
3125  TheCall->setType(Context.UnsignedLongTy);
3126  return false;
3127 }

3324  {{ 3, false, 1, 0 }} },
3325  };
3326 
3327  // Use a dynamically initialized static to sort the table exactly once on
3328  // first run.
3329  static const bool SortOnce =
3330  (llvm::sort(Infos,
3331  [](const BuiltinInfo &LHS, const BuiltinInfo &RHS) {
3332  return LHS.BuiltinID < RHS.BuiltinID;
3333  }),
3334  true);
3335  (void)SortOnce;
3336 
3337  const BuiltinInfo *F = llvm::partition_point(
3338  Infos, [=](const BuiltinInfo &BI) { return BI.BuiltinID < BuiltinID; });
3339  if (F == std::end(Infos) || F->BuiltinID != BuiltinID)
3340  return false;
3341 
3342  bool Error = false;
3343 
3344  for (const ArgInfo &A : F->Infos) {
3345  // Ignore empty ArgInfo elements.
3346  if (A.BitWidth == 0)
3347  continue;
3348 
3349  int32_t Min = A.IsSigned ? -(1 << (A.BitWidth - 1)) : 0;
3350  int32_t Max = (1 << (A.IsSigned ? A.BitWidth - 1 : A.BitWidth)) - 1;
3351  if (!A.Align) {
3352  Error |= SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, A.OpNum, Min, Max);
3353  } else {
3354  unsigned M = 1 << A.Align;
3355  Min *= M;
3356  Max *= M;
3357  Error |= SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, A.OpNum, Min, Max);
3358  Error |= SemaBuiltinConstantArgMultiple(TheCall, A.OpNum, M);
3359  }
3360  }
3361  return Error;
3362 }
3363 
3364 bool Sema::CheckHexagonBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID,
3365  CallExpr *TheCall) {
3366  return CheckHexagonBuiltinArgument(BuiltinID, TheCall);
3367 }
3368 
3369 bool Sema::CheckMipsBuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI,
3370  unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
3371  return CheckMipsBuiltinCpu(TI, BuiltinID, TheCall) ||
3372  CheckMipsBuiltinArgument(BuiltinID, TheCall);
3373 }
3374 
3375 bool Sema::CheckMipsBuiltinCpu(const TargetInfo &TI, unsigned BuiltinID,
3376  CallExpr *TheCall) {
3377 
3378  if (Mips::BI__builtin_mips_addu_qb <= BuiltinID &&
3379  BuiltinID <= Mips::BI__builtin_mips_lwx) {
3380  if (!TI.hasFeature("dsp"))
3381  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_mips_builtin_requires_dsp);
3382  }
3383 
3384  if (Mips::BI__builtin_mips_absq_s_qb <= BuiltinID &&
3385  BuiltinID <= Mips::BI__builtin_mips_subuh_r_qb) {
3386  if (!TI.hasFeature("dspr2"))
3387  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
3388  diag::err_mips_builtin_requires_dspr2);
3389  }
3390 
3391  if (Mips::BI__builtin_msa_add_a_b <= BuiltinID &&
3392  BuiltinID <= Mips::BI__builtin_msa_xori_b) {
3393  if (!TI.hasFeature("msa"))
3394  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_mips_builtin_requires_msa);
3395  }
3396 
3397  return false;
3398 }
3399 
3400 // CheckMipsBuiltinArgument - Checks the constant value passed to the
3401 // intrinsic is correct. The switch statement is ordered by DSP, MSA. The
3402 // ordering for DSP is unspecified. MSA is ordered by the data format used
3403 // by the underlying instruction i.e., df/m, df/n and then by size.
3404 //
3405 // FIXME: The size tests here should instead be tablegen'd along with the
3406 // definitions from include/clang/Basic/BuiltinsMips.def.
3407 // FIXME: GCC is strict on signedness for some of these intrinsics, we should
3408 // be too.
3409 bool Sema::CheckMipsBuiltinArgument(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
3410  unsigned i = 0, l = 0, u = 0, m = 0;
3411  switch (BuiltinID) {
3412  default: return false;
3413  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_wrdsp: i = 1; l = 0; u = 63; break;
3414  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_rddsp: i = 0; l = 0; u = 63; break;
3415  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_append: i = 2; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3416  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_balign: i = 2; l = 0; u = 3; break;
3417  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_precr_sra_ph_w: i = 2; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3418  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_precr_sra_r_ph_w: i = 2; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3419  case Mips::BI__builtin_mips_prepend: i = 2; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3420  // MSA intrinsics. Instructions (which the intrinsics maps to) which use the
3421  // df/m field.
3422  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 3 bit immediate.
3423  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bclri_b:
3424  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bnegi_b:
3425  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bseti_b:
3426  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_s_b:
3427  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_u_b:
3428  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_slli_b:
3429  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srai_b:
3430  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srari_b:
3431  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srli_b:
3432  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srlri_b: i = 1; l = 0; u = 7; break;
3433  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsli_b:
3434  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsri_b: i = 2; l = 0; u = 7; break;
3435  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 4 bit immediate.
3436  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bclri_h:
3437  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bnegi_h:
3438  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bseti_h:
3439  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_s_h:
3440  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_u_h:
3441  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_slli_h:
3442  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srai_h:
3443  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srari_h:
3444  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srli_h:
3445  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srlri_h: i = 1; l = 0; u = 15; break;
3446  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsli_h:
3447  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsri_h: i = 2; l = 0; u = 15; break;
3448  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 5 bit immediate.
3449  // The first block of intrinsics actually have an unsigned 5 bit field,
3450  // not a df/n field.
3451  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_cfcmsa:
3452  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ctcmsa: i = 0; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3453  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_u_b:
3454  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_u_h:
3455  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_u_w:
3456  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_u_d:
3457  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_u_b:
3458  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_u_h:
3459  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_u_w:
3460  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_u_d:
3461  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_u_b:
3462  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_u_h:
3463  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_u_w:
3464  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_u_d:
3465  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_u_b:
3466  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_u_h:
3467  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_u_w:
3468  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_u_d:
3469  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_addvi_b:
3470  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_addvi_h:
3471  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_addvi_w:
3472  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_addvi_d:
3473  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bclri_w:
3474  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bnegi_w:
3475  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bseti_w:
3476  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_s_w:
3477  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_u_w:
3478  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_slli_w:
3479  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srai_w:
3480  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srari_w:
3481  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srli_w:
3482  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srlri_w:
3483  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_subvi_b:
3484  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_subvi_h:
3485  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_subvi_w:
3486  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_subvi_d: i = 1; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3487  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsli_w:
3488  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsri_w: i = 2; l = 0; u = 31; break;
3489  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 6 bit immediate.
3490  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bclri_d:
3491  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bnegi_d:
3492  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bseti_d:
3493  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_s_d:
3494  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sat_u_d:
3495  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_slli_d:
3496  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srai_d:
3497  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srari_d:
3498  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srli_d:
3499  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_srlri_d: i = 1; l = 0; u = 63; break;
3500  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsli_d:
3501  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_binsri_d: i = 2; l = 0; u = 63; break;
3502  // These intrinsics take a signed 5 bit immediate.
3503  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ceqi_b:
3504  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ceqi_h:
3505  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ceqi_w:
3506  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ceqi_d:
3507  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_s_b:
3508  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_s_h:
3509  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_s_w:
3510  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clti_s_d:
3511  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_s_b:
3512  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_s_h:
3513  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_s_w:
3514  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_clei_s_d:
3515  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_s_b:
3516  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_s_h:
3517  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_s_w:
3518  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_maxi_s_d:
3519  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_s_b:
3520  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_s_h:
3521  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_s_w:
3522  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_mini_s_d: i = 1; l = -16; u = 15; break;
3523  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 8 bit immediate.
3524  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_andi_b:
3525  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_nori_b:
3526  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ori_b:
3527  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_shf_b:
3528  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_shf_h:
3529  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_shf_w:
3530  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_xori_b: i = 1; l = 0; u = 255; break;
3531  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bseli_b:
3532  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bmnzi_b:
3533  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_bmzi_b: i = 2; l = 0; u = 255; break;
3534  // df/n format
3535  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 4 bit immediate.
3536  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_s_b:
3537  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_u_b:
3538  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_insve_b:
3539  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_splati_b: i = 1; l = 0; u = 15; break;
3540  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sldi_b: i = 2; l = 0; u = 15; break;
3541  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 3 bit immediate.
3542  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_s_h:
3543  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_u_h:
3544  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_insve_h:
3545  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_splati_h: i = 1; l = 0; u = 7; break;
3546  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sldi_h: i = 2; l = 0; u = 7; break;
3547  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 2 bit immediate.
3548  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_s_w:
3549  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_u_w:
3550  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_insve_w:
3551  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_splati_w: i = 1; l = 0; u = 3; break;
3552  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sldi_w: i = 2; l = 0; u = 3; break;
3553  // These intrinsics take an unsigned 1 bit immediate.
3554  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_s_d:
3555  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_copy_u_d:
3556  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_insve_d:
3557  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_splati_d: i = 1; l = 0; u = 1; break;
3558  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_sldi_d: i = 2; l = 0; u = 1; break;
3559  // Memory offsets and immediate loads.
3560  // These intrinsics take a signed 10 bit immediate.
3561  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ldi_b: i = 0; l = -128; u = 255; break;
3562  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ldi_h:
3563  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ldi_w:
3564  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ldi_d: i = 0; l = -512; u = 511; break;
3565  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ld_b: i = 1; l = -512; u = 511; m = 1; break;
3566  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ld_h: i = 1; l = -1024; u = 1022; m = 2; break;
3567  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ld_w: i = 1; l = -2048; u = 2044; m = 4; break;
3568  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ld_d: i = 1; l = -4096; u = 4088; m = 8; break;
3569  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ldr_d: i = 1; l = -4096; u = 4088; m = 8; break;
3570  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_ldr_w: i = 1; l = -2048; u = 2044; m = 4; break;
3571  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_st_b: i = 2; l = -512; u = 511; m = 1; break;
3572  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_st_h: i = 2; l = -1024; u = 1022; m = 2; break;
3573  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_st_w: i = 2; l = -2048; u = 2044; m = 4; break;
3574  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_st_d: i = 2; l = -4096; u = 4088; m = 8; break;
3575  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_str_d: i = 2; l = -4096; u = 4088; m = 8; break;
3576  case Mips::BI__builtin_msa_str_w: i = 2; l = -2048; u = 2044; m = 4; break;
3577  }
3578 
3579  if (!m)
3580  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, l, u);
3581 
3582  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, l, u) ||
3583  SemaBuiltinConstantArgMultiple(TheCall, i, m);
3584 }
3585 
3586 /// DecodePPCMMATypeFromStr - This decodes one PPC MMA type descriptor from Str,
3587 /// advancing the pointer over the consumed characters. The decoded type is
3588 /// returned. If the decoded type represents a constant integer with a
3589 /// constraint on its value then Mask is set to that value. The type descriptors
3590 /// used in Str are specific to PPC MMA builtins and are documented in the file
3591 /// defining the PPC builtins.
3592 static QualType DecodePPCMMATypeFromStr(ASTContext &Context, const char *&Str,
3593  unsigned &Mask) {
3594  bool RequireICE = false;
3595  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error = ASTContext::GE_None;
3596  switch (*Str++) {
3597  case 'V':
3598  return Context.getVectorType(Context.UnsignedCharTy, 16,
3599  VectorType::VectorKind::AltiVecVector);
3600  case 'i': {
3601  char *End;
3602  unsigned size = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
3603  assert(End != Str && "Missing constant parameter constraint");
3604  Str = End;
3605  Mask = size;
3606  return Context.IntTy;
3607  }
3608  case 'W': {
3609  char *End;
3610  unsigned size = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
3611  assert(End != Str && "Missing PowerPC MMA type size");
3612  Str = End;
3613  QualType Type;
3614  switch (size) {
3615  #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(typeName, Id, size) \
3616  case size: Type = Context.Id##Ty; break;
3617  #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
3618  default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid PowerPC MMA vector type");
3619  }
3620  bool CheckVectorArgs = false;
3621  while (!CheckVectorArgs) {
3622  switch (*Str++) {
3623  case '*':
3624  Type = Context.getPointerType(Type);
3625  break;
3626  case 'C':
3627  Type = Type.withConst();
3628  break;
3629  default:
3630  CheckVectorArgs = true;
3631  --Str;
3632  break;
3633  }
3634  }
3635  return Type;
3636  }
3637  default:
3638  return Context.DecodeTypeStr(--Str, Context, Error, RequireICE, true);
3639  }
3640 }
3641 
3642 static bool isPPC_64Builtin(unsigned BuiltinID) {
3643  // These builtins only work on PPC 64bit targets.
3644  switch (BuiltinID) {
3645  case PPC::BI__builtin_divde:
3646  case PPC::BI__builtin_divdeu:
3647  case PPC::BI__builtin_bpermd:
3648  case PPC::BI__builtin_pdepd:
3649  case PPC::BI__builtin_pextd:
3650  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_ldarx:
3651  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_stdcx:
3652  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_tdw:
3653  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_trapd:
3654  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_cmpeqb:
3655  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_setb:
3656  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mulhd:
3657  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mulhdu:
3658  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_maddhd:
3659  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_maddhdu:
3660  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_maddld:
3661  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_load8r:
3662  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_store8r:
3663  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_insert_exp:
3664  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_extract_sig:
3665  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_addex:
3666  case PPC::BI__builtin_darn:
3667  case PPC::BI__builtin_darn_raw:
3668  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_and_swaplp:
3669  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_addlp:
3670  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_andlp:
3671  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_orlp:
3672  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_swaplp:
3673  return true;
3674  }
3675  return false;
3676 }

3678 static bool SemaFeatureCheck(Sema &S, CallExpr *TheCall,
3679  StringRef FeatureToCheck, unsigned DiagID,
3680  StringRef DiagArg = "") {
3681  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature(FeatureToCheck))
3682  return false;
3683 
3684  if (DiagArg.empty())
3685  S.Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), DiagID) << TheCall->getSourceRange();
3686  else
3687  S.Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), DiagID)
3688  << DiagArg << TheCall->getSourceRange();
3689 
3690  return true;
3691 }
3692 
3693 /// Returns true if the argument consists of one contiguous run of 1s with any
3694 /// number of 0s on either side. The 1s are allowed to wrap from LSB to MSB, so
3695 /// 0x000FFF0, 0x0000FFFF, 0xFF0000FF, 0x0 are all runs. 0x0F0F0000 is not,
3696 /// since all 1s are not contiguous.
3697 bool Sema::SemaValueIsRunOfOnes(CallExpr *TheCall, unsigned ArgNum) {
3698  llvm::APSInt Result;
3699  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
3700  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
3701  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
3702  return false;
3703 
3704  // Check constant-ness first.
3705  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
3706  return true;
3707 
3708  // Check contiguous run of 1s, 0xFF0000FF is also a run of 1s.
3709  if (Result.isShiftedMask() || (~Result).isShiftedMask())
3710  return false;
3711 
3712  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
3713  diag::err_argument_not_contiguous_bit_field)
3714  << ArgNum << Arg->getSourceRange();
3715 }
3716 
3717 bool Sema::CheckPPCBuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI, unsigned BuiltinID,
3718  CallExpr *TheCall) {
3719  unsigned i = 0, l = 0, u = 0;
3720  bool IsTarget64Bit = TI.getTypeWidth(TI.getIntPtrType()) == 64;
3721  llvm::APSInt Result;
3722 
3723  if (isPPC_64Builtin(BuiltinID) && !IsTarget64Bit)
3724  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_64_bit_builtin_32_bit_tgt)
3725  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
3726 
3727  switch (BuiltinID) {
3728  default: return false;
3729  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_crypto_vshasigmaw:
3730  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_crypto_vshasigmad:
3731  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1) ||
3732  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 15);
3733  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_dss:
3734  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 3);
3735  case PPC::BI__builtin_tbegin:
3736  case PPC::BI__builtin_tend:
3737  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 1) ||
3738  SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "htm",
3739  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_htm);
3740  case PPC::BI__builtin_tsr:
3741  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 7) ||
3742  SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "htm",
3743  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_htm);
3744  case PPC::BI__builtin_tabortwc:
3745  case PPC::BI__builtin_tabortdc:
3746  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 31) ||
3747  SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "htm",
3748  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_htm);
3749  case PPC::BI__builtin_tabortwci:
3750  case PPC::BI__builtin_tabortdci:
3751  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "htm",
3752  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_htm) ||
3753  (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 31) ||
3754  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 31));
3755  case PPC::BI__builtin_tabort:
3756  case PPC::BI__builtin_tcheck:
3757  case PPC::BI__builtin_treclaim:
3758  case PPC::BI__builtin_trechkpt:
3759  case PPC::BI__builtin_tendall:
3760  case PPC::BI__builtin_tresume:
3761  case PPC::BI__builtin_tsuspend:
3762  case PPC::BI__builtin_get_texasr:
3763  case PPC::BI__builtin_get_texasru:
3764  case PPC::BI__builtin_get_tfhar:
3765  case PPC::BI__builtin_get_tfiar:
3766  case PPC::BI__builtin_set_texasr:
3767  case PPC::BI__builtin_set_texasru:
3768  case PPC::BI__builtin_set_tfhar:
3769  case PPC::BI__builtin_set_tfiar:
3770  case PPC::BI__builtin_ttest:
3771  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "htm",
3772  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_htm);
3773  // According to GCC 'Basic PowerPC Built-in Functions Available on ISA 2.05',
3774  // __builtin_(un)pack_longdouble are available only if long double uses IBM
3775  // extended double representation.
3776  case PPC::BI__builtin_unpack_longdouble:
3777  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1))
3778  return true;
3779  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3780  case PPC::BI__builtin_pack_longdouble:
3781  if (&TI.getLongDoubleFormat() != &llvm::APFloat::PPCDoubleDouble())
3782  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_abi)
3783  << "ibmlongdouble";
3784  return false;
3785  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_dst:
3786  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_dstt:
3787  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_dstst:
3788  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_dststt:
3789  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 3);
3790  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxpermdi:
3791  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxsldwi:
3792  return SemaBuiltinVSX(TheCall);
3793  case PPC::BI__builtin_divwe:
3794  case PPC::BI__builtin_divweu:
3795  case PPC::BI__builtin_divde:
3796  case PPC::BI__builtin_divdeu:
3797  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "extdiv",
3798  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "7");
3799  case PPC::BI__builtin_bpermd:
3800  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "bpermd",
3801  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "7");
3802  case PPC::BI__builtin_unpack_vector_int128:
3803  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "vsx",
3804  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "7") ||
3805  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1);
3806  case PPC::BI__builtin_pack_vector_int128:
3807  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "vsx",
3808  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "7");
3809  case PPC::BI__builtin_pdepd:
3810  case PPC::BI__builtin_pextd:
3811  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v31-instructions",
3812  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "10");
3813  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vgnb:
3814  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 2, 7);
3815  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_elt:
3816  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_unaligned: {
3817  QualType VecTy = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
3818  QualType EltTy = TheCall->getArg(1)->getType();
3819  unsigned Width = Context.getIntWidth(EltTy);
3820  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, Width == 32 ? 12 : 8) ||
3821  !isEltOfVectorTy(Context, TheCall, *this, VecTy, EltTy);
3822  }
3823  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxeval:
3824  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 3, 0, 255);
3825  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vsldbi:
3826  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 7);
3827  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vsrdbi:
3828  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 7);
3829  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxpermx:
3830  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 3, 0, 7);
3831  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_tw:
3832  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_tdw:
3833  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 1, 31);
3834  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_cmpeqb:
3835  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_setb:
3836  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_maddhd:
3837  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_maddhdu:
3838  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_maddld:
3839  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v30-instructions",
3840  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9");
3841  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_cmprb:
3842  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v30-instructions",
3843  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9") ||
3844  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 1);
3845  // For __rlwnm, __rlwimi and __rldimi, the last parameter mask must
3846  // be a constant that represents a contiguous bit field.
3847  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rlwnm:
3848  return SemaValueIsRunOfOnes(TheCall, 2);
3849  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rlwimi:
3850  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rldimi:
3851  return SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, 2, Result) ||
3852  SemaValueIsRunOfOnes(TheCall, 3);
3853  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_extract_exp:
3854  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_extract_sig:
3855  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_insert_exp:
3856  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "power9-vector",
3857  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9");
3858  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_addex: {
3859  if (SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v30-instructions",
3860  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9") ||
3861  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 3))
3862  return true;
3863  // Output warning for reserved values 1 to 3.
3864  int ArgValue =
3865  TheCall->getArg(2)->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)->getSExtValue();
3866  if (ArgValue != 0)
3867  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_argument_undefined_behaviour)
3868  << ArgValue;
3869  return false;
3870  }
3871  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mtfsb0:
3872  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mtfsb1:
3873  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 31);
3874  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mtfsf:
3875  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 255);
3876  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mtfsfi:
3877  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 7) ||
3878  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 15);
3879  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_alignx:
3880  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgPower2(TheCall, 0);
3881  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rdlam:
3882  return SemaValueIsRunOfOnes(TheCall, 2);
3883  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_icbt:
3884  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_sthcx:
3885  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_stbcx:
3886  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_lharx:
3887  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_lbarx:
3888  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v207-instructions",
3889  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "8");
3890  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_ldrmb:
3891  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_strmb:
3892  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v207-instructions",
3893  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "8") ||
3894  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 1, 16);
3895  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vcntmbb:
3896  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vcntmbh:
3897  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vcntmbw:
3898  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vcntmbd:
3899  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 1);
3900  case PPC::BI__builtin_darn:
3901  case PPC::BI__builtin_darn_raw:
3902  case PPC::BI__builtin_darn_32:
3903  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v30-instructions",
3904  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9");
3905  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxgenpcvbm:
3906  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxgenpcvhm:
3907  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxgenpcvwm:
3908  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxgenpcvdm:
3909  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 3);
3910  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_exp_uo:
3911  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_exp_lt:
3912  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_exp_gt:
3913  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_exp_eq:
3914  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v30-instructions",
3915  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9") ||
3916  SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "vsx",
3917  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_vsx);
3918  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_test_data_class: {
3919  // Check if the first argument of the __builtin_ppc_test_data_class call is
3920  // valid. The argument must be either a 'float' or a 'double'.
3921  QualType ArgType = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
3922  if (ArgType != QualType(Context.FloatTy) &&
3923  ArgType != QualType(Context.DoubleTy))
3924  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
3925  diag::err_ppc_invalid_test_data_class_type);
3926  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v30-instructions",
3927  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "9") ||
3928  SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "vsx",
3929  diag::err_ppc_builtin_requires_vsx) ||
3930  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 127);
3931  }
3932  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_load8r:
3933  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_store8r:
3934  return SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "isa-v206-instructions",
3935  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "7");
3936 #define CUSTOM_BUILTIN(Name, Intr, Types, Acc) \
3937  case PPC::BI__builtin_##Name: \
3938  return SemaBuiltinPPCMMACall(TheCall, BuiltinID, Types);
3939 #include "clang/Basic/BuiltinsPPC.def"
3940  }
3941  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, l, u);
3942 }
3943 
3944 // Check if the given type is a non-pointer PPC MMA type. This function is used
3945 // in Sema to prevent invalid uses of restricted PPC MMA types.
3946 bool Sema::CheckPPCMMAType(QualType Type, SourceLocation TypeLoc) {
3947  if (Type->isPointerType() || Type->isArrayType())
3948  return false;
3949 
3950  QualType CoreType = Type.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
3951 #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, Size) || CoreType == Context.Id##Ty
3952  if (false
3953 #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
3954  ) {
3955  Diag(TypeLoc, diag::err_ppc_invalid_use_mma_type);
3956  return true;
3957  }
3958  return false;
3959 }
3960 
3961 bool Sema::CheckAMDGCNBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID,
3962  CallExpr *TheCall) {
3963  // position of memory order and scope arguments in the builtin
3964  unsigned OrderIndex, ScopeIndex;
3965  switch (BuiltinID) {
3966  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_inc32:
3967  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_inc64:
3968  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_dec32:
3969  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_dec64:
3970  OrderIndex = 2;
3971  ScopeIndex = 3;
3972  break;
3973  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_fence:
3974  OrderIndex = 0;
3975  ScopeIndex = 1;
3976  break;
3977  default:
3978  return false;
3979  }
3980 
3981  ExprResult Arg = TheCall->getArg(OrderIndex);
3982  auto ArgExpr = Arg.get();
3983  Expr::EvalResult ArgResult;
3984 
3985  if (!ArgExpr->EvaluateAsInt(ArgResult, Context))
3986  return Diag(ArgExpr->getExprLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_expect_int)
3987  << ArgExpr->getType();
3988  auto Ord = ArgResult.Val.getInt().getZExtValue();
3989 
3990  // Check validity of memory ordering as per C11 / C++11's memody model.
3991  // Only fence needs check. Atomic dec/inc allow all memory orders.
3992  if (!llvm::isValidAtomicOrderingCABI(Ord))
3993  return Diag(ArgExpr->getBeginLoc(),
3994  diag::warn_atomic_op_has_invalid_memory_order)
3995  << ArgExpr->getSourceRange();
3996  switch (static_cast<llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI>(Ord)) {
3997  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::relaxed:
3998  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume:
3999  if (BuiltinID == AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_fence)
4000  return Diag(ArgExpr->getBeginLoc(),
4001  diag::warn_atomic_op_has_invalid_memory_order)
4002  << ArgExpr->getSourceRange();
4003  break;
4004  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire:
4005  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::release:
4006  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel:
4007  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::seq_cst:
4008  break;
4009  }
4010 
4011  Arg = TheCall->getArg(ScopeIndex);
4012  ArgExpr = Arg.get();
4013  Expr::EvalResult ArgResult1;
4014  // Check that sync scope is a constant literal
4015  if (!ArgExpr->EvaluateAsConstantExpr(ArgResult1, Context))
4016  return Diag(ArgExpr->getExprLoc(), diag::err_expr_not_string_literal)
4017  << ArgExpr->getType();
4018 
4019  return false;
4020 }
4021 
4022 bool Sema::CheckRISCVLMUL(CallExpr *TheCall, unsigned ArgNum) {
4023  llvm::APSInt Result;
4024 
4025  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
4026  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
4027  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
4028  return false;
4029 
4030  // Check constant-ness first.
4031  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
4032  return true;
4033 
4034  int64_t Val = Result.getSExtValue();
4035  if ((Val >= 0 && Val <= 3) || (Val >= 5 && Val <= 7))
4036  return false;
4037 
4038  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_riscv_builtin_invalid_lmul)
4039  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4040 }
4041 
4042 static bool isRISCV32Builtin(unsigned BuiltinID) {
4043  // These builtins only work on riscv32 targets.
4044  switch (BuiltinID) {
4045  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_zip_32:
4046  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_unzip_32:
4047  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32dsi_32:
4048  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32dsmi_32:
4049  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32esi_32:
4050  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32esmi_32:
4051  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sha512sig0h_32:
4052  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sha512sig0l_32:
4053  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sha512sig1h_32:
4054  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sha512sig1l_32:
4055  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sha512sum0r_32:
4056  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sha512sum1r_32:
4057  return true;
4058  }
4059 
4060  return false;
4061 }
4062 
4063 bool Sema::CheckRISCVBuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI,
4064  unsigned BuiltinID,
4065  CallExpr *TheCall) {
4066  // CodeGenFunction can also detect this, but this gives a better error
4067  // message.
4068  bool FeatureMissing = false;
4069  SmallVector<StringRef> ReqFeatures;
4070  StringRef Features = Context.BuiltinInfo.getRequiredFeatures(BuiltinID);
4071  Features.split(ReqFeatures, ',');
4072 
4073  // Check for 32-bit only builtins on a 64-bit target.
4074  const llvm::Triple &TT = TI.getTriple();
4075  if (TT.getArch() != llvm::Triple::riscv32 && isRISCV32Builtin(BuiltinID))
4076  return Diag(TheCall->getCallee()->getBeginLoc(),
4077  diag::err_32_bit_builtin_64_bit_tgt);
4078 
4079  // Check if each required feature is included
4080  for (StringRef F : ReqFeatures) {
4081  SmallVector<StringRef> ReqOpFeatures;
4082  F.split(ReqOpFeatures, '|');
4083  bool HasFeature = false;
4084  for (StringRef OF : ReqOpFeatures) {
4085  if (TI.hasFeature(OF)) {
4086  HasFeature = true;
4087  continue;
4088  }
4089  }
4090 
4091  if (!HasFeature) {
4092  std::string FeatureStrs;
4093  for (StringRef OF : ReqOpFeatures) {
4094  // If the feature is 64bit, alter the string so it will print better in
4095  // the diagnostic.
4096  if (OF == "64bit")
4097  OF = "RV64";
4098 
4099  // Convert features like "zbr" and "experimental-zbr" to "Zbr".
4100  OF.consume_front("experimental-");
4101  std::string FeatureStr = OF.str();
4102  FeatureStr[0] = std::toupper(FeatureStr[0]);
4103  // Combine strings.
4104  FeatureStrs += FeatureStrs == "" ? "" : ", ";
4105  FeatureStrs += "'";
4106  FeatureStrs += FeatureStr;
4107  FeatureStrs += "'";
4108  }
4109  // Error message
4110  FeatureMissing = true;
4111  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_riscv_builtin_requires_extension)
4112  << TheCall->getSourceRange() << StringRef(FeatureStrs);
4113  }
4114  }
4115 
4116  if (FeatureMissing)
4117  return true;
4118 
4119  switch (BuiltinID) {
4120  case RISCVVector::BI__builtin_rvv_vsetvli:
4121  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 3) ||
4122  CheckRISCVLMUL(TheCall, 2);
4123  case RISCVVector::BI__builtin_rvv_vsetvlimax:
4124  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 0, 0, 3) ||
4125  CheckRISCVLMUL(TheCall, 1);
4126  // Check if byteselect is in [0, 3]
4127  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32dsi_32:
4128  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32dsmi_32:
4129  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32esi_32:
4130  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes32esmi_32:
4131  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sm4ks:
4132  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_sm4ed:
4133  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 3);
4134  // Check if rnum is in [0, 10]
4135  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_aes64ks1i_64:
4136  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 10);
4137  }
4138 
4139  return false;
4140 }
4141 
4142 bool Sema::CheckSystemZBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID,
4143  CallExpr *TheCall) {
4144  if (BuiltinID == SystemZ::BI__builtin_tabort) {
4145  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
4146  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> AbortCode = Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context))
4147  if (AbortCode->getSExtValue() >= 0 && AbortCode->getSExtValue() < 256)
4148  return Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_systemz_invalid_tabort_code)
4149  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4150  }
4151 
4152  // For intrinsics which take an immediate value as part of the instruction,
4153  // range check them here.
4154  unsigned i = 0, l = 0, u = 0;
4155  switch (BuiltinID) {
4156  default: return false;
4157  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_lcbb: i = 1; l = 0; u = 15; break;
4158  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_verimb:
4159  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_verimh:
4160  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_verimf:

4163  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaeh:

4166  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaehs:
4167  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaefs:

4169  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaezh:
4170  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaezf:
4171  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaezbs:
4172  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaezhs:
4173  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfaezfs: i = 2; l = 0; u = 15; break;

4175  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfidb:
4176  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 15) ||
4177  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 2, 0, 15);
4178  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vftcisb:
4179  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vftcidb: i = 1; l = 0; u = 4095; break;
4180  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vlbb: i = 1; l = 0; u = 15; break;
4181  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vpdi: i = 2; l = 0; u = 15; break;
4182  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vsldb: i = 2; l = 0; u = 15; break;
4183  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrcb:
4184  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrch:
4185  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrcf:

4187  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrczh:

4190  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrchs:

4192  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrczbs:
4193  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrczhs:
4194  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vstrczfs: i = 3; l = 0; u = 15; break;
4195  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vmslg: i = 3; l = 0; u = 15; break;
4196  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfminsb:

4201  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vsrd: i = 2; l = 0; u = 7; break;
4202  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vclfnhs:
4203  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vclfnls:
4204  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vcfn:

4206  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vcrnfs: i = 2; l = 0; u = 15; break;

4211 /// SemaBuiltinCpuSupports - Handle __builtin_cpu_supports(char *).
4212 /// This checks that the target supports __builtin_cpu_supports and
4213 /// that the string argument is constant and valid.
4214 static bool SemaBuiltinCpuSupports(Sema &S, const TargetInfo &TI,
4215  CallExpr *TheCall) {
4216  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
4217 
4218  // Check if the argument is a string literal.
4219  if (!isa<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
4220  return S.Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_expr_not_string_literal)
4221  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4222 
4223  // Check the contents of the string.
4224  StringRef Feature =
4225  cast<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts())->getString();
4226  if (!TI.validateCpuSupports(Feature))
4227  return S.Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_invalid_cpu_supports)
4228  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4229  return false;
4230 }
4231 
4232 /// SemaBuiltinCpuIs - Handle __builtin_cpu_is(char *).
4233 /// This checks that the target supports __builtin_cpu_is and
4234 /// that the string argument is constant and valid.
4235 static bool SemaBuiltinCpuIs(Sema &S, const TargetInfo &TI, CallExpr *TheCall) {
4236  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
4237 
4238  // Check if the argument is a string literal.
4239  if (!isa<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
4240  return S.Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_expr_not_string_literal)
4241  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4242 
4243  // Check the contents of the string.
4244  StringRef Feature =
4245  cast<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts())->getString();
4246  if (!TI.validateCpuIs(Feature))
4247  return S.Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_invalid_cpu_is)
4248  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4249  return false;
4250 }

4506  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddcph512_maskz:
4507  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddcph512_mask3:

4509  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcsh_round_mask:
4510  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcsh_round_mask3:
4511  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcph512_mask:
4512  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcph512_maskz:
4513  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcph512_mask3:
4514  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmulcsh_mask:
4515  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmulcph512_mask:
4516  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmulcsh_mask:
4517  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmulcph512_mask:
4518  ArgNum = 4;
4519  HasRC = true;
4520  break;
4521  }
4522 
4523  llvm::APSInt Result;
4524 
4525  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
4526  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
4527  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
4528  return false;
4529 
4530  // Check constant-ness first.
4531  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
4532  return true;
4533 
4534  // Make sure rounding mode is either ROUND_CUR_DIRECTION or ROUND_NO_EXC bit
4535  // is set. If the intrinsic has rounding control(bits 1:0), make sure its only
4536  // combined with ROUND_NO_EXC. If the intrinsic does not have rounding
4537  // control, allow ROUND_NO_EXC and ROUND_CUR_DIRECTION together.
4538  if (Result == 4/*ROUND_CUR_DIRECTION*/ ||
4539  Result == 8/*ROUND_NO_EXC*/ ||
4540  (!HasRC && Result == 12/*ROUND_CUR_DIRECTION|ROUND_NO_EXC*/) ||
4541  (HasRC && Result.getZExtValue() >= 8 && Result.getZExtValue() <= 11))
4542  return false;
4543 
4544  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_x86_builtin_invalid_rounding)
4545  << Arg->getSourceRange();
4546 }
