4651 enum { TileRegLow = 0, TileRegHigh = 7 };
4652 
4653 bool Sema::CheckX86BuiltinTileArgumentsRange(CallExpr *TheCall,
4654  ArrayRef<int> ArgNums) {
4655  for (int ArgNum : ArgNums) {
4656  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, TileRegLow, TileRegHigh))
4657  return true;
4658  }
4659  return false;
4660 }
4661 
4662 bool Sema::CheckX86BuiltinTileDuplicate(CallExpr *TheCall,
4663  ArrayRef<int> ArgNums) {
4664  // Because the max number of tile register is TileRegHigh + 1, so here we use
4665  // each bit to represent the usage of them in bitset.
4666  std::bitset<TileRegHigh + 1> ArgValues;
4667  for (int ArgNum : ArgNums) {
4668  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
4669  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
4670  continue;
4671 
4672  llvm::APSInt Result;
4673  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
4674  return true;
4675  int ArgExtValue = Result.getExtValue();
4676  assert((ArgExtValue >= TileRegLow || ArgExtValue <= TileRegHigh) &&
4677  "Incorrect tile register num.");
4678  if (ArgValues.test(ArgExtValue))
4679  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
4680  diag::err_x86_builtin_tile_arg_duplicate)
4681  << TheCall->getArg(ArgNum)->getSourceRange();
4682  ArgValues.set(ArgExtValue);
4683  }
4684  return false;
4685 }
4686 
4687 bool Sema::CheckX86BuiltinTileRangeAndDuplicate(CallExpr *TheCall,
4688  ArrayRef<int> ArgNums) {
4689  return CheckX86BuiltinTileArgumentsRange(TheCall, ArgNums) ||
4690  CheckX86BuiltinTileDuplicate(TheCall, ArgNums);
4691 }
4692 
4693 bool Sema::CheckX86BuiltinTileArguments(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
4694  switch (BuiltinID) {
4695  default:
4696  return false;
4697  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tileloadd64:
4698  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tileloaddt164:
4699  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tilestored64:
4700  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tilezero:
4701  return CheckX86BuiltinTileArgumentsRange(TheCall, 0);
4702  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tdpbssd:
4703  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tdpbsud:
4704  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tdpbusd:
4705  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tdpbuud:
4706  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tdpbf16ps:
4707  return CheckX86BuiltinTileRangeAndDuplicate(TheCall, {0, 1, 2});
4708  }
4709 }
4710 static bool isX86_32Builtin(unsigned BuiltinID) {
4711  // These builtins only work on x86-32 targets.
4712  switch (BuiltinID) {
4713  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_readeflags_u32:
4714  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_writeeflags_u32:
4715  return true;
4716  }
4717 
4718  return false;
4719 }
4720 
4721 bool Sema::CheckX86BuiltinFunctionCall(const TargetInfo &TI, unsigned BuiltinID,
4722  CallExpr *TheCall) {
4723  if (BuiltinID == X86::BI__builtin_cpu_supports)
4724  return SemaBuiltinCpuSupports(*this, TI, TheCall);
4725 
4726  if (BuiltinID == X86::BI__builtin_cpu_is)
4727  return SemaBuiltinCpuIs(*this, TI, TheCall);
4728 
4729  // Check for 32-bit only builtins on a 64-bit target.
4730  const llvm::Triple &TT = TI.getTriple();
4731  if (TT.getArch() != llvm::Triple::x86 && isX86_32Builtin(BuiltinID))
4732  return Diag(TheCall->getCallee()->getBeginLoc(),
4733  diag::err_32_bit_builtin_64_bit_tgt);
4734 
4735  // If the intrinsic has rounding or SAE make sure its valid.
4736  if (CheckX86BuiltinRoundingOrSAE(BuiltinID, TheCall))
4737  return true;
4738 
4739  // If the intrinsic has a gather/scatter scale immediate make sure its valid.
4740  if (CheckX86BuiltinGatherScatterScale(BuiltinID, TheCall))
4741  return true;
4742 
4743  // If the intrinsic has a tile arguments, make sure they are valid.
4744  if (CheckX86BuiltinTileArguments(BuiltinID, TheCall))
4745  return true;
4746 
4747  // For intrinsics which take an immediate value as part of the instruction,
4748  // range check them here.
4749  int i = 0, l = 0, u = 0;
4750  switch (BuiltinID) {
4751  default:
4752  return false;
4753  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v2si:
4754  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v2di:
4755  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vextractf128_pd256:
4756  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vextractf128_ps256:
4757  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vextractf128_si256:
4758  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extract128i256:
4759  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extractf64x4_mask:
4760  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extracti64x4_mask:
4761  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extractf32x8_mask:
4762  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extracti32x8_mask:
4763  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extractf64x2_256_mask:
4764  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extracti64x2_256_mask:
4765  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extractf32x4_256_mask:
4766  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extracti32x4_256_mask:
4767  i = 1; l = 0; u = 1;
4768  break;
4769  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v2di:
4770  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vinsertf128_pd256:
4771  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vinsertf128_ps256:
4772  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vinsertf128_si256:
4773  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_insert128i256:
4774  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_insertf32x8:
4775  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_inserti32x8:
4776  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_insertf64x4:
4777  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_inserti64x4:
4778  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_insertf64x2_256:
4779  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_inserti64x2_256:
4780  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_insertf32x4_256:
4781  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_inserti32x4_256:
4782  i = 2; l = 0; u = 1;
4783  break;
4784  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpermilpd:
4785  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4hi:
4786  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4si:
4787  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4sf:
4788  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4di:
4789  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extractf32x4_mask:
4790  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extracti32x4_mask:
4791  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extractf64x2_512_mask:
4792  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_extracti64x2_512_mask:
4793  i = 1; l = 0; u = 3;
4794  break;
4795  case X86::BI_mm_prefetch:
4796  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v8hi:

5093  // Note that we don't force a hard error on the range check here, allowing
5094  // template-generated or macro-generated dead code to potentially have out-of-
5095  // range values. These need to code generate, but don't need to necessarily
5096  // make any sense. We use a warning that defaults to an error.
5097  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, l, u, /*RangeIsError*/ false);
5098 }
5099 
5100 static bool checkIntelFPGARegArgument(Sema &S, QualType ArgType,
5101  SourceLocation &Loc) {
5102  if (ArgType.getTypePtr()->isArrayType())
5103  return true;
5104 
5105  // Non-POD classes are allowed. Each field is checked for illegal type.
5106  if (CXXRecordDecl *Record = ArgType->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
5107  for (auto *FD : Record->fields()) {
5108  QualType T = FD->getType();
5109  Loc = FD->getLocation();
5110  if (const ArrayType *AT = T->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
5111  T = AT->getElementType();
5112  if (checkIntelFPGARegArgument(S, T, Loc))
5113  return true;
5114  }
5115  return false;
5116  }
5117 
5118  QualType CTy = ArgType.getCanonicalType();
5119 
5120  if (CTy->isFunctionPointerType() || CTy->isImageType() ||
5121  CTy->isEventT() || CTy->isSamplerT() || CTy->isPipeType())
5122  return true;
5123 
5124  // Check to filter out unintended types. Records are handled above.
5125  if (!CTy.isCXX98PODType(S.Context))
5126  return true;
5127 
5128  return false;
5129 }
5130 
5131 bool Sema::CheckIntelFPGARegBuiltinFunctionCall(unsigned BuiltinID,
5132  CallExpr *TheCall) {
5133  switch (BuiltinID) {
5134  case Builtin::BI__builtin_intel_fpga_reg: {
5135  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 1))
5136  return true;
5137 
5138  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
5139  QualType ArgType = Arg->getType();
5140  SourceLocation Loc;
5141 
5142  if (checkIntelFPGARegArgument(*this, ArgType, Loc)) {
5143  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_intel_fpga_reg_limitations)
5144  << (ArgType.getTypePtr()->isRecordType() ? 1 : 0) << ArgType
5145  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
5146  if (ArgType.getTypePtr()->isRecordType())
5147  Diag(Loc, diag::illegal_type_declared_here);
5148  return true;
5149  }
5150 
5151  TheCall->setType(ArgType);
5152 
5153  return false;
5154  }
5155  default:
5156  return true;
5157  }
5158 }
5159 
5160 bool Sema::CheckIntelFPGAMemBuiltinFunctionCall(CallExpr *TheCall) {
5161  // Make sure we have exactly 3 arguments
5162  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 3))
5163  return true;
5164 
5165  Expr *PointerArg = TheCall->getArg(0);
5166  QualType PointerArgType = PointerArg->getType();
5167 
5168  // Make sure that the first argument is a pointer
5169  if (!isa<PointerType>(PointerArgType))
5170  return Diag(PointerArg->getBeginLoc(),
5171  diag::err_intel_fpga_mem_arg_mismatch)
5172  << 0;
5173 
5174  // Make sure that the pointer points to a legal type
5175  // We use the same argument checks used for __builtin_intel_fpga_reg
5176  QualType PointeeType = PointerArgType->getPointeeType();
5177  SourceLocation Loc;
5178  if (checkIntelFPGARegArgument(*this, PointeeType, Loc)) {
5179  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_intel_fpga_mem_limitations)
5180  << (PointeeType->isRecordType() ? 1 : 0) << PointerArgType
5181  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
5182  if (PointeeType->isRecordType())
5183  Diag(Loc, diag::illegal_type_declared_here);
5184  return true;
5185  }
5186 
5187  // Second argument must be a constant integer
5188  llvm::APSInt Result;
5189  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, 1, Result))
5190  return true;
5191 
5192  // Third argument (CacheSize) must be a non-negative constant integer
5193  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, 2, Result))
5194  return true;
5195  if (Result < 0)
5196  return Diag(TheCall->getArg(2)->getBeginLoc(),
5197  diag::err_intel_fpga_mem_arg_mismatch) << 1;
5198 
5199  // Set the return type to be the same as the type of the first argument
5200  // (pointer argument)
5201  TheCall->setType(PointerArgType);
5202  return false;
5203 }
5204 
5205 /// Given a FunctionDecl's FormatAttr, attempts to populate the FomatStringInfo
5206 /// parameter with the FormatAttr's correct format_idx and firstDataArg.
5207 /// Returns true when the format fits the function and the FormatStringInfo has
5208 /// been populated.
5209 bool Sema::getFormatStringInfo(const FormatAttr *Format, bool IsCXXMember,
5210  FormatStringInfo *FSI) {
5211  FSI->HasVAListArg = Format->getFirstArg() == 0;
5212  FSI->FormatIdx = Format->getFormatIdx() - 1;
5213  FSI->FirstDataArg = FSI->HasVAListArg ? 0 : Format->getFirstArg() - 1;
5214 
5215  // The way the format attribute works in GCC, the implicit this argument
5216  // of member functions is counted. However, it doesn't appear in our own
5217  // lists, so decrement format_idx in that case.
5218  if (IsCXXMember) {
5219  if(FSI->FormatIdx == 0)
5220  return false;
5221  --FSI->FormatIdx;
5222  if (FSI->FirstDataArg != 0)
5223  --FSI->FirstDataArg;
5224  }
5225  return true;
5226 }
5227 
5228 /// Checks if a the given expression evaluates to null.
5229 ///
5230 /// Returns true if the value evaluates to null.
5231 static bool CheckNonNullExpr(Sema &S, const Expr *Expr) {
5232  // If the expression has non-null type, it doesn't evaluate to null.
5233  if (auto nullability
5234  = Expr->IgnoreImplicit()->getType()->getNullability(S.Context)) {
5235  if (*nullability == NullabilityKind::NonNull)
5236  return false;
5237  }
5238 
5239  // As a special case, transparent unions initialized with zero are
5240  // considered null for the purposes of the nonnull attribute.
5241  if (const RecordType *UT = Expr->getType()->getAsUnionType()) {
5242  if (UT->getDecl()->hasAttr<TransparentUnionAttr>())
5243  if (const CompoundLiteralExpr *CLE =
5244  dyn_cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(Expr))
5245  if (const InitListExpr *ILE =
5246  dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(CLE->getInitializer()))
5247  Expr = ILE->getInit(0);
5248  }
5249 
5250  bool Result;
5251  return (!Expr->isValueDependent() &&
5252  Expr->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(Result, S.Context) &&
5253  !Result);
5254 }
5255 
5256 static void CheckNonNullArgument(Sema &S,
5257  const Expr *ArgExpr,
5258  SourceLocation CallSiteLoc) {
5259  if (CheckNonNullExpr(S, ArgExpr))
5260  S.DiagRuntimeBehavior(CallSiteLoc, ArgExpr,
5261  S.PDiag(diag::warn_null_arg)
5262  << ArgExpr->getSourceRange());
5263 }
5264 
5265 bool Sema::GetFormatNSStringIdx(const FormatAttr *Format, unsigned &Idx) {
5266  FormatStringInfo FSI;
5267  if ((GetFormatStringType(Format) == FST_NSString) &&
5268  getFormatStringInfo(Format, false, &FSI)) {
5269  Idx = FSI.FormatIdx;
5270  return true;
5271  }
5272  return false;
5273 }
5274 
5275 /// Diagnose use of %s directive in an NSString which is being passed
5276 /// as formatting string to formatting method.
5277 static void
5278 DiagnoseCStringFormatDirectiveInCFAPI(Sema &S,
5279  const NamedDecl *FDecl,
5280  Expr **Args,
5281  unsigned NumArgs) {
5282  unsigned Idx = 0;
5283  bool Format = false;
5284  ObjCStringFormatFamily SFFamily = FDecl->getObjCFStringFormattingFamily();
5285  if (SFFamily == ObjCStringFormatFamily::SFF_CFString) {
5286  Idx = 2;
5287  Format = true;
5288  }
5289  else
5290  for (const auto *I : FDecl->specific_attrs<FormatAttr>()) {
5291  if (S.GetFormatNSStringIdx(I, Idx)) {
5292  Format = true;
5293  break;
5294  }
5295  }
5296  if (!Format || NumArgs <= Idx)
5297  return;
5298  const Expr *FormatExpr = Args[Idx];
5299  if (const CStyleCastExpr *CSCE = dyn_cast<CStyleCastExpr>(FormatExpr))
5300  FormatExpr = CSCE->getSubExpr();
5301  const StringLiteral *FormatString;
5302  if (const ObjCStringLiteral *OSL =
5303  dyn_cast<ObjCStringLiteral>(FormatExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
5304  FormatString = OSL->getString();
5305  else
5306  FormatString = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(FormatExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
5307  if (!FormatString)
5308  return;
5309  if (S.FormatStringHasSArg(FormatString)) {
5310  S.Diag(FormatExpr->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_objc_cdirective_format_string)
5311  << "%s" << 1 << 1;
5312  S.Diag(FDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_entity_declared_at)
5313  << FDecl->getDeclName();
5314  }
5315 }
5316 
5317 /// Determine whether the given type has a non-null nullability annotation.
5318 static bool isNonNullType(ASTContext &ctx, QualType type) {
5319  if (auto nullability = type->getNullability(ctx))
5320  return *nullability == NullabilityKind::NonNull;
5321 
5322  return false;
5323 }
5324 
5325 static void CheckNonNullArguments(Sema &S,
5326  const NamedDecl *FDecl,
5327  const FunctionProtoType *Proto,
5328  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
5329  SourceLocation CallSiteLoc) {
5330  assert((FDecl || Proto) && "Need a function declaration or prototype");
5331 
5332  // Already checked by by constant evaluator.
5333  if (S.isConstantEvaluated())
5334  return;
5335  // Check the attributes attached to the method/function itself.
5336  llvm::SmallBitVector NonNullArgs;
5337  if (FDecl) {
5338  // Handle the nonnull attribute on the function/method declaration itself.
5339  for (const auto *NonNull : FDecl->specific_attrs<NonNullAttr>()) {
5340  if (!NonNull->args_size()) {
5341  // Easy case: all pointer arguments are nonnull.
5342  for (const auto *Arg : Args)
5343  if (S.isValidPointerAttrType(Arg->getType()))
5344  CheckNonNullArgument(S, Arg, CallSiteLoc);
5345  return;
5346  }
5347 
5348  for (const ParamIdx &Idx : NonNull->args()) {
5349  unsigned IdxAST = Idx.getASTIndex();
5350  if (IdxAST >= Args.size())
5351  continue;
5352  if (NonNullArgs.empty())
5353  NonNullArgs.resize(Args.size());
5354  NonNullArgs.set(IdxAST);
5355  }
5356  }
5357  }
5358 
5359  if (FDecl && (isa<FunctionDecl>(FDecl) || isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(FDecl))) {
5360  // Handle the nonnull attribute on the parameters of the
5361  // function/method.
5362  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl*> parms;
5363  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(FDecl))
5364  parms = FD->parameters();
5365  else
5366  parms = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(FDecl)->parameters();
5367 
5368  unsigned ParamIndex = 0;
5369  for (ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl*>::iterator I = parms.begin(), E = parms.end();
5370  I != E; ++I, ++ParamIndex) {
5371  const ParmVarDecl *PVD = *I;
5372  if (PVD->hasAttr<NonNullAttr>() ||
5373  isNonNullType(S.Context, PVD->getType())) {
5374  if (NonNullArgs.empty())
5375  NonNullArgs.resize(Args.size());
5376 
5377  NonNullArgs.set(ParamIndex);
5378  }
5379  }
5380  } else {
5381  // If we have a non-function, non-method declaration but no
5382  // function prototype, try to dig out the function prototype.
5383  if (!Proto) {
5384  if (const ValueDecl *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(FDecl)) {
5385  QualType type = VD->getType().getNonReferenceType();
5386  if (auto pointerType = type->getAs<PointerType>())
5387  type = pointerType->getPointeeType();
5388  else if (auto blockType = type->getAs<BlockPointerType>())
5389  type = blockType->getPointeeType();
5390  // FIXME: data member pointers?
5391 
5392  // Dig out the function prototype, if there is one.
5393  Proto = type->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5394  }
5395  }
5396 
5397  // Fill in non-null argument information from the nullability
5398  // information on the parameter types (if we have them).
5399  if (Proto) {
5400  unsigned Index = 0;
5401  for (auto paramType : Proto->getParamTypes()) {
5402  if (isNonNullType(S.Context, paramType)) {
5403  if (NonNullArgs.empty())
5404  NonNullArgs.resize(Args.size());
5405 
5406  NonNullArgs.set(Index);
5407  }
5408 
5409  ++Index;
5410  }
5411  }
5412  }
5413 
5414  // Check for non-null arguments.
5415  for (unsigned ArgIndex = 0, ArgIndexEnd = NonNullArgs.size();
5416  ArgIndex != ArgIndexEnd; ++ArgIndex) {
5417  if (NonNullArgs[ArgIndex])
5418  CheckNonNullArgument(S, Args[ArgIndex], CallSiteLoc);
5419  }
5420 }
5421 
5422 /// Warn if a pointer or reference argument passed to a function points to an
5423 /// object that is less aligned than the parameter. This can happen when
5424 /// creating a typedef with a lower alignment than the original type and then
5425 /// calling functions defined in terms of the original type.
5426 void Sema::CheckArgAlignment(SourceLocation Loc, NamedDecl *FDecl,
5427  StringRef ParamName, QualType ArgTy,
5428  QualType ParamTy) {
5429 
5430  // If a function accepts a pointer or reference type
5431  if (!ParamTy->isPointerType() && !ParamTy->isReferenceType())
5432  return;
5433 
5434  // If the parameter is a pointer type, get the pointee type for the
5435  // argument too. If the parameter is a reference type, don't try to get
5436  // the pointee type for the argument.
5437  if (ParamTy->isPointerType())
5438  ArgTy = ArgTy->getPointeeType();
5439 
5440  // Remove reference or pointer
5441  ParamTy = ParamTy->getPointeeType();
5442 
5443  // Find expected alignment, and the actual alignment of the passed object.
5444  // getTypeAlignInChars requires complete types
5445  if (ArgTy.isNull() || ParamTy->isIncompleteType() ||
5446  ArgTy->isIncompleteType() || ParamTy->isUndeducedType() ||
5447  ArgTy->isUndeducedType())
5448  return;
5449 
5450  CharUnits ParamAlign = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(ParamTy);
5451  CharUnits ArgAlign = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(ArgTy);
5452 
5453  // If the argument is less aligned than the parameter, there is a
5454  // potential alignment issue.
5455  if (ArgAlign < ParamAlign)
5456  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_param_mismatched_alignment)
5457  << (int)ArgAlign.getQuantity() << (int)ParamAlign.getQuantity()
5458  << ParamName << (FDecl != nullptr) << FDecl;
5459 }
5460 
5461 /// Handles the checks for format strings, non-POD arguments to vararg
5462 /// functions, NULL arguments passed to non-NULL parameters, and diagnose_if
5463 /// attributes.
5464 void Sema::checkCall(NamedDecl *FDecl, const FunctionProtoType *Proto,
5465  const Expr *ThisArg, ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
5466  bool IsMemberFunction, SourceLocation Loc,
5467  SourceRange Range, VariadicCallType CallType) {
5468  // FIXME: We should check as much as we can in the template definition.
5469  if (CurContext->isDependentContext())
5470  return;
5471 
5472  // Printf and scanf checking.
5473  llvm::SmallBitVector CheckedVarArgs;
5474  if (FDecl) {
5475  for (const auto *I : FDecl->specific_attrs<FormatAttr>()) {
5476  // Only create vector if there are format attributes.
5477  CheckedVarArgs.resize(Args.size());
5478 
5479  CheckFormatArguments(I, Args, IsMemberFunction, CallType, Loc, Range,
5480  CheckedVarArgs);
5481  }
5482  }
5483 
5484  // Refuse POD arguments that weren't caught by the format string
5485  // checks above.
5486  auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(FDecl);
5487  if (CallType != VariadicDoesNotApply &&
5488  (!FD || FD->getBuiltinID() != Builtin::BI__noop)) {
5489  unsigned NumParams = Proto ? Proto->getNumParams()
5490  : FDecl && isa<FunctionDecl>(FDecl)
5491  ? cast<FunctionDecl>(FDecl)->getNumParams()
5492  : FDecl && isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(FDecl)
5493  ? cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(FDecl)->param_size()
5494  : 0;
5495 
5496  for (unsigned ArgIdx = NumParams; ArgIdx < Args.size(); ++ArgIdx) {
5497  // Args[ArgIdx] can be null in malformed code.
5498  if (const Expr *Arg = Args[ArgIdx]) {
5499  if (CheckedVarArgs.empty() || !CheckedVarArgs[ArgIdx])
5500  checkVariadicArgument(Arg, CallType);
5501  }
5502  }
5503  }
5504 
5505  if (FDecl || Proto) {
5506  CheckNonNullArguments(*this, FDecl, Proto, Args, Loc);
5507 
5508  // Type safety checking.
5509  if (FDecl) {
5510  for (const auto *I : FDecl->specific_attrs<ArgumentWithTypeTagAttr>())
5511  CheckArgumentWithTypeTag(I, Args, Loc);
5512  }
5513  }
5514 
5515  // Check that passed arguments match the alignment of original arguments.
5516  // Try to get the missing prototype from the declaration.
5517  if (!Proto && FDecl) {
5518  const auto *FT = FDecl->getFunctionType();
5519  if (isa_and_nonnull<FunctionProtoType>(FT))
5520  Proto = cast<FunctionProtoType>(FDecl->getFunctionType());
5521  }
5522  if (Proto) {
5523  // For variadic functions, we may have more args than parameters.
5524  // For some K&R functions, we may have less args than parameters.
5525  const auto N = std::min<unsigned>(Proto->getNumParams(), Args.size());
5526  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx < N; ++ArgIdx) {
5527  // Args[ArgIdx] can be null in malformed code.
5528  if (const Expr *Arg = Args[ArgIdx]) {
5529  if (Arg->containsErrors())
5530  continue;
5531 
5532  QualType ParamTy = Proto->getParamType(ArgIdx);
5533  QualType ArgTy = Arg->getType();
5534  CheckArgAlignment(Arg->getExprLoc(), FDecl, std::to_string(ArgIdx + 1),
5535  ArgTy, ParamTy);
5536  }
5537  }
5538  }
5539 
5540  if (FDecl && FDecl->hasAttr<AllocAlignAttr>()) {
5541  auto *AA = FDecl->getAttr<AllocAlignAttr>();
5542  const Expr *Arg = Args[AA->getParamIndex().getASTIndex()];
5543  if (!Arg->isValueDependent()) {
5544  Expr::EvalResult Align;
5545  if (Arg->EvaluateAsInt(Align, Context)) {
5546  const llvm::APSInt &I = Align.Val.getInt();
5547  if (!I.isPowerOf2())
5548  Diag(Arg->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_alignment_not_power_of_two)
5549  << Arg->getSourceRange();
5550 
5551  if (I > Sema::MaximumAlignment)
5552  Diag(Arg->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_assume_aligned_too_great)
5553  << Arg->getSourceRange() << Sema::MaximumAlignment;
5554  }
5555  }
5556  }
5557 
5558  if (FD)
5559  diagnoseArgDependentDiagnoseIfAttrs(FD, ThisArg, Args, Loc);
5560 
5561  if (FD && FD->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>())
5562  CheckSYCLKernelCall(FD, Range, Args);
5563 
5564  // Diagnose variadic calls in SYCL.
5565  if (FD && FD ->isVariadic() && getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
5566  !isUnevaluatedContext() && !isKnownGoodSYCLDecl(FD))
5567  SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(Loc, diag::err_sycl_restrict)
5568  << Sema::KernelCallVariadicFunction;
5569 }
5570 
5571 /// CheckConstructorCall - Check a constructor call for correctness and safety
5572 /// properties not enforced by the C type system.
5573 void Sema::CheckConstructorCall(FunctionDecl *FDecl, QualType ThisType,
5574  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
5575  const FunctionProtoType *Proto,
5576  SourceLocation Loc) {
5577  VariadicCallType CallType =
5578  Proto->isVariadic() ? VariadicConstructor : VariadicDoesNotApply;
5579 
5580  auto *Ctor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(FDecl);
5581  CheckArgAlignment(Loc, FDecl, "'this'", Context.getPointerType(ThisType),
5582  Context.getPointerType(Ctor->getThisObjectType()));
5583 
5584  checkCall(FDecl, Proto, /*ThisArg=*/nullptr, Args, /*IsMemberFunction=*/true,
5585  Loc, SourceRange(), CallType);
5586 }
5587 
5588 /// CheckFunctionCall - Check a direct function call for various correctness
5589 /// and safety properties not strictly enforced by the C type system.
5590 bool Sema::CheckFunctionCall(FunctionDecl *FDecl, CallExpr *TheCall,
5591  const FunctionProtoType *Proto) {
5592  bool IsMemberOperatorCall = isa<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(TheCall) &&
5593  isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FDecl);
5594  bool IsMemberFunction = isa<CXXMemberCallExpr>(TheCall) ||
5595  IsMemberOperatorCall;
5596  VariadicCallType CallType = getVariadicCallType(FDecl, Proto,
5597  TheCall->getCallee());
5598  Expr** Args = TheCall->getArgs();
5599  unsigned NumArgs = TheCall->getNumArgs();
5600 
5601  Expr *ImplicitThis = nullptr;
5602  if (IsMemberOperatorCall) {
5603  // If this is a call to a member operator, hide the first argument
5604  // from checkCall.
5605  // FIXME: Our choice of AST representation here is less than ideal.
5606  ImplicitThis = Args[0];
5607  ++Args;
5608  --NumArgs;
5609  } else if (IsMemberFunction)
5610  ImplicitThis =
5611  cast<CXXMemberCallExpr>(TheCall)->getImplicitObjectArgument();
5612 
5613  if (ImplicitThis) {
5614  // ImplicitThis may or may not be a pointer, depending on whether . or -> is
5615  // used.
5616  QualType ThisType = ImplicitThis->getType();
5617  if (!ThisType->isPointerType()) {
5618  assert(!ThisType->isReferenceType());
5619  ThisType = Context.getPointerType(ThisType);
5620  }
5621 
5622  QualType ThisTypeFromDecl =
5623  Context.getPointerType(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FDecl)->getThisObjectType());
5624 
5625  CheckArgAlignment(TheCall->getRParenLoc(), FDecl, "'this'", ThisType,
5626  ThisTypeFromDecl);
5627  }
5628 
5629  checkCall(FDecl, Proto, ImplicitThis, llvm::makeArrayRef(Args, NumArgs),
5630  IsMemberFunction, TheCall->getRParenLoc(),
5631  TheCall->getCallee()->getSourceRange(), CallType);
5632 
5633  IdentifierInfo *FnInfo = FDecl->getIdentifier();
5634  // None of the checks below are needed for functions that don't have
5635  // simple names (e.g., C++ conversion functions).
5636  if (!FnInfo)
5637  return false;
5638 
5639  CheckTCBEnforcement(TheCall, FDecl);
5640 
5641  CheckAbsoluteValueFunction(TheCall, FDecl);
5642  CheckMaxUnsignedZero(TheCall, FDecl);
5643 
5644  if (getLangOpts().ObjC)
5645  DiagnoseCStringFormatDirectiveInCFAPI(*this, FDecl, Args, NumArgs);
5646 
5647  unsigned CMId = FDecl->getMemoryFunctionKind();
5648 
5649  // Handle memory setting and copying functions.
5650  switch (CMId) {
5651  case 0:
5652  return false;
5653  case Builtin::BIstrlcpy: // fallthrough
5654  case Builtin::BIstrlcat:
5655  CheckStrlcpycatArguments(TheCall, FnInfo);
5656  break;
5657  case Builtin::BIstrncat:
5658  CheckStrncatArguments(TheCall, FnInfo);
5659  break;
5660  case Builtin::BIfree:
5661  CheckFreeArguments(TheCall);
5662  break;
5663  default:
5664  CheckMemaccessArguments(TheCall, CMId, FnInfo);
5665  }
5666 
5667  return false;
5668 }
5669 
5670 bool Sema::CheckObjCMethodCall(ObjCMethodDecl *Method, SourceLocation lbrac,
5671  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args) {
5672  VariadicCallType CallType =
5673  Method->isVariadic() ? VariadicMethod : VariadicDoesNotApply;
5674 
5675  checkCall(Method, nullptr, /*ThisArg=*/nullptr, Args,
5676  /*IsMemberFunction=*/false, lbrac, Method->getSourceRange(),
5677  CallType);
5678 
5679  return false;
5680 }
5681 
5682 bool Sema::CheckPointerCall(NamedDecl *NDecl, CallExpr *TheCall,
5683  const FunctionProtoType *Proto) {
5684  QualType Ty;
5685  if (const auto *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(NDecl))
5686  Ty = V->getType().getNonReferenceType();
5687  else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(NDecl))
5688  Ty = F->getType().getNonReferenceType();
5689  else
5690  return false;
5691 
5692  if (!Ty->isBlockPointerType() && !Ty->isFunctionPointerType() &&
5693  !Ty->isFunctionProtoType())
5694  return false;
5695 
5696  VariadicCallType CallType;
5697  if (!Proto || !Proto->isVariadic()) {
5698  CallType = VariadicDoesNotApply;
5699  } else if (Ty->isBlockPointerType()) {
5700  CallType = VariadicBlock;
5701  } else { // Ty->isFunctionPointerType()
5702  CallType = VariadicFunction;
5703  }
5704 
5705  checkCall(NDecl, Proto, /*ThisArg=*/nullptr,
5706  llvm::makeArrayRef(TheCall->getArgs(), TheCall->getNumArgs()),
5707  /*IsMemberFunction=*/false, TheCall->getRParenLoc(),
5708  TheCall->getCallee()->getSourceRange(), CallType);
5709 
5710  return false;
5711 }
