5713 /// Checks function calls when a FunctionDecl or a NamedDecl is not available,
5714 /// such as function pointers returned from functions.
5715 bool Sema::CheckOtherCall(CallExpr *TheCall, const FunctionProtoType *Proto) {
5716  VariadicCallType CallType = getVariadicCallType(/*FDecl=*/nullptr, Proto,
5717  TheCall->getCallee());
5718  checkCall(/*FDecl=*/nullptr, Proto, /*ThisArg=*/nullptr,
5719  llvm::makeArrayRef(TheCall->getArgs(), TheCall->getNumArgs()),
5720  /*IsMemberFunction=*/false, TheCall->getRParenLoc(),
5721  TheCall->getCallee()->getSourceRange(), CallType);
5722 
5723  return false;
5724 }
5725 
5726 static bool isValidOrderingForOp(int64_t Ordering, AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op) {
5727  if (!llvm::isValidAtomicOrderingCABI(Ordering))
5728  return false;
5729 
5730  auto OrderingCABI = (llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI)Ordering;
5731  switch (Op) {
5732  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
5733  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init:
5734  llvm_unreachable("There is no ordering argument for an init");
5735 
5736  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
5737  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load:
5738  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_load:
5739  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
5740  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load:
5741  return OrderingCABI != llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::release &&
5742  OrderingCABI != llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel;
5743 
5744  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
5745  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store:
5746  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_store:
5747  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
5748  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n:
5749  return OrderingCABI != llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume &&
5750  OrderingCABI != llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire &&
5751  OrderingCABI != llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel;
5752 
5753  default:
5754  return true;
5755  }
5756 }
5757 
5758 ExprResult Sema::SemaAtomicOpsOverloaded(ExprResult TheCallResult,
5759  AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op) {
5760  CallExpr *TheCall = cast<CallExpr>(TheCallResult.get());
5761  DeclRefExpr *DRE =cast<DeclRefExpr>(TheCall->getCallee()->IgnoreParenCasts());
5762  MultiExprArg Args{TheCall->getArgs(), TheCall->getNumArgs()};
5763  return BuildAtomicExpr({TheCall->getBeginLoc(), TheCall->getEndLoc()},
5764  DRE->getSourceRange(), TheCall->getRParenLoc(), Args,
5765  Op);
5766 }
5767 
5768 ExprResult Sema::BuildAtomicExpr(SourceRange CallRange, SourceRange ExprRange,
5769  SourceLocation RParenLoc, MultiExprArg Args,
5770  AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op,
5771  AtomicArgumentOrder ArgOrder) {
5772  // All the non-OpenCL operations take one of the following forms.
5773  // The OpenCL operations take the __c11 forms with one extra argument for
5774  // synchronization scope.
5775  enum {
5776  // C __c11_atomic_init(A *, C)
5777  Init,
5778 
5779  // C __c11_atomic_load(A *, int)
5780  Load,
5781 
5782  // void __atomic_load(A *, CP, int)
5783  LoadCopy,
5784 
5785  // void __atomic_store(A *, CP, int)
5786  Copy,
5787 
5788  // C __c11_atomic_add(A *, M, int)
5789  Arithmetic,
5790 
5791  // C __atomic_exchange_n(A *, CP, int)
5792  Xchg,
5793 
5794  // void __atomic_exchange(A *, C *, CP, int)
5795  GNUXchg,
5796 
5797  // bool __c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong(A *, C *, CP, int, int)
5798  C11CmpXchg,
5799 
5800  // bool __atomic_compare_exchange(A *, C *, CP, bool, int, int)
5801  GNUCmpXchg
5802  } Form = Init;
5803 
5804  const unsigned NumForm = GNUCmpXchg + 1;
5805  const unsigned NumArgs[] = { 2, 2, 3, 3, 3, 3, 4, 5, 6 };
5806  const unsigned NumVals[] = { 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3 };
5807  // where:
5808  // C is an appropriate type,
5809  // A is volatile _Atomic(C) for __c11 builtins and is C for GNU builtins,
5810  // CP is C for __c11 builtins and GNU _n builtins and is C * otherwise,
5811  // M is C if C is an integer, and ptrdiff_t if C is a pointer, and
5812  // the int parameters are for orderings.
5813 
5814  static_assert(sizeof(NumArgs)/sizeof(NumArgs[0]) == NumForm
5815  && sizeof(NumVals)/sizeof(NumVals[0]) == NumForm,
5816  "need to update code for modified forms");
5817  static_assert(AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init == 0 &&
5818  AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_min + 1 ==
5819  AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load,
5820  "need to update code for modified C11 atomics");
5821  bool IsOpenCL = Op >= AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init &&
5822  Op <= AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_max;
5823  bool IsHIP = Op >= AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_load &&
5824  Op <= AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_max;
5825  bool IsC11 = (Op >= AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init &&
5826  Op <= AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_min) ||
5827  IsOpenCL;
5828  bool IsN = Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n ||
5829  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n ||
5830  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n ||
5831  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n;
5832  bool IsAddSub = false;
5833 
5834  switch (Op) {
5835  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
5836  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init:
5837  Form = Init;
5838  break;
5839 
5840  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
5841  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load:
5842  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_load:
5843  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
5844  Form = Load;
5845  break;
5846 
5847  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load:
5848  Form = LoadCopy;
5849  break;
5850 
5851  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
5852  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store:
5853  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_store:
5854  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
5855  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n:
5856  Form = Copy;
5857  break;
5858  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_add:
5859  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_min:
5860  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_max:
5861  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_add:
5862  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_sub:
5863  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_add:
5864  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_sub:
5865  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_add:
5866  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_sub:
5867  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_add_fetch:
5868  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_sub_fetch:
5869  IsAddSub = true;
5870  Form = Arithmetic;
5871  break;
5872  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_and:
5873  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_or:
5874  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_xor:
5875  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_and:
5876  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_or:
5877  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_fetch_xor:
5878  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_nand:
5879  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_and:
5880  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_or:
5881  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_xor:
5882  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_and:
5883  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_or:
5884  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_xor:
5885  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_nand:
5886  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_and_fetch:
5887  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_or_fetch:
5888  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_xor_fetch:
5889  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch:
5890  Form = Arithmetic;
5891  break;
5892  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_min:
5893  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_max:
5894  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_min:
5895  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_max:
5896  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_min_fetch:
5897  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_max_fetch:
5898  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_min:
5899  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_max:
5900  Form = Arithmetic;
5901  break;
5902 
5903  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_exchange:
5904  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_exchange:
5905  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_exchange:
5906  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n:
5907  Form = Xchg;
5908  break;
5909 
5910  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange:
5911  Form = GNUXchg;
5912  break;
5913 
5914  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
5915  case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
5916  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
5917  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
5918  case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
5919  case AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
5920  Form = C11CmpXchg;
5921  break;
5922 
5923  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange:
5924  case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n:
5925  Form = GNUCmpXchg;
5926  break;
5927  }
5928 
5929  unsigned AdjustedNumArgs = NumArgs[Form];
5930  if ((IsOpenCL || IsHIP) && Op != AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init)
5931  ++AdjustedNumArgs;
5932  // Check we have the right number of arguments.
5933  if (Args.size() < AdjustedNumArgs) {
5934  Diag(CallRange.getEnd(), diag::err_typecheck_call_too_few_args)
5935  << 0 << AdjustedNumArgs << static_cast<unsigned>(Args.size())
5936  << ExprRange;
5937  return ExprError();
5938  } else if (Args.size() > AdjustedNumArgs) {
5939  Diag(Args[AdjustedNumArgs]->getBeginLoc(),
5940  diag::err_typecheck_call_too_many_args)
5941  << 0 << AdjustedNumArgs << static_cast<unsigned>(Args.size())
5942  << ExprRange;
5943  return ExprError();
5944  }
5945 
5946  // Inspect the first argument of the atomic operation.
5947  Expr *Ptr = Args[0];
5948  ExprResult ConvertedPtr = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Ptr);
5949  if (ConvertedPtr.isInvalid())
5950  return ExprError();
5951 
5952  Ptr = ConvertedPtr.get();
5953  const PointerType *pointerType = Ptr->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
5954  if (!pointerType) {
5955  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_must_be_pointer)
5956  << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
5957  return ExprError();
5958  }
5959 
5960  // For a __c11 builtin, this should be a pointer to an _Atomic type.
5961  QualType AtomTy = pointerType->getPointeeType(); // 'A'
5962  QualType ValType = AtomTy; // 'C'
5963  if (IsC11) {
5964  if (!AtomTy->isAtomicType()) {
5965  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_atomic)
5966  << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
5967  return ExprError();
5968  }
5969  if ((Form != Load && Form != LoadCopy && AtomTy.isConstQualified()) ||
5970  AtomTy.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_constant) {
5971  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_non_const_atomic)
5972  << (AtomTy.isConstQualified() ? 0 : 1) << Ptr->getType()
5973  << Ptr->getSourceRange();
5974  return ExprError();
5975  }
5976  ValType = AtomTy->castAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType();
5977  } else if (Form != Load && Form != LoadCopy) {
5978  if (ValType.isConstQualified()) {
5979  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_non_const_pointer)
5980  << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
5981  return ExprError();
5982  }
5983  }
5984 
5985  // For an arithmetic operation, the implied arithmetic must be well-formed.
5986  if (Form == Arithmetic) {
5987  // GCC does not enforce these rules for GNU atomics, but we do to help catch
5988  // trivial type errors.
5989  auto IsAllowedValueType = [&](QualType ValType) {
5990  if (ValType->isIntegerType())
5991  return true;
5992  if (ValType->isPointerType())
5993  return true;
5994  if (!ValType->isFloatingType())
5995  return false;
5996  // LLVM Parser does not allow atomicrmw with x86_fp80 type.
5997  if (ValType->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::LongDouble) &&
5998  &Context.getTargetInfo().getLongDoubleFormat() ==
5999  &llvm::APFloat::x87DoubleExtended())
6000  return false;
6001  return true;
6002  };
6003  if (IsAddSub && !IsAllowedValueType(ValType)) {
6004  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_atomic_int_ptr_or_fp)
6005  << IsC11 << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
6006  return ExprError();
6007  }
6008  if (!IsAddSub && !ValType->isIntegerType()) {
6009  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_atomic_int)
6010  << IsC11 << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
6011  return ExprError();
6012  }
6013  if (IsC11 && ValType->isPointerType() &&
6014  RequireCompleteType(Ptr->getBeginLoc(), ValType->getPointeeType(),
6015  diag::err_incomplete_type)) {
6016  return ExprError();
6017  }
6018  } else if (IsN && !ValType->isIntegerType() && !ValType->isPointerType()) {
6019  // For __atomic_*_n operations, the value type must be a scalar integral or
6020  // pointer type which is 1, 2, 4, 8 or 16 bytes in length.
6021  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_atomic_int_or_ptr)
6022  << IsC11 << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
6023  return ExprError();
6024  }
6025 
6026  if (!IsC11 && !AtomTy.isTriviallyCopyableType(Context) &&
6027  !AtomTy->isScalarType()) {
6028  // For GNU atomics, require a trivially-copyable type. This is not part of
6029  // the GNU atomics specification but we enforce it for consistency with
6030  // other atomics which generally all require a trivially-copyable type. This
6031  // is because atomics just copy bits.
6032  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_atomic_op_needs_trivial_copy)
6033  << Ptr->getType() << Ptr->getSourceRange();
6034  return ExprError();
6035  }
6036 
6037  switch (ValType.getObjCLifetime()) {
6038  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
6039  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
6040  // okay
6041  break;
6042 
6043  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
6044  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
6045  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
6046  // FIXME: Can this happen? By this point, ValType should be known
6047  // to be trivially copyable.
6048  Diag(ExprRange.getBegin(), diag::err_arc_atomic_ownership)
6049  << ValType << Ptr->getSourceRange();
6050  return ExprError();
6051  }
6052 
6053  // All atomic operations have an overload which takes a pointer to a volatile
6054  // 'A'. We shouldn't let the volatile-ness of the pointee-type inject itself
6055  // into the result or the other operands. Similarly atomic_load takes a
6056  // pointer to a const 'A'.
6057  ValType.removeLocalVolatile();
6058  ValType.removeLocalConst();
6059  QualType ResultType = ValType;
6060  if (Form == Copy || Form == LoadCopy || Form == GNUXchg ||
6061  Form == Init)
6062  ResultType = Context.VoidTy;
6063  else if (Form == C11CmpXchg || Form == GNUCmpXchg)
6064  ResultType = Context.BoolTy;
6065 
6066  // The type of a parameter passed 'by value'. In the GNU atomics, such
6067  // arguments are actually passed as pointers.
6068  QualType ByValType = ValType; // 'CP'
6069  bool IsPassedByAddress = false;
6070  if (!IsC11 && !IsHIP && !IsN) {
6071  ByValType = Ptr->getType();
6072  IsPassedByAddress = true;
6073  }
6074 
6075  SmallVector<Expr *, 5> APIOrderedArgs;
6076  if (ArgOrder == Sema::AtomicArgumentOrder::AST) {
6077  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[0]);
6078  switch (Form) {
6079  case Init:
6080  case Load:
6081  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[1]); // Val1/Order
6082  break;
6083  case LoadCopy:
6084  case Copy:
6085  case Arithmetic:
6086  case Xchg:
6087  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[2]); // Val1
6088  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[1]); // Order
6089  break;
6090  case GNUXchg:
6091  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[2]); // Val1
6092  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[3]); // Val2
6093  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[1]); // Order
6094  break;
6095  case C11CmpXchg:
6096  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[2]); // Val1
6097  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[4]); // Val2
6098  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[1]); // Order
6099  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[3]); // OrderFail
6100  break;
6101  case GNUCmpXchg:
6102  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[2]); // Val1
6103  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[4]); // Val2
6104  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[5]); // Weak
6105  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[1]); // Order
6106  APIOrderedArgs.push_back(Args[3]); // OrderFail
6107  break;
6108  }
6109  } else
6110  APIOrderedArgs.append(Args.begin(), Args.end());
6111 
6112  // The first argument's non-CV pointer type is used to deduce the type of
6113  // subsequent arguments, except for:
6114  // - weak flag (always converted to bool)
6115  // - memory order (always converted to int)
6116  // - scope (always converted to int)
6117  for (unsigned i = 0; i != APIOrderedArgs.size(); ++i) {
6118  QualType Ty;
6119  if (i < NumVals[Form] + 1) {
6120  switch (i) {
6121  case 0:
6122  // The first argument is always a pointer. It has a fixed type.
6123  // It is always dereferenced, a nullptr is undefined.
6124  CheckNonNullArgument(*this, APIOrderedArgs[i], ExprRange.getBegin());
6125  // Nothing else to do: we already know all we want about this pointer.
6126  continue;
6127  case 1:
6128  // The second argument is the non-atomic operand. For arithmetic, this
6129  // is always passed by value, and for a compare_exchange it is always
6130  // passed by address. For the rest, GNU uses by-address and C11 uses
6131  // by-value.
6132  assert(Form != Load);
6133  if (Form == Arithmetic && ValType->isPointerType())
6134  Ty = Context.getPointerDiffType();
6135  else if (Form == Init || Form == Arithmetic)
6136  Ty = ValType;
6137  else if (Form == Copy || Form == Xchg) {
6138  if (IsPassedByAddress) {
6139  // The value pointer is always dereferenced, a nullptr is undefined.
6140  CheckNonNullArgument(*this, APIOrderedArgs[i],
6141  ExprRange.getBegin());
6142  }
6143  Ty = ByValType;
6144  } else {
6145  Expr *ValArg = APIOrderedArgs[i];
6146  // The value pointer is always dereferenced, a nullptr is undefined.
6147  CheckNonNullArgument(*this, ValArg, ExprRange.getBegin());
6148  LangAS AS = LangAS::Default;
6149  // Keep address space of non-atomic pointer type.
6150  if (const PointerType *PtrTy =
6151  ValArg->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
6152  AS = PtrTy->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
6153  }
6154  Ty = Context.getPointerType(
6155  Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(ValType.getUnqualifiedType(), AS));
6156  }
6157  break;
6158  case 2:
6159  // The third argument to compare_exchange / GNU exchange is the desired
6160  // value, either by-value (for the C11 and *_n variant) or as a pointer.
6161  if (IsPassedByAddress)
6162  CheckNonNullArgument(*this, APIOrderedArgs[i], ExprRange.getBegin());
6163  Ty = ByValType;
6164  break;
6165  case 3:
6166  // The fourth argument to GNU compare_exchange is a 'weak' flag.
6167  Ty = Context.BoolTy;
6168  break;
6169  }
6170  } else {
6171  // The order(s) and scope are always converted to int.
6172  Ty = Context.IntTy;
6173  }
6174 
6175  InitializedEntity Entity =
6176  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context, Ty, false);
6177  ExprResult Arg = APIOrderedArgs[i];
6178  Arg = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), Arg);
6179  if (Arg.isInvalid())
6180  return true;
6181  APIOrderedArgs[i] = Arg.get();
6182  }
6183 
6184  // Permute the arguments into a 'consistent' order.
6185  SmallVector<Expr*, 5> SubExprs;
6186  SubExprs.push_back(Ptr);
6187  switch (Form) {
6188  case Init:
6189  // Note, AtomicExpr::getVal1() has a special case for this atomic.
6190  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[1]); // Val1
6191  break;
6192  case Load:
6193  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[1]); // Order
6194  break;
6195  case LoadCopy:
6196  case Copy:
6197  case Arithmetic:
6198  case Xchg:
6199  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[2]); // Order
6200  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[1]); // Val1
6201  break;
6202  case GNUXchg:
6203  // Note, AtomicExpr::getVal2() has a special case for this atomic.
6204  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[3]); // Order
6205  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[1]); // Val1
6206  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[2]); // Val2
6207  break;
6208  case C11CmpXchg:
6209  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[3]); // Order
6210  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[1]); // Val1
6211  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[4]); // OrderFail
6212  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[2]); // Val2
6213  break;
6214  case GNUCmpXchg:
6215  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[4]); // Order
6216  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[1]); // Val1
6217  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[5]); // OrderFail
6218  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[2]); // Val2
6219  SubExprs.push_back(APIOrderedArgs[3]); // Weak
6220  break;
6221  }
6222 
6223  if (SubExprs.size() >= 2 && Form != Init) {
6224  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result =
6225  SubExprs[1]->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context))
6226  if (!isValidOrderingForOp(Result->getSExtValue(), Op))
6227  Diag(SubExprs[1]->getBeginLoc(),
6228  diag::warn_atomic_op_has_invalid_memory_order)
6229  << SubExprs[1]->getSourceRange();
6230  }
6231 
6232  if (auto ScopeModel = AtomicExpr::getScopeModel(Op)) {
6233  auto *Scope = Args[Args.size() - 1];
6234  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result =
6235  Scope->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)) {
6236  if (!ScopeModel->isValid(Result->getZExtValue()))
6237  Diag(Scope->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_op_has_invalid_synch_scope)
6238  << Scope->getSourceRange();
6239  }
6240  SubExprs.push_back(Scope);
6241  }
6242 
6243  AtomicExpr *AE = new (Context)
6244  AtomicExpr(ExprRange.getBegin(), SubExprs, ResultType, Op, RParenLoc);
6245 
6246  if ((Op == AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load ||
6247  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store ||
6248  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load ||
6249  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_load ||
6250  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store ||
6251  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_store) &&
6252  Context.AtomicUsesUnsupportedLibcall(AE))
6253  Diag(AE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_load_store_uses_lib)
6254  << ((Op == AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load ||
6255  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load ||
6256  Op == AtomicExpr::AO__hip_atomic_load)
6257  ? 0
6258  : 1);
6259 
6260  if (ValType->isBitIntType()) {
6261  Diag(Ptr->getExprLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_bit_int_prohibit);
6262  return ExprError();
6263  }
6264 
6265  return AE;
6266 }
6267 
6268 /// checkBuiltinArgument - Given a call to a builtin function, perform
6269 /// normal type-checking on the given argument, updating the call in
6270 /// place. This is useful when a builtin function requires custom
6271 /// type-checking for some of its arguments but not necessarily all of
6272 /// them.
6273 ///
6274 /// Returns true on error.
6275 static bool checkBuiltinArgument(Sema &S, CallExpr *E, unsigned ArgIndex) {
6276  FunctionDecl *Fn = E->getDirectCallee();
6277  assert(Fn && "builtin call without direct callee!");
6278 
6279  ParmVarDecl *Param = Fn->getParamDecl(ArgIndex);
6280  InitializedEntity Entity =
6281  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(S.Context, Param);
6282 
6283  ExprResult Arg = E->getArg(0);
6284  Arg = S.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), Arg);
6285  if (Arg.isInvalid())
6286  return true;
6287 
6288  E->setArg(ArgIndex, Arg.get());
6289  return false;
6290 }
6291 
6292 /// We have a call to a function like __sync_fetch_and_add, which is an
6293 /// overloaded function based on the pointer type of its first argument.
6294 /// The main BuildCallExpr routines have already promoted the types of
6295 /// arguments because all of these calls are prototyped as void(...).
6296 ///
6297 /// This function goes through and does final semantic checking for these
6298 /// builtins, as well as generating any warnings.
6299 ExprResult
6300 Sema::SemaBuiltinAtomicOverloaded(ExprResult TheCallResult) {
6301  CallExpr *TheCall = static_cast<CallExpr *>(TheCallResult.get());
6302  Expr *Callee = TheCall->getCallee();
6303  DeclRefExpr *DRE = cast<DeclRefExpr>(Callee->IgnoreParenCasts());
6304  FunctionDecl *FDecl = cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
6305 
6306  // Ensure that we have at least one argument to do type inference from.
6307  if (TheCall->getNumArgs() < 1) {
6308  Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_call_too_few_args_at_least)
6309  << 0 << 1 << TheCall->getNumArgs() << Callee->getSourceRange();
6310  return ExprError();
6311  }
6312 
6313  // Inspect the first argument of the atomic builtin. This should always be
6314  // a pointer type, whose element is an integral scalar or pointer type.
6315  // Because it is a pointer type, we don't have to worry about any implicit
6316  // casts here.
6317  // FIXME: We don't allow floating point scalars as input.
6318  Expr *FirstArg = TheCall->getArg(0);
6319  ExprResult FirstArgResult = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(FirstArg);
6320  if (FirstArgResult.isInvalid())
6321  return ExprError();
6322  FirstArg = FirstArgResult.get();
6323  TheCall->setArg(0, FirstArg);
6324 
6325  const PointerType *pointerType = FirstArg->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
6326  if (!pointerType) {
6327  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_must_be_pointer)
6328  << FirstArg->getType() << FirstArg->getSourceRange();
6329  return ExprError();
6330  }
6331 
6332  QualType ValType = pointerType->getPointeeType();
6333  if (!ValType->isIntegerType() && !ValType->isAnyPointerType() &&
6334  !ValType->isBlockPointerType()) {
6335  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_must_be_pointer_intptr)
6336  << FirstArg->getType() << FirstArg->getSourceRange();
6337  return ExprError();
6338  }
6339 
6340  if (ValType.isConstQualified()) {
6341  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_cannot_be_const)
6342  << FirstArg->getType() << FirstArg->getSourceRange();
6343  return ExprError();
6344  }
6345 
6346  switch (ValType.getObjCLifetime()) {
6347  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
6348  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
6349  // okay
6350  break;
6351 
6352  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
6353  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
6354  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
6355  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arc_atomic_ownership)
6356  << ValType << FirstArg->getSourceRange();
6357  return ExprError();
6358  }
6359 
6360  // Strip any qualifiers off ValType.
6361  ValType = ValType.getUnqualifiedType();
6362 
6363  // The majority of builtins return a value, but a few have special return
6364  // types, so allow them to override appropriately below.
6365  QualType ResultType = ValType;
6366 
6367  // We need to figure out which concrete builtin this maps onto. For example,
6368  // __sync_fetch_and_add with a 2 byte object turns into
6369  // __sync_fetch_and_add_2.
6370 #define BUILTIN_ROW(x) \
6371  { Builtin::BI##x##_1, Builtin::BI##x##_2, Builtin::BI##x##_4, \
6372  Builtin::BI##x##_8, Builtin::BI##x##_16 }
6373 
6374  static const unsigned BuiltinIndices[][5] = {
6375  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_fetch_and_add),
6376  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_fetch_and_sub),
6377  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_fetch_and_or),
6378  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_fetch_and_and),
6379  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_fetch_and_xor),
6380  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_fetch_and_nand),
6381 
6382  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_add_and_fetch),
6383  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_sub_and_fetch),
6384  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_and_and_fetch),
6385  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_or_and_fetch),
6386  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_xor_and_fetch),
6387  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_nand_and_fetch),
6388 
6389  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_val_compare_and_swap),
6390  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_bool_compare_and_swap),
6391  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_lock_test_and_set),
6392  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_lock_release),
6393  BUILTIN_ROW(__sync_swap)
6394  };
6395 #undef BUILTIN_ROW
6396 
6397  // Determine the index of the size.
6398  unsigned SizeIndex;
6399  switch (Context.getTypeSizeInChars(ValType).getQuantity()) {
6400  case 1: SizeIndex = 0; break;
6401  case 2: SizeIndex = 1; break;
6402  case 4: SizeIndex = 2; break;
6403  case 8: SizeIndex = 3; break;
6404  case 16: SizeIndex = 4; break;
6405  default:
6406  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_pointer_size)
6407  << FirstArg->getType() << FirstArg->getSourceRange();
6408  return ExprError();
6409  }
6410 
6411  // Each of these builtins has one pointer argument, followed by some number of
6412  // values (0, 1 or 2) followed by a potentially empty varags list of stuff
6413  // that we ignore. Find out which row of BuiltinIndices to read from as well
6414  // as the number of fixed args.
6415  unsigned BuiltinID = FDecl->getBuiltinID();
6416  unsigned BuiltinIndex, NumFixed = 1;
6417  bool WarnAboutSemanticsChange = false;
6418  switch (BuiltinID) {
6419  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown overloaded atomic builtin!");
6420  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_add:
6421  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_add_1:
6422  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_add_2:
6423  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_add_4:
6424  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_add_8:
6425  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_add_16:
6426  BuiltinIndex = 0;
6427  break;
6428 
6429  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_sub:
6430  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_sub_1:
6431  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_sub_2:
6432  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_sub_4:
6433  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_sub_8:
6434  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_sub_16:
6435  BuiltinIndex = 1;
6436  break;
6437 
6438  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_or:
6439  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_or_1:
6440  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_or_2:
6441  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_or_4:
6442  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_or_8:
6443  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_or_16:
6444  BuiltinIndex = 2;
6445  break;
6446 
6447  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_and:
6448  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_and_1:
6449  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_and_2:
6450  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_and_4:
6451  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_and_8:
6452  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_and_16:
6453  BuiltinIndex = 3;
6454  break;
6455 
6456  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_xor:
6457  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_xor_1:
6458  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_xor_2:
6459  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_xor_4:
6460  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_xor_8:
6461  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_xor_16:
6462  BuiltinIndex = 4;
6463  break;
6464 
6465  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_nand:
6466  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_nand_1:
6467  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_nand_2:
6468  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_nand_4:
6469  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_nand_8:
6470  case Builtin::BI__sync_fetch_and_nand_16:
6471  BuiltinIndex = 5;
6472  WarnAboutSemanticsChange = true;
6473  break;
6474 
6475  case Builtin::BI__sync_add_and_fetch:
6476  case Builtin::BI__sync_add_and_fetch_1:
6477  case Builtin::BI__sync_add_and_fetch_2:
6478  case Builtin::BI__sync_add_and_fetch_4:
6479  case Builtin::BI__sync_add_and_fetch_8:
6480  case Builtin::BI__sync_add_and_fetch_16:
6481  BuiltinIndex = 6;
6482  break;
6483 
6484  case Builtin::BI__sync_sub_and_fetch:
6485  case Builtin::BI__sync_sub_and_fetch_1:
6486  case Builtin::BI__sync_sub_and_fetch_2:
6487  case Builtin::BI__sync_sub_and_fetch_4:
6488  case Builtin::BI__sync_sub_and_fetch_8:
6489  case Builtin::BI__sync_sub_and_fetch_16:
6490  BuiltinIndex = 7;
6491  break;
6492 
6493  case Builtin::BI__sync_and_and_fetch:
6494  case Builtin::BI__sync_and_and_fetch_1:
6495  case Builtin::BI__sync_and_and_fetch_2:
6496  case Builtin::BI__sync_and_and_fetch_4:
6497  case Builtin::BI__sync_and_and_fetch_8:
6498  case Builtin::BI__sync_and_and_fetch_16:
6499  BuiltinIndex = 8;
6500  break;
6501 
6502  case Builtin::BI__sync_or_and_fetch:
6503  case Builtin::BI__sync_or_and_fetch_1:
6504  case Builtin::BI__sync_or_and_fetch_2:
6505  case Builtin::BI__sync_or_and_fetch_4:
6506  case Builtin::BI__sync_or_and_fetch_8:
6507  case Builtin::BI__sync_or_and_fetch_16:
6508  BuiltinIndex = 9;
6509  break;
6510 
6511  case Builtin::BI__sync_xor_and_fetch:
6512  case Builtin::BI__sync_xor_and_fetch_1:
6513  case Builtin::BI__sync_xor_and_fetch_2:
6514  case Builtin::BI__sync_xor_and_fetch_4:
6515  case Builtin::BI__sync_xor_and_fetch_8:
6516  case Builtin::BI__sync_xor_and_fetch_16:
6517  BuiltinIndex = 10;
6518  break;
6519 
6520  case Builtin::BI__sync_nand_and_fetch:
6521  case Builtin::BI__sync_nand_and_fetch_1:
6522  case Builtin::BI__sync_nand_and_fetch_2:
6523  case Builtin::BI__sync_nand_and_fetch_4:
6524  case Builtin::BI__sync_nand_and_fetch_8:
6525  case Builtin::BI__sync_nand_and_fetch_16:
6526  BuiltinIndex = 11;
6527  WarnAboutSemanticsChange = true;
6528  break;
6529 
6530  case Builtin::BI__sync_val_compare_and_swap:
6531  case Builtin::BI__sync_val_compare_and_swap_1:
6532  case Builtin::BI__sync_val_compare_and_swap_2:
6533  case Builtin::BI__sync_val_compare_and_swap_4:
6534  case Builtin::BI__sync_val_compare_and_swap_8:
6535  case Builtin::BI__sync_val_compare_and_swap_16:
6536  BuiltinIndex = 12;
6537  NumFixed = 2;
6538  break;
6539 
6540  case Builtin::BI__sync_bool_compare_and_swap:
6541  case Builtin::BI__sync_bool_compare_and_swap_1:
6542  case Builtin::BI__sync_bool_compare_and_swap_2:
6543  case Builtin::BI__sync_bool_compare_and_swap_4:
6544  case Builtin::BI__sync_bool_compare_and_swap_8:
6545  case Builtin::BI__sync_bool_compare_and_swap_16:
6546  BuiltinIndex = 13;
6547  NumFixed = 2;
6548  ResultType = Context.BoolTy;
6549  break;
6550 
6551  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_test_and_set:
6552  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_test_and_set_1:
6553  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_test_and_set_2:
6554  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_test_and_set_4:
6555  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_test_and_set_8:
6556  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_test_and_set_16:
6557  BuiltinIndex = 14;
6558  break;
6559 
6560  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_release:
6561  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_release_1:
6562  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_release_2:
6563  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_release_4:
6564  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_release_8:
6565  case Builtin::BI__sync_lock_release_16:
6566  BuiltinIndex = 15;
6567  NumFixed = 0;
6568  ResultType = Context.VoidTy;
6569  break;
6570 
6571  case Builtin::BI__sync_swap:
6572  case Builtin::BI__sync_swap_1:
6573  case Builtin::BI__sync_swap_2:
6574  case Builtin::BI__sync_swap_4:
6575  case Builtin::BI__sync_swap_8:
6576  case Builtin::BI__sync_swap_16:
6577  BuiltinIndex = 16;
6578  break;
6579  }
6580 
6581  // Now that we know how many fixed arguments we expect, first check that we
6582  // have at least that many.
6583  if (TheCall->getNumArgs() < 1+NumFixed) {
6584  Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_call_too_few_args_at_least)
6585  << 0 << 1 + NumFixed << TheCall->getNumArgs()
6586  << Callee->getSourceRange();
6587  return ExprError();
6588  }
6589 
6590  Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(), diag::warn_atomic_implicit_seq_cst)
6591  << Callee->getSourceRange();
6592 
6593  if (WarnAboutSemanticsChange) {
6594  Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(), diag::warn_sync_fetch_and_nand_semantics_change)
6595  << Callee->getSourceRange();
6596  }
6597 
6598  // Get the decl for the concrete builtin from this, we can tell what the
6599  // concrete integer type we should convert to is.
6600  unsigned NewBuiltinID = BuiltinIndices[BuiltinIndex][SizeIndex];
6601  const char *NewBuiltinName = Context.BuiltinInfo.getName(NewBuiltinID);
6602  FunctionDecl *NewBuiltinDecl;
6603  if (NewBuiltinID == BuiltinID)
6604  NewBuiltinDecl = FDecl;
6605  else {
6606  // Perform builtin lookup to avoid redeclaring it.
6607  DeclarationName DN(&Context.Idents.get(NewBuiltinName));
6608  LookupResult Res(*this, DN, DRE->getBeginLoc(), LookupOrdinaryName);
6609  LookupName(Res, TUScope, /*AllowBuiltinCreation=*/true);
6610  assert(Res.getFoundDecl());
6611  NewBuiltinDecl = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Res.getFoundDecl());
6612  if (!NewBuiltinDecl)
6613  return ExprError();
6614  }
6615 
6616  // The first argument --- the pointer --- has a fixed type; we
6617  // deduce the types of the rest of the arguments accordingly. Walk
6618  // the remaining arguments, converting them to the deduced value type.
6619  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumFixed; ++i) {
6620  ExprResult Arg = TheCall->getArg(i+1);
6621 
6622  // GCC does an implicit conversion to the pointer or integer ValType. This
6623  // can fail in some cases (1i -> int**), check for this error case now.
6624  // Initialize the argument.
6625  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context,
6626  ValType, /*consume*/ false);
6627  Arg = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), Arg);
6628  if (Arg.isInvalid())
6629  return ExprError();
6630 
6631  // Okay, we have something that *can* be converted to the right type. Check
6632  // to see if there is a potentially weird extension going on here. This can
6633  // happen when you do an atomic operation on something like an char* and
6634  // pass in 42. The 42 gets converted to char. This is even more strange
6635  // for things like 45.123 -> char, etc.
6636  // FIXME: Do this check.
6637  TheCall->setArg(i+1, Arg.get());
6638  }
6639 
6640  // Create a new DeclRefExpr to refer to the new decl.
6641  DeclRefExpr *NewDRE = DeclRefExpr::Create(
6642  Context, DRE->getQualifierLoc(), SourceLocation(), NewBuiltinDecl,
6643  /*enclosing*/ false, DRE->getLocation(), Context.BuiltinFnTy,
6644  DRE->getValueKind(), nullptr, nullptr, DRE->isNonOdrUse());
6645 
6646  // Set the callee in the CallExpr.
6647  // FIXME: This loses syntactic information.
6648  QualType CalleePtrTy = Context.getPointerType(NewBuiltinDecl->getType());
6649  ExprResult PromotedCall = ImpCastExprToType(NewDRE, CalleePtrTy,
6650  CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr);
6651  TheCall->setCallee(PromotedCall.get());
6652 
6653  // Change the result type of the call to match the original value type. This
6654  // is arbitrary, but the codegen for these builtins ins design to handle it
6655  // gracefully.
6656  TheCall->setType(ResultType);
6657 
6658  // Prohibit problematic uses of bit-precise integer types with atomic
6659  // builtins. The arguments would have already been converted to the first
6660  // argument's type, so only need to check the first argument.
6661  const auto *BitIntValType = ValType->getAs<BitIntType>();
6662  if (BitIntValType && !llvm::isPowerOf2_64(BitIntValType->getNumBits())) {
6663  Diag(FirstArg->getExprLoc(), diag::err_atomic_builtin_ext_int_size);
6664  return ExprError();
6665  }
6666 
6667  return TheCallResult;
6668 }
6669 
6670 /// SemaBuiltinNontemporalOverloaded - We have a call to
6671 /// __builtin_nontemporal_store or __builtin_nontemporal_load, which is an
6672 /// overloaded function based on the pointer type of its last argument.
6673 ///
6674 /// This function goes through and does final semantic checking for these
6675 /// builtins.
6676 ExprResult Sema::SemaBuiltinNontemporalOverloaded(ExprResult TheCallResult) {
6677  CallExpr *TheCall = (CallExpr *)TheCallResult.get();
6678  DeclRefExpr *DRE =
6679  cast<DeclRefExpr>(TheCall->getCallee()->IgnoreParenCasts());
6680  FunctionDecl *FDecl = cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
6681  unsigned BuiltinID = FDecl->getBuiltinID();
6682  assert((BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_nontemporal_store ||
6683  BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_nontemporal_load) &&
6684  "Unexpected nontemporal load/store builtin!");
6685  bool isStore = BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_nontemporal_store;
6686  unsigned numArgs = isStore ? 2 : 1;
6687 
6688  // Ensure that we have the proper number of arguments.
6689  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, numArgs))
6690  return ExprError();
6691 
6692  // Inspect the last argument of the nontemporal builtin. This should always
6693  // be a pointer type, from which we imply the type of the memory access.
6694  // Because it is a pointer type, we don't have to worry about any implicit
6695  // casts here.
6696  Expr *PointerArg = TheCall->getArg(numArgs - 1);
6697  ExprResult PointerArgResult =
6698  DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(PointerArg);
6699 
6700  if (PointerArgResult.isInvalid())
6701  return ExprError();
6702  PointerArg = PointerArgResult.get();
6703  TheCall->setArg(numArgs - 1, PointerArg);
6704 
6705  const PointerType *pointerType = PointerArg->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
6706  if (!pointerType) {
6707  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_nontemporal_builtin_must_be_pointer)
6708  << PointerArg->getType() << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
6709  return ExprError();
6710  }
6711 
6712  QualType ValType = pointerType->getPointeeType();
6713 
6714  // Strip any qualifiers off ValType.
6715  ValType = ValType.getUnqualifiedType();
6716  if (!ValType->isIntegerType() && !ValType->isAnyPointerType() &&
6717  !ValType->isBlockPointerType() && !ValType->isFloatingType() &&
6718  !ValType->isVectorType()) {
6719  Diag(DRE->getBeginLoc(),
6720  diag::err_nontemporal_builtin_must_be_pointer_intfltptr_or_vector)
6721  << PointerArg->getType() << PointerArg->getSourceRange();
6722  return ExprError();
6723  }
6724 
6725  if (!isStore) {
6726  TheCall->setType(ValType);
6727  return TheCallResult;
6728  }
6729 
6730  ExprResult ValArg = TheCall->getArg(0);
6731  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
6732  Context, ValType, /*consume*/ false);
6733  ValArg = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), ValArg);
6734  if (ValArg.isInvalid())
6735  return ExprError();
6736 
6737  TheCall->setArg(0, ValArg.get());
6738  TheCall->setType(Context.VoidTy);
6739  return TheCallResult;
6740 }
6741 
6742 /// CheckObjCString - Checks that the argument to the builtin
6743 /// CFString constructor is correct
6744 /// Note: It might also make sense to do the UTF-16 conversion here (would
6745 /// simplify the backend).
6746 bool Sema::CheckObjCString(Expr *Arg) {
6747  Arg = Arg->IgnoreParenCasts();
6748  StringLiteral *Literal = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Arg);
6749 
6750  if (!Literal || !Literal->isAscii()) {
6751  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cfstring_literal_not_string_constant)
6752  << Arg->getSourceRange();
6753  return true;
6754  }
6755 
6756  if (Literal->containsNonAsciiOrNull()) {
6757  StringRef String = Literal->getString();
6758  unsigned NumBytes = String.size();
6759  SmallVector<llvm::UTF16, 128> ToBuf(NumBytes);
6760  const llvm::UTF8 *FromPtr = (const llvm::UTF8 *)String.data();
6761  llvm::UTF16 *ToPtr = &ToBuf[0];
6762 
6763  llvm::ConversionResult Result =
6764  llvm::ConvertUTF8toUTF16(&FromPtr, FromPtr + NumBytes, &ToPtr,
6765  ToPtr + NumBytes, llvm::strictConversion);
6766  // Check for conversion failure.
6767  if (Result != llvm::conversionOK)
6768  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cfstring_truncated)
6769  << Arg->getSourceRange();
6770  }
6771  return false;
6772 }
6773 
6774 /// CheckObjCString - Checks that the format string argument to the os_log()
6775 /// and os_trace() functions is correct, and converts it to const char *.
6776 ExprResult Sema::CheckOSLogFormatStringArg(Expr *Arg) {
6777  Arg = Arg->IgnoreParenCasts();
6778  auto *Literal = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Arg);
6779  if (!Literal) {
6780  if (auto *ObjcLiteral = dyn_cast<ObjCStringLiteral>(Arg)) {
6781  Literal = ObjcLiteral->getString();
6782  }
6783  }
6784 
6785  if (!Literal || (!Literal->isAscii() && !Literal->isUTF8())) {
6786  return ExprError(
6787  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_os_log_format_not_string_constant)
6788  << Arg->getSourceRange());
6789  }
6790 
6791  ExprResult Result(Literal);
6792  QualType ResultTy = Context.getPointerType(Context.CharTy.withConst());
6793  InitializedEntity Entity =
6794  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context, ResultTy, false);
6795  Result = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), Result);
6796  return Result;
6797 }
6798 
6799 /// Check that the user is calling the appropriate va_start builtin for the
6800 /// target and calling convention.
6801 static bool checkVAStartABI(Sema &S, unsigned BuiltinID, Expr *Fn) {
6802  const llvm::Triple &TT = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
6803  bool IsX64 = TT.getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64;
6804  bool IsAArch64 = (TT.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64 ||
6805  TT.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64_32);
6806  bool IsWindows = TT.isOSWindows();
6807  bool IsMSVAStart = BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_ms_va_start;
6808  if (IsX64 || IsAArch64) {
6809  CallingConv CC = CC_C;
6810  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = S.getCurFunctionDecl())
6811  CC = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getCallConv();
6812  if (IsMSVAStart) {
6813  // Don't allow this in System V ABI functions.
6814  if (CC == CC_X86_64SysV || (!IsWindows && CC != CC_Win64))
6815  return S.Diag(Fn->getBeginLoc(),
6816  diag::err_ms_va_start_used_in_sysv_function);
6817  } else {
6818  // On x86-64/AArch64 Unix, don't allow this in Win64 ABI functions.
6819  // On x64 Windows, don't allow this in System V ABI functions.
6820  // (Yes, that means there's no corresponding way to support variadic
6821  // System V ABI functions on Windows.)
6822  if ((IsWindows && CC == CC_X86_64SysV) ||
6823  (!IsWindows && CC == CC_Win64))
6824  return S.Diag(Fn->getBeginLoc(),
6825  diag::err_va_start_used_in_wrong_abi_function)
6826  << !IsWindows;
6827  }
6828  return false;
6829  }
6830 
6831  if (IsMSVAStart)
6832  return S.Diag(Fn->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_x64_aarch64_only);
6833  return false;
6834 }
6835 
6836 static bool checkVAStartIsInVariadicFunction(Sema &S, Expr *Fn,
6837  ParmVarDecl **LastParam = nullptr) {
6838  // Determine whether the current function, block, or obj-c method is variadic
6839  // and get its parameter list.
6840  bool IsVariadic = false;
6841  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Params;
6842  DeclContext *Caller = S.CurContext;
6843  if (auto *Block = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(Caller)) {
6844  IsVariadic = Block->isVariadic();
6845  Params = Block->parameters();
6846  } else if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Caller)) {
6847  IsVariadic = FD->isVariadic();
6848  Params = FD->parameters();
6849  } else if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(Caller)) {
6850  IsVariadic = MD->isVariadic();
6851  // FIXME: This isn't correct for methods (results in bogus warning).
6852  Params = MD->parameters();
6853  } else if (isa<CapturedDecl>(Caller)) {
6854  // We don't support va_start in a CapturedDecl.
6855  S.Diag(Fn->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_va_start_captured_stmt);
6856  return true;
6857  } else {
6858  // This must be some other declcontext that parses exprs.
6859  S.Diag(Fn->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_va_start_outside_function);
6860  return true;
6861  }
6862 
6863  if (!IsVariadic) {
6864  S.Diag(Fn->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_va_start_fixed_function);
6865  return true;
6866  }
6867 
6868  if (LastParam)
6869  *LastParam = Params.empty() ? nullptr : Params.back();
6870 
6871  return false;
6872 }
6873 
6874 /// Check the arguments to '__builtin_va_start' or '__builtin_ms_va_start'
6875 /// for validity. Emit an error and return true on failure; return false
6876 /// on success.
6877 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinVAStart(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
6878  Expr *Fn = TheCall->getCallee();
6879 
6880  if (checkVAStartABI(*this, BuiltinID, Fn))
6881  return true;
6882 
6883  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
6884  return true;
6885 
6886  // Type-check the first argument normally.
6887  if (checkBuiltinArgument(*this, TheCall, 0))
6888  return true;
6889 
6890  // Check that the current function is variadic, and get its last parameter.
6891  ParmVarDecl *LastParam;
6892  if (checkVAStartIsInVariadicFunction(*this, Fn, &LastParam))
6893  return true;
6894 
6895  // Verify that the second argument to the builtin is the last argument of the
6896  // current function or method.
6897  bool SecondArgIsLastNamedArgument = false;
6898  const Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(1)->IgnoreParenCasts();
6899 
6900  // These are valid if SecondArgIsLastNamedArgument is false after the next
6901  // block.
6902  QualType Type;
6903  SourceLocation ParamLoc;
6904  bool IsCRegister = false;
6905 
6906  if (const DeclRefExpr *DR = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Arg)) {
6907  if (const ParmVarDecl *PV = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(DR->getDecl())) {
6908  SecondArgIsLastNamedArgument = PV == LastParam;
6909 
6910  Type = PV->getType();
6911  ParamLoc = PV->getLocation();
6912  IsCRegister =
6913  PV->getStorageClass() == SC_Register && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
6914  }
6915  }
6916 
6917  if (!SecondArgIsLastNamedArgument)
6918  Diag(TheCall->getArg(1)->getBeginLoc(),
6919  diag::warn_second_arg_of_va_start_not_last_named_param);
6920  else if (IsCRegister || Type->isReferenceType() ||
6921  Type->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Float) || [=] {
6922  // Promotable integers are UB, but enumerations need a bit of
6923  // extra checking to see what their promotable type actually is.
6924  if (!Type->isPromotableIntegerType())
6925  return false;
6926  if (!Type->isEnumeralType())
6927  return true;
6928  const EnumDecl *ED = Type->castAs<EnumType>()->getDecl();
6929  return !(ED &&
6930  Context.typesAreCompatible(ED->getPromotionType(), Type));
6931  }()) {
6932  unsigned Reason = 0;
6933  if (Type->isReferenceType()) Reason = 1;
6934  else if (IsCRegister) Reason = 2;
6935  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_va_start_type_is_undefined) << Reason;
6936  Diag(ParamLoc, diag::note_parameter_type) << Type;
6937  }
6938 
6939  TheCall->setType(Context.VoidTy);
6940  return false;
6941 }
6942 
6943 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinVAStartARMMicrosoft(CallExpr *Call) {
6944  auto IsSuitablyTypedFormatArgument = [this](const Expr *Arg) -> bool {
6945  const LangOptions &LO = getLangOpts();
6946 
6947  if (LO.CPlusPlus)
6948  return Arg->getType()
6949  .getCanonicalType()
6950  .getTypePtr()
6951  ->getPointeeType()
6952  .withoutLocalFastQualifiers() == Context.CharTy;
6953 
6954  // In C, allow aliasing through `char *`, this is required for AArch64 at
6955  // least.
6956  return true;
6957  };
6958 
6959  // void __va_start(va_list *ap, const char *named_addr, size_t slot_size,
6960  // const char *named_addr);
6961 
6962  Expr *Func = Call->getCallee();
6963 
6964  if (Call->getNumArgs() < 3)
6965  return Diag(Call->getEndLoc(),
6966  diag::err_typecheck_call_too_few_args_at_least)
6967  << 0 /*function call*/ << 3 << Call->getNumArgs();
6968 
6969  // Type-check the first argument normally.
6970  if (checkBuiltinArgument(*this, Call, 0))
6971  return true;
6972 
6973  // Check that the current function is variadic.
6974  if (checkVAStartIsInVariadicFunction(*this, Func))
6975  return true;
6976 
6977  // __va_start on Windows does not validate the parameter qualifiers
6978 
6979  const Expr *Arg1 = Call->getArg(1)->IgnoreParens();
6980  const Type *Arg1Ty = Arg1->getType().getCanonicalType().getTypePtr();
6981 
6982  const Expr *Arg2 = Call->getArg(2)->IgnoreParens();
6983  const Type *Arg2Ty = Arg2->getType().getCanonicalType().getTypePtr();
6984 
6985  const QualType &ConstCharPtrTy =
6986  Context.getPointerType(Context.CharTy.withConst());
6987  if (!Arg1Ty->isPointerType() || !IsSuitablyTypedFormatArgument(Arg1))
6988  Diag(Arg1->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_convert_incompatible)
6989  << Arg1->getType() << ConstCharPtrTy << 1 /* different class */
6990  << 0 /* qualifier difference */
6991  << 3 /* parameter mismatch */
6992  << 2 << Arg1->getType() << ConstCharPtrTy;
6993 
6994  const QualType SizeTy = Context.getSizeType();
6995  if (Arg2Ty->getCanonicalTypeInternal().withoutLocalFastQualifiers() != SizeTy)
6996  Diag(Arg2->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_convert_incompatible)
6997  << Arg2->getType() << SizeTy << 1 /* different class */
6998  << 0 /* qualifier difference */
6999  << 3 /* parameter mismatch */
7000  << 3 << Arg2->getType() << SizeTy;
7001 
7002  return false;
7003 }
7004 
7005 /// SemaBuiltinUnorderedCompare - Handle functions like __builtin_isgreater and
7006 /// friends. This is declared to take (...), so we have to check everything.
7007 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinUnorderedCompare(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7008  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
7009  return true;
7010 
7011  ExprResult OrigArg0 = TheCall->getArg(0);
7012  ExprResult OrigArg1 = TheCall->getArg(1);
7013 
7014  // Do standard promotions between the two arguments, returning their common
7015  // type.
7016  QualType Res = UsualArithmeticConversions(
7017  OrigArg0, OrigArg1, TheCall->getExprLoc(), ACK_Comparison);
7018  if (OrigArg0.isInvalid() || OrigArg1.isInvalid())
7019  return true;
7020 
7021  // Make sure any conversions are pushed back into the call; this is
7022  // type safe since unordered compare builtins are declared as "_Bool
7023  // foo(...)".
7024  TheCall->setArg(0, OrigArg0.get());
7025  TheCall->setArg(1, OrigArg1.get());
7026 
7027  if (OrigArg0.get()->isTypeDependent() || OrigArg1.get()->isTypeDependent())
7028  return false;
7029 
7030  // If the common type isn't a real floating type, then the arguments were
7031  // invalid for this operation.
7032  if (Res.isNull() || !Res->isRealFloatingType())
7033  return Diag(OrigArg0.get()->getBeginLoc(),
7034  diag::err_typecheck_call_invalid_ordered_compare)
7035  << OrigArg0.get()->getType() << OrigArg1.get()->getType()
7036  << SourceRange(OrigArg0.get()->getBeginLoc(),
7037  OrigArg1.get()->getEndLoc());
7038 
7039  return false;
7040 }
7041 
7042 /// SemaBuiltinSemaBuiltinFPClassification - Handle functions like
7043 /// __builtin_isnan and friends. This is declared to take (...), so we have
7044 /// to check everything. We expect the last argument to be a floating point
7045 /// value.
7046 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinFPClassification(CallExpr *TheCall, unsigned NumArgs) {
7047  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, NumArgs))
7048  return true;
7049 
7050  // __builtin_fpclassify is the only case where NumArgs != 1, so we can count
7051  // on all preceding parameters just being int. Try all of those.
7052  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumArgs - 1; ++i) {
7053  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(i);
7054 
7055  if (Arg->isTypeDependent())
7056  return false;
7057 
7058  ExprResult Res = PerformImplicitConversion(Arg, Context.IntTy, AA_Passing);
7059 
7060  if (Res.isInvalid())
7061  return true;
7062  TheCall->setArg(i, Res.get());
7063  }
7064 
7065  Expr *OrigArg = TheCall->getArg(NumArgs-1);
7066 
7067  if (OrigArg->isTypeDependent())
7068  return false;
7069 
7070  // Usual Unary Conversions will convert half to float, which we want for
7071  // machines that use fp16 conversion intrinsics. Else, we wnat to leave the
7072  // type how it is, but do normal L->Rvalue conversions.
7073  if (Context.getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics())
7074  OrigArg = UsualUnaryConversions(OrigArg).get();
7075  else
7076  OrigArg = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(OrigArg).get();
7077  TheCall->setArg(NumArgs - 1, OrigArg);
7078 
7079  // This operation requires a non-_Complex floating-point number.
7080  if (!OrigArg->getType()->isRealFloatingType())
7081  return Diag(OrigArg->getBeginLoc(),
7082  diag::err_typecheck_call_invalid_unary_fp)
7083  << OrigArg->getType() << OrigArg->getSourceRange();
7084 
7085  return false;
7086 }
7087 
7088 /// Perform semantic analysis for a call to __builtin_complex.
7089 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinComplex(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7090  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
7091  return true;
7092 
7093  bool Dependent = false;
7094  for (unsigned I = 0; I != 2; ++I) {
7095  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(I);
7096  QualType T = Arg->getType();
7097  if (T->isDependentType()) {
7098  Dependent = true;
7099  continue;
7100  }
7101 
7102  // Despite supporting _Complex int, GCC requires a real floating point type
7103  // for the operands of __builtin_complex.
7104  if (!T->isRealFloatingType()) {
7105  return Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_call_requires_real_fp)
7106  << Arg->getType() << Arg->getSourceRange();
7107  }
7108 
7109  ExprResult Converted = DefaultLvalueConversion(Arg);
7110  if (Converted.isInvalid())
7111  return true;
7112  TheCall->setArg(I, Converted.get());
7113  }
7114 
7115  if (Dependent) {
7116  TheCall->setType(Context.DependentTy);
7117  return false;
7118  }
7119 
7120  Expr *Real = TheCall->getArg(0);
7121  Expr *Imag = TheCall->getArg(1);
7122  if (!Context.hasSameType(Real->getType(), Imag->getType())) {
7123  return Diag(Real->getBeginLoc(),
7124  diag::err_typecheck_call_different_arg_types)
7125  << Real->getType() << Imag->getType()
7126  << Real->getSourceRange() << Imag->getSourceRange();
7127  }
7128 
7129  // We don't allow _Complex _Float16 nor _Complex __fp16 as type specifiers;
7130  // don't allow this builtin to form those types either.
7131  // FIXME: Should we allow these types?
7132  if (Real->getType()->isFloat16Type())
7133  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_invalid_complex_spec)
7134  << "_Float16";
7135  if (Real->getType()->isHalfType())
7136  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_invalid_complex_spec)
7137  << "half";
7138 
7139  TheCall->setType(Context.getComplexType(Real->getType()));
7140  return false;
7141 }
7142 
7143 // Customized Sema Checking for VSX builtins that have the following signature:
7144 // vector [...] builtinName(vector [...], vector [...], const int);
7145 // Which takes the same type of vectors (any legal vector type) for the first
7146 // two arguments and takes compile time constant for the third argument.
7147 // Example builtins are :
7148 // vector double vec_xxpermdi(vector double, vector double, int);
7149 // vector short vec_xxsldwi(vector short, vector short, int);
7150 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinVSX(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7151  unsigned ExpectedNumArgs = 3;
7152  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, ExpectedNumArgs))
7153  return true;
7154 
7155  // Check the third argument is a compile time constant
7156  if (!TheCall->getArg(2)->isIntegerConstantExpr(Context))
7157  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
7158  diag::err_vsx_builtin_nonconstant_argument)
7159  << 3 /* argument index */ << TheCall->getDirectCallee()
7160  << SourceRange(TheCall->getArg(2)->getBeginLoc(),
7161  TheCall->getArg(2)->getEndLoc());
7162 
7163  QualType Arg1Ty = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
7164  QualType Arg2Ty = TheCall->getArg(1)->getType();
7165 
7166  // Check the type of argument 1 and argument 2 are vectors.
7167  SourceLocation BuiltinLoc = TheCall->getBeginLoc();
7168  if ((!Arg1Ty->isVectorType() && !Arg1Ty->isDependentType()) ||
7169  (!Arg2Ty->isVectorType() && !Arg2Ty->isDependentType())) {
7170  return Diag(BuiltinLoc, diag::err_vec_builtin_non_vector)
7171  << TheCall->getDirectCallee()
7172  << SourceRange(TheCall->getArg(0)->getBeginLoc(),
7173  TheCall->getArg(1)->getEndLoc());
7174  }
7175 
7176  // Check the first two arguments are the same type.
7177  if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(Arg1Ty, Arg2Ty)) {
7178  return Diag(BuiltinLoc, diag::err_vec_builtin_incompatible_vector)
7179  << TheCall->getDirectCallee()
7180  << SourceRange(TheCall->getArg(0)->getBeginLoc(),
7181  TheCall->getArg(1)->getEndLoc());
7182  }
7183 
7184  // When default clang type checking is turned off and the customized type
7185  // checking is used, the returning type of the function must be explicitly
7186  // set. Otherwise it is _Bool by default.
7187  TheCall->setType(Arg1Ty);
7188 
7189  return false;
7190 }
7191 
7192 /// SemaBuiltinShuffleVector - Handle __builtin_shufflevector.
7193 // This is declared to take (...), so we have to check everything.
7194 ExprResult Sema::SemaBuiltinShuffleVector(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7195  if (TheCall->getNumArgs() < 2)
7196  return ExprError(Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(),
7197  diag::err_typecheck_call_too_few_args_at_least)
7198  << 0 /*function call*/ << 2 << TheCall->getNumArgs()
7199  << TheCall->getSourceRange());
7200 
7201  // Determine which of the following types of shufflevector we're checking:
7202  // 1) unary, vector mask: (lhs, mask)
7203  // 2) binary, scalar mask: (lhs, rhs, index, ..., index)
7204  QualType resType = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
7205  unsigned numElements = 0;
7206 
7207  if (!TheCall->getArg(0)->isTypeDependent() &&
7208  !TheCall->getArg(1)->isTypeDependent()) {
7209  QualType LHSType = TheCall->getArg(0)->getType();
7210  QualType RHSType = TheCall->getArg(1)->getType();
7211 
7212  if (!LHSType->isVectorType() || !RHSType->isVectorType())
7213  return ExprError(
7214  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_vec_builtin_non_vector)
7215  << TheCall->getDirectCallee()
7216  << SourceRange(TheCall->getArg(0)->getBeginLoc(),
7217  TheCall->getArg(1)->getEndLoc()));
7218 
7219  numElements = LHSType->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
7220  unsigned numResElements = TheCall->getNumArgs() - 2;
7221 
7222  // Check to see if we have a call with 2 vector arguments, the unary shuffle
7223  // with mask. If so, verify that RHS is an integer vector type with the
7224  // same number of elts as lhs.
7225  if (TheCall->getNumArgs() == 2) {
7226  if (!RHSType->hasIntegerRepresentation() ||
7227  RHSType->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() != numElements)
7228  return ExprError(Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
7229  diag::err_vec_builtin_incompatible_vector)
7230  << TheCall->getDirectCallee()
7231  << SourceRange(TheCall->getArg(1)->getBeginLoc(),
7232  TheCall->getArg(1)->getEndLoc()));
7233  } else if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(LHSType, RHSType)) {
7234  return ExprError(Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
7235  diag::err_vec_builtin_incompatible_vector)
7236  << TheCall->getDirectCallee()
7237  << SourceRange(TheCall->getArg(0)->getBeginLoc(),
7238  TheCall->getArg(1)->getEndLoc()));
7239  } else if (numElements != numResElements) {
7240  QualType eltType = LHSType->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
7241  resType = Context.getVectorType(eltType, numResElements,
7242  VectorType::GenericVector);
7243  }
7244  }
7245 
7246  for (unsigned i = 2; i < TheCall->getNumArgs(); i++) {
7247  if (TheCall->getArg(i)->isTypeDependent() ||
7248  TheCall->getArg(i)->isValueDependent())
7249  continue;
7250 
7251  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result;
7252  if (!(Result = TheCall->getArg(i)->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)))
7253  return ExprError(Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
7254  diag::err_shufflevector_nonconstant_argument)
7255  << TheCall->getArg(i)->getSourceRange());
7256 
7257  // Allow -1 which will be translated to undef in the IR.
7258  if (Result->isSigned() && Result->isAllOnes())
7259  continue;
7260 
7261  if (Result->getActiveBits() > 64 ||
7262  Result->getZExtValue() >= numElements * 2)
7263  return ExprError(Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
7264  diag::err_shufflevector_argument_too_large)
7265  << TheCall->getArg(i)->getSourceRange());
7266  }
7267 
7268  SmallVector<Expr*, 32> exprs;
7269 
7270  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TheCall->getNumArgs(); i != e; i++) {
7271  exprs.push_back(TheCall->getArg(i));
7272  TheCall->setArg(i, nullptr);
7273  }
7274 
7275  return new (Context) ShuffleVectorExpr(Context, exprs, resType,
7276  TheCall->getCallee()->getBeginLoc(),
7277  TheCall->getRParenLoc());
7278 }
7279 
7280 /// SemaConvertVectorExpr - Handle __builtin_convertvector
7281 ExprResult Sema::SemaConvertVectorExpr(Expr *E, TypeSourceInfo *TInfo,
7282  SourceLocation BuiltinLoc,
7283  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
7284  ExprValueKind VK = VK_PRValue;
7285  ExprObjectKind OK = OK_Ordinary;
7286  QualType DstTy = TInfo->getType();
7287  QualType SrcTy = E->getType();
7288 
7289  if (!SrcTy->isVectorType() && !SrcTy->isDependentType())
7290  return ExprError(Diag(BuiltinLoc,
7291  diag::err_convertvector_non_vector)
7292  << E->getSourceRange());
7293  if (!DstTy->isVectorType() && !DstTy->isDependentType())
7294  return ExprError(Diag(BuiltinLoc,
7295  diag::err_convertvector_non_vector_type));
7296 
7297  if (!SrcTy->isDependentType() && !DstTy->isDependentType()) {
7298  unsigned SrcElts = SrcTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
7299  unsigned DstElts = DstTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
7300  if (SrcElts != DstElts)
7301  return ExprError(Diag(BuiltinLoc,
7302  diag::err_convertvector_incompatible_vector)
7303  << E->getSourceRange());
7304  }
7305 
7306  return new (Context)
7307  ConvertVectorExpr(E, TInfo, DstTy, VK, OK, BuiltinLoc, RParenLoc);
7308 }

7310 /// SemaBuiltinPrefetch - Handle __builtin_prefetch.
7311 // This is declared to take (const void*, ...) and can take two
7312 // optional constant int args.
7313 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinPrefetch(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7314  unsigned NumArgs = TheCall->getNumArgs();
7315 
7316  if (NumArgs > 3)
7317  return Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(),
7318  diag::err_typecheck_call_too_many_args_at_most)
7319  << 0 /*function call*/ << 3 << NumArgs << TheCall->getSourceRange();
7320 
7321  // Argument 0 is checked for us and the remaining arguments must be
7322  // constant integers.
7323  for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumArgs; ++i)
7324  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, i, 0, i == 1 ? 1 : 3))
7325  return true;
7326 
7327  return false;
7328 }

7330 /// SemaBuiltinArithmeticFence - Handle __arithmetic_fence.
7331 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinArithmeticFence(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7332  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().checkArithmeticFenceSupported())
7333  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_target_unsupported)
7334  << SourceRange(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), TheCall->getEndLoc());
7335  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 1))
7336  return true;
7337  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
7338  if (Arg->isInstantiationDependent())
7339  return false;
7340 
7341  QualType ArgTy = Arg->getType();
7342  if (!ArgTy->hasFloatingRepresentation())
7343  return Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_expect_flt_or_vector)
7344  << ArgTy;
7345  if (Arg->isLValue()) {
7346  ExprResult FirstArg = DefaultLvalueConversion(Arg);
7347  TheCall->setArg(0, FirstArg.get());
7348  }
7349  TheCall->setType(TheCall->getArg(0)->getType());
7350  return false;
7351 }

7353 /// SemaBuiltinAssume - Handle __assume (MS Extension).
7354 // __assume does not evaluate its arguments, and should warn if its argument
7355 // has side effects.
7356 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinAssume(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7357  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(0);
7358  if (Arg->isInstantiationDependent()) return false;
7359 
7360  if (Arg->HasSideEffects(Context))
7361  Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_assume_side_effects)
7362  << Arg->getSourceRange()
7363  << cast<FunctionDecl>(TheCall->getCalleeDecl())->getIdentifier();
7364 
7365  return false;
7366 }
