7368 /// Handle __builtin_alloca_with_align. This is declared
7369 /// as (size_t, size_t) where the second size_t must be a power of 2 greater
7370 /// than 8.
7371 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinAllocaWithAlign(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7372  // The alignment must be a constant integer.
7373  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(1);
7374 
7375  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7376  if (!Arg->isTypeDependent() && !Arg->isValueDependent()) {
7377  if (const auto *UE =
7378  dyn_cast<UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
7379  if (UE->getKind() == UETT_AlignOf ||
7380  UE->getKind() == UETT_PreferredAlignOf)
7381  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_alloca_align_alignof)
7382  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7383 
7384  llvm::APSInt Result = Arg->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Context);
7385 
7386  if (!Result.isPowerOf2())
7387  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
7388  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7389 
7390  if (Result < Context.getCharWidth())
7391  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_alignment_too_small)
7392  << (unsigned)Context.getCharWidth() << Arg->getSourceRange();
7393 
7394  if (Result > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max())
7395  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_alignment_too_big)
7396  << std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max() << Arg->getSourceRange();
7397  }
7398 
7399  return false;
7400 }
7401 
7402 /// Handle __builtin_assume_aligned. This is declared
7403 /// as (const void*, size_t, ...) and can take one optional constant int arg.
7404 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinAssumeAligned(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7405  unsigned NumArgs = TheCall->getNumArgs();
7406 
7407  if (NumArgs > 3)
7408  return Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(),
7409  diag::err_typecheck_call_too_many_args_at_most)
7410  << 0 /*function call*/ << 3 << NumArgs << TheCall->getSourceRange();
7411 
7412  // The alignment must be a constant integer.
7413  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(1);
7414 
7415  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7416  if (!Arg->isTypeDependent() && !Arg->isValueDependent()) {
7417  llvm::APSInt Result;
7418  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, 1, Result))
7419  return true;
7420 
7421  if (!Result.isPowerOf2())
7422  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
7423  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7424 
7425  if (Result > Sema::MaximumAlignment)
7426  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_assume_aligned_too_great)
7427  << Arg->getSourceRange() << Sema::MaximumAlignment;
7428  }
7429 
7430  if (NumArgs > 2) {
7431  ExprResult Arg(TheCall->getArg(2));
7432  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context,
7433  Context.getSizeType(), false);
7434  Arg = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), Arg);
7435  if (Arg.isInvalid()) return true;
7436  TheCall->setArg(2, Arg.get());
7437  }
7438 
7439  return false;
7440 }
7441 
7442 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinOSLogFormat(CallExpr *TheCall) {
7443  unsigned BuiltinID =
7444  cast<FunctionDecl>(TheCall->getCalleeDecl())->getBuiltinID();
7445  bool IsSizeCall = BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_os_log_format_buffer_size;
7446 
7447  unsigned NumArgs = TheCall->getNumArgs();
7448  unsigned NumRequiredArgs = IsSizeCall ? 1 : 2;
7449  if (NumArgs < NumRequiredArgs) {
7450  return Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_call_too_few_args)
7451  << 0 /* function call */ << NumRequiredArgs << NumArgs
7452  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
7453  }
7454  if (NumArgs >= NumRequiredArgs + 0x100) {
7455  return Diag(TheCall->getEndLoc(),
7456  diag::err_typecheck_call_too_many_args_at_most)
7457  << 0 /* function call */ << (NumRequiredArgs + 0xff) << NumArgs
7458  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
7459  }
7460  unsigned i = 0;
7461 
7462  // For formatting call, check buffer arg.
7463  if (!IsSizeCall) {
7464  ExprResult Arg(TheCall->getArg(i));
7465  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
7466  Context, Context.VoidPtrTy, false);
7467  Arg = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), Arg);
7468  if (Arg.isInvalid())
7469  return true;
7470  TheCall->setArg(i, Arg.get());
7471  i++;
7472  }
7473 
7474  // Check string literal arg.
7475  unsigned FormatIdx = i;
7476  {
7477  ExprResult Arg = CheckOSLogFormatStringArg(TheCall->getArg(i));
7478  if (Arg.isInvalid())
7479  return true;
7480  TheCall->setArg(i, Arg.get());
7481  i++;
7482  }
7483 
7484  // Make sure variadic args are scalar.
7485  unsigned FirstDataArg = i;
7486  while (i < NumArgs) {
7487  ExprResult Arg = DefaultVariadicArgumentPromotion(
7488  TheCall->getArg(i), VariadicFunction, nullptr);
7489  if (Arg.isInvalid())
7490  return true;
7491  CharUnits ArgSize = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Arg.get()->getType());
7492  if (ArgSize.getQuantity() >= 0x100) {
7493  return Diag(Arg.get()->getEndLoc(), diag::err_os_log_argument_too_big)
7494  << i << (int)ArgSize.getQuantity() << 0xff
7495  << TheCall->getSourceRange();
7496  }
7497  TheCall->setArg(i, Arg.get());
7498  i++;
7499  }
7500 
7501  // Check formatting specifiers. NOTE: We're only doing this for the non-size
7502  // call to avoid duplicate diagnostics.
7503  if (!IsSizeCall) {
7504  llvm::SmallBitVector CheckedVarArgs(NumArgs, false);
7505  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args(TheCall->getArgs(), TheCall->getNumArgs());
7506  bool Success = CheckFormatArguments(
7507  Args, /*HasVAListArg*/ false, FormatIdx, FirstDataArg, FST_OSLog,
7508  VariadicFunction, TheCall->getBeginLoc(), SourceRange(),
7509  CheckedVarArgs);
7510  if (!Success)
7511  return true;
7512  }
7513 
7514  if (IsSizeCall) {
7515  TheCall->setType(Context.getSizeType());
7516  } else {
7517  TheCall->setType(Context.VoidPtrTy);
7518  }
7519  return false;
7520 }
7521 
7522 /// SemaBuiltinConstantArg - Handle a check if argument ArgNum of CallExpr
7523 /// TheCall is a constant expression.
7524 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinConstantArg(CallExpr *TheCall, int ArgNum,
7525  llvm::APSInt &Result) {
7526  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7527  DeclRefExpr *DRE =cast<DeclRefExpr>(TheCall->getCallee()->IgnoreParenCasts());
7528  FunctionDecl *FDecl = cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
7529 
7530  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent()) return false;
7531 
7532  Optional<llvm::APSInt> R;
7533  if (!(R = Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)))
7534  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_constant_integer_arg_type)
7535  << FDecl->getDeclName() << Arg->getSourceRange();
7536  Result = *R;
7537  return false;
7538 }
7539 
7540 /// SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange - Handle a check if argument ArgNum of CallExpr
7541 /// TheCall is a constant expression in the range [Low, High].
7542 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(CallExpr *TheCall, int ArgNum,
7543  int Low, int High, bool RangeIsError) {
7544  if (isConstantEvaluated())
7545  return false;
7546  llvm::APSInt Result;
7547 
7548  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7549  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7550  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
7551  return false;
7552 
7553  // Check constant-ness first.
7554  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
7555  return true;
7556 
7557  if (Result.getSExtValue() < Low || Result.getSExtValue() > High) {
7558  if (RangeIsError)
7559  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_argument_invalid_range)
7560  << toString(Result, 10) << Low << High << Arg->getSourceRange();
7561  else
7562  // Defer the warning until we know if the code will be emitted so that
7563  // dead code can ignore this.
7564  DiagRuntimeBehavior(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), TheCall,
7565  PDiag(diag::warn_argument_invalid_range)
7566  << toString(Result, 10) << Low << High
7567  << Arg->getSourceRange());
7568  }
7569 
7570  return false;
7571 }
7572 
7573 /// SemaBuiltinConstantArgMultiple - Handle a check if argument ArgNum of CallExpr
7574 /// TheCall is a constant expression is a multiple of Num..
7575 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinConstantArgMultiple(CallExpr *TheCall, int ArgNum,
7576  unsigned Num) {
7577  llvm::APSInt Result;
7578 
7579  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7580  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7581  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
7582  return false;
7583 
7584  // Check constant-ness first.
7585  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
7586  return true;
7587 
7588  if (Result.getSExtValue() % Num != 0)
7589  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_argument_not_multiple)
7590  << Num << Arg->getSourceRange();
7591 
7592  return false;
7593 }
7594 
7595 /// SemaBuiltinConstantArgPower2 - Check if argument ArgNum of TheCall is a
7596 /// constant expression representing a power of 2.
7597 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinConstantArgPower2(CallExpr *TheCall, int ArgNum) {
7598  llvm::APSInt Result;
7599 
7600  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7601  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7602  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
7603  return false;
7604 
7605  // Check constant-ness first.
7606  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
7607  return true;
7608 
7609  // Bit-twiddling to test for a power of 2: for x > 0, x & (x-1) is zero if
7610  // and only if x is a power of 2.
7611  if (Result.isStrictlyPositive() && (Result & (Result - 1)) == 0)
7612  return false;
7613 
7614  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_argument_not_power_of_2)
7615  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7616 }
7617 
7618 static bool IsShiftedByte(llvm::APSInt Value) {
7619  if (Value.isNegative())
7620  return false;
7621 
7622  // Check if it's a shifted byte, by shifting it down
7623  while (true) {
7624  // If the value fits in the bottom byte, the check passes.
7625  if (Value < 0x100)
7626  return true;
7627 
7628  // Otherwise, if the value has _any_ bits in the bottom byte, the check
7629  // fails.
7630  if ((Value & 0xFF) != 0)
7631  return false;
7632 
7633  // If the bottom 8 bits are all 0, but something above that is nonzero,
7634  // then shifting the value right by 8 bits won't affect whether it's a
7635  // shifted byte or not. So do that, and go round again.
7636  Value >>= 8;
7637  }
7638 }
7639 
7640 /// SemaBuiltinConstantArgShiftedByte - Check if argument ArgNum of TheCall is
7641 /// a constant expression representing an arbitrary byte value shifted left by
7642 /// a multiple of 8 bits.
7643 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinConstantArgShiftedByte(CallExpr *TheCall, int ArgNum,
7644  unsigned ArgBits) {
7645  llvm::APSInt Result;
7646 
7647  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7648  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7649  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
7650  return false;
7651 
7652  // Check constant-ness first.
7653  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
7654  return true;
7655 
7656  // Truncate to the given size.
7657  Result = Result.getLoBits(ArgBits);
7658  Result.setIsUnsigned(true);
7659 
7660  if (IsShiftedByte(Result))
7661  return false;
7662 
7663  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_argument_not_shifted_byte)
7664  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7665 }
7666 
7667 /// SemaBuiltinConstantArgShiftedByteOr0xFF - Check if argument ArgNum of
7668 /// TheCall is a constant expression representing either a shifted byte value,
7669 /// or a value of the form 0x??FF (i.e. a member of the arithmetic progression
7670 /// 0x00FF, 0x01FF, ..., 0xFFFF). This strange range check is needed for some
7671 /// Arm MVE intrinsics.
7672 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinConstantArgShiftedByteOrXXFF(CallExpr *TheCall,
7673  int ArgNum,
7674  unsigned ArgBits) {
7675  llvm::APSInt Result;
7676 
7677  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7678  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7679  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
7680  return false;
7681 
7682  // Check constant-ness first.
7683  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, ArgNum, Result))
7684  return true;
7685 
7686  // Truncate to the given size.
7687  Result = Result.getLoBits(ArgBits);
7688  Result.setIsUnsigned(true);
7689 
7690  // Check to see if it's in either of the required forms.
7691  if (IsShiftedByte(Result) ||
7692  (Result > 0 && Result < 0x10000 && (Result & 0xFF) == 0xFF))
7693  return false;
7694 
7695  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(),
7696  diag::err_argument_not_shifted_byte_or_xxff)
7697  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7698 }
7699 
7700 /// SemaBuiltinARMMemoryTaggingCall - Handle calls of memory tagging extensions
7701 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinARMMemoryTaggingCall(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall) {
7702  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_irg) {
7703  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
7704  return true;
7705  Expr *Arg0 = TheCall->getArg(0);
7706  Expr *Arg1 = TheCall->getArg(1);
7707 
7708  ExprResult FirstArg = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Arg0);
7709  if (FirstArg.isInvalid())
7710  return true;
7711  QualType FirstArgType = FirstArg.get()->getType();
7712  if (!FirstArgType->isAnyPointerType())
7713  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_must_be_pointer)
7714  << "first" << FirstArgType << Arg0->getSourceRange();
7715  TheCall->setArg(0, FirstArg.get());
7716 
7717  ExprResult SecArg = DefaultLvalueConversion(Arg1);
7718  if (SecArg.isInvalid())
7719  return true;
7720  QualType SecArgType = SecArg.get()->getType();
7721  if (!SecArgType->isIntegerType())
7722  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_must_be_integer)
7723  << "second" << SecArgType << Arg1->getSourceRange();
7724 
7725  // Derive the return type from the pointer argument.
7726  TheCall->setType(FirstArgType);
7727  return false;
7728  }
7729 
7730  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_addg) {
7731  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
7732  return true;
7733 
7734  Expr *Arg0 = TheCall->getArg(0);
7735  ExprResult FirstArg = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Arg0);
7736  if (FirstArg.isInvalid())
7737  return true;
7738  QualType FirstArgType = FirstArg.get()->getType();
7739  if (!FirstArgType->isAnyPointerType())
7740  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_must_be_pointer)
7741  << "first" << FirstArgType << Arg0->getSourceRange();
7742  TheCall->setArg(0, FirstArg.get());
7743 
7744  // Derive the return type from the pointer argument.
7745  TheCall->setType(FirstArgType);
7746 
7747  // Second arg must be an constant in range [0,15]
7748  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 15);
7749  }
7750 
7751  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_gmi) {
7752  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
7753  return true;
7754  Expr *Arg0 = TheCall->getArg(0);
7755  Expr *Arg1 = TheCall->getArg(1);
7756 
7757  ExprResult FirstArg = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Arg0);
7758  if (FirstArg.isInvalid())
7759  return true;
7760  QualType FirstArgType = FirstArg.get()->getType();
7761  if (!FirstArgType->isAnyPointerType())
7762  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_must_be_pointer)
7763  << "first" << FirstArgType << Arg0->getSourceRange();
7764 
7765  QualType SecArgType = Arg1->getType();
7766  if (!SecArgType->isIntegerType())
7767  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_must_be_integer)
7768  << "second" << SecArgType << Arg1->getSourceRange();
7769  TheCall->setType(Context.IntTy);
7770  return false;
7771  }
7772 
7773  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldg ||
7774  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stg) {
7775  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 1))
7776  return true;
7777  Expr *Arg0 = TheCall->getArg(0);
7778  ExprResult FirstArg = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Arg0);
7779  if (FirstArg.isInvalid())
7780  return true;
7781 
7782  QualType FirstArgType = FirstArg.get()->getType();
7783  if (!FirstArgType->isAnyPointerType())
7784  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_must_be_pointer)
7785  << "first" << FirstArgType << Arg0->getSourceRange();
7786  TheCall->setArg(0, FirstArg.get());
7787 
7788  // Derive the return type from the pointer argument.
7789  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldg)
7790  TheCall->setType(FirstArgType);
7791  return false;
7792  }
7793 
7794  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_subp) {
7795  Expr *ArgA = TheCall->getArg(0);
7796  Expr *ArgB = TheCall->getArg(1);
7797 
7798  ExprResult ArgExprA = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(ArgA);
7799  ExprResult ArgExprB = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(ArgB);
7800 
7801  if (ArgExprA.isInvalid() || ArgExprB.isInvalid())
7802  return true;
7803 
7804  QualType ArgTypeA = ArgExprA.get()->getType();
7805  QualType ArgTypeB = ArgExprB.get()->getType();
7806 
7807  auto isNull = [&] (Expr *E) -> bool {
7808  return E->isNullPointerConstant(
7809  Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull); };
7810 
7811  // argument should be either a pointer or null
7812  if (!ArgTypeA->isAnyPointerType() && !isNull(ArgA))
7813  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_null_or_pointer)
7814  << "first" << ArgTypeA << ArgA->getSourceRange();
7815 
7816  if (!ArgTypeB->isAnyPointerType() && !isNull(ArgB))
7817  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_arg_null_or_pointer)
7818  << "second" << ArgTypeB << ArgB->getSourceRange();
7819 
7820  // Ensure Pointee types are compatible
7821  if (ArgTypeA->isAnyPointerType() && !isNull(ArgA) &&
7822  ArgTypeB->isAnyPointerType() && !isNull(ArgB)) {
7823  QualType pointeeA = ArgTypeA->getPointeeType();
7824  QualType pointeeB = ArgTypeB->getPointeeType();
7825  if (!Context.typesAreCompatible(
7826  Context.getCanonicalType(pointeeA).getUnqualifiedType(),
7827  Context.getCanonicalType(pointeeB).getUnqualifiedType())) {
7828  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_sub_ptr_compatible)
7829  << ArgTypeA << ArgTypeB << ArgA->getSourceRange()
7830  << ArgB->getSourceRange();
7831  }
7832  }
7833 
7834  // at least one argument should be pointer type
7835  if (!ArgTypeA->isAnyPointerType() && !ArgTypeB->isAnyPointerType())
7836  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_memtag_any2arg_pointer)
7837  << ArgTypeA << ArgTypeB << ArgA->getSourceRange();
7838 
7839  if (isNull(ArgA)) // adopt type of the other pointer
7840  ArgExprA = ImpCastExprToType(ArgExprA.get(), ArgTypeB, CK_NullToPointer);
7841 
7842  if (isNull(ArgB))
7843  ArgExprB = ImpCastExprToType(ArgExprB.get(), ArgTypeA, CK_NullToPointer);
7844 
7845  TheCall->setArg(0, ArgExprA.get());
7846  TheCall->setArg(1, ArgExprB.get());
7847  TheCall->setType(Context.LongLongTy);
7848  return false;
7849  }
7850  assert(false && "Unhandled ARM MTE intrinsic");
7851  return true;
7852 }
7853 
7854 /// SemaBuiltinARMSpecialReg - Handle a check if argument ArgNum of CallExpr
7855 /// TheCall is an ARM/AArch64 special register string literal.
7856 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinARMSpecialReg(unsigned BuiltinID, CallExpr *TheCall,
7857  int ArgNum, unsigned ExpectedFieldNum,
7858  bool AllowName) {
7859  bool IsARMBuiltin = BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
7860  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64 ||
7861  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
7862  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
7863  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr ||
7864  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp;
7865  bool IsAArch64Builtin = BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
7866  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64 ||
7867  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
7868  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
7869  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr ||
7870  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp;
7871  assert((IsARMBuiltin || IsAArch64Builtin) && "Unexpected ARM builtin.");
7872 
7873  // We can't check the value of a dependent argument.
7874  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
7875  if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent())
7876  return false;
7877 
7878  // Check if the argument is a string literal.
7879  if (!isa<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
7880  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_expr_not_string_literal)
7881  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7882 
7883  // Check the type of special register given.
7884  StringRef Reg = cast<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts())->getString();
7885  SmallVector<StringRef, 6> Fields;
7886  Reg.split(Fields, ":");
7887 
7888  if (Fields.size() != ExpectedFieldNum && !(AllowName && Fields.size() == 1))
7889  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arm_invalid_specialreg)
7890  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7891 
7892  // If the string is the name of a register then we cannot check that it is
7893  // valid here but if the string is of one the forms described in ACLE then we
7894  // can check that the supplied fields are integers and within the valid
7895  // ranges.
7896  if (Fields.size() > 1) {
7897  bool FiveFields = Fields.size() == 5;
7898 
7899  bool ValidString = true;
7900  if (IsARMBuiltin) {
7901  ValidString &= Fields[0].startswith_insensitive("cp") ||
7902  Fields[0].startswith_insensitive("p");
7903  if (ValidString)
7904  Fields[0] = Fields[0].drop_front(
7905  Fields[0].startswith_insensitive("cp") ? 2 : 1);
7906 
7907  ValidString &= Fields[2].startswith_insensitive("c");
7908  if (ValidString)
7909  Fields[2] = Fields[2].drop_front(1);
7910 
7911  if (FiveFields) {
7912  ValidString &= Fields[3].startswith_insensitive("c");
7913  if (ValidString)
7914  Fields[3] = Fields[3].drop_front(1);
7915  }
7916  }
7917 
7918  SmallVector<int, 5> Ranges;
7919  if (FiveFields)
7920  Ranges.append({IsAArch64Builtin ? 1 : 15, 7, 15, 15, 7});
7921  else
7922  Ranges.append({15, 7, 15});
7923 
7924  for (unsigned i=0; i<Fields.size(); ++i) {
7925  int IntField;
7926  ValidString &= !Fields[i].getAsInteger(10, IntField);
7927  ValidString &= (IntField >= 0 && IntField <= Ranges[i]);
7928  }
7929 
7930  if (!ValidString)
7931  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arm_invalid_specialreg)
7932  << Arg->getSourceRange();
7933  } else if (IsAArch64Builtin && Fields.size() == 1) {
7934  // If the register name is one of those that appear in the condition below
7935  // and the special register builtin being used is one of the write builtins,
7936  // then we require that the argument provided for writing to the register
7937  // is an integer constant expression. This is because it will be lowered to
7938  // an MSR (immediate) instruction, so we need to know the immediate at
7939  // compile time.
7940  if (TheCall->getNumArgs() != 2)
7941  return false;
7942 
7943  std::string RegLower = Reg.lower();
7944  if (RegLower != "spsel" && RegLower != "daifset" && RegLower != "daifclr" &&
7945  RegLower != "pan" && RegLower != "uao")
7946  return false;
7947 
7948  return SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, 1, 0, 15);
7949  }
7950 
7951  return false;
7952 }
7953 
7954 /// SemaBuiltinPPCMMACall - Check the call to a PPC MMA builtin for validity.
7955 /// Emit an error and return true on failure; return false on success.
7956 /// TypeStr is a string containing the type descriptor of the value returned by
7957 /// the builtin and the descriptors of the expected type of the arguments.
7958 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinPPCMMACall(CallExpr *TheCall, unsigned BuiltinID,
7959  const char *TypeStr) {
7960 
7961  assert((TypeStr[0] != '\0') &&
7962  "Invalid types in PPC MMA builtin declaration");
7963 
7964  switch (BuiltinID) {
7965  default:
7966  // This function is called in CheckPPCBuiltinFunctionCall where the
7967  // BuiltinID is guaranteed to be an MMA or pair vector memop builtin, here
7968  // we are isolating the pair vector memop builtins that can be used with mma
7969  // off so the default case is every builtin that requires mma and paired
7970  // vector memops.
7971  if (SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "paired-vector-memops",
7972  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "10") ||
7973  SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "mma",
7974  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "10"))
7975  return true;
7976  break;
7977  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvp:
7978  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvp:
7979  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_assemble_pair:
7980  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_disassemble_pair:
7981  if (SemaFeatureCheck(*this, TheCall, "paired-vector-memops",
7982  diag::err_ppc_builtin_only_on_arch, "10"))
7983  return true;
7984  break;
7985  }
7986 
7987  unsigned Mask = 0;
7988  unsigned ArgNum = 0;
7989 
7990  // The first type in TypeStr is the type of the value returned by the
7991  // builtin. So we first read that type and change the type of TheCall.
7992  QualType type = DecodePPCMMATypeFromStr(Context, TypeStr, Mask);
7993  TheCall->setType(type);
7994 
7995  while (*TypeStr != '\0') {
7996  Mask = 0;
7997  QualType ExpectedType = DecodePPCMMATypeFromStr(Context, TypeStr, Mask);
7998  if (ArgNum >= TheCall->getNumArgs()) {
7999  ArgNum++;
8000  break;
8001  }
8002 
8003  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(ArgNum);
8004  QualType PassedType = Arg->getType();
8005  QualType StrippedRVType = PassedType.getCanonicalType();
8006 
8007  // Strip Restrict/Volatile qualifiers.
8008  if (StrippedRVType.isRestrictQualified() ||
8009  StrippedRVType.isVolatileQualified())
8010  StrippedRVType = StrippedRVType.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
8011 
8012  // The only case where the argument type and expected type are allowed to
8013  // mismatch is if the argument type is a non-void pointer (or array) and
8014  // expected type is a void pointer.
8015  if (StrippedRVType != ExpectedType)
8016  if (!(ExpectedType->isVoidPointerType() &&
8017  (StrippedRVType->isPointerType() || StrippedRVType->isArrayType())))
8018  return Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(),
8019  diag::err_typecheck_convert_incompatible)
8020  << PassedType << ExpectedType << 1 << 0 << 0;
8021 
8022  // If the value of the Mask is not 0, we have a constraint in the size of
8023  // the integer argument so here we ensure the argument is a constant that
8024  // is in the valid range.
8025  if (Mask != 0 &&
8026  SemaBuiltinConstantArgRange(TheCall, ArgNum, 0, Mask, true))
8027  return true;
8028 
8029  ArgNum++;
8030  }
8031 
8032  // In case we exited early from the previous loop, there are other types to
8033  // read from TypeStr. So we need to read them all to ensure we have the right
8034  // number of arguments in TheCall and if it is not the case, to display a
8035  // better error message.
8036  while (*TypeStr != '\0') {
8037  (void) DecodePPCMMATypeFromStr(Context, TypeStr, Mask);
8038  ArgNum++;
8039  }
8040  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, ArgNum))
8041  return true;
8042 
8043  return false;
8044 }
8045 
8046 /// SemaBuiltinLongjmp - Handle __builtin_longjmp(void *env[5], int val).
8047 /// This checks that the target supports __builtin_longjmp and
8048 /// that val is a constant 1.
8049 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinLongjmp(CallExpr *TheCall) {
8050  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().hasSjLjLowering())
8051  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_longjmp_unsupported)
8052  << SourceRange(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), TheCall->getEndLoc());
8053 
8054  Expr *Arg = TheCall->getArg(1);
8055  llvm::APSInt Result;
8056 
8057  // TODO: This is less than ideal. Overload this to take a value.
8058  if (SemaBuiltinConstantArg(TheCall, 1, Result))
8059  return true;
8060 
8061  if (Result != 1)
8062  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_longjmp_invalid_val)
8063  << SourceRange(Arg->getBeginLoc(), Arg->getEndLoc());
8064 
8065  return false;
8066 }
8067 
8068 /// SemaBuiltinSetjmp - Handle __builtin_setjmp(void *env[5]).
8069 /// This checks that the target supports __builtin_setjmp.
8070 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinSetjmp(CallExpr *TheCall) {
8071  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().hasSjLjLowering())
8072  return Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_setjmp_unsupported)
8073  << SourceRange(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), TheCall->getEndLoc());
8074  return false;
8075 }

8077 namespace {
8078 
8079 class UncoveredArgHandler {
8080  enum { Unknown = -1, AllCovered = -2 };
8081 
8082  signed FirstUncoveredArg = Unknown;
8083  SmallVector<const Expr *, 4> DiagnosticExprs;
8084 
8085 public:
8086  UncoveredArgHandler() = default;
8087 
8088  bool hasUncoveredArg() const {
8089  return (FirstUncoveredArg >= 0);
8090  }
8091 
8092  unsigned getUncoveredArg() const {
8093  assert(hasUncoveredArg() && "no uncovered argument");
8094  return FirstUncoveredArg;
8095  }
8096 
8097  void setAllCovered() {
8098  // A string has been found with all arguments covered, so clear out
8099  // the diagnostics.
8100  DiagnosticExprs.clear();
8101  FirstUncoveredArg = AllCovered;
8102  }
8103 
8104  void Update(signed NewFirstUncoveredArg, const Expr *StrExpr) {
8105  assert(NewFirstUncoveredArg >= 0 && "Outside range");
8106 
8107  // Don't update if a previous string covers all arguments.
8108  if (FirstUncoveredArg == AllCovered)
8109  return;
8110 
8111  // UncoveredArgHandler tracks the highest uncovered argument index
8112  // and with it all the strings that match this index.
8113  if (NewFirstUncoveredArg == FirstUncoveredArg)
8114  DiagnosticExprs.push_back(StrExpr);
8115  else if (NewFirstUncoveredArg > FirstUncoveredArg) {
8116  DiagnosticExprs.clear();
8117  DiagnosticExprs.push_back(StrExpr);
8118  FirstUncoveredArg = NewFirstUncoveredArg;
8119  }
8120  }
8121 
8122  void Diagnose(Sema &S, bool IsFunctionCall, const Expr *ArgExpr);
8123 };
8124 
8125 enum StringLiteralCheckType {
8126  SLCT_NotALiteral,
8127  SLCT_UncheckedLiteral,
8128  SLCT_CheckedLiteral
8129 };
8130 
8131 } // namespace
8132 
8133 static void sumOffsets(llvm::APSInt &Offset, llvm::APSInt Addend,
8134  BinaryOperatorKind BinOpKind,
8135  bool AddendIsRight) {
8136  unsigned BitWidth = Offset.getBitWidth();
8137  unsigned AddendBitWidth = Addend.getBitWidth();
8138  // There might be negative interim results.
8139  if (Addend.isUnsigned()) {
8140  Addend = Addend.zext(++AddendBitWidth);
8141  Addend.setIsSigned(true);
8142  }
8143  // Adjust the bit width of the APSInts.
8144  if (AddendBitWidth > BitWidth) {
8145  Offset = Offset.sext(AddendBitWidth);
8146  BitWidth = AddendBitWidth;
8147  } else if (BitWidth > AddendBitWidth) {
8148  Addend = Addend.sext(BitWidth);
8149  }
8150 
8151  bool Ov = false;
8152  llvm::APSInt ResOffset = Offset;
8153  if (BinOpKind == BO_Add)
8154  ResOffset = Offset.sadd_ov(Addend, Ov);
8155  else {
8156  assert(AddendIsRight && BinOpKind == BO_Sub &&
8157  "operator must be add or sub with addend on the right");
8158  ResOffset = Offset.ssub_ov(Addend, Ov);
8159  }
8160 
8161  // We add an offset to a pointer here so we should support an offset as big as
8162  // possible.
8163  if (Ov) {
8164  assert(BitWidth <= std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max() / 2 &&
8165  "index (intermediate) result too big");
8166  Offset = Offset.sext(2 * BitWidth);
8167  sumOffsets(Offset, Addend, BinOpKind, AddendIsRight);
8168  return;
8169  }
8170 
8171  Offset = ResOffset;
8172 }
8173 
8174 namespace {
8175 
8176 // This is a wrapper class around StringLiteral to support offsetted string
8177 // literals as format strings. It takes the offset into account when returning
8178 // the string and its length or the source locations to display notes correctly.
8179 class FormatStringLiteral {
8180  const StringLiteral *FExpr;
8181  int64_t Offset;
8182 
8183  public:
8184  FormatStringLiteral(const StringLiteral *fexpr, int64_t Offset = 0)
8185  : FExpr(fexpr), Offset(Offset) {}
8186 
8187  StringRef getString() const {
8188  return FExpr->getString().drop_front(Offset);
8189  }
8190 
8191  unsigned getByteLength() const {
8192  return FExpr->getByteLength() - getCharByteWidth() * Offset;
8193  }
8194 
8195  unsigned getLength() const { return FExpr->getLength() - Offset; }
8196  unsigned getCharByteWidth() const { return FExpr->getCharByteWidth(); }
8197 
8198  StringLiteral::StringKind getKind() const { return FExpr->getKind(); }
8199 
8200  QualType getType() const { return FExpr->getType(); }
8201 
8202  bool isAscii() const { return FExpr->isAscii(); }
8203  bool isWide() const { return FExpr->isWide(); }
8204  bool isUTF8() const { return FExpr->isUTF8(); }
8205  bool isUTF16() const { return FExpr->isUTF16(); }
8206  bool isUTF32() const { return FExpr->isUTF32(); }
8207  bool isPascal() const { return FExpr->isPascal(); }
8208 
8209  SourceLocation getLocationOfByte(
8210  unsigned ByteNo, const SourceManager &SM, const LangOptions &Features,
8211  const TargetInfo &Target, unsigned *StartToken = nullptr,
8212  unsigned *StartTokenByteOffset = nullptr) const {
8213  return FExpr->getLocationOfByte(ByteNo + Offset, SM, Features, Target,
8214  StartToken, StartTokenByteOffset);
8215  }
8216 
8217  SourceLocation getBeginLoc() const LLVM_READONLY {
8218  return FExpr->getBeginLoc().getLocWithOffset(Offset);
8219  }
8220 
8221  SourceLocation getEndLoc() const LLVM_READONLY { return FExpr->getEndLoc(); }
8222 };
8223 
8224 } // namespace
8225 
8226 static void CheckFormatString(Sema &S, const FormatStringLiteral *FExpr,
8227  const Expr *OrigFormatExpr,
8228  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
8229  bool HasVAListArg, unsigned format_idx,
8230  unsigned firstDataArg,
8231  Sema::FormatStringType Type,
8232  bool inFunctionCall,
8233  Sema::VariadicCallType CallType,
8234  llvm::SmallBitVector &CheckedVarArgs,
8235  UncoveredArgHandler &UncoveredArg,
8236  bool IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8237 
8238 // Determine if an expression is a string literal or constant string.
8239 // If this function returns false on the arguments to a function expecting a
8240 // format string, we will usually need to emit a warning.
8241 // True string literals are then checked by CheckFormatString.
8242 static StringLiteralCheckType
8243 checkFormatStringExpr(Sema &S, const Expr *E, ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
8244  bool HasVAListArg, unsigned format_idx,
8245  unsigned firstDataArg, Sema::FormatStringType Type,
8246  Sema::VariadicCallType CallType, bool InFunctionCall,
8247  llvm::SmallBitVector &CheckedVarArgs,
8248  UncoveredArgHandler &UncoveredArg,
8249  llvm::APSInt Offset,
8250  bool IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers = false) {
8251  if (S.isConstantEvaluated())
8252  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8253  tryAgain:
8254  assert(Offset.isSigned() && "invalid offset");
8255 
8256  if (E->isTypeDependent() || E->isValueDependent())
8257  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8258 
8259  E = E->IgnoreParenCasts();
8260 
8261  if (E->isNullPointerConstant(S.Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull))
8262  // Technically -Wformat-nonliteral does not warn about this case.
8263  // The behavior of printf and friends in this case is implementation
8264  // dependent. Ideally if the format string cannot be null then
8265  // it should have a 'nonnull' attribute in the function prototype.
8266  return SLCT_UncheckedLiteral;
8267 
8268  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
8269  case Stmt::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass:
8270  case Stmt::ConditionalOperatorClass: {
8271  // The expression is a literal if both sub-expressions were, and it was
8272  // completely checked only if both sub-expressions were checked.
8273  const AbstractConditionalOperator *C =
8274  cast<AbstractConditionalOperator>(E);
8275 
8276  // Determine whether it is necessary to check both sub-expressions, for
8277  // example, because the condition expression is a constant that can be
8278  // evaluated at compile time.
8279  bool CheckLeft = true, CheckRight = true;
8280 
8281  bool Cond;
8282  if (C->getCond()->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(Cond, S.getASTContext(),
8283  S.isConstantEvaluated())) {
8284  if (Cond)
8285  CheckRight = false;
8286  else
8287  CheckLeft = false;
8288  }
8289 
8290  // We need to maintain the offsets for the right and the left hand side
8291  // separately to check if every possible indexed expression is a valid
8292  // string literal. They might have different offsets for different string
8293  // literals in the end.
8294  StringLiteralCheckType Left;
8295  if (!CheckLeft)
8296  Left = SLCT_UncheckedLiteral;
8297  else {
8298  Left = checkFormatStringExpr(S, C->getTrueExpr(), Args,
8299  HasVAListArg, format_idx, firstDataArg,
8300  Type, CallType, InFunctionCall,
8301  CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg, Offset,
8302  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8303  if (Left == SLCT_NotALiteral || !CheckRight) {
8304  return Left;
8305  }
8306  }
8307 
8308  StringLiteralCheckType Right = checkFormatStringExpr(
8309  S, C->getFalseExpr(), Args, HasVAListArg, format_idx, firstDataArg,
8310  Type, CallType, InFunctionCall, CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg, Offset,
8311  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8312 
8313  return (CheckLeft && Left < Right) ? Left : Right;
8314  }
8315 
8316  case Stmt::ImplicitCastExprClass:
8317  E = cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
8318  goto tryAgain;
8319 
8320  case Stmt::OpaqueValueExprClass:
8321  if (const Expr *src = cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E)->getSourceExpr()) {
8322  E = src;
8323  goto tryAgain;
8324  }
8325  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8326 
8327  case Stmt::PredefinedExprClass:
8328  // While __func__, etc., are technically not string literals, they
8329  // cannot contain format specifiers and thus are not a security
8330  // liability.
8331  return SLCT_UncheckedLiteral;
8332 
8333  case Stmt::DeclRefExprClass: {
8334  const DeclRefExpr *DR = cast<DeclRefExpr>(E);
8335 
8336  // As an exception, do not flag errors for variables binding to
8337  // const string literals.
8338  if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DR->getDecl())) {
8339  bool isConstant = false;
8340  QualType T = DR->getType();
8341 
8342  if (const ArrayType *AT = S.Context.getAsArrayType(T)) {
8343  isConstant = AT->getElementType().isConstant(S.Context);
8344  } else if (const PointerType *PT = T->getAs<PointerType>()) {
8345  isConstant = T.isConstant(S.Context) &&
8346  PT->getPointeeType().isConstant(S.Context);
8347  } else if (T->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
8348  // In ObjC, there is usually no "const ObjectPointer" type,
8349  // so don't check if the pointee type is constant.
8350  isConstant = T.isConstant(S.Context);
8351  }
8352 
8353  if (isConstant) {
8354  if (const Expr *Init = VD->getAnyInitializer()) {
8355  // Look through initializers like const char c[] = { "foo" }
8356  if (const InitListExpr *InitList = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Init)) {
8357  if (InitList->isStringLiteralInit())
8358  Init = InitList->getInit(0)->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
8359  }
8360  return checkFormatStringExpr(S, Init, Args,
8361  HasVAListArg, format_idx,
8362  firstDataArg, Type, CallType,
8363  /*InFunctionCall*/ false, CheckedVarArgs,
8364  UncoveredArg, Offset);
8365  }
8366  }
8367 
8368  // For vprintf* functions (i.e., HasVAListArg==true), we add a
8369  // special check to see if the format string is a function parameter
8370  // of the function calling the printf function. If the function
8371  // has an attribute indicating it is a printf-like function, then we
8372  // should suppress warnings concerning non-literals being used in a call
8373  // to a vprintf function. For example:
8374  //
8375  // void
8376  // logmessage(char const *fmt __attribute__ (format (printf, 1, 2)), ...){
8377  // va_list ap;
8378  // va_start(ap, fmt);
8379  // vprintf(fmt, ap); // Do NOT emit a warning about "fmt".
8380  // ...
8381  // }
8382  if (HasVAListArg) {
8383  if (const ParmVarDecl *PV = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(VD)) {
8384  if (const Decl *D = dyn_cast<Decl>(PV->getDeclContext())) {
8385  int PVIndex = PV->getFunctionScopeIndex() + 1;
8386  for (const auto *PVFormat : D->specific_attrs<FormatAttr>()) {
8387  // adjust for implicit parameter
8388  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
8389  if (MD->isInstance())
8390  ++PVIndex;
8391  // We also check if the formats are compatible.
8392  // We can't pass a 'scanf' string to a 'printf' function.
8393  if (PVIndex == PVFormat->getFormatIdx() &&
8394  Type == S.GetFormatStringType(PVFormat))
8395  return SLCT_UncheckedLiteral;
8396  }
8397  }
8398  }
8399  }
8400  }
8401 
8402  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8403  }
8404 
8405  case Stmt::CallExprClass:
8406  case Stmt::CXXMemberCallExprClass: {
8407  const CallExpr *CE = cast<CallExpr>(E);
8408  if (const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(CE->getCalleeDecl())) {
8409  bool IsFirst = true;
8410  StringLiteralCheckType CommonResult;
8411  for (const auto *FA : ND->specific_attrs<FormatArgAttr>()) {
8412  const Expr *Arg = CE->getArg(FA->getFormatIdx().getASTIndex());
8413  StringLiteralCheckType Result = checkFormatStringExpr(
8414  S, Arg, Args, HasVAListArg, format_idx, firstDataArg, Type,
8415  CallType, InFunctionCall, CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg, Offset,
8416  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8417  if (IsFirst) {
8418  CommonResult = Result;
8419  IsFirst = false;
8420  }
8421  }
8422  if (!IsFirst)
8423  return CommonResult;
8424 
8425  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND)) {
8426  unsigned BuiltinID = FD->getBuiltinID();
8427  if (BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin___CFStringMakeConstantString ||
8428  BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin___NSStringMakeConstantString) {
8429  const Expr *Arg = CE->getArg(0);
8430  return checkFormatStringExpr(S, Arg, Args,
8431  HasVAListArg, format_idx,
8432  firstDataArg, Type, CallType,
8433  InFunctionCall, CheckedVarArgs,
8434  UncoveredArg, Offset,
8435  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8436  }
8437  }
8438  }
8439 
8440  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8441  }
8442  case Stmt::ObjCMessageExprClass: {
8443  const auto *ME = cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E);
8444  if (const auto *MD = ME->getMethodDecl()) {
8445  if (const auto *FA = MD->getAttr<FormatArgAttr>()) {
8446  // As a special case heuristic, if we're using the method -[NSBundle
8447  // localizedStringForKey:value:table:], ignore any key strings that lack
8448  // format specifiers. The idea is that if the key doesn't have any
8449  // format specifiers then its probably just a key to map to the
8450  // localized strings. If it does have format specifiers though, then its
8451  // likely that the text of the key is the format string in the
8452  // programmer's language, and should be checked.
8453  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace;
8454  if (MD->isInstanceMethod() && (IFace = MD->getClassInterface()) &&
8455  IFace->getIdentifier()->isStr("NSBundle") &&
8456  MD->getSelector().isKeywordSelector(
8457  {"localizedStringForKey", "value", "table"})) {
8458  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers = true;
8459  }
8460 
8461  const Expr *Arg = ME->getArg(FA->getFormatIdx().getASTIndex());
8462  return checkFormatStringExpr(
8463  S, Arg, Args, HasVAListArg, format_idx, firstDataArg, Type,
8464  CallType, InFunctionCall, CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg, Offset,
8465  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8466  }
8467  }
8468 
8469  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8470  }
8471  case Stmt::ObjCStringLiteralClass:
8472  case Stmt::StringLiteralClass: {
8473  const StringLiteral *StrE = nullptr;
8474 
8475  if (const ObjCStringLiteral *ObjCFExpr = dyn_cast<ObjCStringLiteral>(E))
8476  StrE = ObjCFExpr->getString();
8477  else
8478  StrE = cast<StringLiteral>(E);
8479 
8480  if (StrE) {
8481  if (Offset.isNegative() || Offset > StrE->getLength()) {
8482  // TODO: It would be better to have an explicit warning for out of
8483  // bounds literals.
8484  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8485  }
8486  FormatStringLiteral FStr(StrE, Offset.sextOrTrunc(64).getSExtValue());
8487  CheckFormatString(S, &FStr, E, Args, HasVAListArg, format_idx,
8488  firstDataArg, Type, InFunctionCall, CallType,
8489  CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg,
8490  IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers);
8491  return SLCT_CheckedLiteral;
8492  }
8493 
8494  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8495  }
8496  case Stmt::BinaryOperatorClass: {
8497  const BinaryOperator *BinOp = cast<BinaryOperator>(E);
8498 
8499  // A string literal + an int offset is still a string literal.
8500  if (BinOp->isAdditiveOp()) {
8501  Expr::EvalResult LResult, RResult;
8502 
8503  bool LIsInt = BinOp->getLHS()->EvaluateAsInt(
8504  LResult, S.Context, Expr::SE_NoSideEffects, S.isConstantEvaluated());
8505  bool RIsInt = BinOp->getRHS()->EvaluateAsInt(
8506  RResult, S.Context, Expr::SE_NoSideEffects, S.isConstantEvaluated());
8507 
8508  if (LIsInt != RIsInt) {
8509  BinaryOperatorKind BinOpKind = BinOp->getOpcode();
8510 
8511  if (LIsInt) {
8512  if (BinOpKind == BO_Add) {
8513  sumOffsets(Offset, LResult.Val.getInt(), BinOpKind, RIsInt);
8514  E = BinOp->getRHS();
8515  goto tryAgain;
8516  }
8517  } else {
8518  sumOffsets(Offset, RResult.Val.getInt(), BinOpKind, RIsInt);
8519  E = BinOp->getLHS();
8520  goto tryAgain;
8521  }
8522  }
8523  }
8524 
8525  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8526  }
8527  case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
8528  const UnaryOperator *UnaOp = cast<UnaryOperator>(E);
8529  auto ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(UnaOp->getSubExpr());
8530  if (UnaOp->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf && ASE) {
8531  Expr::EvalResult IndexResult;
8532  if (ASE->getRHS()->EvaluateAsInt(IndexResult, S.Context,
8533  Expr::SE_NoSideEffects,
8534  S.isConstantEvaluated())) {
8535  sumOffsets(Offset, IndexResult.Val.getInt(), BO_Add,
8536  /*RHS is int*/ true);
8537  E = ASE->getBase();
8538  goto tryAgain;
8539  }
8540  }
8541 
8542  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8543  }
8544 
8545  default:
8546  return SLCT_NotALiteral;
8547  }
8548 }
8549 
8550 Sema::FormatStringType Sema::GetFormatStringType(const FormatAttr *Format) {
8551  return llvm::StringSwitch<FormatStringType>(Format->getType()->getName())
8552  .Case("scanf", FST_Scanf)
8553  .Cases("printf", "printf0", FST_Printf)
8554  .Cases("NSString", "CFString", FST_NSString)
8555  .Case("strftime", FST_Strftime)
8556  .Case("strfmon", FST_Strfmon)
8557  .Cases("kprintf", "cmn_err", "vcmn_err", "zcmn_err", FST_Kprintf)
8558  .Case("freebsd_kprintf", FST_FreeBSDKPrintf)
8559  .Case("os_trace", FST_OSLog)
8560  .Case("os_log", FST_OSLog)
8561  .Default(FST_Unknown);
8562 }
8563 
8564 /// CheckFormatArguments - Check calls to printf and scanf (and similar
8565 /// functions) for correct use of format strings.
8566 /// Returns true if a format string has been fully checked.
8567 bool Sema::CheckFormatArguments(const FormatAttr *Format,
8568  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
8569  bool IsCXXMember,
8570  VariadicCallType CallType,
8571  SourceLocation Loc, SourceRange Range,
8572  llvm::SmallBitVector &CheckedVarArgs) {
8573  FormatStringInfo FSI;
8574  if (getFormatStringInfo(Format, IsCXXMember, &FSI))
8575  return CheckFormatArguments(Args, FSI.HasVAListArg, FSI.FormatIdx,
8576  FSI.FirstDataArg, GetFormatStringType(Format),
8577  CallType, Loc, Range, CheckedVarArgs);
8578  return false;
8579 }
8580 
8581 bool Sema::CheckFormatArguments(ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
8582  bool HasVAListArg, unsigned format_idx,
8583  unsigned firstDataArg, FormatStringType Type,
8584  VariadicCallType CallType,
8585  SourceLocation Loc, SourceRange Range,
8586  llvm::SmallBitVector &CheckedVarArgs) {
8587  // CHECK: printf/scanf-like function is called with no format string.
8588  if (format_idx >= Args.size()) {
8589  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_missing_format_string) << Range;
8590  return false;
8591  }
8592 
8593  const Expr *OrigFormatExpr = Args[format_idx]->IgnoreParenCasts();
8594 
8595  // CHECK: format string is not a string literal.
8596  //
8597  // Dynamically generated format strings are difficult to
8598  // automatically vet at compile time. Requiring that format strings
8599  // are string literals: (1) permits the checking of format strings by
8600  // the compiler and thereby (2) can practically remove the source of
8601  // many format string exploits.
8602 
8603  // Format string can be either ObjC string (e.g. @"%d") or
8604  // C string (e.g. "%d")
8605  // ObjC string uses the same format specifiers as C string, so we can use
8606  // the same format string checking logic for both ObjC and C strings.
8607  UncoveredArgHandler UncoveredArg;
8608  StringLiteralCheckType CT =
8609  checkFormatStringExpr(*this, OrigFormatExpr, Args, HasVAListArg,
8610  format_idx, firstDataArg, Type, CallType,
8611  /*IsFunctionCall*/ true, CheckedVarArgs,
8612  UncoveredArg,
8613  /*no string offset*/ llvm::APSInt(64, false) = 0);
8614 
8615  // Generate a diagnostic where an uncovered argument is detected.
8616  if (UncoveredArg.hasUncoveredArg()) {
8617  unsigned ArgIdx = UncoveredArg.getUncoveredArg() + firstDataArg;
8618  assert(ArgIdx < Args.size() && "ArgIdx outside bounds");
8619  UncoveredArg.Diagnose(*this, /*IsFunctionCall*/true, Args[ArgIdx]);
8620  }
8621 
8622  if (CT != SLCT_NotALiteral)
8623  // Literal format string found, check done!
8624  return CT == SLCT_CheckedLiteral;
8625 
8626  // Strftime is particular as it always uses a single 'time' argument,
8627  // so it is safe to pass a non-literal string.
8628  if (Type == FST_Strftime)
8629  return false;
8630 
8631  // Do not emit diag when the string param is a macro expansion and the
8632  // format is either NSString or CFString. This is a hack to prevent
8633  // diag when using the NSLocalizedString and CFCopyLocalizedString macros
8634  // which are usually used in place of NS and CF string literals.
8635  SourceLocation FormatLoc = Args[format_idx]->getBeginLoc();
8636  if (Type == FST_NSString && SourceMgr.isInSystemMacro(FormatLoc))
8637  return false;
8638 
8639  // If there are no arguments specified, warn with -Wformat-security, otherwise
8640  // warn only with -Wformat-nonliteral.
8641  if (Args.size() == firstDataArg) {
8642  Diag(FormatLoc, diag::warn_format_nonliteral_noargs)
8643  << OrigFormatExpr->getSourceRange();
8644  switch (Type) {
8645  default:
8646  break;
8647  case FST_Kprintf:
8648  case FST_FreeBSDKPrintf:
8649  case FST_Printf:
8650  Diag(FormatLoc, diag::note_format_security_fixit)
8651  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FormatLoc, "\"%s\", ");
8652  break;
8653  case FST_NSString:
8654  Diag(FormatLoc, diag::note_format_security_fixit)
8655  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FormatLoc, "@\"%@\", ");
8656  break;
8657  }
8658  } else {
8659  Diag(FormatLoc, diag::warn_format_nonliteral)
8660  << OrigFormatExpr->getSourceRange();
8661  }
8662  return false;
8663 }
8664

8771 SourceRange CheckFormatHandler::getFormatStringRange() {
8772  return OrigFormatExpr->getSourceRange();
8773 }
8774 
8775 CharSourceRange CheckFormatHandler::
8776 getSpecifierRange(const char *startSpecifier, unsigned specifierLen) {
8777  SourceLocation Start = getLocationOfByte(startSpecifier);
8778  SourceLocation End = getLocationOfByte(startSpecifier + specifierLen - 1);
8779 
8780  // Advance the end SourceLocation by one due to half-open ranges.
8781  End = End.getLocWithOffset(1);
8782 
8783  return CharSourceRange::getCharRange(Start, End);
8784 }
8785 
8786 SourceLocation CheckFormatHandler::getLocationOfByte(const char *x) {
8787  return FExpr->getLocationOfByte(x - Beg, S.getSourceManager(),
8788  S.getLangOpts(), S.Context.getTargetInfo());
8789 }

8798 
8799 void CheckFormatHandler::HandleInvalidLengthModifier(
8800  const analyze_format_string::FormatSpecifier &FS,
8801  const analyze_format_string::ConversionSpecifier &CS,
8802  const char *startSpecifier, unsigned specifierLen, unsigned DiagID) {
8803  using namespace analyze_format_string;
8804 
8805  const LengthModifier &LM = FS.getLengthModifier();
8806  CharSourceRange LMRange = getSpecifierRange(LM.getStart(), LM.getLength());
8807 
8808  // See if we know how to fix this length modifier.
8809  Optional<LengthModifier> FixedLM = FS.getCorrectedLengthModifier();
8810  if (FixedLM) {
8811  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(DiagID) << LM.toString() << CS.toString(),
8812  getLocationOfByte(LM.getStart()),
8813  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
8814  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
8815 
8816  S.Diag(getLocationOfByte(LM.getStart()), diag::note_format_fix_specifier)
8817  << FixedLM->toString()
8818  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(LMRange, FixedLM->toString());
8819 
8820  } else {
8821  FixItHint Hint;
8822  if (DiagID == diag::warn_format_nonsensical_length)
8823  Hint = FixItHint::CreateRemoval(LMRange);
8824 
8825  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(DiagID) << LM.toString() << CS.toString(),
8826  getLocationOfByte(LM.getStart()),
8827  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
8828  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen),
8829  Hint);
8830  }
8831 }

8833 void CheckFormatHandler::HandleNonStandardLengthModifier(
8834  const analyze_format_string::FormatSpecifier &FS,
8835  const char *startSpecifier, unsigned specifierLen) {
8836  using namespace analyze_format_string;
8837 
8838  const LengthModifier &LM = FS.getLengthModifier();
8839  CharSourceRange LMRange = getSpecifierRange(LM.getStart(), LM.getLength());
8840 
8841  // See if we know how to fix this length modifier.
8842  Optional<LengthModifier> FixedLM = FS.getCorrectedLengthModifier();
8843  if (FixedLM) {
8844  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_non_standard)
8845  << LM.toString() << 0,
8846  getLocationOfByte(LM.getStart()),
8847  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
8848  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
8849 
8850  S.Diag(getLocationOfByte(LM.getStart()), diag::note_format_fix_specifier)
8851  << FixedLM->toString()
8852  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(LMRange, FixedLM->toString());
8853 
8854  } else {
8855  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_non_standard)
8856  << LM.toString() << 0,
8857  getLocationOfByte(LM.getStart()),
8858  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
8859  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
8860  }
8861 }

8863 void CheckFormatHandler::HandleNonStandardConversionSpecifier(
8864  const analyze_format_string::ConversionSpecifier &CS,
8865  const char *startSpecifier, unsigned specifierLen) {
8866  using namespace analyze_format_string;
8867 
8868  // See if we know how to fix this conversion specifier.
8869  Optional<ConversionSpecifier> FixedCS = CS.getStandardSpecifier();
8870  if (FixedCS) {
8871  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_non_standard)
8872  << CS.toString() << /*conversion specifier*/1,
8873  getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
8874  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
8875  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
8876 
8877  CharSourceRange CSRange = getSpecifierRange(CS.getStart(), CS.getLength());
8878  S.Diag(getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()), diag::note_format_fix_specifier)
8879  << FixedCS->toString()
8880  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(CSRange, FixedCS->toString());
8881  } else {
8882  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_non_standard)
8883  << CS.toString() << /*conversion specifier*/1,
8884  getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
8885  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
8886  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
8887  }
8888 }

8915 void CheckFormatHandler::HandleNullChar(const char *nullCharacter) {
8916  if (!isa<ObjCStringLiteral>(OrigFormatExpr)) {
8917  // The presence of a null character is likely an error.
8918  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
8919  S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_format_string_contains_null_char),

8921  getFormatStringRange());

8925 // Note that this may return NULL if there was an error parsing or building
8926 // one of the argument expressions.
8927 const Expr *CheckFormatHandler::getDataArg(unsigned i) const {
8928  return Args[FirstDataArg + i];
8929 }
8930 
8931 void CheckFormatHandler::DoneProcessing() {
8932  // Does the number of data arguments exceed the number of
8933  // format conversions in the format string?
8934  if (!HasVAListArg) {
8935  // Find any arguments that weren't covered.
8936  CoveredArgs.flip();
8937  signed notCoveredArg = CoveredArgs.find_first();
8938  if (notCoveredArg >= 0) {
8939  assert((unsigned)notCoveredArg < NumDataArgs);
8940  UncoveredArg.Update(notCoveredArg, OrigFormatExpr);
8941  } else {
8942  UncoveredArg.setAllCovered();
8943  }
8944  }
8945 }
8946 
8947 void UncoveredArgHandler::Diagnose(Sema &S, bool IsFunctionCall,
8948  const Expr *ArgExpr) {
8949  assert(hasUncoveredArg() && DiagnosticExprs.size() > 0 &&
8950  "Invalid state");
8951 
8952  if (!ArgExpr)
8953  return;
8954 
8955  SourceLocation Loc = ArgExpr->getBeginLoc();
8956 
8957  if (S.getSourceManager().isInSystemMacro(Loc))
8958  return;
8959 
8960  PartialDiagnostic PDiag = S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_data_arg_not_used);
8961  for (auto E : DiagnosticExprs)
8962  PDiag << E->getSourceRange();
8963 
8964  CheckFormatHandler::EmitFormatDiagnostic(
8965  S, IsFunctionCall, DiagnosticExprs[0],
8966  PDiag, Loc, /*IsStringLocation*/false,
8967  DiagnosticExprs[0]->getSourceRange());
8968 }
8969 
8970 bool
8971 CheckFormatHandler::HandleInvalidConversionSpecifier(unsigned argIndex,
8972  SourceLocation Loc,
8973  const char *startSpec,
8974  unsigned specifierLen,
8975  const char *csStart,
8976  unsigned csLen) {
8977  bool keepGoing = true;
8978  if (argIndex < NumDataArgs) {
8979  // Consider the argument coverered, even though the specifier doesn't
8980  // make sense.
8981  CoveredArgs.set(argIndex);
8982  }
8983  else {
8984  // If argIndex exceeds the number of data arguments we
8985  // don't issue a warning because that is just a cascade of warnings (and
8986  // they may have intended '%%' anyway). We don't want to continue processing
8987  // the format string after this point, however, as we will like just get
8988  // gibberish when trying to match arguments.
8989  keepGoing = false;
8990  }
8991 
8992  StringRef Specifier(csStart, csLen);
8993 
8994  // If the specifier in non-printable, it could be the first byte of a UTF-8
8995  // sequence. In that case, print the UTF-8 code point. If not, print the byte
8996  // hex value.
8997  std::string CodePointStr;
8998  if (!llvm::sys::locale::isPrint(*csStart)) {
8999  llvm::UTF32 CodePoint;
9000  const llvm::UTF8 **B = reinterpret_cast<const llvm::UTF8 **>(&csStart);
9001  const llvm::UTF8 *E =
9002  reinterpret_cast<const llvm::UTF8 *>(csStart + csLen);
9003  llvm::ConversionResult Result =
9004  llvm::convertUTF8Sequence(B, E, &CodePoint, llvm::strictConversion);
9005 
9006  if (Result != llvm::conversionOK) {
9007  unsigned char FirstChar = *csStart;
9008  CodePoint = (llvm::UTF32)FirstChar;
9009  }
9010 
9011  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(CodePointStr);
9012  if (CodePoint < 256)
9013  OS << "\\x" << llvm::format("%02x", CodePoint);
9014  else if (CodePoint <= 0xFFFF)
9015  OS << "\\u" << llvm::format("%04x", CodePoint);
9016  else
9017  OS << "\\U" << llvm::format("%08x", CodePoint);
9018  OS.flush();
9019  Specifier = CodePointStr;
9020  }
9021 
9022  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9023  S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_invalid_conversion) << Specifier, Loc,
9024  /*IsStringLocation*/ true, getSpecifierRange(startSpec, specifierLen));
9025 
9026  return keepGoing;
9027 }
9028 
9029 void
9030 CheckFormatHandler::HandlePositionalNonpositionalArgs(SourceLocation Loc,
9031  const char *startSpec,
9032  unsigned specifierLen) {
9033  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9034  S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_mix_positional_nonpositional_args),
9035  Loc, /*isStringLoc*/true, getSpecifierRange(startSpec, specifierLen));
9036 }
9037 
9038 bool
9039 CheckFormatHandler::CheckNumArgs(
9040  const analyze_format_string::FormatSpecifier &FS,
9041  const analyze_format_string::ConversionSpecifier &CS,
9042  const char *startSpecifier, unsigned specifierLen, unsigned argIndex) {
9043 
9044  if (argIndex >= NumDataArgs) {
9045  PartialDiagnostic PDiag = FS.usesPositionalArg()
9046  ? (S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_positional_arg_exceeds_data_args)
9047  << (argIndex+1) << NumDataArgs)
9048  : S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_insufficient_data_args);
9049  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9050  PDiag, getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()), /*IsStringLocation*/true,
9051  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9052 
9053  // Since more arguments than conversion tokens are given, by extension
9054  // all arguments are covered, so mark this as so.
9055  UncoveredArg.setAllCovered();
9056  return false;
9057  }
9058  return true;
9059 }

9061 template<typename Range>
9062 void CheckFormatHandler::EmitFormatDiagnostic(PartialDiagnostic PDiag,
9063  SourceLocation Loc,
9064  bool IsStringLocation,
9065  Range StringRange,
9066  ArrayRef<FixItHint> FixIt) {
9067  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S, inFunctionCall, Args[FormatIdx], PDiag,
9068  Loc, IsStringLocation, StringRange, FixIt);
9069 }
9070 
9071 /// If the format string is not within the function call, emit a note
9072 /// so that the function call and string are in diagnostic messages.
9073 ///
9074 /// \param InFunctionCall if true, the format string is within the function
9075 /// call and only one diagnostic message will be produced. Otherwise, an
9076 /// extra note will be emitted pointing to location of the format string.
9077 ///
9078 /// \param ArgumentExpr the expression that is passed as the format string
9079 /// argument in the function call. Used for getting locations when two
9080 /// diagnostics are emitted.
9081 ///
9082 /// \param PDiag the callee should already have provided any strings for the
9083 /// diagnostic message. This function only adds locations and fixits
9084 /// to diagnostics.
9085 ///
9086 /// \param Loc primary location for diagnostic. If two diagnostics are
9087 /// required, one will be at Loc and a new SourceLocation will be created for
9088 /// the other one.
9089 ///
9090 /// \param IsStringLocation if true, Loc points to the format string should be
9091 /// used for the note. Otherwise, Loc points to the argument list and will
9092 /// be used with PDiag.
9093 ///
9094 /// \param StringRange some or all of the string to highlight. This is
9095 /// templated so it can accept either a CharSourceRange or a SourceRange.
9096 ///
9097 /// \param FixIt optional fix it hint for the format string.
9098 template <typename Range>
9099 void CheckFormatHandler::EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9100  Sema &S, bool InFunctionCall, const Expr *ArgumentExpr,
9101  const PartialDiagnostic &PDiag, SourceLocation Loc, bool IsStringLocation,
9102  Range StringRange, ArrayRef<FixItHint> FixIt) {
9103  if (InFunctionCall) {
9104  const Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder &D = S.Diag(Loc, PDiag);
9105  D << StringRange;
9106  D << FixIt;
9107  } else {
9108  S.Diag(IsStringLocation ? ArgumentExpr->getExprLoc() : Loc, PDiag)
9109  << ArgumentExpr->getSourceRange();
9110 
9111  const Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder &Note =
9112  S.Diag(IsStringLocation ? Loc : StringRange.getBegin(),
9113  diag::note_format_string_defined);
9114 
9115  Note << StringRange;
9116  Note << FixIt;
9117  }
9118 }

9193 bool CheckPrintfHandler::HandleInvalidPrintfConversionSpecifier(
9194  const analyze_printf::PrintfSpecifier &FS,
9195  const char *startSpecifier,
9196  unsigned specifierLen) {

9198  FS.getConversionSpecifier();
9199 
9200  return HandleInvalidConversionSpecifier(FS.getArgIndex(),
9201  getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
9202  startSpecifier, specifierLen,
9203  CS.getStart(), CS.getLength());
9204 }

9209 
9210 bool CheckPrintfHandler::HandleAmount(
9211  const analyze_format_string::OptionalAmount &Amt,
9212  unsigned k, const char *startSpecifier,
9213  unsigned specifierLen) {
9214  if (Amt.hasDataArgument()) {
9215  if (!HasVAListArg) {
9216  unsigned argIndex = Amt.getArgIndex();
9217  if (argIndex >= NumDataArgs) {
9218  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_asterisk_missing_arg)
9219  << k,
9220  getLocationOfByte(Amt.getStart()),
9221  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
9222  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9223  // Don't do any more checking. We will just emit
9224  // spurious errors.
9225  return false;
9226  }
9227 
9228  // Type check the data argument. It should be an 'int'.
9229  // Although not in conformance with C99, we also allow the argument to be
9230  // an 'unsigned int' as that is a reasonably safe case. GCC also
9231  // doesn't emit a warning for that case.
9232  CoveredArgs.set(argIndex);
9233  const Expr *Arg = getDataArg(argIndex);
9234  if (!Arg)
9235  return false;
9236 
9237  QualType T = Arg->getType();
9238 
9239  const analyze_printf::ArgType &AT = Amt.getArgType(S.Context);
9240  assert(AT.isValid());
9241 
9242  if (!AT.matchesType(S.Context, T)) {
9243  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_asterisk_wrong_type)
9244  << k << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context)
9245  << T << Arg->getSourceRange(),
9246  getLocationOfByte(Amt.getStart()),
9247  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
9248  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9249  // Don't do any more checking. We will just emit
9250  // spurious errors.
9251  return false;
9252  }
9253  }
9254  }
9255  return true;
9256 }
9257 
9258 void CheckPrintfHandler::HandleInvalidAmount(
9259  const analyze_printf::PrintfSpecifier &FS,
9260  const analyze_printf::OptionalAmount &Amt,
9261  unsigned type,
9262  const char *startSpecifier,
9263  unsigned specifierLen) {
9264  const analyze_printf::PrintfConversionSpecifier &CS =
9265  FS.getConversionSpecifier();
9266 
9267  FixItHint fixit =
9268  Amt.getHowSpecified() == analyze_printf::OptionalAmount::Constant
9269  ? FixItHint::CreateRemoval(getSpecifierRange(Amt.getStart(),
9270  Amt.getConstantLength()))
9271  : FixItHint();
9272 
9273  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_nonsensical_optional_amount)
9274  << type << CS.toString(),
9275  getLocationOfByte(Amt.getStart()),
9276  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
9277  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen),
9278  fixit);
9279 }

9281 void CheckPrintfHandler::HandleFlag(const analyze_printf::PrintfSpecifier &FS,
9282  const analyze_printf::OptionalFlag &flag,
9283  const char *startSpecifier,
9284  unsigned specifierLen) {
9285  // Warn about pointless flag with a fixit removal.
9286  const analyze_printf::PrintfConversionSpecifier &CS =
9287  FS.getConversionSpecifier();
9288  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_nonsensical_flag)
9289  << flag.toString() << CS.toString(),
9290  getLocationOfByte(flag.getPosition()),
9291  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
9292  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen),
9293  FixItHint::CreateRemoval(
9294  getSpecifierRange(flag.getPosition(), 1)));
9295 }

9333 void CheckPrintfHandler::HandleObjCFlagsWithNonObjCConversion(
9334  const char *flagsStart, const char *flagsEnd, const char *conversionPosition) {
9335  // Warn about using '[...]' without a '@' conversion.
9336  auto Range = getSpecifierRange(flagsStart, flagsEnd - flagsStart + 1);
9337  auto diag = diag::warn_printf_ObjCflags_without_ObjCConversion;
9338  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag) << StringRef(conversionPosition, 1),
9339  getLocationOfByte(conversionPosition),
9340  /*IsStringLocation*/true,
9341  Range, FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Range));
