9343 
9344 // Determines if the specified is a C++ class or struct containing
9345 // a member with the specified name and kind (e.g. a CXXMethodDecl named
9346 // "c_str()").
9347 template<typename MemberKind>
9348 static llvm::SmallPtrSet<MemberKind*, 1>
9349 CXXRecordMembersNamed(StringRef Name, Sema &S, QualType Ty) {
9350  const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
9351  llvm::SmallPtrSet<MemberKind*, 1> Results;
9352 
9353  if (!RT)
9354  return Results;
9355  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
9356  if (!RD || !RD->getDefinition())
9357  return Results;
9358 
9359  LookupResult R(S, &S.Context.Idents.get(Name), SourceLocation(),
9360  Sema::LookupMemberName);
9361  R.suppressDiagnostics();
9362 
9363  // We just need to include all members of the right kind turned up by the
9364  // filter, at this point.
9365  if (S.LookupQualifiedName(R, RT->getDecl()))
9366  for (LookupResult::iterator I = R.begin(), E = R.end(); I != E; ++I) {
9367  NamedDecl *decl = (*I)->getUnderlyingDecl();
9368  if (MemberKind *FK = dyn_cast<MemberKind>(decl))
9369  Results.insert(FK);
9370  }
9371  return Results;
9372 }
9373 
9374 /// Check if we could call '.c_str()' on an object.
9375 ///
9376 /// FIXME: This returns the wrong results in some cases (if cv-qualifiers don't
9377 /// allow the call, or if it would be ambiguous).
9378 bool Sema::hasCStrMethod(const Expr *E) {
9379  using MethodSet = llvm::SmallPtrSet<CXXMethodDecl *, 1>;
9380 
9381  MethodSet Results =
9382  CXXRecordMembersNamed<CXXMethodDecl>("c_str", *this, E->getType());
9383  for (MethodSet::iterator MI = Results.begin(), ME = Results.end();
9384  MI != ME; ++MI)
9385  if ((*MI)->getMinRequiredArguments() == 0)
9386  return true;
9387  return false;
9388 }
9389 
9390 // Check if a (w)string was passed when a (w)char* was needed, and offer a
9391 // better diagnostic if so. AT is assumed to be valid.
9392 // Returns true when a c_str() conversion method is found.
9393 bool CheckPrintfHandler::checkForCStrMembers(
9394  const analyze_printf::ArgType &AT, const Expr *E) {
9395  using MethodSet = llvm::SmallPtrSet<CXXMethodDecl *, 1>;
9396 
9397  MethodSet Results =
9398  CXXRecordMembersNamed<CXXMethodDecl>("c_str", S, E->getType());
9399 
9400  for (MethodSet::iterator MI = Results.begin(), ME = Results.end();
9401  MI != ME; ++MI) {
9402  const CXXMethodDecl *Method = *MI;
9403  if (Method->getMinRequiredArguments() == 0 &&
9404  AT.matchesType(S.Context, Method->getReturnType())) {
9405  // FIXME: Suggest parens if the expression needs them.
9406  SourceLocation EndLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(E->getEndLoc());
9407  S.Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_printf_c_str)
9408  << "c_str()" << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EndLoc, ".c_str()");
9409  return true;
9410  }
9411  }
9412 
9413  return false;
9414 }
9415 
9416 bool CheckPrintfHandler::HandlePrintfSpecifier(
9417  const analyze_printf::PrintfSpecifier &FS, const char *startSpecifier,
9418  unsigned specifierLen, const TargetInfo &Target) {
9419  using namespace analyze_format_string;
9420  using namespace analyze_printf;
9421 
9422  const PrintfConversionSpecifier &CS = FS.getConversionSpecifier();
9423 
9424  if (FS.consumesDataArgument()) {
9425  if (atFirstArg) {
9426  atFirstArg = false;
9427  usesPositionalArgs = FS.usesPositionalArg();
9428  }
9429  else if (usesPositionalArgs != FS.usesPositionalArg()) {
9430  HandlePositionalNonpositionalArgs(getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
9431  startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9432  return false;
9433  }
9434  }
9435 
9436  // First check if the field width, precision, and conversion specifier
9437  // have matching data arguments.
9438  if (!HandleAmount(FS.getFieldWidth(), /* field width */ 0,
9439  startSpecifier, specifierLen)) {
9440  return false;
9441  }
9442 
9443  if (!HandleAmount(FS.getPrecision(), /* precision */ 1,
9444  startSpecifier, specifierLen)) {
9445  return false;
9446  }
9447 
9448  if (!CS.consumesDataArgument()) {
9449  // FIXME: Technically specifying a precision or field width here
9450  // makes no sense. Worth issuing a warning at some point.
9451  return true;
9452  }
9453 
9454  // Consume the argument.
9455  unsigned argIndex = FS.getArgIndex();
9456  if (argIndex < NumDataArgs) {
9457  // The check to see if the argIndex is valid will come later.
9458  // We set the bit here because we may exit early from this
9459  // function if we encounter some other error.
9460  CoveredArgs.set(argIndex);
9461  }
9462 
9463  // FreeBSD kernel extensions.
9464  if (CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::FreeBSDbArg ||
9465  CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::FreeBSDDArg) {
9466  // We need at least two arguments.
9467  if (!CheckNumArgs(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen, argIndex + 1))
9468  return false;
9469 
9470  // Claim the second argument.
9471  CoveredArgs.set(argIndex + 1);
9472 
9473  // Type check the first argument (int for %b, pointer for %D)
9474  const Expr *Ex = getDataArg(argIndex);
9475  const analyze_printf::ArgType &AT =
9476  (CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::FreeBSDbArg) ?
9477  ArgType(S.Context.IntTy) : ArgType::CPointerTy;
9478  if (AT.isValid() && !AT.matchesType(S.Context, Ex->getType()))
9479  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9480  S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch)
9481  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << Ex->getType()
9482  << false << Ex->getSourceRange(),
9483  Ex->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9484  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9485 
9486  // Type check the second argument (char * for both %b and %D)
9487  Ex = getDataArg(argIndex + 1);
9488  const analyze_printf::ArgType &AT2 = ArgType::CStrTy;
9489  if (AT2.isValid() && !AT2.matchesType(S.Context, Ex->getType()))
9490  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9491  S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch)
9492  << AT2.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << Ex->getType()
9493  << false << Ex->getSourceRange(),
9494  Ex->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9495  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9496 
9497  return true;
9498  }
9499 
9500  // Check for using an Objective-C specific conversion specifier
9501  // in a non-ObjC literal.
9502  if (!allowsObjCArg() && CS.isObjCArg()) {
9503  return HandleInvalidPrintfConversionSpecifier(FS, startSpecifier,
9504  specifierLen);
9505  }
9506 
9507  // %P can only be used with os_log.
9508  if (FSType != Sema::FST_OSLog && CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::PArg) {
9509  return HandleInvalidPrintfConversionSpecifier(FS, startSpecifier,
9510  specifierLen);
9511  }
9512 
9513  // %n is not allowed with os_log.
9514  if (FSType == Sema::FST_OSLog && CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::nArg) {
9515  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_os_log_format_narg),
9516  getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
9517  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9518  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9519 
9520  return true;
9521  }
9522 
9523  // Only scalars are allowed for os_trace.
9524  if (FSType == Sema::FST_OSTrace &&
9525  (CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::PArg ||
9526  CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::sArg ||
9527  CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::ObjCObjArg)) {
9528  return HandleInvalidPrintfConversionSpecifier(FS, startSpecifier,
9529  specifierLen);
9530  }
9531 
9532  // Check for use of public/private annotation outside of os_log().
9533  if (FSType != Sema::FST_OSLog) {
9534  if (FS.isPublic().isSet()) {
9535  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_invalid_annotation)
9536  << "public",
9537  getLocationOfByte(FS.isPublic().getPosition()),
9538  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9539  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9540  }
9541  if (FS.isPrivate().isSet()) {
9542  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_invalid_annotation)
9543  << "private",
9544  getLocationOfByte(FS.isPrivate().getPosition()),
9545  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9546  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9547  }
9548  }
9549 
9550  const llvm::Triple &Triple = Target.getTriple();
9551  if (CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::nArg &&
9552  (Triple.isAndroid() || Triple.isOSFuchsia())) {
9553  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_narg_not_supported),
9554  getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
9555  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9556  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9557  }
9558 
9559  // Check for invalid use of field width
9560  if (!FS.hasValidFieldWidth()) {
9561  HandleInvalidAmount(FS, FS.getFieldWidth(), /* field width */ 0,
9562  startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9563  }
9564 
9565  // Check for invalid use of precision
9566  if (!FS.hasValidPrecision()) {
9567  HandleInvalidAmount(FS, FS.getPrecision(), /* precision */ 1,
9568  startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9569  }
9570 
9571  // Precision is mandatory for %P specifier.
9572  if (CS.getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::PArg &&
9573  FS.getPrecision().getHowSpecified() == OptionalAmount::NotSpecified) {
9574  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_P_no_precision),
9575  getLocationOfByte(startSpecifier),
9576  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
9577  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
9578  }
9579 
9580  // Check each flag does not conflict with any other component.
9581  if (!FS.hasValidThousandsGroupingPrefix())
9582  HandleFlag(FS, FS.hasThousandsGrouping(), startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9583  if (!FS.hasValidLeadingZeros())
9584  HandleFlag(FS, FS.hasLeadingZeros(), startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9585  if (!FS.hasValidPlusPrefix())
9586  HandleFlag(FS, FS.hasPlusPrefix(), startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9587  if (!FS.hasValidSpacePrefix())
9588  HandleFlag(FS, FS.hasSpacePrefix(), startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9589  if (!FS.hasValidAlternativeForm())
9590  HandleFlag(FS, FS.hasAlternativeForm(), startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9591  if (!FS.hasValidLeftJustified())
9592  HandleFlag(FS, FS.isLeftJustified(), startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9593 
9594  // Check that flags are not ignored by another flag
9595  if (FS.hasSpacePrefix() && FS.hasPlusPrefix()) // ' ' ignored by '+'
9596  HandleIgnoredFlag(FS, FS.hasSpacePrefix(), FS.hasPlusPrefix(),
9597  startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9598  if (FS.hasLeadingZeros() && FS.isLeftJustified()) // '0' ignored by '-'
9599  HandleIgnoredFlag(FS, FS.hasLeadingZeros(), FS.isLeftJustified(),
9600  startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9601 
9602  // Check the length modifier is valid with the given conversion specifier.
9603  if (!FS.hasValidLengthModifier(S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo(),
9604  S.getLangOpts()))
9605  HandleInvalidLengthModifier(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen,
9606  diag::warn_format_nonsensical_length);
9607  else if (!FS.hasStandardLengthModifier())
9608  HandleNonStandardLengthModifier(FS, startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9609  else if (!FS.hasStandardLengthConversionCombination())
9610  HandleInvalidLengthModifier(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen,
9611  diag::warn_format_non_standard_conversion_spec);
9612 
9613  if (!FS.hasStandardConversionSpecifier(S.getLangOpts()))
9614  HandleNonStandardConversionSpecifier(CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen);
9615 
9616  // The remaining checks depend on the data arguments.
9617  if (HasVAListArg)
9618  return true;
9619 
9620  if (!CheckNumArgs(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen, argIndex))
9621  return false;
9622 
9623  const Expr *Arg = getDataArg(argIndex);
9624  if (!Arg)
9625  return true;
9626 
9627  return checkFormatExpr(FS, startSpecifier, specifierLen, Arg);
9628 }
9629 
9630 static bool requiresParensToAddCast(const Expr *E) {
9631  // FIXME: We should have a general way to reason about operator
9632  // precedence and whether parens are actually needed here.
9633  // Take care of a few common cases where they aren't.
9634  const Expr *Inside = E->IgnoreImpCasts();
9635  if (const PseudoObjectExpr *POE = dyn_cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(Inside))
9636  Inside = POE->getSyntacticForm()->IgnoreImpCasts();
9637 
9638  switch (Inside->getStmtClass()) {
9639  case Stmt::ArraySubscriptExprClass:
9640  case Stmt::CallExprClass:
9641  case Stmt::CharacterLiteralClass:
9642  case Stmt::CXXBoolLiteralExprClass:
9643  case Stmt::DeclRefExprClass:
9644  case Stmt::FloatingLiteralClass:
9645  case Stmt::IntegerLiteralClass:
9646  case Stmt::MemberExprClass:
9647  case Stmt::ObjCArrayLiteralClass:
9648  case Stmt::ObjCBoolLiteralExprClass:
9649  case Stmt::ObjCBoxedExprClass:
9650  case Stmt::ObjCDictionaryLiteralClass:
9651  case Stmt::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
9652  case Stmt::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
9653  case Stmt::ObjCMessageExprClass:
9654  case Stmt::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
9655  case Stmt::ObjCStringLiteralClass:
9656  case Stmt::ObjCSubscriptRefExprClass:
9657  case Stmt::ParenExprClass:
9658  case Stmt::StringLiteralClass:
9659  case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass:
9660  return false;
9661  default:
9662  return true;
9663  }
9664 }
9665 
9666 static std::pair<QualType, StringRef>
9667 shouldNotPrintDirectly(const ASTContext &Context,
9668  QualType IntendedTy,
9669  const Expr *E) {
9670  // Use a 'while' to peel off layers of typedefs.
9671  QualType TyTy = IntendedTy;
9672  while (const TypedefType *UserTy = TyTy->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
9673  StringRef Name = UserTy->getDecl()->getName();
9674  QualType CastTy = llvm::StringSwitch<QualType>(Name)
9675  .Case("CFIndex", Context.getNSIntegerType())
9676  .Case("NSInteger", Context.getNSIntegerType())
9677  .Case("NSUInteger", Context.getNSUIntegerType())
9678  .Case("SInt32", Context.IntTy)
9679  .Case("UInt32", Context.UnsignedIntTy)
9680  .Default(QualType());
9681 
9682  if (!CastTy.isNull())
9683  return std::make_pair(CastTy, Name);
9684 
9685  TyTy = UserTy->desugar();
9686  }
9687 
9688  // Strip parens if necessary.
9689  if (const ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E))
9690  return shouldNotPrintDirectly(Context,
9691  PE->getSubExpr()->getType(),
9692  PE->getSubExpr());
9693 
9694  // If this is a conditional expression, then its result type is constructed
9695  // via usual arithmetic conversions and thus there might be no necessary
9696  // typedef sugar there. Recurse to operands to check for NSInteger &
9697  // Co. usage condition.
9698  if (const ConditionalOperator *CO = dyn_cast<ConditionalOperator>(E)) {
9699  QualType TrueTy, FalseTy;
9700  StringRef TrueName, FalseName;
9701 
9702  std::tie(TrueTy, TrueName) =
9703  shouldNotPrintDirectly(Context,
9704  CO->getTrueExpr()->getType(),
9705  CO->getTrueExpr());
9706  std::tie(FalseTy, FalseName) =
9707  shouldNotPrintDirectly(Context,
9708  CO->getFalseExpr()->getType(),
9709  CO->getFalseExpr());
9710 
9711  if (TrueTy == FalseTy)
9712  return std::make_pair(TrueTy, TrueName);
9713  else if (TrueTy.isNull())
9714  return std::make_pair(FalseTy, FalseName);
9715  else if (FalseTy.isNull())
9716  return std::make_pair(TrueTy, TrueName);
9717  }
9718 
9719  return std::make_pair(QualType(), StringRef());
9720 }
9721 
9722 /// Return true if \p ICE is an implicit argument promotion of an arithmetic
9723 /// type. Bit-field 'promotions' from a higher ranked type to a lower ranked
9724 /// type do not count.
9725 static bool
9726 isArithmeticArgumentPromotion(Sema &S, const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE) {
9727  QualType From = ICE->getSubExpr()->getType();
9728  QualType To = ICE->getType();
9729  // It's an integer promotion if the destination type is the promoted
9730  // source type.
9731  if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_IntegralCast &&
9732  From->isPromotableIntegerType() &&
9733  S.Context.getPromotedIntegerType(From) == To)
9734  return true;
9735  // Look through vector types, since we do default argument promotion for
9736  // those in OpenCL.
9737  if (const auto *VecTy = From->getAs<ExtVectorType>())
9738  From = VecTy->getElementType();
9739  if (const auto *VecTy = To->getAs<ExtVectorType>())
9740  To = VecTy->getElementType();
9741  // It's a floating promotion if the source type is a lower rank.
9742  return ICE->getCastKind() == CK_FloatingCast &&
9743  S.Context.getFloatingTypeOrder(From, To) < 0;
9744 }
9745 
9746 bool
9747 CheckPrintfHandler::checkFormatExpr(const analyze_printf::PrintfSpecifier &FS,
9748  const char *StartSpecifier,
9749  unsigned SpecifierLen,
9750  const Expr *E) {
9751  using namespace analyze_format_string;
9752  using namespace analyze_printf;
9753 
9754  // Now type check the data expression that matches the
9755  // format specifier.
9756  const analyze_printf::ArgType &AT = FS.getArgType(S.Context, isObjCContext());
9757  if (!AT.isValid())
9758  return true;
9759 
9760  QualType ExprTy = E->getType();
9761  while (const TypeOfExprType *TET = dyn_cast<TypeOfExprType>(ExprTy)) {
9762  ExprTy = TET->getUnderlyingExpr()->getType();
9763  }
9764 
9765  // Diagnose attempts to print a boolean value as a character. Unlike other
9766  // -Wformat diagnostics, this is fine from a type perspective, but it still
9767  // doesn't make sense.
9768  if (FS.getConversionSpecifier().getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::cArg &&
9769  E->isKnownToHaveBooleanValue()) {
9770  const CharSourceRange &CSR =
9771  getSpecifierRange(StartSpecifier, SpecifierLen);
9772  SmallString<4> FSString;
9773  llvm::raw_svector_ostream os(FSString);
9774  FS.toString(os);
9775  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_bool_as_character)
9776  << FSString,
9777  E->getExprLoc(), false, CSR);
9778  return true;
9779  }
9780 
9781  analyze_printf::ArgType::MatchKind Match = AT.matchesType(S.Context, ExprTy);
9782  if (Match == analyze_printf::ArgType::Match)
9783  return true;
9784 
9785  // Look through argument promotions for our error message's reported type.
9786  // This includes the integral and floating promotions, but excludes array
9787  // and function pointer decay (seeing that an argument intended to be a
9788  // string has type 'char [6]' is probably more confusing than 'char *') and
9789  // certain bitfield promotions (bitfields can be 'demoted' to a lesser type).
9790  if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
9791  if (isArithmeticArgumentPromotion(S, ICE)) {
9792  E = ICE->getSubExpr();
9793  ExprTy = E->getType();
9794 
9795  // Check if we didn't match because of an implicit cast from a 'char'
9796  // or 'short' to an 'int'. This is done because printf is a varargs
9797  // function.
9798  if (ICE->getType() == S.Context.IntTy ||
9799  ICE->getType() == S.Context.UnsignedIntTy) {
9800  // All further checking is done on the subexpression
9801  const analyze_printf::ArgType::MatchKind ImplicitMatch =
9802  AT.matchesType(S.Context, ExprTy);
9803  if (ImplicitMatch == analyze_printf::ArgType::Match)
9804  return true;
9805  if (ImplicitMatch == ArgType::NoMatchPedantic ||
9806  ImplicitMatch == ArgType::NoMatchTypeConfusion)
9807  Match = ImplicitMatch;
9808  }
9809  }
9810  } else if (const CharacterLiteral *CL = dyn_cast<CharacterLiteral>(E)) {
9811  // Special case for 'a', which has type 'int' in C.
9812  // Note, however, that we do /not/ want to treat multibyte constants like
9813  // 'MooV' as characters! This form is deprecated but still exists. In
9814  // addition, don't treat expressions as of type 'char' if one byte length
9815  // modifier is provided.
9816  if (ExprTy == S.Context.IntTy &&
9817  FS.getLengthModifier().getKind() != LengthModifier::AsChar)
9818  if (llvm::isUIntN(S.Context.getCharWidth(), CL->getValue()))
9819  ExprTy = S.Context.CharTy;
9820  }
9821 
9822  // Look through enums to their underlying type.
9823  bool IsEnum = false;
9824  if (auto EnumTy = ExprTy->getAs<EnumType>()) {
9825  ExprTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
9826  IsEnum = true;
9827  }
9828 
9829  // %C in an Objective-C context prints a unichar, not a wchar_t.
9830  // If the argument is an integer of some kind, believe the %C and suggest
9831  // a cast instead of changing the conversion specifier.
9832  QualType IntendedTy = ExprTy;
9833  if (isObjCContext() &&
9834  FS.getConversionSpecifier().getKind() == ConversionSpecifier::CArg) {
9835  if (ExprTy->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType() &&
9836  !ExprTy->isCharType()) {
9837  // 'unichar' is defined as a typedef of unsigned short, but we should
9838  // prefer using the typedef if it is visible.
9839  IntendedTy = S.Context.UnsignedShortTy;
9840 
9841  // While we are here, check if the value is an IntegerLiteral that happens
9842  // to be within the valid range.
9843  if (const IntegerLiteral *IL = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(E)) {
9844  const llvm::APInt &V = IL->getValue();
9845  if (V.getActiveBits() <= S.Context.getTypeSize(IntendedTy))
9846  return true;
9847  }
9848 
9849  LookupResult Result(S, &S.Context.Idents.get("unichar"), E->getBeginLoc(),
9850  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
9851  if (S.LookupName(Result, S.getCurScope())) {
9852  NamedDecl *ND = Result.getFoundDecl();
9853  if (TypedefNameDecl *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(ND))
9854  if (TD->getUnderlyingType() == IntendedTy)
9855  IntendedTy = S.Context.getTypedefType(TD);
9856  }
9857  }
9858  }
9859 
9860  // Special-case some of Darwin's platform-independence types by suggesting
9861  // casts to primitive types that are known to be large enough.
9862  bool ShouldNotPrintDirectly = false; StringRef CastTyName;
9863  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
9864  QualType CastTy;
9865  std::tie(CastTy, CastTyName) = shouldNotPrintDirectly(S.Context, IntendedTy, E);
9866  if (!CastTy.isNull()) {
9867  // %zi/%zu and %td/%tu are OK to use for NSInteger/NSUInteger of type int
9868  // (long in ASTContext). Only complain to pedants.
9869  if ((CastTyName == "NSInteger" || CastTyName == "NSUInteger") &&
9870  (AT.isSizeT() || AT.isPtrdiffT()) &&
9871  AT.matchesType(S.Context, CastTy))
9872  Match = ArgType::NoMatchPedantic;
9873  IntendedTy = CastTy;
9874  ShouldNotPrintDirectly = true;
9875  }
9876  }
9877 
9878  // We may be able to offer a FixItHint if it is a supported type.
9879  PrintfSpecifier fixedFS = FS;
9880  bool Success =
9881  fixedFS.fixType(IntendedTy, S.getLangOpts(), S.Context, isObjCContext());
9882 
9883  if (Success) {
9884  // Get the fix string from the fixed format specifier
9885  SmallString<16> buf;
9886  llvm::raw_svector_ostream os(buf);
9887  fixedFS.toString(os);
9888 
9889  CharSourceRange SpecRange = getSpecifierRange(StartSpecifier, SpecifierLen);
9890 
9891  if (IntendedTy == ExprTy && !ShouldNotPrintDirectly) {
9892  unsigned Diag;
9893  switch (Match) {
9894  case ArgType::Match: llvm_unreachable("expected non-matching");
9895  case ArgType::NoMatchPedantic:
9896  Diag = diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch_pedantic;
9897  break;
9898  case ArgType::NoMatchTypeConfusion:
9899  Diag = diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch_confusion;
9900  break;
9901  case ArgType::NoMatch:
9902  Diag = diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch;
9903  break;
9904  }
9905 
9906  // In this case, the specifier is wrong and should be changed to match
9907  // the argument.
9908  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(Diag)
9909  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context)
9910  << IntendedTy << IsEnum << E->getSourceRange(),
9911  E->getBeginLoc(),
9912  /*IsStringLocation*/ false, SpecRange,
9913  FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SpecRange, os.str()));
9914  } else {
9915  // The canonical type for formatting this value is different from the
9916  // actual type of the expression. (This occurs, for example, with Darwin's
9917  // NSInteger on 32-bit platforms, where it is typedef'd as 'int', but
9918  // should be printed as 'long' for 64-bit compatibility.)
9919  // Rather than emitting a normal format/argument mismatch, we want to
9920  // add a cast to the recommended type (and correct the format string
9921  // if necessary).
9922  SmallString<16> CastBuf;
9923  llvm::raw_svector_ostream CastFix(CastBuf);
9924  CastFix << "(";
9925  IntendedTy.print(CastFix, S.Context.getPrintingPolicy());
9926  CastFix << ")";
9927 
9928  SmallVector<FixItHint,4> Hints;
9929  if (!AT.matchesType(S.Context, IntendedTy) || ShouldNotPrintDirectly)
9930  Hints.push_back(FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SpecRange, os.str()));
9931 
9932  if (const CStyleCastExpr *CCast = dyn_cast<CStyleCastExpr>(E)) {
9933  // If there's already a cast present, just replace it.
9934  SourceRange CastRange(CCast->getLParenLoc(), CCast->getRParenLoc());
9935  Hints.push_back(FixItHint::CreateReplacement(CastRange, CastFix.str()));
9936 
9937  } else if (!requiresParensToAddCast(E)) {
9938  // If the expression has high enough precedence,
9939  // just write the C-style cast.
9940  Hints.push_back(
9941  FixItHint::CreateInsertion(E->getBeginLoc(), CastFix.str()));
9942  } else {
9943  // Otherwise, add parens around the expression as well as the cast.
9944  CastFix << "(";
9945  Hints.push_back(
9946  FixItHint::CreateInsertion(E->getBeginLoc(), CastFix.str()));
9947 
9948  SourceLocation After = S.getLocForEndOfToken(E->getEndLoc());
9949  Hints.push_back(FixItHint::CreateInsertion(After, ")"));
9950  }
9951 
9952  if (ShouldNotPrintDirectly) {
9953  // The expression has a type that should not be printed directly.
9954  // We extract the name from the typedef because we don't want to show
9955  // the underlying type in the diagnostic.
9956  StringRef Name;
9957  if (const TypedefType *TypedefTy = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(ExprTy))
9958  Name = TypedefTy->getDecl()->getName();
9959  else
9960  Name = CastTyName;
9961  unsigned Diag = Match == ArgType::NoMatchPedantic
9962  ? diag::warn_format_argument_needs_cast_pedantic
9963  : diag::warn_format_argument_needs_cast;
9964  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(Diag) << Name << IntendedTy << IsEnum
9965  << E->getSourceRange(),
9966  E->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation=*/false,
9967  SpecRange, Hints);
9968  } else {
9969  // In this case, the expression could be printed using a different
9970  // specifier, but we've decided that the specifier is probably correct
9971  // and we should cast instead. Just use the normal warning message.
9972  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
9973  S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch)
9974  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << ExprTy << IsEnum
9975  << E->getSourceRange(),
9976  E->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation*/ false, SpecRange, Hints);
9977  }
9978  }
9979  } else {
9980  const CharSourceRange &CSR = getSpecifierRange(StartSpecifier,
9981  SpecifierLen);
9982  // Since the warning for passing non-POD types to variadic functions
9983  // was deferred until now, we emit a warning for non-POD
9984  // arguments here.
9985  switch (S.isValidVarArgType(ExprTy)) {
9986  case Sema::VAK_Valid:
9987  case Sema::VAK_ValidInCXX11: {
9988  unsigned Diag;
9989  switch (Match) {
9990  case ArgType::Match: llvm_unreachable("expected non-matching");
9991  case ArgType::NoMatchPedantic:
9992  Diag = diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch_pedantic;
9993  break;
9994  case ArgType::NoMatchTypeConfusion:
9995  Diag = diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch_confusion;
9996  break;
9997  case ArgType::NoMatch:
9998  Diag = diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch;
9999  break;
10000  }
10001 
10002  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
10003  S.PDiag(Diag) << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << ExprTy
10004  << IsEnum << CSR << E->getSourceRange(),
10005  E->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation*/ false, CSR);
10006  break;
10007  }
10008  case Sema::VAK_Undefined:
10009  case Sema::VAK_MSVCUndefined:
10010  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_non_pod_vararg_with_format_string)
10011  << S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 << ExprTy
10012  << CallType
10013  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << CSR
10014  << E->getSourceRange(),
10015  E->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation*/ false, CSR);
10016  checkForCStrMembers(AT, E);
10017  break;
10018 
10019  case Sema::VAK_Invalid:
10020  if (ExprTy->isObjCObjectType())
10021  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
10022  S.PDiag(diag::err_cannot_pass_objc_interface_to_vararg_format)
10023  << S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 << ExprTy << CallType
10024  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << CSR
10025  << E->getSourceRange(),
10026  E->getBeginLoc(), /*IsStringLocation*/ false, CSR);
10027  else
10028  // FIXME: If this is an initializer list, suggest removing the braces
10029  // or inserting a cast to the target type.
10030  S.Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cannot_pass_to_vararg_format)
10031  << isa<InitListExpr>(E) << ExprTy << CallType
10032  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context) << E->getSourceRange();
10033  break;
10034  }
10035 
10036  assert(FirstDataArg + FS.getArgIndex() < CheckedVarArgs.size() &&
10037  "format string specifier index out of range");
10038  CheckedVarArgs[FirstDataArg + FS.getArgIndex()] = true;
10039  }
10040 
10041  return true;
10042 }

10076 
10077 void CheckScanfHandler::HandleIncompleteScanList(const char *start,
10078  const char *end) {
10079  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_scanf_scanlist_incomplete),
10080  getLocationOfByte(end), /*IsStringLocation*/true,
10081  getSpecifierRange(start, end - start));
10082 }
10083 
10084 bool CheckScanfHandler::HandleInvalidScanfConversionSpecifier(
10085  const analyze_scanf::ScanfSpecifier &FS,
10086  const char *startSpecifier,
10087  unsigned specifierLen) {
10088  const analyze_scanf::ScanfConversionSpecifier &CS =
10089  FS.getConversionSpecifier();
10090 
10091  return HandleInvalidConversionSpecifier(FS.getArgIndex(),
10092  getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
10093  startSpecifier, specifierLen,
10094  CS.getStart(), CS.getLength());
10095 }
10096 
10097 bool CheckScanfHandler::HandleScanfSpecifier(
10098  const analyze_scanf::ScanfSpecifier &FS,
10099  const char *startSpecifier,
10100  unsigned specifierLen) {
10101  using namespace analyze_scanf;
10102  using namespace analyze_format_string;
10103 
10104  const ScanfConversionSpecifier &CS = FS.getConversionSpecifier();
10105 
10106  // Handle case where '%' and '*' don't consume an argument. These shouldn't
10107  // be used to decide if we are using positional arguments consistently.
10108  if (FS.consumesDataArgument()) {
10109  if (atFirstArg) {
10110  atFirstArg = false;
10111  usesPositionalArgs = FS.usesPositionalArg();
10112  }
10113  else if (usesPositionalArgs != FS.usesPositionalArg()) {
10114  HandlePositionalNonpositionalArgs(getLocationOfByte(CS.getStart()),
10115  startSpecifier, specifierLen);
10116  return false;
10117  }
10118  }
10119 
10120  // Check if the field with is non-zero.
10121  const OptionalAmount &Amt = FS.getFieldWidth();
10122  if (Amt.getHowSpecified() == OptionalAmount::Constant) {
10123  if (Amt.getConstantAmount() == 0) {
10124  const CharSourceRange &R = getSpecifierRange(Amt.getStart(),
10125  Amt.getConstantLength());
10126  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(diag::warn_scanf_nonzero_width),
10127  getLocationOfByte(Amt.getStart()),
10128  /*IsStringLocation*/true, R,
10129  FixItHint::CreateRemoval(R));
10130  }
10131  }
10132 
10133  if (!FS.consumesDataArgument()) {
10134  // FIXME: Technically specifying a precision or field width here
10135  // makes no sense. Worth issuing a warning at some point.
10136  return true;
10137  }
10138 
10139  // Consume the argument.
10140  unsigned argIndex = FS.getArgIndex();
10141  if (argIndex < NumDataArgs) {
10142  // The check to see if the argIndex is valid will come later.
10143  // We set the bit here because we may exit early from this
10144  // function if we encounter some other error.
10145  CoveredArgs.set(argIndex);
10146  }
10147 
10148  // Check the length modifier is valid with the given conversion specifier.
10149  if (!FS.hasValidLengthModifier(S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo(),
10150  S.getLangOpts()))
10151  HandleInvalidLengthModifier(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen,
10152  diag::warn_format_nonsensical_length);
10153  else if (!FS.hasStandardLengthModifier())
10154  HandleNonStandardLengthModifier(FS, startSpecifier, specifierLen);
10155  else if (!FS.hasStandardLengthConversionCombination())
10156  HandleInvalidLengthModifier(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen,
10157  diag::warn_format_non_standard_conversion_spec);
10158 
10159  if (!FS.hasStandardConversionSpecifier(S.getLangOpts()))
10160  HandleNonStandardConversionSpecifier(CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen);
10161 
10162  // The remaining checks depend on the data arguments.
10163  if (HasVAListArg)
10164  return true;
10165 
10166  if (!CheckNumArgs(FS, CS, startSpecifier, specifierLen, argIndex))
10167  return false;
10168 
10169  // Check that the argument type matches the format specifier.
10170  const Expr *Ex = getDataArg(argIndex);
10171  if (!Ex)
10172  return true;
10173 
10174  const analyze_format_string::ArgType &AT = FS.getArgType(S.Context);
10175 
10176  if (!AT.isValid()) {
10177  return true;
10178  }
10179 
10180  analyze_format_string::ArgType::MatchKind Match =
10181  AT.matchesType(S.Context, Ex->getType());
10182  bool Pedantic = Match == analyze_format_string::ArgType::NoMatchPedantic;
10183  if (Match == analyze_format_string::ArgType::Match)
10184  return true;
10185 
10186  ScanfSpecifier fixedFS = FS;
10187  bool Success = fixedFS.fixType(Ex->getType(), Ex->IgnoreImpCasts()->getType(),
10188  S.getLangOpts(), S.Context);
10189 
10190  unsigned Diag =
10191  Pedantic ? diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch_pedantic
10192  : diag::warn_format_conversion_argument_type_mismatch;
10193 
10194  if (Success) {
10195  // Get the fix string from the fixed format specifier.
10196  SmallString<128> buf;
10197  llvm::raw_svector_ostream os(buf);
10198  fixedFS.toString(os);
10199 
10200  EmitFormatDiagnostic(
10201  S.PDiag(Diag) << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context)
10202  << Ex->getType() << false << Ex->getSourceRange(),
10203  Ex->getBeginLoc(),
10204  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
10205  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen),
10206  FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
10207  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen), os.str()));
10208  } else {
10209  EmitFormatDiagnostic(S.PDiag(Diag)
10210  << AT.getRepresentativeTypeName(S.Context)
10211  << Ex->getType() << false << Ex->getSourceRange(),
10212  Ex->getBeginLoc(),
10213  /*IsStringLocation*/ false,
10214  getSpecifierRange(startSpecifier, specifierLen));
10215  }
10216 
10217  return true;
10218 }
10219 
10220 static void CheckFormatString(Sema &S, const FormatStringLiteral *FExpr,
10221  const Expr *OrigFormatExpr,
10222  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
10223  bool HasVAListArg, unsigned format_idx,
10224  unsigned firstDataArg,
10225  Sema::FormatStringType Type,
10226  bool inFunctionCall,
10227  Sema::VariadicCallType CallType,
10228  llvm::SmallBitVector &CheckedVarArgs,
10229  UncoveredArgHandler &UncoveredArg,
10230  bool IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers) {
10231  // CHECK: is the format string a wide literal?
10232  if (!FExpr->isAscii() && !FExpr->isUTF8()) {
10233  CheckFormatHandler::EmitFormatDiagnostic(
10234  S, inFunctionCall, Args[format_idx],
10235  S.PDiag(diag::warn_format_string_is_wide_literal), FExpr->getBeginLoc(),
10236  /*IsStringLocation*/ true, OrigFormatExpr->getSourceRange());
10237  return;
10238  }
10239 
10240  // Str - The format string. NOTE: this is NOT null-terminated!
10241  StringRef StrRef = FExpr->getString();
10242  const char *Str = StrRef.data();
10243  // Account for cases where the string literal is truncated in a declaration.
10244  const ConstantArrayType *T =
10245  S.Context.getAsConstantArrayType(FExpr->getType());
10246  assert(T && "String literal not of constant array type!");
10247  size_t TypeSize = T->getSize().getZExtValue();
10248  size_t StrLen = std::min(std::max(TypeSize, size_t(1)) - 1, StrRef.size());
10249  const unsigned numDataArgs = Args.size() - firstDataArg;
10250 
10251  if (IgnoreStringsWithoutSpecifiers &&
10252  !analyze_format_string::parseFormatStringHasFormattingSpecifiers(
10253  Str, Str + StrLen, S.getLangOpts(), S.Context.getTargetInfo()))
10254  return;
10255 
10256  // Emit a warning if the string literal is truncated and does not contain an
10257  // embedded null character.
10258  if (TypeSize <= StrRef.size() && !StrRef.substr(0, TypeSize).contains('\0')) {
10259  CheckFormatHandler::EmitFormatDiagnostic(
10260  S, inFunctionCall, Args[format_idx],
10261  S.PDiag(diag::warn_printf_format_string_not_null_terminated),
10262  FExpr->getBeginLoc(),
10263  /*IsStringLocation=*/true, OrigFormatExpr->getSourceRange());
10264  return;
10265  }
10266 
10267  // CHECK: empty format string?
10268  if (StrLen == 0 && numDataArgs > 0) {
10269  CheckFormatHandler::EmitFormatDiagnostic(
10270  S, inFunctionCall, Args[format_idx],
10271  S.PDiag(diag::warn_empty_format_string), FExpr->getBeginLoc(),
10272  /*IsStringLocation*/ true, OrigFormatExpr->getSourceRange());
10273  return;
10274  }
10275 
10276  if (Type == Sema::FST_Printf || Type == Sema::FST_NSString ||
10277  Type == Sema::FST_FreeBSDKPrintf || Type == Sema::FST_OSLog ||
10278  Type == Sema::FST_OSTrace) {
10279  CheckPrintfHandler H(
10280  S, FExpr, OrigFormatExpr, Type, firstDataArg, numDataArgs,
10281  (Type == Sema::FST_NSString || Type == Sema::FST_OSTrace), Str,
10282  HasVAListArg, Args, format_idx, inFunctionCall, CallType,
10283  CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg);
10284 
10285  if (!analyze_format_string::ParsePrintfString(H, Str, Str + StrLen,
10286  S.getLangOpts(),
10287  S.Context.getTargetInfo(),
10288  Type == Sema::FST_FreeBSDKPrintf))
10289  H.DoneProcessing();
10290  } else if (Type == Sema::FST_Scanf) {
10291  CheckScanfHandler H(S, FExpr, OrigFormatExpr, Type, firstDataArg,
10292  numDataArgs, Str, HasVAListArg, Args, format_idx,
10293  inFunctionCall, CallType, CheckedVarArgs, UncoveredArg);
10294 
10295  if (!analyze_format_string::ParseScanfString(H, Str, Str + StrLen,
10296  S.getLangOpts(),
10297  S.Context.getTargetInfo()))
10298  H.DoneProcessing();
10299  } // TODO: handle other formats
10300 }
10301 
10302 bool Sema::FormatStringHasSArg(const StringLiteral *FExpr) {
10303  // Str - The format string. NOTE: this is NOT null-terminated!
10304  StringRef StrRef = FExpr->getString();
10305  const char *Str = StrRef.data();
10306  // Account for cases where the string literal is truncated in a declaration.
10307  const ConstantArrayType *T = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(FExpr->getType());
10308  assert(T && "String literal not of constant array type!");
10309  size_t TypeSize = T->getSize().getZExtValue();
10310  size_t StrLen = std::min(std::max(TypeSize, size_t(1)) - 1, StrRef.size());
10311  return analyze_format_string::ParseFormatStringHasSArg(Str, Str + StrLen,
10312  getLangOpts(),
10313  Context.getTargetInfo());
10314 }

10317 
10318 // Returns the related absolute value function that is larger, of 0 if one
10319 // does not exist.
10320 static unsigned getLargerAbsoluteValueFunction(unsigned AbsFunction) {
10321  switch (AbsFunction) {
10322  default:
10323  return 0;
10324 
10325  case Builtin::BI__builtin_abs:
10326  return Builtin::BI__builtin_labs;
10327  case Builtin::BI__builtin_labs:
10328  return Builtin::BI__builtin_llabs;
10329  case Builtin::BI__builtin_llabs:
10330  return 0;
10331 
10332  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf:
10333  return Builtin::BI__builtin_fabs;
10334  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabs:
10335  return Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl;
10336  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
10337  return 0;
10338 
10339  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsf:
10340  return Builtin::BI__builtin_cabs;
10341  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabs:
10342  return Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsl;
10343  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsl:
10344  return 0;
10345 
10346  case Builtin::BIabs:
10347  return Builtin::BIlabs;
10348  case Builtin::BIlabs:
10349  return Builtin::BIllabs;
10350  case Builtin::BIllabs:
10351  return 0;
10352 
10353  case Builtin::BIfabsf:
10354  return Builtin::BIfabs;
10355  case Builtin::BIfabs:
10356  return Builtin::BIfabsl;
10357  case Builtin::BIfabsl:
10358  return 0;
10359 
10360  case Builtin::BIcabsf:
10361  return Builtin::BIcabs;
10362  case Builtin::BIcabs:
10363  return Builtin::BIcabsl;
10364  case Builtin::BIcabsl:
10365  return 0;
10366  }
10367 }

10369 // Returns the argument type of the absolute value function.
10370 static QualType getAbsoluteValueArgumentType(ASTContext &Context,
10371  unsigned AbsType) {
10372  if (AbsType == 0)
10373  return QualType();
10374 
10375  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error = ASTContext::GE_None;
10376  QualType BuiltinType = Context.GetBuiltinType(AbsType, Error);
10377  if (Error != ASTContext::GE_None)
10378  return QualType();
10379 
10380  const FunctionProtoType *FT = BuiltinType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
10381  if (!FT)
10382  return QualType();
10383 
10384  if (FT->getNumParams() != 1)
10385  return QualType();
10386 
10387  return FT->getParamType(0);
10388 }
10389 
10390 // Returns the best absolute value function, or zero, based on type and
10391 // current absolute value function.
10392 static unsigned getBestAbsFunction(ASTContext &Context, QualType ArgType,
10393  unsigned AbsFunctionKind) {
10394  unsigned BestKind = 0;
10395  uint64_t ArgSize = Context.getTypeSize(ArgType);
10396  for (unsigned Kind = AbsFunctionKind; Kind != 0;
10397  Kind = getLargerAbsoluteValueFunction(Kind)) {
10398  QualType ParamType = getAbsoluteValueArgumentType(Context, Kind);
10399  if (Context.getTypeSize(ParamType) >= ArgSize) {
10400  if (BestKind == 0)
10401  BestKind = Kind;
10402  else if (Context.hasSameType(ParamType, ArgType)) {
10403  BestKind = Kind;
10404  break;
10405  }
10406  }
10407  }
10408  return BestKind;
10409 }

10411 enum AbsoluteValueKind {
10412  AVK_Integer,
10413  AVK_Floating,
10414  AVK_Complex
10415 };
10416 
10417 static AbsoluteValueKind getAbsoluteValueKind(QualType T) {
10418  if (T->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
10419  return AVK_Integer;
10420  if (T->isRealFloatingType())
10421  return AVK_Floating;
10422  if (T->isAnyComplexType())
10423  return AVK_Complex;
10424 
10425  llvm_unreachable("Type not integer, floating, or complex");
10426 }
10427 
10428 // Changes the absolute value function to a different type. Preserves whether
10429 // the function is a builtin.
10430 static unsigned changeAbsFunction(unsigned AbsKind,
10431  AbsoluteValueKind ValueKind) {
10432  switch (ValueKind) {
10433  case AVK_Integer:
10434  switch (AbsKind) {
10435  default:
10436  return 0;
10437  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf:
10438  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabs:
10439  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
10440  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsf:
10441  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabs:
10442  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsl:
10443  return Builtin::BI__builtin_abs;
10444  case Builtin::BIfabsf:
10445  case Builtin::BIfabs:
10446  case Builtin::BIfabsl:
10447  case Builtin::BIcabsf:
10448  case Builtin::BIcabs:
10449  case Builtin::BIcabsl:
10450  return Builtin::BIabs;
10451  }
10452  case AVK_Floating:
10453  switch (AbsKind) {
10454  default:
10455  return 0;
10456  case Builtin::BI__builtin_abs:
10457  case Builtin::BI__builtin_labs:
10458  case Builtin::BI__builtin_llabs:
10459  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsf:
10460  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabs:
10461  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsl:
10462  return Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf;
10463  case Builtin::BIabs:
10464  case Builtin::BIlabs:
10465  case Builtin::BIllabs:
10466  case Builtin::BIcabsf:
10467  case Builtin::BIcabs:
10468  case Builtin::BIcabsl:
10469  return Builtin::BIfabsf;
10470  }
10471  case AVK_Complex:
10472  switch (AbsKind) {
10473  default:
10474  return 0;
10475  case Builtin::BI__builtin_abs:
10476  case Builtin::BI__builtin_labs:
10477  case Builtin::BI__builtin_llabs:
10478  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf:
10479  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabs:
10480  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
10481  return Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsf;
10482  case Builtin::BIabs:
10483  case Builtin::BIlabs:
10484  case Builtin::BIllabs:
10485  case Builtin::BIfabsf:
10486  case Builtin::BIfabs:
10487  case Builtin::BIfabsl:
10488  return Builtin::BIcabsf;
10489  }
10490  }
10491  llvm_unreachable("Unable to convert function");
10492 }

10494 static unsigned getAbsoluteValueFunctionKind(const FunctionDecl *FDecl) {
10495  const IdentifierInfo *FnInfo = FDecl->getIdentifier();
10496  if (!FnInfo)
10497  return 0;
10498 
10499  switch (FDecl->getBuiltinID()) {
10500  default:
10501  return 0;
10502  case Builtin::BI__builtin_abs:
10503  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabs:
10504  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf:
10505  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
10506  case Builtin::BI__builtin_labs:
10507  case Builtin::BI__builtin_llabs:
10508  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabs:
10509  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsf:
10510  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cabsl:
10511  case Builtin::BIabs:
10512  case Builtin::BIlabs:
10513  case Builtin::BIllabs:
10514  case Builtin::BIfabs:
10515  case Builtin::BIfabsf:
10516  case Builtin::BIfabsl:
10517  case Builtin::BIcabs:
10518  case Builtin::BIcabsf:
10519  case Builtin::BIcabsl:
10520  return FDecl->getBuiltinID();
10521  }
10522  llvm_unreachable("Unknown Builtin type");
10523 }
10524 
10525 // If the replacement is valid, emit a note with replacement function.
10526 // Additionally, suggest including the proper header if not already included.
10527 static void emitReplacement(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, SourceRange Range,
10528  unsigned AbsKind, QualType ArgType) {
10529  bool EmitHeaderHint = true;
10530  const char *HeaderName = nullptr;
10531  const char *FunctionName = nullptr;
10532  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !ArgType->isAnyComplexType()) {
10533  FunctionName = "std::abs";
10534  if (ArgType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
10535  HeaderName = "cstdlib";
10536  } else if (ArgType->isRealFloatingType()) {
10537  HeaderName = "cmath";
10538  } else {
10539  llvm_unreachable("Invalid Type");
10540  }
10541 
10542  // Lookup all std::abs
10543  if (NamespaceDecl *Std = S.getStdNamespace()) {
10544  LookupResult R(S, &S.Context.Idents.get("abs"), Loc, Sema::LookupAnyName);
10545  R.suppressDiagnostics();
10546  S.LookupQualifiedName(R, Std);
10547 
10548  for (const auto *I : R) {
10549  const FunctionDecl *FDecl = nullptr;
10550  if (const UsingShadowDecl *UsingD = dyn_cast<UsingShadowDecl>(I)) {
10551  FDecl = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(UsingD->getTargetDecl());
10552  } else {
10553  FDecl = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(I);
10554  }
10555  if (!FDecl)
10556  continue;
10557 
10558  // Found std::abs(), check that they are the right ones.
10559  if (FDecl->getNumParams() != 1)
10560  continue;
10561 
10562  // Check that the parameter type can handle the argument.
10563  QualType ParamType = FDecl->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
10564  if (getAbsoluteValueKind(ArgType) == getAbsoluteValueKind(ParamType) &&
10565  S.Context.getTypeSize(ArgType) <=
10566  S.Context.getTypeSize(ParamType)) {
10567  // Found a function, don't need the header hint.
10568  EmitHeaderHint = false;
10569  break;
10570  }
10571  }
10572  }
10573  } else {
10574  FunctionName = S.Context.BuiltinInfo.getName(AbsKind);
10575  HeaderName = S.Context.BuiltinInfo.getHeaderName(AbsKind);
10576 
10577  if (HeaderName) {
10578  DeclarationName DN(&S.Context.Idents.get(FunctionName));
10579  LookupResult R(S, DN, Loc, Sema::LookupAnyName);
10580  R.suppressDiagnostics();
10581  S.LookupName(R, S.getCurScope());
10582 
10583  if (R.isSingleResult()) {
10584  FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(R.getFoundDecl());
10585  if (FD && FD->getBuiltinID() == AbsKind) {
10586  EmitHeaderHint = false;
10587  } else {
10588  return;
10589  }
10590  } else if (!R.empty()) {
10591  return;
10592  }
10593  }
10594  }
10595 
10596  S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_replace_abs_function)
10597  << FunctionName << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(Range, FunctionName);
10598 
10599  if (!HeaderName)
10600  return;
10601 
10602  if (!EmitHeaderHint)
10603  return;
10604 
10605  S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_include_header_or_declare) << HeaderName
10606  << FunctionName;
10607 }
10608 
10609 template <std::size_t StrLen>
10610 static bool IsStdFunction(const FunctionDecl *FDecl,
10611  const char (&Str)[StrLen]) {
10612  if (!FDecl)
10613  return false;
10614  if (!FDecl->getIdentifier() || !FDecl->getIdentifier()->isStr(Str))
10615  return false;
10616  if (!FDecl->isInStdNamespace())
10617  return false;
10618 
10619  return true;
10620 }
10621 
10622 // Warn when using the wrong abs() function.
10623 void Sema::CheckAbsoluteValueFunction(const CallExpr *Call,
10624  const FunctionDecl *FDecl) {
10625  if (Call->getNumArgs() != 1)
10626  return;
10627 
10628  unsigned AbsKind = getAbsoluteValueFunctionKind(FDecl);
10629  bool IsStdAbs = IsStdFunction(FDecl, "abs");
10630  if (AbsKind == 0 && !IsStdAbs)
10631  return;
10632 
10633  QualType ArgType = Call->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->getType();
10634  QualType ParamType = Call->getArg(0)->getType();
10635 
10636  // Unsigned types cannot be negative. Suggest removing the absolute value
10637  // function call.
10638  if (ArgType->isUnsignedIntegerType()) {
10639  const char *FunctionName =
10640  IsStdAbs ? "std::abs" : Context.BuiltinInfo.getName(AbsKind);
10641  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_unsigned_abs) << ArgType << ParamType;
10642  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::note_remove_abs)
10643  << FunctionName
10644  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange());
10645  return;
10646  }
10647 
10648  // Taking the absolute value of a pointer is very suspicious, they probably
10649  // wanted to index into an array, dereference a pointer, call a function, etc.
10650  if (ArgType->isPointerType() || ArgType->canDecayToPointerType()) {
10651  unsigned DiagType = 0;
10652  if (ArgType->isFunctionType())
10653  DiagType = 1;
10654  else if (ArgType->isArrayType())
10655  DiagType = 2;
10656 
10657  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_pointer_abs) << DiagType << ArgType;
10658  return;
10659  }
10660 
10661  // std::abs has overloads which prevent most of the absolute value problems
10662  // from occurring.
10663  if (IsStdAbs)
10664  return;
10665 
10666  AbsoluteValueKind ArgValueKind = getAbsoluteValueKind(ArgType);
10667  AbsoluteValueKind ParamValueKind = getAbsoluteValueKind(ParamType);
10668 
10669  // The argument and parameter are the same kind. Check if they are the right
10670  // size.
10671  if (ArgValueKind == ParamValueKind) {
10672  if (Context.getTypeSize(ArgType) <= Context.getTypeSize(ParamType))
10673  return;
10674 
10675  unsigned NewAbsKind = getBestAbsFunction(Context, ArgType, AbsKind);
10676  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_abs_too_small)
10677  << FDecl << ArgType << ParamType;
10678 
10679  if (NewAbsKind == 0)
10680  return;
10681 
10682  emitReplacement(*this, Call->getExprLoc(),
10683  Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange(), NewAbsKind, ArgType);
10684  return;
10685  }
10686 
10687  // ArgValueKind != ParamValueKind
10688  // The wrong type of absolute value function was used. Attempt to find the
10689  // proper one.
10690  unsigned NewAbsKind = changeAbsFunction(AbsKind, ArgValueKind);
10691  NewAbsKind = getBestAbsFunction(Context, ArgType, NewAbsKind);
10692  if (NewAbsKind == 0)
10693  return;
10694 
10695  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_wrong_absolute_value_type)
10696  << FDecl << ParamValueKind << ArgValueKind;
10697 
10698  emitReplacement(*this, Call->getExprLoc(),
10699  Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange(), NewAbsKind, ArgType);
10700 }
10701 
10702 //===--- CHECK: Warn on use of std::max and unsigned zero. r---------------===//
10703 void Sema::CheckMaxUnsignedZero(const CallExpr *Call,
10704  const FunctionDecl *FDecl) {
10705  if (!Call || !FDecl) return;
10706 
10707  // Ignore template specializations and macros.
10708  if (inTemplateInstantiation()) return;
10709  if (Call->getExprLoc().isMacroID()) return;
10710 
10711  // Only care about the one template argument, two function parameter std::max
10712  if (Call->getNumArgs() != 2) return;
10713  if (!IsStdFunction(FDecl, "max")) return;
10714  const auto * ArgList = FDecl->getTemplateSpecializationArgs();
10715  if (!ArgList) return;
10716  if (ArgList->size() != 1) return;
10717 
10718  // Check that template type argument is unsigned integer.
10719  const auto& TA = ArgList->get(0);
10720  if (TA.getKind() != TemplateArgument::Type) return;
10721  QualType ArgType = TA.getAsType();
10722  if (!ArgType->isUnsignedIntegerType()) return;
10723 
10724  // See if either argument is a literal zero.
10725  auto IsLiteralZeroArg = [](const Expr* E) -> bool {
10726  const auto *MTE = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E);
10727  if (!MTE) return false;
10728  const auto *Num = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(MTE->getSubExpr());
10729  if (!Num) return false;
10730  if (Num->getValue() != 0) return false;
10731  return true;
10732  };
10733 
10734  const Expr *FirstArg = Call->getArg(0);
10735  const Expr *SecondArg = Call->getArg(1);
10736  const bool IsFirstArgZero = IsLiteralZeroArg(FirstArg);
10737  const bool IsSecondArgZero = IsLiteralZeroArg(SecondArg);
10738 
10739  // Only warn when exactly one argument is zero.
10740  if (IsFirstArgZero == IsSecondArgZero) return;
10741 
10742  SourceRange FirstRange = FirstArg->getSourceRange();
10743  SourceRange SecondRange = SecondArg->getSourceRange();
10744 
10745  SourceRange ZeroRange = IsFirstArgZero ? FirstRange : SecondRange;
10746 
10747  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_max_unsigned_zero)
10748  << IsFirstArgZero << Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange() << ZeroRange;
10749 
10750  // Deduce what parts to remove so that "std::max(0u, foo)" becomes "(foo)".
10751  SourceRange RemovalRange;
10752  if (IsFirstArgZero) {
10753  RemovalRange = SourceRange(FirstRange.getBegin(),
10754  SecondRange.getBegin().getLocWithOffset(-1));
10755  } else {
10756  RemovalRange = SourceRange(getLocForEndOfToken(FirstRange.getEnd()),
10757  SecondRange.getEnd());
10758  }
10759 
10760  Diag(Call->getExprLoc(), diag::note_remove_max_call)
10761  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange())
10762  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(RemovalRange);
10763 }
10764 
10765 //===--- CHECK: Standard memory functions ---------------------------------===//
10766 
10767 /// Takes the expression passed to the size_t parameter of functions
10768 /// such as memcmp, strncat, etc and warns if it's a comparison.
10769 ///
10770 /// This is to catch typos like `if (memcmp(&a, &b, sizeof(a) > 0))`.
10771 static bool CheckMemorySizeofForComparison(Sema &S, const Expr *E,
10772  IdentifierInfo *FnName,
10773  SourceLocation FnLoc,
10774  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
10775  const BinaryOperator *Size = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E);
10776  if (!Size)
10777  return false;
10778 
10779  // if E is binop and op is <=>, >, <, >=, <=, ==, &&, ||:
10780  if (!Size->isComparisonOp() && !Size->isLogicalOp())
10781  return false;
10782 
10783  SourceRange SizeRange = Size->getSourceRange();
10784  S.Diag(Size->getOperatorLoc(), diag::warn_memsize_comparison)
10785  << SizeRange << FnName;
10786  S.Diag(FnLoc, diag::note_memsize_comparison_paren)
10787  << FnName
10788  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
10789  S.getLocForEndOfToken(Size->getLHS()->getEndLoc()), ")")
10790  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(RParenLoc);
10791  S.Diag(SizeRange.getBegin(), diag::note_memsize_comparison_cast_silence)
10792  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(SizeRange.getBegin(), "(size_t)(")
10793  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(S.getLocForEndOfToken(SizeRange.getEnd()),
10794  ")");
10795 
10796  return true;
10797 }
10798 
10799 /// Determine whether the given type is or contains a dynamic class type
10800 /// (e.g., whether it has a vtable).
10801 static const CXXRecordDecl *getContainedDynamicClass(QualType T,
10802  bool &IsContained) {
10803  // Look through array types while ignoring qualifiers.
10804  const Type *Ty = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();
10805  IsContained = false;
10806 
10807  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
10808  RD = RD ? RD->getDefinition() : nullptr;
10809  if (!RD || RD->isInvalidDecl())
10810  return nullptr;
10811 
10812  if (RD->isDynamicClass())
10813  return RD;
10814 
10815  // Check all the fields. If any bases were dynamic, the class is dynamic.
10816  // It's impossible for a class to transitively contain itself by value, so
10817  // infinite recursion is impossible.
10818  for (auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
10819  bool SubContained;
10820  if (const CXXRecordDecl *ContainedRD =
10821  getContainedDynamicClass(FD->getType(), SubContained)) {
10822  IsContained = true;
10823  return ContainedRD;
10824  }
10825  }
10826 
10827  return nullptr;
10828 }
10829 
10830 static const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *getAsSizeOfExpr(const Expr *E) {
10831  if (const auto *Unary = dyn_cast<UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr>(E))
10832  if (Unary->getKind() == UETT_SizeOf)
10833  return Unary;
10834  return nullptr;
10835 }
10836 
10837 /// If E is a sizeof expression, returns its argument expression,
10838 /// otherwise returns NULL.
10839 static const Expr *getSizeOfExprArg(const Expr *E) {
10840  if (const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *SizeOf = getAsSizeOfExpr(E))
10841  if (!SizeOf->isArgumentType())
10842  return SizeOf->getArgumentExpr()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
10843  return nullptr;
10844 }
10845 
10846 /// If E is a sizeof expression, returns its argument type.
10847 static QualType getSizeOfArgType(const Expr *E) {
10848  if (const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *SizeOf = getAsSizeOfExpr(E))
10849  return SizeOf->getTypeOfArgument();
10850  return QualType();
10851 }

10945 /// Detect if \c SizeofExpr is likely to calculate the sizeof an object.
10946 static bool doesExprLikelyComputeSize(const Expr *SizeofExpr) {
10947  SizeofExpr = SizeofExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
10948 
10949  if (const auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(SizeofExpr)) {
10950  if (BO->getOpcode() != BO_Mul && BO->getOpcode() != BO_Add)
10951  return false;
10952 
10953  return doesExprLikelyComputeSize(BO->getLHS()) ||
10954  doesExprLikelyComputeSize(BO->getRHS());
10955  }
10956 
10957  return getAsSizeOfExpr(SizeofExpr) != nullptr;
10958 }
10959 
10960 /// Check if the ArgLoc originated from a macro passed to the call at CallLoc.
10961 ///
10962 /// \code
10963 /// #define MACRO 0
10964 /// foo(MACRO);
10965 /// foo(0);
10966 /// \endcode
10967 ///
10968 /// This should return true for the first call to foo, but not for the second
10969 /// (regardless of whether foo is a macro or function).
10970 static bool isArgumentExpandedFromMacro(SourceManager &SM,
10971  SourceLocation CallLoc,
10972  SourceLocation ArgLoc) {
10973  if (!CallLoc.isMacroID())
10974  return SM.getFileID(CallLoc) != SM.getFileID(ArgLoc);
10975 
10976  return SM.getFileID(SM.getImmediateMacroCallerLoc(CallLoc)) !=
10977  SM.getFileID(SM.getImmediateMacroCallerLoc(ArgLoc));
10978 }
10979 
10980 /// Diagnose cases like 'memset(buf, sizeof(buf), 0)', which should have the
10981 /// last two arguments transposed.
10982 static void CheckMemaccessSize(Sema &S, unsigned BId, const CallExpr *Call) {
10983  if (BId != Builtin::BImemset && BId != Builtin::BIbzero)
10984  return;
10985 
10986  const Expr *SizeArg =
10987  Call->getArg(BId == Builtin::BImemset ? 2 : 1)->IgnoreImpCasts();
10988 
10989  auto isLiteralZero = [](const Expr *E) {
10990  return isa<IntegerLiteral>(E) && cast<IntegerLiteral>(E)->getValue() == 0;
10991  };
10992 
10993  // If we're memsetting or bzeroing 0 bytes, then this is likely an error.
10994  SourceLocation CallLoc = Call->getRParenLoc();
10995  SourceManager &SM = S.getSourceManager();
10996  if (isLiteralZero(SizeArg) &&
10997  !isArgumentExpandedFromMacro(SM, CallLoc, SizeArg->getExprLoc())) {
10998 
10999  SourceLocation DiagLoc = SizeArg->getExprLoc();
11000 
11001  // Some platforms #define bzero to __builtin_memset. See if this is the
11002  // case, and if so, emit a better diagnostic.
11003  if (BId == Builtin::BIbzero ||
11004  (CallLoc.isMacroID() && Lexer::getImmediateMacroName(
11005  CallLoc, SM, S.getLangOpts()) == "bzero")) {
11006  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_suspicious_bzero_size);
11007  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::note_suspicious_bzero_size_silence);
11008  } else if (!isLiteralZero(Call->getArg(1)->IgnoreImpCasts())) {
11009  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_suspicious_sizeof_memset) << 0;
11010  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::note_suspicious_sizeof_memset_silence) << 0;
11011  }
11012  return;
11013  }
11014 
11015  // If the second argument to a memset is a sizeof expression and the third
11016  // isn't, this is also likely an error. This should catch
11017  // 'memset(buf, sizeof(buf), 0xff)'.
11018  if (BId == Builtin::BImemset &&
11019  doesExprLikelyComputeSize(Call->getArg(1)) &&
11020  !doesExprLikelyComputeSize(Call->getArg(2))) {
11021  SourceLocation DiagLoc = Call->getArg(1)->getExprLoc();
11022  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_suspicious_sizeof_memset) << 1;
11023  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::note_suspicious_sizeof_memset_silence) << 1;
11024  return;
11025  }
11026 }
11027 
11028 /// Check for dangerous or invalid arguments to memset().
11029 ///
11030 /// This issues warnings on known problematic, dangerous or unspecified
11031 /// arguments to the standard 'memset', 'memcpy', 'memmove', and 'memcmp'
11032 /// function calls.
11033 ///
11034 /// \param Call The call expression to diagnose.
11035 void Sema::CheckMemaccessArguments(const CallExpr *Call,
11036  unsigned BId,
11037  IdentifierInfo *FnName) {
11038  assert(BId != 0);
11039 
11040  // It is possible to have a non-standard definition of memset. Validate
11041  // we have enough arguments, and if not, abort further checking.
11042  unsigned ExpectedNumArgs =
11043  (BId == Builtin::BIstrndup || BId == Builtin::BIbzero ? 2 : 3);
11044  if (Call->getNumArgs() < ExpectedNumArgs)
11045  return;
11046 
11047  unsigned LastArg = (BId == Builtin::BImemset || BId == Builtin::BIbzero ||
11048  BId == Builtin::BIstrndup ? 1 : 2);
11049  unsigned LenArg =
11050  (BId == Builtin::BIbzero || BId == Builtin::BIstrndup ? 1 : 2);
11051  const Expr *LenExpr = Call->getArg(LenArg)->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
11052 
11053  if (CheckMemorySizeofForComparison(*this, LenExpr, FnName,
11054  Call->getBeginLoc(), Call->getRParenLoc()))
11055  return;
11056 
11057  // Catch cases like 'memset(buf, sizeof(buf), 0)'.
11058  CheckMemaccessSize(*this, BId, Call);
11059 
11060  // We have special checking when the length is a sizeof expression.
11061  QualType SizeOfArgTy = getSizeOfArgType(LenExpr);
11062  const Expr *SizeOfArg = getSizeOfExprArg(LenExpr);
11063  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID SizeOfArgID;
11064 
11065  // Although widely used, 'bzero' is not a standard function. Be more strict
11066  // with the argument types before allowing diagnostics and only allow the
11067  // form bzero(ptr, sizeof(...)).
11068  QualType FirstArgTy = Call->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->getType();
11069  if (BId == Builtin::BIbzero && !FirstArgTy->getAs<PointerType>())
11070  return;
11071 
11072  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx != LastArg; ++ArgIdx) {
11073  const Expr *Dest = Call->getArg(ArgIdx)->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
11074  SourceRange ArgRange = Call->getArg(ArgIdx)->getSourceRange();
11075 
11076  QualType DestTy = Dest->getType();
11077  QualType PointeeTy;
11078  if (const PointerType *DestPtrTy = DestTy->getAs<PointerType>()) {
11079  PointeeTy = DestPtrTy->getPointeeType();
11080 
11081  // Never warn about void type pointers. This can be used to suppress
11082  // false positives.
11083  if (PointeeTy->isVoidType())
11084  continue;
11085 
11086  // Catch "memset(p, 0, sizeof(p))" -- needs to be sizeof(*p). Do this by
11087  // actually comparing the expressions for equality. Because computing the
11088  // expression IDs can be expensive, we only do this if the diagnostic is
11089  // enabled.
11090  if (SizeOfArg &&
11091  !Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_sizeof_pointer_expr_memaccess,
11092  SizeOfArg->getExprLoc())) {
11093  // We only compute IDs for expressions if the warning is enabled, and
11094  // cache the sizeof arg's ID.
11095  if (SizeOfArgID == llvm::FoldingSetNodeID())
11096  SizeOfArg->Profile(SizeOfArgID, Context, true);
11097  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID DestID;
11098  Dest->Profile(DestID, Context, true);
11099  if (DestID == SizeOfArgID) {
11100  // TODO: For strncpy() and friends, this could suggest sizeof(dst)
11101  // over sizeof(src) as well.
11102  unsigned ActionIdx = 0; // Default is to suggest dereferencing.
11103  StringRef ReadableName = FnName->getName();
11104 
11105  if (const UnaryOperator *UnaryOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Dest))
11106  if (UnaryOp->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
11107  ActionIdx = 1; // If its an address-of operator, just remove it.
11108  if (!PointeeTy->isIncompleteType() &&
11109  (Context.getTypeSize(PointeeTy) == Context.getCharWidth()))
11110  ActionIdx = 2; // If the pointee's size is sizeof(char),
11111  // suggest an explicit length.
11112 
11113  // If the function is defined as a builtin macro, do not show macro
11114  // expansion.
11115  SourceLocation SL = SizeOfArg->getExprLoc();
11116  SourceRange DSR = Dest->getSourceRange();
11117  SourceRange SSR = SizeOfArg->getSourceRange();
11118  SourceManager &SM = getSourceManager();
11119 
11120  if (SM.isMacroArgExpansion(SL)) {
11121  ReadableName = Lexer::getImmediateMacroName(SL, SM, LangOpts);
11122  SL = SM.getSpellingLoc(SL);
11123  DSR = SourceRange(SM.getSpellingLoc(DSR.getBegin()),
11124  SM.getSpellingLoc(DSR.getEnd()));
11125  SSR = SourceRange(SM.getSpellingLoc(SSR.getBegin()),
11126  SM.getSpellingLoc(SSR.getEnd()));
11127  }
11128 
11129  DiagRuntimeBehavior(SL, SizeOfArg,
11130  PDiag(diag::warn_sizeof_pointer_expr_memaccess)
11131  << ReadableName
11132  << PointeeTy
11133  << DestTy
11134  << DSR
11135  << SSR);
11136  DiagRuntimeBehavior(SL, SizeOfArg,
11137  PDiag(diag::warn_sizeof_pointer_expr_memaccess_note)
11138  << ActionIdx
11139  << SSR);
11140 
11141  break;
11142  }
11143  }
11144 
11145  // Also check for cases where the sizeof argument is the exact same
11146  // type as the memory argument, and where it points to a user-defined
11147  // record type.
11148  if (SizeOfArgTy != QualType()) {
11149  if (PointeeTy->isRecordType() &&
11150  Context.typesAreCompatible(SizeOfArgTy, DestTy)) {
11151  DiagRuntimeBehavior(LenExpr->getExprLoc(), Dest,
11152  PDiag(diag::warn_sizeof_pointer_type_memaccess)
11153  << FnName << SizeOfArgTy << ArgIdx
11154  << PointeeTy << Dest->getSourceRange()
11155  << LenExpr->getSourceRange());
11156  break;
11157  }
11158  }
11159  } else if (DestTy->isArrayType()) {
11160  PointeeTy = DestTy;
11161  }
11162 
11163  if (PointeeTy == QualType())
11164  continue;
11165 
11166  // Always complain about dynamic classes.
11167  bool IsContained;
11168  if (const CXXRecordDecl *ContainedRD =
11169  getContainedDynamicClass(PointeeTy, IsContained)) {
11170 
11171  unsigned OperationType = 0;
11172  const bool IsCmp = BId == Builtin::BImemcmp || BId == Builtin::BIbcmp;
11173  // "overwritten" if we're warning about the destination for any call
11174  // but memcmp; otherwise a verb appropriate to the call.
11175  if (ArgIdx != 0 || IsCmp) {
11176  if (BId == Builtin::BImemcpy)
11177  OperationType = 1;
11178  else if(BId == Builtin::BImemmove)
11179  OperationType = 2;
11180  else if (IsCmp)
11181  OperationType = 3;
11182  }
11183 
11184  DiagRuntimeBehavior(Dest->getExprLoc(), Dest,
11185  PDiag(diag::warn_dyn_class_memaccess)
11186  << (IsCmp ? ArgIdx + 2 : ArgIdx) << FnName
11187  << IsContained << ContainedRD << OperationType
11188  << Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange());
11189  } else if (PointeeTy.hasNonTrivialObjCLifetime() &&
11190  BId != Builtin::BImemset)
11191  DiagRuntimeBehavior(
11192  Dest->getExprLoc(), Dest,
11193  PDiag(diag::warn_arc_object_memaccess)
11194  << ArgIdx << FnName << PointeeTy
11195  << Call->getCallee()->getSourceRange());
11196  else if (const auto *RT = PointeeTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
11197  if ((BId == Builtin::BImemset || BId == Builtin::BIbzero) &&
11198  RT->getDecl()->isNonTrivialToPrimitiveDefaultInitialize()) {
11199  DiagRuntimeBehavior(Dest->getExprLoc(), Dest,
11200  PDiag(diag::warn_cstruct_memaccess)
11201  << ArgIdx << FnName << PointeeTy << 0);
11202  SearchNonTrivialToInitializeField::diag(PointeeTy, Dest, *this);
11203  } else if ((BId == Builtin::BImemcpy || BId == Builtin::BImemmove) &&
11204  RT->getDecl()->isNonTrivialToPrimitiveCopy()) {
11205  DiagRuntimeBehavior(Dest->getExprLoc(), Dest,
11206  PDiag(diag::warn_cstruct_memaccess)
11207  << ArgIdx << FnName << PointeeTy << 1);
11208  SearchNonTrivialToCopyField::diag(PointeeTy, Dest, *this);
11209  } else {
11210  continue;
11211  }
11212  } else
11213  continue;
11214 
11215  DiagRuntimeBehavior(
11216  Dest->getExprLoc(), Dest,
11217  PDiag(diag::note_bad_memaccess_silence)
11218  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(ArgRange.getBegin(), "(void*)"));
11219  break;
11220  }
11221 }
11222 
11223 // A little helper routine: ignore addition and subtraction of integer literals.
11224 // This intentionally does not ignore all integer constant expressions because
11225 // we don't want to remove sizeof().
11226 static const Expr *ignoreLiteralAdditions(const Expr *Ex, ASTContext &Ctx) {
11227  Ex = Ex->IgnoreParenCasts();
11228 
11229  while (true) {
11230  const BinaryOperator * BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Ex);
11231  if (!BO || !BO->isAdditiveOp())
11232  break;
11233 
11234  const Expr *RHS = BO->getRHS()->IgnoreParenCasts();
11235  const Expr *LHS = BO->getLHS()->IgnoreParenCasts();
11236 
11237  if (isa<IntegerLiteral>(RHS))
11238  Ex = LHS;
11239  else if (isa<IntegerLiteral>(LHS))
11240  Ex = RHS;
11241  else
11242  break;
11243  }
11244 
11245  return Ex;
11246 }
11247 
11248 static bool isConstantSizeArrayWithMoreThanOneElement(QualType Ty,
11249  ASTContext &Context) {
11250  // Only handle constant-sized or VLAs, but not flexible members.
11251  if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(Ty)) {
11252  // Only issue the FIXIT for arrays of size > 1.
11253  if (CAT->getSize().getSExtValue() <= 1)
11254  return false;
11255  } else if (!Ty->isVariableArrayType()) {
11256  return false;
11257  }
11258  return true;
11259 }
11260 
11261 // Warn if the user has made the 'size' argument to strlcpy or strlcat
11262 // be the size of the source, instead of the destination.
11263 void Sema::CheckStrlcpycatArguments(const CallExpr *Call,
11264  IdentifierInfo *FnName) {
11265 
11266  // Don't crash if the user has the wrong number of arguments
11267  unsigned NumArgs = Call->getNumArgs();
11268  if ((NumArgs != 3) && (NumArgs != 4))
11269  return;
11270 
11271  const Expr *SrcArg = ignoreLiteralAdditions(Call->getArg(1), Context);
11272  const Expr *SizeArg = ignoreLiteralAdditions(Call->getArg(2), Context);
11273  const Expr *CompareWithSrc = nullptr;
11274 
11275  if (CheckMemorySizeofForComparison(*this, SizeArg, FnName,
11276  Call->getBeginLoc(), Call->getRParenLoc()))
11277  return;
11278 
11279  // Look for 'strlcpy(dst, x, sizeof(x))'
11280  if (const Expr *Ex = getSizeOfExprArg(SizeArg))
11281  CompareWithSrc = Ex;
11282  else {
11283  // Look for 'strlcpy(dst, x, strlen(x))'
11284  if (const CallExpr *SizeCall = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(SizeArg)) {
11285  if (SizeCall->getBuiltinCallee() == Builtin::BIstrlen &&
11286  SizeCall->getNumArgs() == 1)
11287  CompareWithSrc = ignoreLiteralAdditions(SizeCall->getArg(0), Context);
11288  }
11289  }
11290 
11291  if (!CompareWithSrc)
11292  return;
11293 
11294  // Determine if the argument to sizeof/strlen is equal to the source
11295  // argument. In principle there's all kinds of things you could do
11296  // here, for instance creating an == expression and evaluating it with
11297  // EvaluateAsBooleanCondition, but this uses a more direct technique:
11298  const DeclRefExpr *SrcArgDRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(SrcArg);
11299  if (!SrcArgDRE)
11300  return;
11301 
11302  const DeclRefExpr *CompareWithSrcDRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(CompareWithSrc);
11303  if (!CompareWithSrcDRE ||
11304  SrcArgDRE->getDecl() != CompareWithSrcDRE->getDecl())
11305  return;
11306 
11307  const Expr *OriginalSizeArg = Call->getArg(2);
11308  Diag(CompareWithSrcDRE->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_strlcpycat_wrong_size)
11309  << OriginalSizeArg->getSourceRange() << FnName;
11310 
11311  // Output a FIXIT hint if the destination is an array (rather than a
11312  // pointer to an array). This could be enhanced to handle some
11313  // pointers if we know the actual size, like if DstArg is 'array+2'
11314  // we could say 'sizeof(array)-2'.
11315  const Expr *DstArg = Call->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
11316  if (!isConstantSizeArrayWithMoreThanOneElement(DstArg->getType(), Context))
11317  return;
11318 
11319  SmallString<128> sizeString;
11320  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(sizeString);
11321  OS << "sizeof(";
11322  DstArg->printPretty(OS, nullptr, getPrintingPolicy());
11323  OS << ")";
11324 
11325  Diag(OriginalSizeArg->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_strlcpycat_wrong_size)
11326  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OriginalSizeArg->getSourceRange(),
11327  OS.str());
11328 }
11329 
11330 /// Check if two expressions refer to the same declaration.
11331 static bool referToTheSameDecl(const Expr *E1, const Expr *E2) {
11332  if (const DeclRefExpr *D1 = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclRefExpr>(E1))
11333  if (const DeclRefExpr *D2 = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclRefExpr>(E2))
11334  return D1->getDecl() == D2->getDecl();
11335  return false;
11336 }
11337 
11338 static const Expr *getStrlenExprArg(const Expr *E) {
11339  if (const CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(E)) {
11340  const FunctionDecl *FD = CE->getDirectCallee();
11341  if (!FD || FD->getMemoryFunctionKind() != Builtin::BIstrlen)
11342  return nullptr;
11343  return CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenCasts();
11344  }
11345  return nullptr;
11346 }
11347 
11348 // Warn on anti-patterns as the 'size' argument to strncat.
11349 // The correct size argument should look like following:
11350 // strncat(dst, src, sizeof(dst) - strlen(dest) - 1);
11351 void Sema::CheckStrncatArguments(const CallExpr *CE,
11352  IdentifierInfo *FnName) {
11353  // Don't crash if the user has the wrong number of arguments.
11354  if (CE->getNumArgs() < 3)
11355  return;
11356  const Expr *DstArg = CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenCasts();
11357  const Expr *SrcArg = CE->getArg(1)->IgnoreParenCasts();
11358  const Expr *LenArg = CE->getArg(2)->IgnoreParenCasts();
11359 
11360  if (CheckMemorySizeofForComparison(*this, LenArg, FnName, CE->getBeginLoc(),
11361  CE->getRParenLoc()))
11362  return;
11363 
11364  // Identify common expressions, which are wrongly used as the size argument
11365  // to strncat and may lead to buffer overflows.
11366  unsigned PatternType = 0;
11367  if (const Expr *SizeOfArg = getSizeOfExprArg(LenArg)) {
11368  // - sizeof(dst)
11369  if (referToTheSameDecl(SizeOfArg, DstArg))
11370  PatternType = 1;
11371  // - sizeof(src)
11372  else if (referToTheSameDecl(SizeOfArg, SrcArg))
11373  PatternType = 2;
11374  } else if (const BinaryOperator *BE = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(LenArg)) {
11375  if (BE->getOpcode() == BO_Sub) {
11376  const Expr *L = BE->getLHS()->IgnoreParenCasts();
11377  const Expr *R = BE->getRHS()->IgnoreParenCasts();
11378  // - sizeof(dst) - strlen(dst)
11379  if (referToTheSameDecl(DstArg, getSizeOfExprArg(L)) &&
11380  referToTheSameDecl(DstArg, getStrlenExprArg(R)))
11381  PatternType = 1;
11382  // - sizeof(src) - (anything)
11383  else if (referToTheSameDecl(SrcArg, getSizeOfExprArg(L)))
11384  PatternType = 2;
11385  }
11386  }
11387 
11388  if (PatternType == 0)
11389  return;
11390 
11391  // Generate the diagnostic.
11392  SourceLocation SL = LenArg->getBeginLoc();
11393  SourceRange SR = LenArg->getSourceRange();
11394  SourceManager &SM = getSourceManager();
11395 
11396  // If the function is defined as a builtin macro, do not show macro expansion.
11397  if (SM.isMacroArgExpansion(SL)) {
11398  SL = SM.getSpellingLoc(SL);
11399  SR = SourceRange(SM.getSpellingLoc(SR.getBegin()),
11400  SM.getSpellingLoc(SR.getEnd()));
11401  }
11402 
11403  // Check if the destination is an array (rather than a pointer to an array).
11404  QualType DstTy = DstArg->getType();
11405  bool isKnownSizeArray = isConstantSizeArrayWithMoreThanOneElement(DstTy,
11406  Context);
11407  if (!isKnownSizeArray) {
11408  if (PatternType == 1)
11409  Diag(SL, diag::warn_strncat_wrong_size) << SR;
11410  else
11411  Diag(SL, diag::warn_strncat_src_size) << SR;
11412  return;
11413  }
11414 
11415  if (PatternType == 1)
11416  Diag(SL, diag::warn_strncat_large_size) << SR;
11417  else
11418  Diag(SL, diag::warn_strncat_src_size) << SR;
11419 
11420  SmallString<128> sizeString;
11421  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(sizeString);
11422  OS << "sizeof(";
11423  DstArg->printPretty(OS, nullptr, getPrintingPolicy());
11424  OS << ") - ";
11425  OS << "strlen(";
11426  DstArg->printPretty(OS, nullptr, getPrintingPolicy());
11427  OS << ") - 1";
11428 
11429  Diag(SL, diag::note_strncat_wrong_size)
11430  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SR, OS.str());
11431 }
11432 
11433 namespace {
11434 void CheckFreeArgumentsOnLvalue(Sema &S, const std::string &CalleeName,
11435  const UnaryOperator *UnaryExpr, const Decl *D) {
11436  if (isa<FieldDecl, FunctionDecl, VarDecl>(D)) {
11437  S.Diag(UnaryExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_free_nonheap_object)
11438  << CalleeName << 0 /*object: */ << cast<NamedDecl>(D);
11439  return;
11440  }
11441 }
11442 
11443 void CheckFreeArgumentsAddressof(Sema &S, const std::string &CalleeName,
11444  const UnaryOperator *UnaryExpr) {
11445  if (const auto *Lvalue = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(UnaryExpr->getSubExpr())) {
11446  const Decl *D = Lvalue->getDecl();
11447  if (isa<DeclaratorDecl>(D))
11448  if (!dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(D)->getType()->isReferenceType())
11449  return CheckFreeArgumentsOnLvalue(S, CalleeName, UnaryExpr, D);
11450  }
11451 
11452  if (const auto *Lvalue = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(UnaryExpr->getSubExpr()))
11453  return CheckFreeArgumentsOnLvalue(S, CalleeName, UnaryExpr,
11454  Lvalue->getMemberDecl());
11455 }

11457 void CheckFreeArgumentsPlus(Sema &S, const std::string &CalleeName,
11458  const UnaryOperator *UnaryExpr) {
11459  const auto *Lambda = dyn_cast<LambdaExpr>(
11460  UnaryExpr->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicitAsWritten()->IgnoreParens());
11461  if (!Lambda)
11462  return;
11463 
11464  S.Diag(Lambda->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_free_nonheap_object)
11465  << CalleeName << 2 /*object: lambda expression*/;
11466 }

11468 void CheckFreeArgumentsStackArray(Sema &S, const std::string &CalleeName,
11469  const DeclRefExpr *Lvalue) {
11470  const auto *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Lvalue->getDecl());
11471  if (Var == nullptr)
11472  return;
11473 
11474  S.Diag(Lvalue->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_free_nonheap_object)
11475  << CalleeName << 0 /*object: */ << Var;
11476 }
11477 
11478 void CheckFreeArgumentsCast(Sema &S, const std::string &CalleeName,
11479  const CastExpr *Cast) {
11480  SmallString<128> SizeString;
11481  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(SizeString);
11482 
11483  clang::CastKind Kind = Cast->getCastKind();
11484  if (Kind == clang::CK_BitCast &&
11485  !Cast->getSubExpr()->getType()->isFunctionPointerType())
11486  return;
11487  if (Kind == clang::CK_IntegralToPointer &&
11488  !isa<IntegerLiteral>(
11489  Cast->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->IgnoreParens()))
11490  return;
11491 
11492  switch (Cast->getCastKind()) {
11493  case clang::CK_BitCast:
11494  case clang::CK_IntegralToPointer:
11495  case clang::CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
11496  OS << '\'';
11497  Cast->printPretty(OS, nullptr, S.getPrintingPolicy());
11498  OS << '\'';
11499  break;
11500  default:
11501  return;
11502  }
11503 
11504  S.Diag(Cast->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_free_nonheap_object)
11505  << CalleeName << 0 /*object: */ << OS.str();
11506 }
11507 } // namespace
11508 
11509 /// Alerts the user that they are attempting to free a non-malloc'd object.
