15110 
15111 static void diagnoseArrayStarInParamType(Sema &S, QualType PType,
15112  SourceLocation Loc) {
15113  if (!PType->isVariablyModifiedType())
15114  return;
15115  if (const auto *PointerTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(PType)) {
15116  diagnoseArrayStarInParamType(S, PointerTy->getPointeeType(), Loc);
15117  return;
15118  }
15119  if (const auto *ReferenceTy = dyn_cast<ReferenceType>(PType)) {
15120  diagnoseArrayStarInParamType(S, ReferenceTy->getPointeeType(), Loc);
15121  return;
15122  }
15123  if (const auto *ParenTy = dyn_cast<ParenType>(PType)) {
15124  diagnoseArrayStarInParamType(S, ParenTy->getInnerType(), Loc);
15125  return;
15126  }
15127 
15128  const ArrayType *AT = S.Context.getAsArrayType(PType);
15129  if (!AT)
15130  return;
15131 
15132  if (AT->getSizeModifier() != ArrayType::Star) {
15133  diagnoseArrayStarInParamType(S, AT->getElementType(), Loc);
15134  return;
15135  }
15136 
15137  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_star_in_function_definition);
15138 }
15139 
15140 /// CheckParmsForFunctionDef - Check that the parameters of the given
15141 /// function are appropriate for the definition of a function. This
15142 /// takes care of any checks that cannot be performed on the
15143 /// declaration itself, e.g., that the types of each of the function
15144 /// parameters are complete.
15145 bool Sema::CheckParmsForFunctionDef(ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Parameters,
15146  bool CheckParameterNames) {
15147  bool HasInvalidParm = false;
15148  for (ParmVarDecl *Param : Parameters) {
15149  // C99 6.7.5.3p4: the parameters in a parameter type list in a
15150  // function declarator that is part of a function definition of
15151  // that function shall not have incomplete type.
15152  //
15153  // This is also C++ [dcl.fct]p6.
15154  if (!Param->isInvalidDecl() &&
15155  RequireCompleteType(Param->getLocation(), Param->getType(),
15156  diag::err_typecheck_decl_incomplete_type)) {
15157  Param->setInvalidDecl();
15158  HasInvalidParm = true;
15159  }
15160 
15161  // C99 6.9.1p5: If the declarator includes a parameter type list, the
15162  // declaration of each parameter shall include an identifier.
15163  if (CheckParameterNames && Param->getIdentifier() == nullptr &&
15164  !Param->isImplicit() && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
15165  // Diagnose this as an extension in C17 and earlier.
15166  if (!getLangOpts().C2x)
15167  Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::ext_parameter_name_omitted_c2x);
15168  }
15169 
15170  // C99 6.7.5.3p12:
15171  // If the function declarator is not part of a definition of that
15172  // function, parameters may have incomplete type and may use the [*]
15173  // notation in their sequences of declarator specifiers to specify
15174  // variable length array types.
15175  QualType PType = Param->getOriginalType();
15176  // FIXME: This diagnostic should point the '[*]' if source-location
15177  // information is added for it.
15178  diagnoseArrayStarInParamType(*this, PType, Param->getLocation());
15179 
15180  // If the parameter is a c++ class type and it has to be destructed in the
15181  // callee function, declare the destructor so that it can be called by the
15182  // callee function. Do not perform any direct access check on the dtor here.
15183  if (!Param->isInvalidDecl()) {
15184  if (CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = Param->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
15185  if (!ClassDecl->isInvalidDecl() &&
15186  !ClassDecl->hasIrrelevantDestructor() &&
15187  !ClassDecl->isDependentContext() &&
15188  ClassDecl->isParamDestroyedInCallee()) {
15189  CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = LookupDestructor(ClassDecl);
15190  MarkFunctionReferenced(Param->getLocation(), Destructor);
15191  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, Param->getLocation());
15192  }
15193  }
15194  }
15195 
15196  // Parameters with the pass_object_size attribute only need to be marked
15197  // constant at function definitions. Because we lack information about
15198  // whether we're on a declaration or definition when we're instantiating the
15199  // attribute, we need to check for constness here.
15200  if (const auto *Attr = Param->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>())
15201  if (!Param->getType().isConstQualified())
15202  Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_pointers_only)
15203  << Attr->getSpelling() << 1;
15204 
15205  // Check for parameter names shadowing fields from the class.
15206  if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && !Param->isInvalidDecl()) {
15207  // The owning context for the parameter should be the function, but we
15208  // want to see if this function's declaration context is a record.
15209  DeclContext *DC = Param->getDeclContext();
15210  if (DC && DC->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
15211  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC->getParent()))
15212  CheckShadowInheritedFields(Param->getLocation(), Param->getDeclName(),
15213  RD, /*DeclIsField*/ false);
15214  }
15215  }
15216  }
15217 
15218  return HasInvalidParm;
15219 }
15220 
15221 Optional<std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>>
15222 static getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(const Expr *E, ASTContext &Ctx);
15223 
15224 /// Compute the alignment and offset of the base class object given the
15225 /// derived-to-base cast expression and the alignment and offset of the derived
15226 /// class object.
15227 static std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>
15228 getDerivedToBaseAlignmentAndOffset(const CastExpr *CE, QualType DerivedType,
15229  CharUnits BaseAlignment, CharUnits Offset,
15230  ASTContext &Ctx) {
15231  for (auto PathI = CE->path_begin(), PathE = CE->path_end(); PathI != PathE;
15232  ++PathI) {
15233  const CXXBaseSpecifier *Base = *PathI;
15234  const CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl = Base->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
15235  if (Base->isVirtual()) {
15236  // The complete object may have a lower alignment than the non-virtual
15237  // alignment of the base, in which case the base may be misaligned. Choose
15238  // the smaller of the non-virtual alignment and BaseAlignment, which is a
15239  // conservative lower bound of the complete object alignment.
15240  CharUnits NonVirtualAlignment =
15241  Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(BaseDecl).getNonVirtualAlignment();
15242  BaseAlignment = std::min(BaseAlignment, NonVirtualAlignment);
15243  Offset = CharUnits::Zero();
15244  } else {
15245  const ASTRecordLayout &RL =
15246  Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(DerivedType->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
15247  Offset += RL.getBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
15248  }
15249  DerivedType = Base->getType();
15250  }
15251 
15252  return std::make_pair(BaseAlignment, Offset);
15253 }
15254 
15255 /// Compute the alignment and offset of a binary additive operator.
15256 static Optional<std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>>
15257 getAlignmentAndOffsetFromBinAddOrSub(const Expr *PtrE, const Expr *IntE,
15258  bool IsSub, ASTContext &Ctx) {
15259  QualType PointeeType = PtrE->getType()->getPointeeType();
15260 
15261  if (!PointeeType->isConstantSizeType())
15262  return llvm::None;
15263 
15264  auto P = getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(PtrE, Ctx);
15265 
15266  if (!P)
15267  return llvm::None;
15268 
15269  CharUnits EltSize = Ctx.getTypeSizeInChars(PointeeType);
15270  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> IdxRes = IntE->getIntegerConstantExpr(Ctx)) {
15271  CharUnits Offset = EltSize * IdxRes->getExtValue();
15272  if (IsSub)
15273  Offset = -Offset;
15274  return std::make_pair(P->first, P->second + Offset);
15275  }
15276 
15277  // If the integer expression isn't a constant expression, compute the lower
15278  // bound of the alignment using the alignment and offset of the pointer
15279  // expression and the element size.
15280  return std::make_pair(
15281  P->first.alignmentAtOffset(P->second).alignmentAtOffset(EltSize),
15282  CharUnits::Zero());
15283 }
15284 
15285 /// This helper function takes an lvalue expression and returns the alignment of
15286 /// a VarDecl and a constant offset from the VarDecl.
15287 Optional<std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>>
15288 static getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(const Expr *E, ASTContext &Ctx) {
15289  E = E->IgnoreParens();
15290  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
15291  default:
15292  break;
15293  case Stmt::CStyleCastExprClass:
15294  case Stmt::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
15295  case Stmt::ImplicitCastExprClass: {
15296  auto *CE = cast<CastExpr>(E);
15297  const Expr *From = CE->getSubExpr();
15298  switch (CE->getCastKind()) {
15299  default:
15300  break;
15301  case CK_NoOp:
15302  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(From, Ctx);
15303  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
15304  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
15305  auto P = getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(From, Ctx);
15306  if (!P)
15307  break;
15308  return getDerivedToBaseAlignmentAndOffset(CE, From->getType(), P->first,
15309  P->second, Ctx);
15310  }
15311  }
15312  break;
15313  }
15314  case Stmt::ArraySubscriptExprClass: {
15315  auto *ASE = cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E);
15316  return getAlignmentAndOffsetFromBinAddOrSub(ASE->getBase(), ASE->getIdx(),
15317  false, Ctx);
15318  }
15319  case Stmt::DeclRefExprClass: {
15320  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)->getDecl())) {
15321  // FIXME: If VD is captured by copy or is an escaping __block variable,
15322  // use the alignment of VD's type.
15323  if (!VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
15324  return std::make_pair(Ctx.getDeclAlign(VD), CharUnits::Zero());
15325  if (VD->hasInit())
15326  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(VD->getInit(), Ctx);
15327  }
15328  break;
15329  }
15330  case Stmt::MemberExprClass: {
15331  auto *ME = cast<MemberExpr>(E);
15332  auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl());
15333  if (!FD || FD->getType()->isReferenceType() ||
15334  FD->getParent()->isInvalidDecl())
15335  break;
15336  Optional<std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>> P;
15337  if (ME->isArrow())
15338  P = getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(ME->getBase(), Ctx);
15339  else
15340  P = getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(ME->getBase(), Ctx);
15341  if (!P)
15342  break;
15343  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(FD->getParent());
15344  uint64_t Offset = Layout.getFieldOffset(FD->getFieldIndex());
15345  return std::make_pair(P->first,
15346  P->second + CharUnits::fromQuantity(Offset));
15347  }
15348  case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
15349  auto *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(E);
15350  switch (UO->getOpcode()) {
15351  default:
15352  break;
15353  case UO_Deref:
15354  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(UO->getSubExpr(), Ctx);
15355  }
15356  break;
15357  }
15358  case Stmt::BinaryOperatorClass: {
15359  auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(E);
15360  auto Opcode = BO->getOpcode();
15361  switch (Opcode) {
15362  default:
15363  break;
15364  case BO_Comma:
15365  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(BO->getRHS(), Ctx);
15366  }
15367  break;
15368  }
15369  }
15370  return llvm::None;
15371 }
15372 
15373 /// This helper function takes a pointer expression and returns the alignment of
15374 /// a VarDecl and a constant offset from the VarDecl.
15375 Optional<std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>>
15376 static getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(const Expr *E, ASTContext &Ctx) {
15377  E = E->IgnoreParens();
15378  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
15379  default:
15380  break;
15381  case Stmt::CStyleCastExprClass:
15382  case Stmt::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
15383  case Stmt::ImplicitCastExprClass: {
15384  auto *CE = cast<CastExpr>(E);
15385  const Expr *From = CE->getSubExpr();
15386  switch (CE->getCastKind()) {
15387  default:
15388  break;
15389  case CK_NoOp:
15390  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(From, Ctx);
15391  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
15392  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(From, Ctx);
15393  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
15394  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
15395  auto P = getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(From, Ctx);
15396  if (!P)
15397  break;
15398  return getDerivedToBaseAlignmentAndOffset(
15399  CE, From->getType()->getPointeeType(), P->first, P->second, Ctx);
15400  }
15401  }
15402  break;
15403  }
15404  case Stmt::CXXThisExprClass: {
15405  auto *RD = E->getType()->getPointeeType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
15406  CharUnits Alignment = Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(RD).getNonVirtualAlignment();
15407  return std::make_pair(Alignment, CharUnits::Zero());
15408  }
15409  case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
15410  auto *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(E);
15411  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
15412  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromLValue(UO->getSubExpr(), Ctx);
15413  break;
15414  }
15415  case Stmt::BinaryOperatorClass: {
15416  auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(E);
15417  auto Opcode = BO->getOpcode();
15418  switch (Opcode) {
15419  default:
15420  break;
15421  case BO_Add:
15422  case BO_Sub: {
15423  const Expr *LHS = BO->getLHS(), *RHS = BO->getRHS();
15424  if (Opcode == BO_Add && !RHS->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
15425  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
15426  return getAlignmentAndOffsetFromBinAddOrSub(LHS, RHS, Opcode == BO_Sub,
15427  Ctx);
15428  }
15429  case BO_Comma:
15430  return getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(BO->getRHS(), Ctx);
15431  }
15432  break;
15433  }
15434  }
15435  return llvm::None;
15436 }
15437 
15438 static CharUnits getPresumedAlignmentOfPointer(const Expr *E, Sema &S) {
15439  // See if we can compute the alignment of a VarDecl and an offset from it.
15440  Optional<std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>> P =
15441  getBaseAlignmentAndOffsetFromPtr(E, S.Context);
15442 
15443  if (P)
15444  return P->first.alignmentAtOffset(P->second);
15445 
15446  // If that failed, return the type's alignment.
15447  return S.Context.getTypeAlignInChars(E->getType()->getPointeeType());
15448 }
15449 
15450 /// CheckCastAlign - Implements -Wcast-align, which warns when a
15451 /// pointer cast increases the alignment requirements.
15452 void Sema::CheckCastAlign(Expr *Op, QualType T, SourceRange TRange) {
15453  // This is actually a lot of work to potentially be doing on every
15454  // cast; don't do it if we're ignoring -Wcast_align (as is the default).
15455  if (getDiagnostics().isIgnored(diag::warn_cast_align, TRange.getBegin()))
15456  return;
15457 
15458  // Ignore dependent types.
15459  if (T->isDependentType() || Op->getType()->isDependentType())
15460  return;
15461 
15462  // Require that the destination be a pointer type.
15463  const PointerType *DestPtr = T->getAs<PointerType>();
15464  if (!DestPtr) return;
15465 
15466  // If the destination has alignment 1, we're done.
15467  QualType DestPointee = DestPtr->getPointeeType();
15468  if (DestPointee->isIncompleteType()) return;
15469  CharUnits DestAlign = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(DestPointee);
15470  if (DestAlign.isOne()) return;
15471 
15472  // Require that the source be a pointer type.
15473  const PointerType *SrcPtr = Op->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
15474  if (!SrcPtr) return;
15475  QualType SrcPointee = SrcPtr->getPointeeType();
15476 
15477  // Explicitly allow casts from cv void*. We already implicitly
15478  // allowed casts to cv void*, since they have alignment 1.
15479  // Also allow casts involving incomplete types, which implicitly
15480  // includes 'void'.
15481  if (SrcPointee->isIncompleteType()) return;
15482 
15483  CharUnits SrcAlign = getPresumedAlignmentOfPointer(Op, *this);
15484 
15485  if (SrcAlign >= DestAlign) return;
15486 
15487  Diag(TRange.getBegin(), diag::warn_cast_align)
15488  << Op->getType() << T
15489  << static_cast<unsigned>(SrcAlign.getQuantity())
15490  << static_cast<unsigned>(DestAlign.getQuantity())
15491  << TRange << Op->getSourceRange();
15492 }
15493 
15494 /// Check whether this array fits the idiom of a size-one tail padded
15495 /// array member of a struct.
15496 ///
15497 /// We avoid emitting out-of-bounds access warnings for such arrays as they are
15498 /// commonly used to emulate flexible arrays in C89 code.
15499 static bool IsTailPaddedMemberArray(Sema &S, const llvm::APInt &Size,
15500  const NamedDecl *ND) {
15501  if (Size != 1 || !ND) return false;
15502 
15503  const FieldDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ND);
15504  if (!FD) return false;
15505 
15506  // Don't consider sizes resulting from macro expansions or template argument
15507  // substitution to form C89 tail-padded arrays.
15508 
15509  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = FD->getTypeSourceInfo();
15510  while (TInfo) {
15511  TypeLoc TL = TInfo->getTypeLoc();
15512  // Look through typedefs.
15513  if (TypedefTypeLoc TTL = TL.getAs<TypedefTypeLoc>()) {
15514  const TypedefNameDecl *TDL = TTL.getTypedefNameDecl();
15515  TInfo = TDL->getTypeSourceInfo();
15516  continue;
15517  }
15518  if (ConstantArrayTypeLoc CTL = TL.getAs<ConstantArrayTypeLoc>()) {
15519  const Expr *SizeExpr = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(CTL.getSizeExpr());
15520  if (!SizeExpr || SizeExpr->getExprLoc().isMacroID())
15521  return false;
15522  }
15523  break;
15524  }
15525 
15526  const RecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(FD->getDeclContext());
15527  if (!RD) return false;
15528  if (RD->isUnion()) return false;
15529  if (const CXXRecordDecl *CRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
15530  if (!CRD->isStandardLayout()) return false;
15531  }
15532 
15533  // See if this is the last field decl in the record.
15534  const Decl *D = FD;
15535  while ((D = D->getNextDeclInContext()))
15536  if (isa<FieldDecl>(D))
15537  return false;
15538  return true;
15539 }
15540 
15541 void Sema::CheckArrayAccess(const Expr *BaseExpr, const Expr *IndexExpr,
15542  const ArraySubscriptExpr *ASE,
15543  bool AllowOnePastEnd, bool IndexNegated) {
15544  // Already diagnosed by the constant evaluator.
15545  if (isConstantEvaluated())
15546  return;
15547 
15548  IndexExpr = IndexExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
15549  if (IndexExpr->isValueDependent())
15550  return;
15551 
15552  const Type *EffectiveType =
15553  BaseExpr->getType()->getPointeeOrArrayElementType();
15554  BaseExpr = BaseExpr->IgnoreParenCasts();
15555  const ConstantArrayType *ArrayTy =
15556  Context.getAsConstantArrayType(BaseExpr->getType());
15557 
15558  const Type *BaseType =
15559  ArrayTy == nullptr ? nullptr : ArrayTy->getElementType().getTypePtr();
15560  bool IsUnboundedArray = (BaseType == nullptr);
15561  if (EffectiveType->isDependentType() ||
15562  (!IsUnboundedArray && BaseType->isDependentType()))
15563  return;
15564 
15565  Expr::EvalResult Result;
15566  if (!IndexExpr->EvaluateAsInt(Result, Context, Expr::SE_AllowSideEffects))
15567  return;
15568 
15569  llvm::APSInt index = Result.Val.getInt();
15570  if (IndexNegated) {
15571  index.setIsUnsigned(false);
15572  index = -index;
15573  }
15574 
15575  const NamedDecl *ND = nullptr;
15576  if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(BaseExpr))
15577  ND = DRE->getDecl();
15578  if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(BaseExpr))
15579  ND = ME->getMemberDecl();
15580 
15581  if (IsUnboundedArray) {
15582  if (index.isUnsigned() || !index.isNegative()) {
15583  const auto &ASTC = getASTContext();
15584  unsigned AddrBits =
15585  ASTC.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(ASTC.getTargetAddressSpace(
15586  EffectiveType->getCanonicalTypeInternal()));
15587  if (index.getBitWidth() < AddrBits)
15588  index = index.zext(AddrBits);
15589  Optional<CharUnits> ElemCharUnits =
15590  ASTC.getTypeSizeInCharsIfKnown(EffectiveType);
15591  // PR50741 - If EffectiveType has unknown size (e.g., if it's a void
15592  // pointer) bounds-checking isn't meaningful.
15593  if (!ElemCharUnits)
15594  return;
15595  llvm::APInt ElemBytes(index.getBitWidth(), ElemCharUnits->getQuantity());
15596  // If index has more active bits than address space, we already know
15597  // we have a bounds violation to warn about. Otherwise, compute
15598  // address of (index + 1)th element, and warn about bounds violation
15599  // only if that address exceeds address space.
15600  if (index.getActiveBits() <= AddrBits) {
15601  bool Overflow;
15602  llvm::APInt Product(index);
15603  Product += 1;
15604  Product = Product.umul_ov(ElemBytes, Overflow);
15605  if (!Overflow && Product.getActiveBits() <= AddrBits)
15606  return;
15607  }
15608 
15609  // Need to compute max possible elements in address space, since that
15610  // is included in diag message.
15611  llvm::APInt MaxElems = llvm::APInt::getMaxValue(AddrBits);
15612  MaxElems = MaxElems.zext(std::max(AddrBits + 1, ElemBytes.getBitWidth()));
15613  MaxElems += 1;
15614  ElemBytes = ElemBytes.zextOrTrunc(MaxElems.getBitWidth());
15615  MaxElems = MaxElems.udiv(ElemBytes);
15616 
15617  unsigned DiagID =
15618  ASE ? diag::warn_array_index_exceeds_max_addressable_bounds
15619  : diag::warn_ptr_arith_exceeds_max_addressable_bounds;
15620 
15621  // Diag message shows element size in bits and in "bytes" (platform-
15622  // dependent CharUnits)
15623  DiagRuntimeBehavior(BaseExpr->getBeginLoc(), BaseExpr,
15624  PDiag(DiagID)
15625  << toString(index, 10, true) << AddrBits
15626  << (unsigned)ASTC.toBits(*ElemCharUnits)
15627  << toString(ElemBytes, 10, false)
15628  << toString(MaxElems, 10, false)
15629  << (unsigned)MaxElems.getLimitedValue(~0U)
15630  << IndexExpr->getSourceRange());
15631 
15632  if (!ND) {
15633  // Try harder to find a NamedDecl to point at in the note.
15634  while (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(BaseExpr))
15635  BaseExpr = ASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts();
15636  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(BaseExpr))
15637  ND = DRE->getDecl();
15638  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(BaseExpr))
15639  ND = ME->getMemberDecl();
15640  }
15641 
15642  if (ND)
15643  DiagRuntimeBehavior(ND->getBeginLoc(), BaseExpr,
15644  PDiag(diag::note_array_declared_here) << ND);
15645  }
15646  return;
15647  }
15648 
15649  if (index.isUnsigned() || !index.isNegative()) {
15650  // It is possible that the type of the base expression after
15651  // IgnoreParenCasts is incomplete, even though the type of the base
15652  // expression before IgnoreParenCasts is complete (see PR39746 for an
15653  // example). In this case we have no information about whether the array
15654  // access exceeds the array bounds. However we can still diagnose an array
15655  // access which precedes the array bounds.
15656  if (BaseType->isIncompleteType())
15657  return;
15658 
15659  llvm::APInt size = ArrayTy->getSize();
15660  if (!size.isStrictlyPositive())
15661  return;
15662 
15663  if (BaseType != EffectiveType) {
15664  // Make sure we're comparing apples to apples when comparing index to size
15665  uint64_t ptrarith_typesize = Context.getTypeSize(EffectiveType);
15666  uint64_t array_typesize = Context.getTypeSize(BaseType);
15667  // Handle ptrarith_typesize being zero, such as when casting to void*
15668  if (!ptrarith_typesize) ptrarith_typesize = 1;
15669  if (ptrarith_typesize != array_typesize) {
15670  // There's a cast to a different size type involved
15671  uint64_t ratio = array_typesize / ptrarith_typesize;
15672  // TODO: Be smarter about handling cases where array_typesize is not a
15673  // multiple of ptrarith_typesize
15674  if (ptrarith_typesize * ratio == array_typesize)
15675  size *= llvm::APInt(size.getBitWidth(), ratio);
15676  }
15677  }
15678 
15679  if (size.getBitWidth() > index.getBitWidth())
15680  index = index.zext(size.getBitWidth());
15681  else if (size.getBitWidth() < index.getBitWidth())
15682  size = size.zext(index.getBitWidth());
15683 
15684  // For array subscripting the index must be less than size, but for pointer
15685  // arithmetic also allow the index (offset) to be equal to size since
15686  // computing the next address after the end of the array is legal and
15687  // commonly done e.g. in C++ iterators and range-based for loops.
15688  if (AllowOnePastEnd ? index.ule(size) : index.ult(size))
15689  return;
15690 
15691  // Also don't warn for arrays of size 1 which are members of some
15692  // structure. These are often used to approximate flexible arrays in C89
15693  // code.
15694  if (IsTailPaddedMemberArray(*this, size, ND))
15695  return;
15696 
15697  // Suppress the warning if the subscript expression (as identified by the
15698  // ']' location) and the index expression are both from macro expansions
15699  // within a system header.
15700  if (ASE) {
15701  SourceLocation RBracketLoc = SourceMgr.getSpellingLoc(
15702  ASE->getRBracketLoc());
15703  if (SourceMgr.isInSystemHeader(RBracketLoc)) {
15704  SourceLocation IndexLoc =
15705  SourceMgr.getSpellingLoc(IndexExpr->getBeginLoc());
15706  if (SourceMgr.isWrittenInSameFile(RBracketLoc, IndexLoc))
15707  return;
15708  }
15709  }
15710 
15711  unsigned DiagID = ASE ? diag::warn_array_index_exceeds_bounds
15712  : diag::warn_ptr_arith_exceeds_bounds;
15713 
15714  DiagRuntimeBehavior(BaseExpr->getBeginLoc(), BaseExpr,
15715  PDiag(DiagID) << toString(index, 10, true)
15716  << toString(size, 10, true)
15717  << (unsigned)size.getLimitedValue(~0U)
15718  << IndexExpr->getSourceRange());
15719  } else {
15720  unsigned DiagID = diag::warn_array_index_precedes_bounds;
15721  if (!ASE) {
15722  DiagID = diag::warn_ptr_arith_precedes_bounds;
15723  if (index.isNegative()) index = -index;
15724  }
15725 
15726  DiagRuntimeBehavior(BaseExpr->getBeginLoc(), BaseExpr,
15727  PDiag(DiagID) << toString(index, 10, true)
15728  << IndexExpr->getSourceRange());
15729  }
15730 
15731  if (!ND) {
15732  // Try harder to find a NamedDecl to point at in the note.
15733  while (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(BaseExpr))
15734  BaseExpr = ASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts();
15735  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(BaseExpr))
15736  ND = DRE->getDecl();
15737  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(BaseExpr))
15738  ND = ME->getMemberDecl();
15739  }
15740 
15741  if (ND)
15742  DiagRuntimeBehavior(ND->getBeginLoc(), BaseExpr,
15743  PDiag(diag::note_array_declared_here) << ND);
15744 }
15745 
15746 void Sema::CheckArrayAccess(const Expr *expr) {
15747  int AllowOnePastEnd = 0;
15748  while (expr) {
15749  expr = expr->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
15750  switch (expr->getStmtClass()) {
15751  case Stmt::ArraySubscriptExprClass: {
15752  const ArraySubscriptExpr *ASE = cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(expr);
15753  CheckArrayAccess(ASE->getBase(), ASE->getIdx(), ASE,
15754  AllowOnePastEnd > 0);
15755  expr = ASE->getBase();
15756  break;
15757  }
15758  case Stmt::MemberExprClass: {
15759  expr = cast<MemberExpr>(expr)->getBase();
15760  break;
15761  }
15762  case Stmt::OMPArraySectionExprClass: {
15763  const OMPArraySectionExpr *ASE = cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(expr);
15764  if (ASE->getLowerBound())
15765  CheckArrayAccess(ASE->getBase(), ASE->getLowerBound(),
15766  /*ASE=*/nullptr, AllowOnePastEnd > 0);
15767  return;
15768  }
15769  case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
15770  // Only unwrap the * and & unary operators
15771  const UnaryOperator *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(expr);
15772  expr = UO->getSubExpr();
15773  switch (UO->getOpcode()) {
15774  case UO_AddrOf:
15775  AllowOnePastEnd++;
15776  break;
15777  case UO_Deref:
15778  AllowOnePastEnd--;
15779  break;
15780  default:
15781  return;
15782  }
15783  break;
15784  }
15785  case Stmt::ConditionalOperatorClass: {
15786  const ConditionalOperator *cond = cast<ConditionalOperator>(expr);
15787  if (const Expr *lhs = cond->getLHS())
15788  CheckArrayAccess(lhs);
15789  if (const Expr *rhs = cond->getRHS())
15790  CheckArrayAccess(rhs);
15791  return;
15792  }
15793  case Stmt::CXXOperatorCallExprClass: {
15794  const auto *OCE = cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(expr);
15795  for (const auto *Arg : OCE->arguments())
15796  CheckArrayAccess(Arg);
15797  return;
15798  }
15799  default:
15800  return;
15801  }
15802  }
15803 }
15804 
15805 //===--- CHECK: Objective-C retain cycles ----------------------------------//
15806 
15807 namespace {
15808 
15809 struct RetainCycleOwner {
15810  VarDecl *Variable = nullptr;
15811  SourceRange Range;
15812  SourceLocation Loc;
15813  bool Indirect = false;
15814 
15815  RetainCycleOwner() = default;
15816 
15817  void setLocsFrom(Expr *e) {
15818  Loc = e->getExprLoc();
15819  Range = e->getSourceRange();
15820  }
15821 };
15822 
15823 } // namespace
15824 
15825 /// Consider whether capturing the given variable can possibly lead to
15826 /// a retain cycle.
15827 static bool considerVariable(VarDecl *var, Expr *ref, RetainCycleOwner &owner) {
15828  // In ARC, it's captured strongly iff the variable has __strong
15829  // lifetime. In MRR, it's captured strongly if the variable is
15830  // __block and has an appropriate type.
15831  if (var->getType().getObjCLifetime() != Qualifiers::OCL_Strong)
15832  return false;
15833 
15834  owner.Variable = var;
15835  if (ref)
15836  owner.setLocsFrom(ref);
15837  return true;
15838 }
15839 
15840 static bool findRetainCycleOwner(Sema &S, Expr *e, RetainCycleOwner &owner) {
15841  while (true) {
15842  e = e->IgnoreParens();
15843  if (CastExpr *cast = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(e)) {
15844  switch (cast->getCastKind()) {
15845  case CK_BitCast:
15846  case CK_LValueBitCast:
15847  case CK_LValueToRValue:
15848  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
15849  e = cast->getSubExpr();
15850  continue;
15851 
15852  default:
15853  return false;
15854  }
15855  }
15856 
15857  if (ObjCIvarRefExpr *ref = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(e)) {
15858  ObjCIvarDecl *ivar = ref->getDecl();
15859  if (ivar->getType().getObjCLifetime() != Qualifiers::OCL_Strong)
15860  return false;
15861 
15862  // Try to find a retain cycle in the base.
15863  if (!findRetainCycleOwner(S, ref->getBase(), owner))
15864  return false;
15865 
15866  if (ref->isFreeIvar()) owner.setLocsFrom(ref);
15867  owner.Indirect = true;
15868  return true;
15869  }
15870 
15871  if (DeclRefExpr *ref = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(e)) {
15872  VarDecl *var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ref->getDecl());
15873  if (!var) return false;
15874  return considerVariable(var, ref, owner);
15875  }
15876 
15877  if (MemberExpr *member = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(e)) {
15878  if (member->isArrow()) return false;
15879 
15880  // Don't count this as an indirect ownership.
15881  e = member->getBase();
15882  continue;
15883  }
15884 
15885  if (PseudoObjectExpr *pseudo = dyn_cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(e)) {
15886  // Only pay attention to pseudo-objects on property references.
15887  ObjCPropertyRefExpr *pre
15888  = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(pseudo->getSyntacticForm()
15889  ->IgnoreParens());
15890  if (!pre) return false;
15891  if (pre->isImplicitProperty()) return false;
15892  ObjCPropertyDecl *property = pre->getExplicitProperty();
15893  if (!property->isRetaining() &&
15894  !(property->getPropertyIvarDecl() &&
15895  property->getPropertyIvarDecl()->getType()
15896  .getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong))
15897  return false;
15898 
15899  owner.Indirect = true;
15900  if (pre->isSuperReceiver()) {
15901  owner.Variable = S.getCurMethodDecl()->getSelfDecl();
15902  if (!owner.Variable)
15903  return false;
15904  owner.Loc = pre->getLocation();
15905  owner.Range = pre->getSourceRange();
15906  return true;
15907  }
15908  e = const_cast<Expr*>(cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(pre->getBase())
15909  ->getSourceExpr());
15910  continue;
15911  }
15912 
15913  // Array ivars?
15914 
15915  return false;
15916  }
15917 }
15918 
15919 namespace {
15920 
15921  struct FindCaptureVisitor : EvaluatedExprVisitor<FindCaptureVisitor> {
15922  ASTContext &Context;
15923  VarDecl *Variable;
15924  Expr *Capturer = nullptr;
15925  bool VarWillBeReased = false;
15926 
15927  FindCaptureVisitor(ASTContext &Context, VarDecl *variable)
15928  : EvaluatedExprVisitor<FindCaptureVisitor>(Context),
15929  Context(Context), Variable(variable) {}
15930 
15931  void VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *ref) {
15932  if (ref->getDecl() == Variable && !Capturer)
15933  Capturer = ref;
15934  }
15935 
15936  void VisitObjCIvarRefExpr(ObjCIvarRefExpr *ref) {
15937  if (Capturer) return;
15938  Visit(ref->getBase());
15939  if (Capturer && ref->isFreeIvar())
15940  Capturer = ref;
15941  }
15942 
15943  void VisitBlockExpr(BlockExpr *block) {
15944  // Look inside nested blocks
15945  if (block->getBlockDecl()->capturesVariable(Variable))
15946  Visit(block->getBlockDecl()->getBody());
15947  }
15948 
15949  void VisitOpaqueValueExpr(OpaqueValueExpr *OVE) {
15950  if (Capturer) return;
15951  if (OVE->getSourceExpr())
15952  Visit(OVE->getSourceExpr());
15953  }
15954 
15955  void VisitBinaryOperator(BinaryOperator *BinOp) {
15956  if (!Variable || VarWillBeReased || BinOp->getOpcode() != BO_Assign)
15957  return;
15958  Expr *LHS = BinOp->getLHS();
15959  if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclRefExpr>(LHS)) {
15960  if (DRE->getDecl() != Variable)
15961  return;
15962  if (Expr *RHS = BinOp->getRHS()) {
15963  RHS = RHS->IgnoreParenCasts();
15964  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Value;
15965  VarWillBeReased =
15966  (RHS && (Value = RHS->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)) &&
15967  *Value == 0);
15968  }
15969  }
15970  }
15971  };
15972 
15973 } // namespace
15974 
15975 /// Check whether the given argument is a block which captures a
15976 /// variable.
15977 static Expr *findCapturingExpr(Sema &S, Expr *e, RetainCycleOwner &owner) {
15978  assert(owner.Variable && owner.Loc.isValid());
15979 
15980  e = e->IgnoreParenCasts();
15981 
15982  // Look through [^{...} copy] and Block_copy(^{...}).
15983  if (ObjCMessageExpr *ME = dyn_cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(e)) {
15984  Selector Cmd = ME->getSelector();
15985  if (Cmd.isUnarySelector() && Cmd.getNameForSlot(0) == "copy") {
15986  e = ME->getInstanceReceiver();
15987  if (!e)
15988  return nullptr;
15989  e = e->IgnoreParenCasts();
15990  }
15991  } else if (CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(e)) {
15992  if (CE->getNumArgs() == 1) {
15993  FunctionDecl *Fn = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CE->getCalleeDecl());
15994  if (Fn) {
15995  const IdentifierInfo *FnI = Fn->getIdentifier();
15996  if (FnI && FnI->isStr("_Block_copy")) {
15997  e = CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenCasts();
15998  }
15999  }
16000  }
16001  }
16002 
16003  BlockExpr *block = dyn_cast<BlockExpr>(e);
16004  if (!block || !block->getBlockDecl()->capturesVariable(owner.Variable))
16005  return nullptr;
16006 
16007  FindCaptureVisitor visitor(S.Context, owner.Variable);
16008  visitor.Visit(block->getBlockDecl()->getBody());
16009  return visitor.VarWillBeReased ? nullptr : visitor.Capturer;
16010 }
16011 
16012 static void diagnoseRetainCycle(Sema &S, Expr *capturer,
16013  RetainCycleOwner &owner) {
16014  assert(capturer);
16015  assert(owner.Variable && owner.Loc.isValid());
16016 
16017  S.Diag(capturer->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_arc_retain_cycle)
16018  << owner.Variable << capturer->getSourceRange();
16019  S.Diag(owner.Loc, diag::note_arc_retain_cycle_owner)
16020  << owner.Indirect << owner.Range;
16021 }
16022 
16023 /// Check for a keyword selector that starts with the word 'add' or
16024 /// 'set'.
16025 static bool isSetterLikeSelector(Selector sel) {
16026  if (sel.isUnarySelector()) return false;
16027 
16028  StringRef str = sel.getNameForSlot(0);
16029  while (!str.empty() && str.front() == '_') str = str.substr(1);
16030  if (str.startswith("set"))
16031  str = str.substr(3);
16032  else if (str.startswith("add")) {
16033  // Specially allow 'addOperationWithBlock:'.
16034  if (sel.getNumArgs() == 1 && str.startswith("addOperationWithBlock"))
16035  return false;
16036  str = str.substr(3);
16037  }
16038  else
16039  return false;
16040 
16041  if (str.empty()) return true;
16042  return !isLowercase(str.front());
16043 }
16044 
16045 static Optional<int> GetNSMutableArrayArgumentIndex(Sema &S,
16046  ObjCMessageExpr *Message) {
16047  bool IsMutableArray = S.NSAPIObj->isSubclassOfNSClass(
16048  Message->getReceiverInterface(),
16049  NSAPI::ClassId_NSMutableArray);
16050  if (!IsMutableArray) {
16051  return None;
16052  }
16053 
16054  Selector Sel = Message->getSelector();
16055 
16056  Optional<NSAPI::NSArrayMethodKind> MKOpt =
16057  S.NSAPIObj->getNSArrayMethodKind(Sel);
16058  if (!MKOpt) {
16059  return None;
16060  }
16061 
16062  NSAPI::NSArrayMethodKind MK = *MKOpt;
16063 
16064  switch (MK) {
16065  case NSAPI::NSMutableArr_addObject:
16066  case NSAPI::NSMutableArr_insertObjectAtIndex:
16067  case NSAPI::NSMutableArr_setObjectAtIndexedSubscript:
16068  return 0;
16069  case NSAPI::NSMutableArr_replaceObjectAtIndex:
16070  return 1;
16071 
16072  default:
16073  return None;
16074  }
16075 
16076  return None;
16077 }
16078 
16079 static
16080 Optional<int> GetNSMutableDictionaryArgumentIndex(Sema &S,
16081  ObjCMessageExpr *Message) {
16082  bool IsMutableDictionary = S.NSAPIObj->isSubclassOfNSClass(
16083  Message->getReceiverInterface(),
16084  NSAPI::ClassId_NSMutableDictionary);
16085  if (!IsMutableDictionary) {
16086  return None;
16087  }
16088 
16089  Selector Sel = Message->getSelector();
16090 
16091  Optional<NSAPI::NSDictionaryMethodKind> MKOpt =
16092  S.NSAPIObj->getNSDictionaryMethodKind(Sel);
16093  if (!MKOpt) {
16094  return None;
16095  }
16096 
16097  NSAPI::NSDictionaryMethodKind MK = *MKOpt;
16098 
16099  switch (MK) {
16100  case NSAPI::NSMutableDict_setObjectForKey:
16101  case NSAPI::NSMutableDict_setValueForKey:
16102  case NSAPI::NSMutableDict_setObjectForKeyedSubscript:
16103  return 0;
16104 
16105  default:
16106  return None;
16107  }
16108 
16109  return None;
16110 }
16111 
16112 static Optional<int> GetNSSetArgumentIndex(Sema &S, ObjCMessageExpr *Message) {
16113  bool IsMutableSet = S.NSAPIObj->isSubclassOfNSClass(
16114  Message->getReceiverInterface(),
16115  NSAPI::ClassId_NSMutableSet);
16116 
16117  bool IsMutableOrderedSet = S.NSAPIObj->isSubclassOfNSClass(
16118  Message->getReceiverInterface(),
16119  NSAPI::ClassId_NSMutableOrderedSet);
16120  if (!IsMutableSet && !IsMutableOrderedSet) {
16121  return None;
16122  }
16123 
16124  Selector Sel = Message->getSelector();
16125 
16126  Optional<NSAPI::NSSetMethodKind> MKOpt = S.NSAPIObj->getNSSetMethodKind(Sel);
16127  if (!MKOpt) {
16128  return None;
16129  }
16130 
16131  NSAPI::NSSetMethodKind MK = *MKOpt;
16132 
16133  switch (MK) {
16134  case NSAPI::NSMutableSet_addObject:
16135  case NSAPI::NSOrderedSet_setObjectAtIndex:
16136  case NSAPI::NSOrderedSet_setObjectAtIndexedSubscript:
16137  case NSAPI::NSOrderedSet_insertObjectAtIndex:
16138  return 0;
16139  case NSAPI::NSOrderedSet_replaceObjectAtIndexWithObject:
16140  return 1;
16141  }
16142 
16143  return None;
16144 }
16145 
16146 void Sema::CheckObjCCircularContainer(ObjCMessageExpr *Message) {
16147  if (!Message->isInstanceMessage()) {
16148  return;
16149  }
16150 
16151  Optional<int> ArgOpt;
16152 
16153  if (!(ArgOpt = GetNSMutableArrayArgumentIndex(*this, Message)) &&
16154  !(ArgOpt = GetNSMutableDictionaryArgumentIndex(*this, Message)) &&
16155  !(ArgOpt = GetNSSetArgumentIndex(*this, Message))) {
16156  return;
16157  }
16158 
16159  int ArgIndex = *ArgOpt;
16160 
16161  Expr *Arg = Message->getArg(ArgIndex)->IgnoreImpCasts();
16162  if (OpaqueValueExpr *OE = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(Arg)) {
16163  Arg = OE->getSourceExpr()->IgnoreImpCasts();
16164  }
16165 
16166  if (Message->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::SuperInstance) {
16167  if (DeclRefExpr *ArgRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Arg)) {
16168  if (ArgRE->isObjCSelfExpr()) {
16169  Diag(Message->getSourceRange().getBegin(),
16170  diag::warn_objc_circular_container)
16171  << ArgRE->getDecl() << StringRef("'super'");
16172  }
16173  }
16174  } else {
16175  Expr *Receiver = Message->getInstanceReceiver()->IgnoreImpCasts();
16176 
16177  if (OpaqueValueExpr *OE = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(Receiver)) {
16178  Receiver = OE->getSourceExpr()->IgnoreImpCasts();
16179  }
16180 
16181  if (DeclRefExpr *ReceiverRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Receiver)) {
16182  if (DeclRefExpr *ArgRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Arg)) {
16183  if (ReceiverRE->getDecl() == ArgRE->getDecl()) {
16184  ValueDecl *Decl = ReceiverRE->getDecl();
16185  Diag(Message->getSourceRange().getBegin(),
16186  diag::warn_objc_circular_container)
16187  << Decl << Decl;
16188  if (!ArgRE->isObjCSelfExpr()) {
16189  Diag(Decl->getLocation(),
16190  diag::note_objc_circular_container_declared_here)
16191  << Decl;
16192  }
16193  }
16194  }
16195  } else if (ObjCIvarRefExpr *IvarRE = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(Receiver)) {
16196  if (ObjCIvarRefExpr *IvarArgRE = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(Arg)) {
16197  if (IvarRE->getDecl() == IvarArgRE->getDecl()) {
16198  ObjCIvarDecl *Decl = IvarRE->getDecl();
16199  Diag(Message->getSourceRange().getBegin(),
16200  diag::warn_objc_circular_container)
16201  << Decl << Decl;
16202  Diag(Decl->getLocation(),
16203  diag::note_objc_circular_container_declared_here)
16204  << Decl;
16205  }
16206  }
16207  }
16208  }
16209 }
16210 
16211 /// Check a message send to see if it's likely to cause a retain cycle.
16212 void Sema::checkRetainCycles(ObjCMessageExpr *msg) {
16213  // Only check instance methods whose selector looks like a setter.
16214  if (!msg->isInstanceMessage() || !isSetterLikeSelector(msg->getSelector()))
16215  return;
16216 
16217  // Try to find a variable that the receiver is strongly owned by.
16218  RetainCycleOwner owner;
16219  if (msg->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::Instance) {
16220  if (!findRetainCycleOwner(*this, msg->getInstanceReceiver(), owner))
16221  return;
16222  } else {
16223  assert(msg->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::SuperInstance);
16224  owner.Variable = getCurMethodDecl()->getSelfDecl();
16225  owner.Loc = msg->getSuperLoc();
16226  owner.Range = msg->getSuperLoc();
16227  }
16228 
16229  // Check whether the receiver is captured by any of the arguments.
16230  const ObjCMethodDecl *MD = msg->getMethodDecl();
16231  for (unsigned i = 0, e = msg->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i) {
16232  if (Expr *capturer = findCapturingExpr(*this, msg->getArg(i), owner)) {
16233  // noescape blocks should not be retained by the method.
16234  if (MD && MD->parameters()[i]->hasAttr<NoEscapeAttr>())
16235  continue;
16236  return diagnoseRetainCycle(*this, capturer, owner);
16237  }
16238  }
16239 }
16240 
16241 /// Check a property assign to see if it's likely to cause a retain cycle.
16242 void Sema::checkRetainCycles(Expr *receiver, Expr *argument) {
16243  RetainCycleOwner owner;
16244  if (!findRetainCycleOwner(*this, receiver, owner))
16245  return;
16246 
16247  if (Expr *capturer = findCapturingExpr(*this, argument, owner))
16248  diagnoseRetainCycle(*this, capturer, owner);
16249 }
16250 
16251 void Sema::checkRetainCycles(VarDecl *Var, Expr *Init) {
16252  RetainCycleOwner Owner;
16253  if (!considerVariable(Var, /*DeclRefExpr=*/nullptr, Owner))
16254  return;
16255 
16256  // Because we don't have an expression for the variable, we have to set the
16257  // location explicitly here.
16258  Owner.Loc = Var->getLocation();
16259  Owner.Range = Var->getSourceRange();
16260 
16261  if (Expr *Capturer = findCapturingExpr(*this, Init, Owner))
16262  diagnoseRetainCycle(*this, Capturer, Owner);
16263 }
16264 
16265 static bool checkUnsafeAssignLiteral(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
16266  Expr *RHS, bool isProperty) {
16267  // Check if RHS is an Objective-C object literal, which also can get
16268  // immediately zapped in a weak reference. Note that we explicitly
16269  // allow ObjCStringLiterals, since those are designed to never really die.
16270  RHS = RHS->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
16271 
16272  // This enum needs to match with the 'select' in
16273  // warn_objc_arc_literal_assign (off-by-1).
16274  Sema::ObjCLiteralKind Kind = S.CheckLiteralKind(RHS);
16275  if (Kind == Sema::LK_String || Kind == Sema::LK_None)
16276  return false;
16277 
16278  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_arc_literal_assign)
16279  << (unsigned) Kind
16280  << (isProperty ? 0 : 1)
16281  << RHS->getSourceRange();
16282 
16283  return true;
16284 }
16285 
16286 static bool checkUnsafeAssignObject(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
16287  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime LT,
16288  Expr *RHS, bool isProperty) {
16289  // Strip off any implicit cast added to get to the one ARC-specific.
16290  while (ImplicitCastExpr *cast = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(RHS)) {
16291  if (cast->getCastKind() == CK_ARCConsumeObject) {
16292  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_arc_retained_assign)
16293  << (LT == Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone)
16294  << (isProperty ? 0 : 1)
16295  << RHS->getSourceRange();
16296  return true;
16297  }
16298  RHS = cast->getSubExpr();
16299  }
16300 
16301  if (LT == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak &&
16302  checkUnsafeAssignLiteral(S, Loc, RHS, isProperty))
16303  return true;
16304 
16305  return false;
16306 }
16307 
16308 bool Sema::checkUnsafeAssigns(SourceLocation Loc,
16309  QualType LHS, Expr *RHS) {
16310  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime LT = LHS.getObjCLifetime();
16311 
16312  if (LT != Qualifiers::OCL_Weak && LT != Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone)
16313  return false;
16314 
16315  if (checkUnsafeAssignObject(*this, Loc, LT, RHS, false))
16316  return true;
16317 
16318  return false;
16319 }
16320 
16321 void Sema::checkUnsafeExprAssigns(SourceLocation Loc,
16322  Expr *LHS, Expr *RHS) {
16323  QualType LHSType;
16324  // PropertyRef on LHS type need be directly obtained from
16325  // its declaration as it has a PseudoType.
16326  ObjCPropertyRefExpr *PRE
16327  = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(LHS->IgnoreParens());
16328  if (PRE && !PRE->isImplicitProperty()) {
16329  const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PRE->getExplicitProperty();
16330  if (PD)
16331  LHSType = PD->getType();
16332  }
16333 
16334  if (LHSType.isNull())
16335  LHSType = LHS->getType();
16336 
16337  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime LT = LHSType.getObjCLifetime();
16338 
16339  if (LT == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
16340  if (!Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_arc_repeated_use_of_weak, Loc))
16341  getCurFunction()->markSafeWeakUse(LHS);
16342  }
16343 
16344  if (checkUnsafeAssigns(Loc, LHSType, RHS))
16345  return;
16346 
16347  // FIXME. Check for other life times.
16348  if (LT != Qualifiers::OCL_None)
16349  return;
16350 
16351  if (PRE) {
16352  if (PRE->isImplicitProperty())
16353  return;
16354  const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PRE->getExplicitProperty();
16355  if (!PD)
16356  return;
16357 
16358  unsigned Attributes = PD->getPropertyAttributes();
16359  if (Attributes & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_assign) {
16360  // when 'assign' attribute was not explicitly specified
16361  // by user, ignore it and rely on property type itself
16362  // for lifetime info.
16363  unsigned AsWrittenAttr = PD->getPropertyAttributesAsWritten();
16364  if (!(AsWrittenAttr & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_assign) &&
16365  LHSType->isObjCRetainableType())
16366  return;
16367 
16368  while (ImplicitCastExpr *cast = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(RHS)) {
16369  if (cast->getCastKind() == CK_ARCConsumeObject) {
16370  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_arc_retained_property_assign)
16371  << RHS->getSourceRange();
16372  return;
16373  }
16374  RHS = cast->getSubExpr();
16375  }
16376  } else if (Attributes & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_weak) {
16377  if (checkUnsafeAssignObject(*this, Loc, Qualifiers::OCL_Weak, RHS, true))
16378  return;
16379  }
16380  }
16381 }
16382 
16383 //===--- CHECK: Empty statement body (-Wempty-body) ---------------------===//
16384 
16385 static bool ShouldDiagnoseEmptyStmtBody(const SourceManager &SourceMgr,
16386  SourceLocation StmtLoc,
16387  const NullStmt *Body) {
16388  // Do not warn if the body is a macro that expands to nothing, e.g:
16389  //
16390  // #define CALL(x)
16391  // if (condition)
16392  // CALL(0);
16393  if (Body->hasLeadingEmptyMacro())
16394  return false;
16395 
16396  // Get line numbers of statement and body.
16397  bool StmtLineInvalid;
16398  unsigned StmtLine = SourceMgr.getPresumedLineNumber(StmtLoc,
16399  &StmtLineInvalid);
16400  if (StmtLineInvalid)
16401  return false;
16402 
16403  bool BodyLineInvalid;
16404  unsigned BodyLine = SourceMgr.getSpellingLineNumber(Body->getSemiLoc(),
16405  &BodyLineInvalid);
16406  if (BodyLineInvalid)
16407  return false;
16408 
16409  // Warn if null statement and body are on the same line.
16410  if (StmtLine != BodyLine)
16411  return false;
16412 
16413  return true;
16414 }
16415 
16416 void Sema::DiagnoseEmptyStmtBody(SourceLocation StmtLoc,
16417  const Stmt *Body,
16418  unsigned DiagID) {
16419  // Since this is a syntactic check, don't emit diagnostic for template
16420  // instantiations, this just adds noise.
16421  if (CurrentInstantiationScope)
16422  return;
16423 
16424  // The body should be a null statement.
16425  const NullStmt *NBody = dyn_cast<NullStmt>(Body);
16426  if (!NBody)
16427  return;
16428 
16429  // Do the usual checks.
16430  if (!ShouldDiagnoseEmptyStmtBody(SourceMgr, StmtLoc, NBody))
16431  return;
16432 
16433  Diag(NBody->getSemiLoc(), DiagID);
16434  Diag(NBody->getSemiLoc(), diag::note_empty_body_on_separate_line);
16435 }
16436 
16437 void Sema::DiagnoseEmptyLoopBody(const Stmt *S,
16438  const Stmt *PossibleBody) {
16439  assert(!CurrentInstantiationScope); // Ensured by caller
16440 
16441  SourceLocation StmtLoc;
16442  const Stmt *Body;
16443  unsigned DiagID;
16444  if (const ForStmt *FS = dyn_cast<ForStmt>(S)) {
16445  StmtLoc = FS->getRParenLoc();
16446  Body = FS->getBody();
16447  DiagID = diag::warn_empty_for_body;
16448  } else if (const WhileStmt *WS = dyn_cast<WhileStmt>(S)) {
16449  StmtLoc = WS->getCond()->getSourceRange().getEnd();
16450  Body = WS->getBody();
16451  DiagID = diag::warn_empty_while_body;
16452  } else
16453  return; // Neither `for' nor `while'.
16454 
16455  // The body should be a null statement.
16456  const NullStmt *NBody = dyn_cast<NullStmt>(Body);
16457  if (!NBody)
16458  return;
16459 
16460  // Skip expensive checks if diagnostic is disabled.
16461  if (Diags.isIgnored(DiagID, NBody->getSemiLoc()))
16462  return;
16463 
16464  // Do the usual checks.
16465  if (!ShouldDiagnoseEmptyStmtBody(SourceMgr, StmtLoc, NBody))
16466  return;
16467 
16468  // `for(...);' and `while(...);' are popular idioms, so in order to keep
16469  // noise level low, emit diagnostics only if for/while is followed by a
16470  // CompoundStmt, e.g.:
16471  // for (int i = 0; i < n; i++);
16472  // {
16473  // a(i);
16474  // }
16475  // or if for/while is followed by a statement with more indentation
16476  // than for/while itself:
16477  // for (int i = 0; i < n; i++);
16478  // a(i);
16479  bool ProbableTypo = isa<CompoundStmt>(PossibleBody);
16480  if (!ProbableTypo) {
16481  bool BodyColInvalid;
16482  unsigned BodyCol = SourceMgr.getPresumedColumnNumber(
16483  PossibleBody->getBeginLoc(), &BodyColInvalid);
16484  if (BodyColInvalid)
16485  return;
16486 
16487  bool StmtColInvalid;
16488  unsigned StmtCol =
16489  SourceMgr.getPresumedColumnNumber(S->getBeginLoc(), &StmtColInvalid);
16490  if (StmtColInvalid)
16491  return;
16492 
16493  if (BodyCol > StmtCol)
16494  ProbableTypo = true;
16495  }
16496 
16497  if (ProbableTypo) {
16498  Diag(NBody->getSemiLoc(), DiagID);
16499  Diag(NBody->getSemiLoc(), diag::note_empty_body_on_separate_line);
16500  }
16501 }
16502 
16503 //===--- CHECK: Warn on self move with std::move. -------------------------===//
16504 
16505 /// DiagnoseSelfMove - Emits a warning if a value is moved to itself.
16506 void Sema::DiagnoseSelfMove(const Expr *LHSExpr, const Expr *RHSExpr,
16507  SourceLocation OpLoc) {
16508  if (Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_sizeof_pointer_expr_memaccess, OpLoc))
16509  return;
16510 
16511  if (inTemplateInstantiation())
16512  return;
16513 
16514  // Strip parens and casts away.
16515  LHSExpr = LHSExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
16516  RHSExpr = RHSExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
16517 
16518  // Check for a call expression
16519  const CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(RHSExpr);
16520  if (!CE || CE->getNumArgs() != 1)
16521  return;
16522 
16523  // Check for a call to std::move
16524  if (!CE->isCallToStdMove())
16525  return;
16526 
16527  // Get argument from std::move
16528  RHSExpr = CE->getArg(0);
16529 
16530  const DeclRefExpr *LHSDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(LHSExpr);
16531  const DeclRefExpr *RHSDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(RHSExpr);
16532 
16533  // Two DeclRefExpr's, check that the decls are the same.
16534  if (LHSDeclRef && RHSDeclRef) {
16535  if (!LHSDeclRef->getDecl() || !RHSDeclRef->getDecl())
16536  return;
16537  if (LHSDeclRef->getDecl()->getCanonicalDecl() !=
16538  RHSDeclRef->getDecl()->getCanonicalDecl())
16539  return;
16540 
16541  Diag(OpLoc, diag::warn_self_move) << LHSExpr->getType()
16542  << LHSExpr->getSourceRange()
16543  << RHSExpr->getSourceRange();
16544  return;
16545  }
16546 
16547  // Member variables require a different approach to check for self moves.
16548  // MemberExpr's are the same if every nested MemberExpr refers to the same
16549  // Decl and that the base Expr's are DeclRefExpr's with the same Decl or
16550  // the base Expr's are CXXThisExpr's.
16551  const Expr *LHSBase = LHSExpr;
16552  const Expr *RHSBase = RHSExpr;
16553  const MemberExpr *LHSME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(LHSExpr);
16554  const MemberExpr *RHSME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(RHSExpr);
16555  if (!LHSME || !RHSME)
16556  return;
16557 
16558  while (LHSME && RHSME) {
16559  if (LHSME->getMemberDecl()->getCanonicalDecl() !=
16560  RHSME->getMemberDecl()->getCanonicalDecl())
16561  return;
16562 
16563  LHSBase = LHSME->getBase();
16564  RHSBase = RHSME->getBase();
16565  LHSME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(LHSBase);
16566  RHSME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(RHSBase);
16567  }
16568 
16569  LHSDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(LHSBase);
16570  RHSDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(RHSBase);
16571  if (LHSDeclRef && RHSDeclRef) {
16572  if (!LHSDeclRef->getDecl() || !RHSDeclRef->getDecl())
16573  return;
16574  if (LHSDeclRef->getDecl()->getCanonicalDecl() !=
16575  RHSDeclRef->getDecl()->getCanonicalDecl())
16576  return;
16577 
16578  Diag(OpLoc, diag::warn_self_move) << LHSExpr->getType()
16579  << LHSExpr->getSourceRange()
16580  << RHSExpr->getSourceRange();
16581  return;
16582  }
16583 
16584  if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(LHSBase) && isa<CXXThisExpr>(RHSBase))
16585  Diag(OpLoc, diag::warn_self_move) << LHSExpr->getType()
16586  << LHSExpr->getSourceRange()
16587  << RHSExpr->getSourceRange();
16588 }
16589 
16590 //===--- Layout compatibility ----------------------------------------------//
16591 
16592 static bool isLayoutCompatible(ASTContext &C, QualType T1, QualType T2);
16593 
16594 /// Check if two enumeration types are layout-compatible.
16595 static bool isLayoutCompatible(ASTContext &C, EnumDecl *ED1, EnumDecl *ED2) {
16596  // C++11 [dcl.enum] p8:
16597  // Two enumeration types are layout-compatible if they have the same
16598  // underlying type.
16599  return ED1->isComplete() && ED2->isComplete() &&
16600  C.hasSameType(ED1->getIntegerType(), ED2->getIntegerType());
16601 }
16602 
16603 /// Check if two fields are layout-compatible.
16604 static bool isLayoutCompatible(ASTContext &C, FieldDecl *Field1,
16605  FieldDecl *Field2) {
16606  if (!isLayoutCompatible(C, Field1->getType(), Field2->getType()))
16607  return false;
16608 
16609  if (Field1->isBitField() != Field2->isBitField())
16610  return false;
16611 
16612  if (Field1->isBitField()) {
16613  // Make sure that the bit-fields are the same length.
16614  unsigned Bits1 = Field1->getBitWidthValue(C);
16615  unsigned Bits2 = Field2->getBitWidthValue(C);
16616 
16617  if (Bits1 != Bits2)
16618  return false;
16619  }
16620 
16621  return true;
16622 }
16623 
16624 /// Check if two standard-layout structs are layout-compatible.
16625 /// (C++11 [class.mem] p17)
16626 static bool isLayoutCompatibleStruct(ASTContext &C, RecordDecl *RD1,
16627  RecordDecl *RD2) {
16628  // If both records are C++ classes, check that base classes match.
16629  if (const CXXRecordDecl *D1CXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD1)) {
16630  // If one of records is a CXXRecordDecl we are in C++ mode,
16631  // thus the other one is a CXXRecordDecl, too.
16632  const CXXRecordDecl *D2CXX = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD2);
16633  // Check number of base classes.
16634  if (D1CXX->getNumBases() != D2CXX->getNumBases())
16635  return false;
16636 
16637  // Check the base classes.
16638  for (CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_iterator
16639  Base1 = D1CXX->bases_begin(),
16640  BaseEnd1 = D1CXX->bases_end(),
16641  Base2 = D2CXX->bases_begin();
16642  Base1 != BaseEnd1;
16643  ++Base1, ++Base2) {
16644  if (!isLayoutCompatible(C, Base1->getType(), Base2->getType()))
16645  return false;
16646  }
16647  } else if (const CXXRecordDecl *D2CXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD2)) {
16648  // If only RD2 is a C++ class, it should have zero base classes.
16649  if (D2CXX->getNumBases() > 0)
16650  return false;
16651  }
16652 
16653  // Check the fields.
16654  RecordDecl::field_iterator Field2 = RD2->field_begin(),
16655  Field2End = RD2->field_end(),
16656  Field1 = RD1->field_begin(),
16657  Field1End = RD1->field_end();
16658  for ( ; Field1 != Field1End && Field2 != Field2End; ++Field1, ++Field2) {
16659  if (!isLayoutCompatible(C, *Field1, *Field2))
16660  return false;
16661  }
16662  if (Field1 != Field1End || Field2 != Field2End)
16663  return false;
16664 
16665  return true;
16666 }
16667 
16668 /// Check if two standard-layout unions are layout-compatible.
16669 /// (C++11 [class.mem] p18)
16670 static bool isLayoutCompatibleUnion(ASTContext &C, RecordDecl *RD1,
16671  RecordDecl *RD2) {
16672  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FieldDecl *, 8> UnmatchedFields;
16673  for (auto *Field2 : RD2->fields())
16674  UnmatchedFields.insert(Field2);
16675 
16676  for (auto *Field1 : RD1->fields()) {
16677  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FieldDecl *, 8>::iterator
16678  I = UnmatchedFields.begin(),
16679  E = UnmatchedFields.end();
16680 
16681  for ( ; I != E; ++I) {
16682  if (isLayoutCompatible(C, Field1, *I)) {
16683  bool Result = UnmatchedFields.erase(*I);
16684  (void) Result;
16685  assert(Result);
16686  break;
16687  }
16688  }
16689  if (I == E)
16690  return false;
16691  }
16692 
16693  return UnmatchedFields.empty();
16694 }
16695 
16696 static bool isLayoutCompatible(ASTContext &C, RecordDecl *RD1,
16697  RecordDecl *RD2) {
16698  if (RD1->isUnion() != RD2->isUnion())
16699  return false;
16700 
16701  if (RD1->isUnion())
16702  return isLayoutCompatibleUnion(C, RD1, RD2);
16703  else
16704  return isLayoutCompatibleStruct(C, RD1, RD2);
16705 }
16706 
16707 /// Check if two types are layout-compatible in C++11 sense.
16708 static bool isLayoutCompatible(ASTContext &C, QualType T1, QualType T2) {
16709  if (T1.isNull() || T2.isNull())
16710  return false;
16711 
16712  // C++11 [basic.types] p11:
16713  // If two types T1 and T2 are the same type, then T1 and T2 are
16714  // layout-compatible types.
16715  if (C.hasSameType(T1, T2))
16716  return true;
16717 
16718  T1 = T1.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
16719  T2 = T2.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
16720 
16721  const Type::TypeClass TC1 = T1->getTypeClass();
16722  const Type::TypeClass TC2 = T2->getTypeClass();
16723 
16724  if (TC1 != TC2)
16725  return false;
16726 
16727  if (TC1 == Type::Enum) {
16728  return isLayoutCompatible(C,
16729  cast<EnumType>(T1)->getDecl(),
16730  cast<EnumType>(T2)->getDecl());
16731  } else if (TC1 == Type::Record) {
16732  if (!T1->isStandardLayoutType() || !T2->isStandardLayoutType())
16733  return false;
16734 
16735  return isLayoutCompatible(C,
16736  cast<RecordType>(T1)->getDecl(),
16737  cast<RecordType>(T2)->getDecl());
16738  }
16739 
16740  return false;
16741 }
16742 
16743 //===--- CHECK: pointer_with_type_tag attribute: datatypes should match ----//
16744 
16745 /// Given a type tag expression find the type tag itself.
16746 ///
16747 /// \param TypeExpr Type tag expression, as it appears in user's code.
16748 ///
16749 /// \param VD Declaration of an identifier that appears in a type tag.
16750 ///
16751 /// \param MagicValue Type tag magic value.
16752 ///
16753 /// \param isConstantEvaluated whether the evalaution should be performed in
16754 
16755 /// constant context.
16756 static bool FindTypeTagExpr(const Expr *TypeExpr, const ASTContext &Ctx,
16757  const ValueDecl **VD, uint64_t *MagicValue,
16758  bool isConstantEvaluated) {
16759  while(true) {
16760  if (!TypeExpr)
16761  return false;
16762 
16763  TypeExpr = TypeExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->IgnoreParenCasts();
16764 
16765  switch (TypeExpr->getStmtClass()) {
16766  case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
16767  const UnaryOperator *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(TypeExpr);
16768  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf || UO->getOpcode() == UO_Deref) {
16769  TypeExpr = UO->getSubExpr();
16770  continue;
16771  }
16772  return false;
16773  }
16774 
16775  case Stmt::DeclRefExprClass: {
16776  const DeclRefExpr *DRE = cast<DeclRefExpr>(TypeExpr);
16777  *VD = DRE->getDecl();
16778  return true;
16779  }
16780 
16781  case Stmt::IntegerLiteralClass: {
16782  const IntegerLiteral *IL = cast<IntegerLiteral>(TypeExpr);
16783  llvm::APInt MagicValueAPInt = IL->getValue();
16784  if (MagicValueAPInt.getActiveBits() <= 64) {
16785  *MagicValue = MagicValueAPInt.getZExtValue();
16786  return true;
16787  } else
16788  return false;
16789  }
16790 
16791  case Stmt::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass:
16792  case Stmt::ConditionalOperatorClass: {
16793  const AbstractConditionalOperator *ACO =
16794  cast<AbstractConditionalOperator>(TypeExpr);
16795  bool Result;
16796  if (ACO->getCond()->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(Result, Ctx,
16797  isConstantEvaluated)) {
16798  if (Result)
16799  TypeExpr = ACO->getTrueExpr();
16800  else
16801  TypeExpr = ACO->getFalseExpr();
16802  continue;
16803  }
16804  return false;
16805  }
16806 
16807  case Stmt::BinaryOperatorClass: {
16808  const BinaryOperator *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(TypeExpr);
16809  if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
16810  TypeExpr = BO->getRHS();
16811  continue;
16812  }
16813  return false;
16814  }
16815 
16816  default:
16817  return false;
16818  }
16819  }
16820 }
16821 
16822 /// Retrieve the C type corresponding to type tag TypeExpr.
16823 ///
16824 /// \param TypeExpr Expression that specifies a type tag.
16825 ///
16826 /// \param MagicValues Registered magic values.
16827 ///
16828 /// \param FoundWrongKind Set to true if a type tag was found, but of a wrong
16829 /// kind.
16830 ///
16831 /// \param TypeInfo Information about the corresponding C type.
16832 ///
16833 /// \param isConstantEvaluated whether the evalaution should be performed in
16834 /// constant context.
16835 ///
16836 /// \returns true if the corresponding C type was found.
16837 static bool GetMatchingCType(
16838  const IdentifierInfo *ArgumentKind, const Expr *TypeExpr,
16839  const ASTContext &Ctx,
16840  const llvm::DenseMap<Sema::TypeTagMagicValue, Sema::TypeTagData>
16841  *MagicValues,
16842  bool &FoundWrongKind, Sema::TypeTagData &TypeInfo,
16843  bool isConstantEvaluated) {
16844  FoundWrongKind = false;
16845 
16846  // Variable declaration that has type_tag_for_datatype attribute.
16847  const ValueDecl *VD = nullptr;
16848 
16849  uint64_t MagicValue;
16850 
16851  if (!FindTypeTagExpr(TypeExpr, Ctx, &VD, &MagicValue, isConstantEvaluated))
16852  return false;
16853 
16854  if (VD) {
16855  if (TypeTagForDatatypeAttr *I = VD->getAttr<TypeTagForDatatypeAttr>()) {
16856  if (I->getArgumentKind() != ArgumentKind) {
16857  FoundWrongKind = true;
16858  return false;
16859  }
16860  TypeInfo.Type = I->getMatchingCType();
16861  TypeInfo.LayoutCompatible = I->getLayoutCompatible();
16862  TypeInfo.MustBeNull = I->getMustBeNull();
16863  return true;
16864  }
16865  return false;
16866  }
16867 
16868  if (!MagicValues)
16869  return false;
16870 
16871  llvm::DenseMap<Sema::TypeTagMagicValue,
16872  Sema::TypeTagData>::const_iterator I =
16873  MagicValues->find(std::make_pair(ArgumentKind, MagicValue));
16874  if (I == MagicValues->end())
16875  return false;
16876 
16877  TypeInfo = I->second;
16878  return true;
16879 }
16880 
16881 void Sema::RegisterTypeTagForDatatype(const IdentifierInfo *ArgumentKind,
16882  uint64_t MagicValue, QualType Type,
16883  bool LayoutCompatible,
16884  bool MustBeNull) {
16885  if (!TypeTagForDatatypeMagicValues)
16886  TypeTagForDatatypeMagicValues.reset(
16887  new llvm::DenseMap<TypeTagMagicValue, TypeTagData>);
16888 
16889  TypeTagMagicValue Magic(ArgumentKind, MagicValue);
16890  (*TypeTagForDatatypeMagicValues)[Magic] =
16891  TypeTagData(Type, LayoutCompatible, MustBeNull);
16892 }
16893 
16894 static bool IsSameCharType(QualType T1, QualType T2) {
16895  const BuiltinType *BT1 = T1->getAs<BuiltinType>();
16896  if (!BT1)
16897  return false;
16898 
16899  const BuiltinType *BT2 = T2->getAs<BuiltinType>();
16900  if (!BT2)
16901  return false;
16902 
16903  BuiltinType::Kind T1Kind = BT1->getKind();
16904  BuiltinType::Kind T2Kind = BT2->getKind();
16905 
16906  return (T1Kind == BuiltinType::SChar && T2Kind == BuiltinType::Char_S) ||
16907  (T1Kind == BuiltinType::UChar && T2Kind == BuiltinType::Char_U) ||
16908  (T1Kind == BuiltinType::Char_U && T2Kind == BuiltinType::UChar) ||
16909  (T1Kind == BuiltinType::Char_S && T2Kind == BuiltinType::SChar);
16910 }
16911 
16912 void Sema::CheckArgumentWithTypeTag(const ArgumentWithTypeTagAttr *Attr,
16913  const ArrayRef<const Expr *> ExprArgs,
16914  SourceLocation CallSiteLoc) {
16915  const IdentifierInfo *ArgumentKind = Attr->getArgumentKind();
16916  bool IsPointerAttr = Attr->getIsPointer();
16917 
16918  // Retrieve the argument representing the 'type_tag'.
16919  unsigned TypeTagIdxAST = Attr->getTypeTagIdx().getASTIndex();
16920  if (TypeTagIdxAST >= ExprArgs.size()) {
16921  Diag(CallSiteLoc, diag::err_tag_index_out_of_range)
16922  << 0 << Attr->getTypeTagIdx().getSourceIndex();
16923  return;
16924  }
16925  const Expr *TypeTagExpr = ExprArgs[TypeTagIdxAST];
16926  bool FoundWrongKind;
16927  TypeTagData TypeInfo;
16928  if (!GetMatchingCType(ArgumentKind, TypeTagExpr, Context,
16929  TypeTagForDatatypeMagicValues.get(), FoundWrongKind,
16930  TypeInfo, isConstantEvaluated())) {
16931  if (FoundWrongKind)
16932  Diag(TypeTagExpr->getExprLoc(),
16933  diag::warn_type_tag_for_datatype_wrong_kind)
16934  << TypeTagExpr->getSourceRange();
16935  return;
16936  }
16937 
16938  // Retrieve the argument representing the 'arg_idx'.
16939  unsigned ArgumentIdxAST = Attr->getArgumentIdx().getASTIndex();
16940  if (ArgumentIdxAST >= ExprArgs.size()) {
16941  Diag(CallSiteLoc, diag::err_tag_index_out_of_range)
16942  << 1 << Attr->getArgumentIdx().getSourceIndex();
16943  return;
16944  }
16945  const Expr *ArgumentExpr = ExprArgs[ArgumentIdxAST];
16946  if (IsPointerAttr) {
16947  // Skip implicit cast of pointer to `void *' (as a function argument).
16948  if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(ArgumentExpr))
16949  if (ICE->getType()->isVoidPointerType() &&
16950  ICE->getCastKind() == CK_BitCast)
16951  ArgumentExpr = ICE->getSubExpr();
16952  }
16953  QualType ArgumentType = ArgumentExpr->getType();
16954 
16955  // Passing a `void*' pointer shouldn't trigger a warning.
16956  if (IsPointerAttr && ArgumentType->isVoidPointerType())
16957  return;
16958 
16959  if (TypeInfo.MustBeNull) {
16960  // Type tag with matching void type requires a null pointer.
16961  if (!ArgumentExpr->isNullPointerConstant(Context,
16962  Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
16963  Diag(ArgumentExpr->getExprLoc(),
16964  diag::warn_type_safety_null_pointer_required)
16965  << ArgumentKind->getName()
16966  << ArgumentExpr->getSourceRange()
16967  << TypeTagExpr->getSourceRange();
16968  }
16969  return;
16970  }
16971 
16972  QualType RequiredType = TypeInfo.Type;
16973  if (IsPointerAttr)
16974  RequiredType = Context.getPointerType(RequiredType);
16975 
16976  bool mismatch = false;
16977  if (!TypeInfo.LayoutCompatible) {
16978  mismatch = !Context.hasSameType(ArgumentType, RequiredType);
16979 
16980  // C++11 [basic.fundamental] p1:
16981  // Plain char, signed char, and unsigned char are three distinct types.
16982  //
16983  // But we treat plain `char' as equivalent to `signed char' or `unsigned
16984  // char' depending on the current char signedness mode.
16985  if (mismatch)
16986  if ((IsPointerAttr && IsSameCharType(ArgumentType->getPointeeType(),
16987  RequiredType->getPointeeType())) ||
16988  (!IsPointerAttr && IsSameCharType(ArgumentType, RequiredType)))
16989  mismatch = false;
16990  } else
16991  if (IsPointerAttr)
16992  mismatch = !isLayoutCompatible(Context,
16993  ArgumentType->getPointeeType(),
16994  RequiredType->getPointeeType());
16995  else
16996  mismatch = !isLayoutCompatible(Context, ArgumentType, RequiredType);
16997 
16998  if (mismatch)
16999  Diag(ArgumentExpr->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_type_safety_type_mismatch)
17000  << ArgumentType << ArgumentKind
17001  << TypeInfo.LayoutCompatible << RequiredType
17002  << ArgumentExpr->getSourceRange()
17003  << TypeTagExpr->getSourceRange();
17004 }
17005 
17006 void Sema::AddPotentialMisalignedMembers(Expr *E, RecordDecl *RD, ValueDecl *MD,
17007  CharUnits Alignment) {
17008  MisalignedMembers.emplace_back(E, RD, MD, Alignment);
17009 }
17010 
17011 void Sema::DiagnoseMisalignedMembers() {
17012  for (MisalignedMember &m : MisalignedMembers) {
17013  const NamedDecl *ND = m.RD;
17014  if (ND->getName().empty()) {
17015  if (const TypedefNameDecl *TD = m.RD->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl())
17016  ND = TD;
17017  }
17018  Diag(m.E->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_taking_address_of_packed_member)
17019  << m.MD << ND << m.E->getSourceRange();
17020  }
17021  MisalignedMembers.clear();
17022 }
17023 
17024 void Sema::DiscardMisalignedMemberAddress(const Type *T, Expr *E) {
17025  E = E->IgnoreParens();
17026  if (!T->isPointerType() && !T->isIntegerType())
17027  return;
17028  if (isa<UnaryOperator>(E) &&
17029  cast<UnaryOperator>(E)->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf) {
17030  auto *Op = cast<UnaryOperator>(E)->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParens();
17031  if (isa<MemberExpr>(Op)) {
17032  auto MA = llvm::find(MisalignedMembers, MisalignedMember(Op));
17033  if (MA != MisalignedMembers.end() &&
17034  (T->isIntegerType() ||
17035  (T->isPointerType() && (T->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteType() ||
17036  Context.getTypeAlignInChars(
17037  T->getPointeeType()) <= MA->Alignment))))
17038  MisalignedMembers.erase(MA);
17039  }
17040  }
17041 }
17042 
17043 void Sema::RefersToMemberWithReducedAlignment(
17044  Expr *E,
17045  llvm::function_ref<void(Expr *, RecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, CharUnits)>
17046  Action) {
17047  const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E);
17048  if (!ME)
17049  return;
17050 
17051  // No need to check expressions with an __unaligned-qualified type.
17052  if (E->getType().getQualifiers().hasUnaligned())
17053  return;
17054 
17055  // For a chain of MemberExpr like "a.b.c.d" this list
17056  // will keep FieldDecl's like [d, c, b].
17057  SmallVector<FieldDecl *, 4> ReverseMemberChain;
17058  const MemberExpr *TopME = nullptr;
17059  bool AnyIsPacked = false;
17060  do {
17061  QualType BaseType = ME->getBase()->getType();
17062  if (BaseType->isDependentType())
17063  return;
17064  if (ME->isArrow())
17065  BaseType = BaseType->getPointeeType();
17066  RecordDecl *RD = BaseType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
17067  if (RD->isInvalidDecl())
17068  return;
17069 
17070  ValueDecl *MD = ME->getMemberDecl();
17071  auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(MD);
17072  // We do not care about non-data members.
17073  if (!FD || FD->isInvalidDecl())
17074  return;
17075 
17076  AnyIsPacked =
17077  AnyIsPacked || (RD->hasAttr<PackedAttr>() || MD->hasAttr<PackedAttr>());
17078  ReverseMemberChain.push_back(FD);
17079 
17080  TopME = ME;
17081  ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(ME->getBase()->IgnoreParens());
17082  } while (ME);
17083  assert(TopME && "We did not compute a topmost MemberExpr!");
17084 
17085  // Not the scope of this diagnostic.
17086  if (!AnyIsPacked)
17087  return;
17088 
17089  const Expr *TopBase = TopME->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
17090  const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(TopBase);
17091  // TODO: The innermost base of the member expression may be too complicated.
17092  // For now, just disregard these cases. This is left for future
17093  // improvement.
17094  if (!DRE && !isa<CXXThisExpr>(TopBase))
17095  return;
17096 
17097  // Alignment expected by the whole expression.
17098  CharUnits ExpectedAlignment = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(E->getType());
17099 
17100  // No need to do anything else with this case.
17101  if (ExpectedAlignment.isOne())
17102  return;
17103 
17104  // Synthesize offset of the whole access.
17105  CharUnits Offset;
17106  for (const FieldDecl *FD : llvm::reverse(ReverseMemberChain))
17107  Offset += Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Context.getFieldOffset(FD));
17108 
17109  // Compute the CompleteObjectAlignment as the alignment of the whole chain.
17110  CharUnits CompleteObjectAlignment = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(
17111  ReverseMemberChain.back()->getParent()->getTypeForDecl());
17112 
17113  // The base expression of the innermost MemberExpr may give
17114  // stronger guarantees than the class containing the member.
17115  if (DRE && !TopME->isArrow()) {
17116  const ValueDecl *VD = DRE->getDecl();
17117  if (!VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
17118  CompleteObjectAlignment =
17119  std::max(CompleteObjectAlignment, Context.getDeclAlign(VD));
17120  }
17121 
17122  // Check if the synthesized offset fulfills the alignment.
17123  if (Offset % ExpectedAlignment != 0 ||
17124  // It may fulfill the offset it but the effective alignment may still be
17125  // lower than the expected expression alignment.
17126  CompleteObjectAlignment < ExpectedAlignment) {
17127  // If this happens, we want to determine a sensible culprit of this.
17128  // Intuitively, watching the chain of member expressions from right to
17129  // left, we start with the required alignment (as required by the field
17130  // type) but some packed attribute in that chain has reduced the alignment.
17131  // It may happen that another packed structure increases it again. But if
17132  // we are here such increase has not been enough. So pointing the first
17133  // FieldDecl that either is packed or else its RecordDecl is,
17134  // seems reasonable.
17135  FieldDecl *FD = nullptr;
17136  CharUnits Alignment;
17137  for (FieldDecl *FDI : ReverseMemberChain) {
17138  if (FDI->hasAttr<PackedAttr>() ||
17139  FDI->getParent()->hasAttr<PackedAttr>()) {
17140  FD = FDI;
17141  Alignment = std::min(
17142  Context.getTypeAlignInChars(FD->getType()),
17143  Context.getTypeAlignInChars(FD->getParent()->getTypeForDecl()));
17144  break;
17145  }
17146  }
17147  assert(FD && "We did not find a packed FieldDecl!");
17148  Action(E, FD->getParent(), FD, Alignment);
17149  }
17150 }
17151 
17152 void Sema::CheckAddressOfPackedMember(Expr *rhs) {
17153  using namespace std::placeholders;
17154 
17155  RefersToMemberWithReducedAlignment(
17156  rhs, std::bind(&Sema::AddPotentialMisalignedMembers, std::ref(*this), _1,
17157  _2, _3, _4));
17158 }

17160 // Check if \p Ty is a valid type for the elementwise math builtins. If it is
17161 // not a valid type, emit an error message and return true. Otherwise return
17162 // false.
17163 static bool checkMathBuiltinElementType(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
17164  QualType Ty) {
17165  if (!Ty->getAs<VectorType>() && !ConstantMatrixType::isValidElementType(Ty)) {
17166  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
17167  << 1 << /* vector, integer or float ty*/ 0 << Ty;
17168  return true;
17169  }
17170  return false;
17171 }
17172 
17173 bool Sema::PrepareBuiltinElementwiseMathOneArgCall(CallExpr *TheCall) {
17174  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 1))
17175  return true;
17176 
17177  ExprResult A = UsualUnaryConversions(TheCall->getArg(0));
17178  if (A.isInvalid())
17179  return true;
17180 
17181  TheCall->setArg(0, A.get());
17182  QualType TyA = A.get()->getType();
17183 
17184  if (checkMathBuiltinElementType(*this, A.get()->getBeginLoc(), TyA))
17185  return true;
17186 
17187  TheCall->setType(TyA);
17188  return false;
17189 }
17190 
17191 bool Sema::SemaBuiltinElementwiseMath(CallExpr *TheCall) {
17192  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 2))
17193  return true;
17194 
17195  ExprResult A = TheCall->getArg(0);
17196  ExprResult B = TheCall->getArg(1);
17197  // Do standard promotions between the two arguments, returning their common
17198  // type.
17199  QualType Res =
17200  UsualArithmeticConversions(A, B, TheCall->getExprLoc(), ACK_Comparison);
17201  if (A.isInvalid() || B.isInvalid())
17202  return true;
17203 
17204  QualType TyA = A.get()->getType();
17205  QualType TyB = B.get()->getType();
17206 
17207  if (Res.isNull() || TyA.getCanonicalType() != TyB.getCanonicalType())
17208  return Diag(A.get()->getBeginLoc(),
17209  diag::err_typecheck_call_different_arg_types)
17210  << TyA << TyB;
17211 
17212  if (checkMathBuiltinElementType(*this, A.get()->getBeginLoc(), TyA))
17213  return true;
17214 
17215  TheCall->setArg(0, A.get());
17216  TheCall->setArg(1, B.get());
17217  TheCall->setType(Res);
17218  return false;
17219 }
17220 
17221 bool Sema::PrepareBuiltinReduceMathOneArgCall(CallExpr *TheCall) {
17222  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 1))
17223  return true;
17224 
17225  ExprResult A = UsualUnaryConversions(TheCall->getArg(0));
17226  if (A.isInvalid())
17227  return true;
17228 
17229  TheCall->setArg(0, A.get());
17230  return false;
17231 }
