17233 ExprResult Sema::SemaBuiltinMatrixTranspose(CallExpr *TheCall,
17234  ExprResult CallResult) {
17235  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 1))
17236  return ExprError();
17237 
17238  ExprResult MatrixArg = DefaultLvalueConversion(TheCall->getArg(0));
17239  if (MatrixArg.isInvalid())
17240  return MatrixArg;
17241  Expr *Matrix = MatrixArg.get();
17242 
17243  auto *MType = Matrix->getType()->getAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
17244  if (!MType) {
17245  Diag(Matrix->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
17246  << 1 << /* matrix ty*/ 1 << Matrix->getType();
17247  return ExprError();
17248  }
17249 
17250  // Create returned matrix type by swapping rows and columns of the argument
17251  // matrix type.
17252  QualType ResultType = Context.getConstantMatrixType(
17253  MType->getElementType(), MType->getNumColumns(), MType->getNumRows());
17254 
17255  // Change the return type to the type of the returned matrix.
17256  TheCall->setType(ResultType);
17257 
17258  // Update call argument to use the possibly converted matrix argument.
17259  TheCall->setArg(0, Matrix);
17260  return CallResult;
17261 }
17262 
17263 // Get and verify the matrix dimensions.
17264 static llvm::Optional<unsigned>
17265 getAndVerifyMatrixDimension(Expr *Expr, StringRef Name, Sema &S) {
17266  SourceLocation ErrorPos;
17267  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Value =
17268  Expr->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context, &ErrorPos);
17269  if (!Value) {
17270  S.Diag(Expr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_matrix_scalar_unsigned_arg)
17271  << Name;
17272  return {};
17273  }
17274  uint64_t Dim = Value->getZExtValue();
17275  if (!ConstantMatrixType::isDimensionValid(Dim)) {
17276  S.Diag(Expr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_matrix_invalid_dimension)
17277  << Name << ConstantMatrixType::getMaxElementsPerDimension();
17278  return {};
17279  }
17280  return Dim;
17281 }
17282 
17283 ExprResult Sema::SemaBuiltinMatrixColumnMajorLoad(CallExpr *TheCall,
17284  ExprResult CallResult) {
17285  if (!getLangOpts().MatrixTypes) {
17286  Diag(TheCall->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_matrix_disabled);
17287  return ExprError();
17288  }
17289 
17290  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 4))
17291  return ExprError();
17292 
17293  unsigned PtrArgIdx = 0;
17294  Expr *PtrExpr = TheCall->getArg(PtrArgIdx);
17295  Expr *RowsExpr = TheCall->getArg(1);
17296  Expr *ColumnsExpr = TheCall->getArg(2);
17297  Expr *StrideExpr = TheCall->getArg(3);
17298 
17299  bool ArgError = false;
17300 
17301  // Check pointer argument.
17302  {
17303  ExprResult PtrConv = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(PtrExpr);
17304  if (PtrConv.isInvalid())
17305  return PtrConv;
17306  PtrExpr = PtrConv.get();
17307  TheCall->setArg(0, PtrExpr);
17308  if (PtrExpr->isTypeDependent()) {
17309  TheCall->setType(Context.DependentTy);
17310  return TheCall;
17311  }
17312  }
17313 
17314  auto *PtrTy = PtrExpr->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
17315  QualType ElementTy;
17316  if (!PtrTy) {
17317  Diag(PtrExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
17318  << PtrArgIdx + 1 << /*pointer to element ty*/ 2 << PtrExpr->getType();
17319  ArgError = true;
17320  } else {
17321  ElementTy = PtrTy->getPointeeType().getUnqualifiedType();
17322 
17323  if (!ConstantMatrixType::isValidElementType(ElementTy)) {
17324  Diag(PtrExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
17325  << PtrArgIdx + 1 << /* pointer to element ty*/ 2
17326  << PtrExpr->getType();
17327  ArgError = true;
17328  }
17329  }
17330 
17331  // Apply default Lvalue conversions and convert the expression to size_t.
17332  auto ApplyArgumentConversions = [this](Expr *E) {
17333  ExprResult Conv = DefaultLvalueConversion(E);
17334  if (Conv.isInvalid())
17335  return Conv;
17336 
17337  return tryConvertExprToType(Conv.get(), Context.getSizeType());
17338  };
17339 
17340  // Apply conversion to row and column expressions.
17341  ExprResult RowsConv = ApplyArgumentConversions(RowsExpr);
17342  if (!RowsConv.isInvalid()) {
17343  RowsExpr = RowsConv.get();
17344  TheCall->setArg(1, RowsExpr);
17345  } else
17346  RowsExpr = nullptr;
17347 
17348  ExprResult ColumnsConv = ApplyArgumentConversions(ColumnsExpr);
17349  if (!ColumnsConv.isInvalid()) {
17350  ColumnsExpr = ColumnsConv.get();
17351  TheCall->setArg(2, ColumnsExpr);
17352  } else
17353  ColumnsExpr = nullptr;
17354 
17355  // If any any part of the result matrix type is still pending, just use
17356  // Context.DependentTy, until all parts are resolved.
17357  if ((RowsExpr && RowsExpr->isTypeDependent()) ||
17358  (ColumnsExpr && ColumnsExpr->isTypeDependent())) {
17359  TheCall->setType(Context.DependentTy);
17360  return CallResult;
17361  }
17362 
17363  // Check row and column dimensions.
17364  llvm::Optional<unsigned> MaybeRows;
17365  if (RowsExpr)
17366  MaybeRows = getAndVerifyMatrixDimension(RowsExpr, "row", *this);
17367 
17368  llvm::Optional<unsigned> MaybeColumns;
17369  if (ColumnsExpr)
17370  MaybeColumns = getAndVerifyMatrixDimension(ColumnsExpr, "column", *this);
17371 
17372  // Check stride argument.
17373  ExprResult StrideConv = ApplyArgumentConversions(StrideExpr);
17374  if (StrideConv.isInvalid())
17375  return ExprError();
17376  StrideExpr = StrideConv.get();
17377  TheCall->setArg(3, StrideExpr);
17378 
17379  if (MaybeRows) {
17380  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> Value =
17381  StrideExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)) {
17382  uint64_t Stride = Value->getZExtValue();
17383  if (Stride < *MaybeRows) {
17384  Diag(StrideExpr->getBeginLoc(),
17385  diag::err_builtin_matrix_stride_too_small);
17386  ArgError = true;
17387  }
17388  }
17389  }
17390 
17391  if (ArgError || !MaybeRows || !MaybeColumns)
17392  return ExprError();
17393 
17394  TheCall->setType(
17395  Context.getConstantMatrixType(ElementTy, *MaybeRows, *MaybeColumns));
17396  return CallResult;
17397 }
17398 
17399 ExprResult Sema::SemaBuiltinMatrixColumnMajorStore(CallExpr *TheCall,
17400  ExprResult CallResult) {
17401  if (checkArgCount(*this, TheCall, 3))
17402  return ExprError();
17403 
17404  unsigned PtrArgIdx = 1;
17405  Expr *MatrixExpr = TheCall->getArg(0);
17406  Expr *PtrExpr = TheCall->getArg(PtrArgIdx);
17407  Expr *StrideExpr = TheCall->getArg(2);
17408 
17409  bool ArgError = false;
17410 
17411  {
17412  ExprResult MatrixConv = DefaultLvalueConversion(MatrixExpr);
17413  if (MatrixConv.isInvalid())
17414  return MatrixConv;
17415  MatrixExpr = MatrixConv.get();
17416  TheCall->setArg(0, MatrixExpr);
17417  }
17418  if (MatrixExpr->isTypeDependent()) {
17419  TheCall->setType(Context.DependentTy);
17420  return TheCall;
17421  }
17422 
17423  auto *MatrixTy = MatrixExpr->getType()->getAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
17424  if (!MatrixTy) {
17425  Diag(MatrixExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
17426  << 1 << /*matrix ty */ 1 << MatrixExpr->getType();
17427  ArgError = true;
17428  }
17429 
17430  {
17431  ExprResult PtrConv = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(PtrExpr);
17432  if (PtrConv.isInvalid())
17433  return PtrConv;
17434  PtrExpr = PtrConv.get();
17435  TheCall->setArg(1, PtrExpr);
17436  if (PtrExpr->isTypeDependent()) {
17437  TheCall->setType(Context.DependentTy);
17438  return TheCall;
17439  }
17440  }
17441 
17442  // Check pointer argument.
17443  auto *PtrTy = PtrExpr->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
17444  if (!PtrTy) {
17445  Diag(PtrExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_invalid_arg_type)
17446  << PtrArgIdx + 1 << /*pointer to element ty*/ 2 << PtrExpr->getType();
17447  ArgError = true;
17448  } else {
17449  QualType ElementTy = PtrTy->getPointeeType();
17450  if (ElementTy.isConstQualified()) {
17451  Diag(PtrExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_builtin_matrix_store_to_const);
17452  ArgError = true;
17453  }
17454  ElementTy = ElementTy.getUnqualifiedType().getCanonicalType();
17455  if (MatrixTy &&
17456  !Context.hasSameType(ElementTy, MatrixTy->getElementType())) {
17457  Diag(PtrExpr->getBeginLoc(),
17458  diag::err_builtin_matrix_pointer_arg_mismatch)
17459  << ElementTy << MatrixTy->getElementType();
17460  ArgError = true;
17461  }
17462  }
17463 
17464  // Apply default Lvalue conversions and convert the stride expression to
17465  // size_t.
17466  {
17467  ExprResult StrideConv = DefaultLvalueConversion(StrideExpr);
17468  if (StrideConv.isInvalid())
17469  return StrideConv;
17470 
17471  StrideConv = tryConvertExprToType(StrideConv.get(), Context.getSizeType());
17472  if (StrideConv.isInvalid())
17473  return StrideConv;
17474  StrideExpr = StrideConv.get();
17475  TheCall->setArg(2, StrideExpr);
17476  }
17477 
17478  // Check stride argument.
17479  if (MatrixTy) {
17480  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> Value =
17481  StrideExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)) {
17482  uint64_t Stride = Value->getZExtValue();
17483  if (Stride < MatrixTy->getNumRows()) {
17484  Diag(StrideExpr->getBeginLoc(),
17485  diag::err_builtin_matrix_stride_too_small);
17486  ArgError = true;
17487  }
17488  }
17489  }
17490 
17491  if (ArgError)
17492  return ExprError();
17493 
17494  return CallResult;
17495 }
17496 
17497 /// \brief Enforce the bounds of a TCB
17498 /// CheckTCBEnforcement - Enforces that every function in a named TCB only
17499 /// directly calls other functions in the same TCB as marked by the enforce_tcb
17500 /// and enforce_tcb_leaf attributes.
17501 void Sema::CheckTCBEnforcement(const CallExpr *TheCall,
17502  const FunctionDecl *Callee) {
17503  const FunctionDecl *Caller = getCurFunctionDecl();
17504 
17505  // Calls to builtins are not enforced.
17506  if (!Caller || !Caller->hasAttr<EnforceTCBAttr>() ||
17507  Callee->getBuiltinID() != 0)
17508  return;
17509 
17510  // Search through the enforce_tcb and enforce_tcb_leaf attributes to find
17511  // all TCBs the callee is a part of.
17512  llvm::StringSet<> CalleeTCBs;
17513  for_each(Callee->specific_attrs<EnforceTCBAttr>(),
17514  [&](const auto *A) { CalleeTCBs.insert(A->getTCBName()); });
17515  for_each(Callee->specific_attrs<EnforceTCBLeafAttr>(),
17516  [&](const auto *A) { CalleeTCBs.insert(A->getTCBName()); });
17517 
17518  // Go through the TCBs the caller is a part of and emit warnings if Caller
17519  // is in a TCB that the Callee is not.
17520  for_each(
17521  Caller->specific_attrs<EnforceTCBAttr>(),
17522  [&](const auto *A) {
17523  StringRef CallerTCB = A->getTCBName();
17524  if (CalleeTCBs.count(CallerTCB) == 0) {
17525  this->Diag(TheCall->getExprLoc(),
17526  diag::warn_tcb_enforcement_violation) << Callee
17527  << CallerTCB;
17528  }
17529  });
17530 }
